#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:77
msgid "Performing an inventory count"
msgstr "Udførelse af en lageroptælling"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:79
msgid ""
"To perform an inventory adjustment, first navigate to "
"the :menuselection:`Barcode app`. If assigned counts exist, "
"tap :guilabel:`Count Inventory` to view pending tasks."
msgstr ""
"For at udføre en lagerjustering skal du først navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Stregkode-appen`. Hvis der findes tildelte optællinger, "
"skal du trykke på :guilabel:`Tæl lager` for at se afventende opgaver."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:None
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/receipts_deliveries.rst:None
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/transfers_scratch.rst:None
msgid "Barcode app start screen with scanner."
msgstr "Stregkode-appens startskærm med scanner."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:85
msgid ""
"Walk to the designated storage location, then scan the location barcode."
msgstr ""
"Gå til den udpegede lagerlokation og scan derefter lokationsstregkoden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:88
msgid ""
"If the warehouse *multi-location* feature is **not** enabled in the "
"database, a source location does not need to be scanned. Instead, scan the "
"product barcode to start the inventory adjustment."
msgstr ""
"Hvis lagerhus-funktionen *multi-lokation* **ikke** er aktiveret i databasen, "
"behøver en kildelokation ikke at blive scannet. Scan i stedet "
"produktstregkoden for at starte lagerjusteringen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:91
msgid ""
"Doing so highlights the location and displays all of the products stored "
"there. Scan the barcode of each product to adjust its count."
msgstr ""
"Dette fremhæver lokationen og viser alle de produkter, der er lagret der. "
"Scan stregkoden for hvert produkt for at justere dets antal."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:95
msgid ""
"If no counts have been assigned to a user, and the :ref:`Count Entire "
"Locations <inventory/barcode/count-location>` feature is **not** enabled, no "
"products may appear after the location barcode is scanned."
msgstr ""
"Hvis der ikke er tildelt nogen optællinger til en bruger, og "
"funktionen :ref:`Tæl hele lokationer <inventory/barcode/count-location>` "
"**ikke** er aktiveret, vises der muligvis ingen produkter efter "
"lokationsstregkoden er scannet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:99
msgid ""
"Manually adjust quantities if necessary by tapping the :icon:`fa-"
"pencil` :guilabel:`(edit)` icon. Doing so opens a separate window with a "
"keypad. Edit the number in the :guilabel:`Quantity` line to change the "
"quantity. Additionally, the :guilabel:`+1` and :guilabel:`-1` buttons can be "
"clicked to add or subtract quantity of the product, and the number keys can "
"be used to add quantity, as well."
msgstr ""
"Juster antal manuelt om nødvendigt ved at trykke på ikonet :icon:`fa-"
"pencil` :guilabel:`(rediger)`. Dette åbner et separat vindue med et "
"tastefelt. Rediger nummeret i linjen :guilabel:`Antal` for at ændre "
"antallet. Desuden kan knapperne :guilabel:`+1` og :guilabel:`-1` klikkes for "
"at tilføje eller trække antal af produktet fra, og taltasterne kan også "
"bruges til at tilføje antal."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:105
msgid ""
"In the below inventory adjustment, the source location `WH/Stock/Shelf 1` "
"was scanned, assigning the location. Then, the barcode for the product "
"`[FURN_7888] Desk Stand with Screen` was scanned three times, increasing the "
"units in the adjustment. Additional products can be added to this adjustment "
"by scanning the barcodes for those specific products."
msgstr ""
"I nedenstående lagerregulering blev kildelokationen `WH/Stock/Shelf 1` "
"skannet, hvilket tildelte lokationen. Derefter blev stregkoden for produktet "
"`[FURN_7888] Desk Stand with Screen` skannet tre gange, hvilket øgede "
"antallet af enheder i reguleringen. Yderligere produkter kan tilføjes til "
"denne regulering ved at skanne stregkoderne for disse specifikke produkter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:0
msgid "Barcode Physical Inventory page with inventory adjustment."
msgstr "Stregkode fysisk lagerside med lagerjustering."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:116
msgid "Count entire locations"
msgstr "Tæl hele lokationer"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:118
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Count Entire Locations` feature assigns a user to count all "
"the products within a location once they scan the barcode for that location. "
"This allows for easier cycle counts by assigning an entire location to a "
"user by assigning a single product count. During cycle counts, users can "
"ensure accurate inventory numbers, see if products that should be in a "
"location are missing, or discover products incorrectly stored within a "
"location."
msgstr ""
"Funktionen :guilabel:`Tæl hele lokationer` tildeler en bruger til at tælle "
"alle produkter inden for en lokation, når de skanner stregkoden for den "
"pågældende lokation. Dette gør det lettere at udføre cyklusoptællinger ved "
"at tildele en hel lokation til en bruger gennem tildeling af en enkelt "
"produktoptælling. Under cyklusoptællinger kan brugere sikre nøjagtige "
"lagertal, se om produkter, der burde være på en lokation, mangler, eller "
"opdage produkter, der fejlagtigt er opbevaret inden for en lokation."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:125
msgid ""
"You can only count entire locations if :guilabel:`Storage Locations` is "
"enabled in the Inventory settings, found at :menuselection:`Inventory app --"
"> Configuration --> Settings`."
msgstr ""
"Du kan kun tælle hele lokationer, hvis :guilabel:`Lagerplaceringer` er "
"aktiveret i lagerindstillingerne, som findes under :menuselection:`Lager-app "
"--> Konfiguration --> Indstillinger`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:128
msgid ""
"To perform an inventory count of an entire location, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Barcode app --> Count Inventory`. Tap the :icon:`fa-"
"cog` :guilabel:`(actions)` icon. Enter or scan a location barcode, and "
"select the :guilabel:`Count Entire Locations` check box. "
"Tap :guilabel:`Apply`. The app then displays all assigned products in that "
"location. :ref:`Proceed with the count <inventory/barcode/perform-count>` as "
"normal."
msgstr ""
"For at udføre en lageroptælling af en hel lokation skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Stregkode-app --> Tæl lager`. Tryk på :icon:`fa-"
"cog` :guilabel:`(handlinger)`-ikonet. Indtast eller scan en "
"lokationsstregkode, og marker afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Tæl hele "
"lokationer`. Tryk på :guilabel:`Anvend`. Appen viser derefter alle tildelte "
"produkter på den pågældende lokation. :ref:`Fortsæt med optællingen "
"<inventory/barcode/perform-count>` som normalt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:135
msgid "Show quantity to count"
msgstr "Vis antal, der skal tælles"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:137
msgid ""
"When conducting an inventory count, the expected quantity of products is not "
"displayed by default, as displaying expected quantities can result in users "
"relying on this count instead of performing a new count."
msgstr ""
"Når der udføres en lageroptælling, vises det forventede antal produkter ikke "
"som standard, da visning af forventede antal kan resultere i, at brugere "
"stoler på denne optælling i stedet for at udføre en ny optælling."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:141
msgid ""
"To show the expected quantity, navigate to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> "
"Operations --> Physical Inventory`. Request a count by selecting the check "
"boxes to the left of the products to count, then clicking "
"the :guilabel:`Request a Count` button. The *Inventory Request* window opens."
msgstr ""
"For at vise det forventede antal skal du navigere til :menuselection:`Lager-"
"app --> Operationer --> Fysisk lager`. Anmod om en optælling ved at markere "
"afkrydsningsfelterne til venstre for de produkter, der skal tælles, og "
"derefter klikke på knappen :guilabel:`Anmod om optælling`. Vinduet "
"*Lageranmodning* åbnes."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:145
msgid ""
"Specify a user to assign the count to in the :guilabel:`Assign to` field. "
"Specify the date to perform the count in the :guilabel:`Scheduled at` field. "
"Select the :guilabel:`Show Expected Quantity` check box to show the expected "
"quantity on the *Barcode* :guilabel:`Count Inventory` page."
msgstr ""
"Angiv en bruger, som optællingen skal tildeles til, i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Tildel til`. Angiv datoen for udførelsen af optællingen i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Planlagt til`. Marker afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Vis "
"forventet antal` for at vise det forventede antal på siden "
"*Stregkode* :guilabel:`Tæl lager`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:150
msgid ""
"Warehouse managers have requested a count of all `Cable Management Box` "
"products in inventory."
msgstr ""
"Lagerledere har anmodet om en optælling af alle `Cable Management Box`-"
"produkter på lageret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:0
msgid ""
"An inventory request with the Show Expected Quantity check box selected."
msgstr "En lageranmodning med afkrydsningsfeltet Vis forventet antal markeret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:155
msgid ""
"When the assigned user opens the :guilabel:`Count Inventory` page in the "
"*Barcode* app, the expected quantity of `90` units of the `Cable Management "
"Box` product is displayed."
msgstr ""
"Når den tildelte bruger åbner siden :guilabel:`Tæl lager` i *Stregkode*-"
"appen, vises det forventede antal på `90` enheder af produktet `Cable "
"Management Box`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:0
msgid "The expected quantity is displayed."
msgstr "Det forventede antal vises."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:162
msgid "Manually add products to an inventory count"
msgstr "Tilføj produkter manuelt til en lageroptælling"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:164
msgid ""
"When barcodes for location or products are not available, Odoo **Barcode** "
"can still be used to perform inventory counts."
msgstr ""
"Når stregkoder for lokation eller produkter ikke er tilgængelige, kan Odoo "
"**Stregkode** stadig bruges til at udføre lageroptællinger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:167
msgid ""
"To do this, navigate to :menuselection:`Barcode app --> Count Inventory`."
msgstr ""
"For at gøre dette skal du navigere til :menuselection:`Stregkode-app --> Tæl "
"lager`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:169
msgid ""
"To manually add products to this adjustment, click the white :guilabel:`Add "
"Product` button at the bottom of the screen."
msgstr ""
"For at tilføje produkter manuelt til denne regulering skal du klikke på den "
"hvide knap :guilabel:`Tilføj produkt` nederst på skærmen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:172
msgid ""
"This navigates to a new, blank page where the desired product, quantity, and "
"source location must be chosen."
msgstr ""
"Dette navigerer til en ny, tom side, hvor det ønskede produkt, antal og "
"kildelokation skal vælges."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:175
msgid ""
"First, click the :guilabel:`Product` line, and choose the product whose "
"stock count should be adjusted. Then, manually enter the quantity of that "
"product, either by changing the `1` in the :guilabel:`Quantity` line, or by "
"clicking the :guilabel:`+1` and :guilabel:`-1` buttons to add or subtract "
"quantity of the product. The number pad can be used to add quantity, as well."
msgstr ""
"Klik først på linjen :guilabel:`Produkt`, og vælg det produkt, hvis "
"lageroptælling skal justeres. Indtast derefter manuelt antallet af det "
"pågældende produkt, enten ved at ændre `1` i linjen :guilabel:`Antal`, eller "
"ved at klikke på knapperne :guilabel:`+1` og :guilabel:`-1` for at tilføje "
"eller trække antal af produktet fra. Taltastaturet kan også bruges til at "
"tilføje antal."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:180
msgid ""
"Below the number pad is the :guilabel:`Location` line, which should read `WH/"
"Stock` by default. Click this line to reveal a list of locations to choose "
"from, and choose the location for this inventory adjustment."
msgstr ""
"Under taltastaturet er linjen :guilabel:`Lokation`, som som standard bør "
"vise `WH/Stock`. Klik på denne linje for at se en liste over lokationer at "
"vælge mellem, og vælg lokationen til denne lagerjustering."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:184
msgid "Click :guilabel:`Confirm` to confirm the changes."
msgstr "Klik på :guilabel:`Bekræft` for at bekræfte ændringerne."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:None
msgid "Keypad to add products on Barcode Inventory Client Action page."
msgstr ""
"Tastatur til tilføjelse af produkter på Stregkode-lagerklients handlingsside."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:190
msgid "Finalizing an inventory count"
msgstr "Færdiggørelse af en lageroptælling"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:192
msgid ""
"After counting all of the products, review the entries to ensure all the "
"counted quantities are accurately entered. To complete the inventory "
"adjustment, click :guilabel:`Confirm`."
msgstr ""
"Efter at have talt alle produkterne skal du gennemgå indtastningerne for at "
"sikre, at alle de talte mængder er korrekt indtastet. For at afslutte "
"lagerjusteringen skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Bekræft`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:196
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Validate` barcode can be scanned in place of clicking "
"the :guilabel:`Confirm` button."
msgstr ""
"Stregkoden :guilabel:`Valider` kan scannes i stedet for at klikke på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Bekræft`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/adjustments.rst:199
msgid ""
"Odoo then navigates back to the :guilabel:`Barcode Scanning` screen. A small "
"green banner appears in the top-right corner, confirming the inventory count "
"has been updated."
msgstr ""
"Odoo navigerer derefter tilbage til skærmen :guilabel:`Stregkodeskanning`. "
"Et lille grønt banner vises i øverste højre hjørne, som bekræfter, at "
"lageroptællingen er blevet opdateret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:3
msgid "Default barcode nomenclature"
msgstr "Standard stregkodenomenklatur"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:10
msgid ""
"*Barcode nomenclatures* define how barcodes are recognized and categorized. "
"When a barcode is scanned, it is associated to the **first** rule with a "
"matching pattern. The pattern syntax is described in Odoo's nomenclature "
"list using a regular expression, and a barcode is successfully read by Odoo "
"if its prefix and/or length matches the one defined in the barcode's rule."
msgstr ""
"*Stregkodenomenklaturer* definerer, hvordan stregkoder genkendes og "
"kategoriseres. Når en stregkode skannes, bliver den associeret med den "
"**første** regel med et matchende mønster. Mønstersyntaksen er beskrevet i "
"Odoos nomenklaturoversigt ved hjælp af et regulært udtryk, og en stregkode "
"læses med succes af Odoo, hvis dens præfiks og/eller længde matcher den, der "
"er defineret i stregkodens regel."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:15
msgid ""
"For instance, at a :doc:`Point of Sale <../../../sales/point_of_sale>` "
"station, product weight barcodes in the European Article Number (EAN) "
"format, which begin with `21` and have five digits specifying the weight, "
"are used to weigh products and generate a barcode depicting the weight and "
"price. The `21` and five-digit weight is the barcode pattern used to "
"identify the barcode and can be customized to ensure Odoo correctly "
"interprets all barcodes for the business."
msgstr ""
"For eksempel bruges produktvægtstregkoder på en :doc:`POS <../../../sales/"
"point_of_sale>`-station i European Article Number (EAN)-formatet, som "
"begynder med `21` og har fem cifre, der angiver vægten, til at veje "
"produkter og generere en stregkode, der viser vægten og prisen. `21` og den "
"femsifrede vægt er det stregkodemønster, der bruges til at identificere "
"stregkoden, og det kan tilpasses for at sikre, at Odoo korrekt fortolker "
"alle stregkoder for virksomheden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:22
msgid ""
"Barcodes are also commonly used with Odoo's **Inventory** and **Barcode** "
"apps."
msgstr ""
"Stregkoder bruges også almindeligvis med Odoos apps **Lager** og "
"**Stregkode**."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:24
msgid ""
"Odoo **Barcode** supports |EAN|, Universal Product Code (UPC), and :doc:`GS1 "
"<gs1_nomenclature>` formats. This document exclusively focuses "
"on :ref:`default rules and patterns in Odoo <barcode/operations/default-"
"nomenclature-list>`, which use |UPC| and |EAN| encoding."
msgstr ""
"Odoo **Stregkode** understøtter |EAN|, Universal Product Code (UPC) "
"og :doc:`GS1 <gs1_nomenclature>`-formater. Dette dokument fokuserer "
"udelukkende på :ref:`standardregler og -mønstre i Odoo <barcode/operations/"
"default-nomenclature-list>`, som bruger |UPC| og |EAN|-kodning."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:29
msgid ""
"To use |UPC| and |EAN| barcodes for uniquely identifying products across the "
"entire supply chain, they **must** be `purchased from GS1 <https://"
"www.gs1.org/standards/get-barcodes>`_."
msgstr ""
"For at bruge |UPC| og |EAN| stregkoder til entydigt at identificere "
"produkter i hele forsyningskæden, **skal** de `købes fra GS1 <https://"
"www.gs1.org/standards/get-barcodes>`_."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:32
msgid ""
"In Odoo, custom barcode patterns can be defined to recognize barcodes "
"specific to the company. Barcodes do not need to be purchased if used only "
"within the company, such as in the :ref:`example <barcode/operations/product-"
"weight>` where the barcode is written in the |EAN| format."
msgstr ""
"I Odoo kan brugerdefinerede stregkodemønstre defineres for at genkende "
"stregkoder, der er specifikke for virksomheden. Stregkoder behøver ikke at "
"blive købt, hvis de kun bruges internt i virksomheden, som i :ref:`eksemplet "
"<barcode/operations/product-weight>`, hvor stregkoden er skrevet i |EAN|-"
"formatet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:40
msgid ""
"To use default nomenclature, navigate to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> "
"Configuration --> Settings`. Under the :guilabel:`Barcode` section, tick "
"the :guilabel:`Barcode Scanner` checkbox. Doing so installs the **Barcode** "
"app in the database."
msgstr ""
"For at bruge standardnomenklaturen skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Lager-appen --> Konfiguration --> Indstillinger`. Under "
"afsnittet :guilabel:`Stregkode` skal du sætte flueben i "
"afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Stregkodescanner`. Dette installerer "
"**Stregkode**-appen i databasen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:44
msgid ""
"Next, in the :guilabel:`Barcode Nomenclature` field, "
"ensure :guilabel:`Default Nomenclature` is selected. Then, "
"click :guilabel:`Save`."
msgstr ""
"Dernæst skal du i feltet :guilabel:`Stregkodenomenklatur` sikre, "
"at :guilabel:`Standardnomenklatur` er valgt. Klik derefter "
"på :guilabel:`Gem`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:None
msgid "Enabled barcode setting with Default Nomenclature selected."
msgstr "Aktiveret stregkodeindstilling med valgt standardnomenklatur."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:51
msgid ""
"With the **Barcode** module installed, and the :guilabel:`Default "
"Nomenclature` selected, the barcode actions using |UPC| and |EAN|, detailed "
"in the :ref:`default nomenclature list <barcode/operations/default-"
"nomenclature-list>`, are available for use. And, by default, Odoo "
"automatically handles |UPC|/|EAN| conversion."
msgstr ""
"Med **Stregkode**-modulet installeret og :guilabel:`Standardnomenklatur` "
"valgt er stregkodehandlingerne ved brug af |UPC| og |EAN|, som er beskrevet "
"i :ref:`standardnomenklaturoversigten <barcode/operations/default-"
"nomenclature-list>`, tilgængelige. Som standard håndterer Odoo automatisk "
"konvertering mellem |UPC| og |EAN|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:59
msgid "Example: product weight barcode"
msgstr "Eksempel: produktvægtstregkode"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:61
msgid ""
"To better understand how barcode nomenclature is used to identify products "
"in Odoo, this example where product weight barcodes in |EAN| format are used "
"to allow a :doc:`Point of Sale <../../../sales/point_of_sale>` business to "
"automatically print barcodes, and calculate the price using the weight of "
"the item."
msgstr ""
"For bedre at forstå, hvordan stregkodenomenklatur bruges til at identificere "
"produkter i Odoo, viser dette eksempel, hvordan produktvægtstregkoder i |"
"EAN|-format bruges til at gøre det muligt for en :doc:`POS <../../../sales/"
"point_of_sale>`-virksomhed automatisk at udskrive stregkoder og beregne "
"prisen ud fra varens vægt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:66
msgid "To set up barcodes for weighted products, the following rule is used:"
msgstr ""
"For at konfigurere stregkoder til vejede produkter bruges følgende regel:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:71
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:186
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/gs1_nomenclature.rst:173
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/gs1_usage.rst:38
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/gs1_usage.rst:166
msgid "Rule Name"
msgstr "Regelnavn"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:72
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:189
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/gs1_nomenclature.rst:173
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/gs1_usage.rst:38
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/gs1_usage.rst:166
msgid "Barcode Pattern"
msgstr "Stregkodemønster"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:73
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/gs1_usage.rst:38
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/gs1_usage.rst:166
msgid "Field in Odoo"
msgstr "Felt i Odoo"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:74
msgid "Weighted Barcodes 3 Decimals"
msgstr "Vejede stregkoder 3 decimaler"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:75
msgid "(21)....{NNDDD}"
msgstr "(21)....{NNDDD}"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:76
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/gs1_nomenclature.rst:177
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/gs1_usage.rst:40
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/gs1_usage.rst:168
msgid ":guilabel:`Barcode` field on product form"
msgstr ":guilabel:`Stregkode`-felt på produktformular"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:79
msgid ""
"To better understand the barcode pattern for weighted products, consider the "
"barcode, `2112345000008`:"
msgstr ""
"For bedre at forstå stregkodemønsteret for vejede produkter skal du overveje "
"stregkoden `2112345000008`:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:82
msgid "`21`: code that identifies this a barcode for weighted products."
msgstr ""
"`21`: kode, der identificerer dette som en stregkode for vejede produkter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:83
msgid ""
"`12345`: five digits (denoted by `.....` in the table above) that identify "
"the product."
msgstr ""
"`12345`: fem cifre (angivet med `.....` i tabellen ovenfor), der "
"identificerer produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:84
msgid ""
"`00000`: five digits (denoted by `{NNDDD}` in the table) representing the "
"weight of the product. On the product form, the five weight values **must** "
"be `00000`. The first two digits are whole number values, and the last three "
"digits are decimal values. For example, \"13.5 grams\" in the `{NNDDD}` "
"format is `13500`."
msgstr ""
"`00000`: fem cifre (angivet med `{NNDDD}` i tabellen), der repræsenterer "
"produktets vægt. På produktformularen **skal** de fem vægtværdier være "
"`00000`. De første to cifre er heltalværdier, og de sidste tre cifre er "
"decimalværdier. For eksempel er \"13,5 gram\" i `{NNDDD}`-formatet `13500`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:88
msgid ""
"`8`: `check digit <https://www.gs1.org/services/check-digit-calculator>`_ "
"for `211234500000`."
msgstr ""
"`8`: `kontrolciffer <https://www.gs1.org/services/check-digit-calculator>`_ "
"for `211234500000`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:90
msgid "Together, these components make up a 13-character |EAN| - 13 barcode."
msgstr "Tilsammen udgør disse komponenter en 13-tegns |EAN|-13-stregkode."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:92
msgid ""
"To configure the product barcode for `Pasta Bolognese`, the |EAN| barcode "
"for weighted products, `2112345000008`, is entered in "
"the :guilabel:`Barcode` field on the product form (accessible by going "
"to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> Products --> Products`, and selecting "
"the desired product). In addition, the :guilabel:`Unit of Measure` is set "
"to :guilabel:`kg`."
msgstr ""
"For at konfigurere produktstregkoden for `Pasta Bolognese` indtastes |EAN|-"
"stregkoden for vejede produkter, `2112345000008`, i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Stregkode` på produktformularen (tilgængelig ved at gå "
"til :menuselection:`Lager-app --> Produkter --> Produkter` og vælge det "
"ønskede produkt). Derudover er :guilabel:`Måleenhed` indstillet "
"til :guilabel:`kg`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:None
msgid "Barcode field on the product form."
msgstr "Stregkodefelt på produktformularen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:101
msgid ""
"Next, a customer's bowl of pasta is weighed to be `1.5` kilograms. This "
"generates a new barcode for the pasta, according to the weight: "
"`211234501500`, which has a check digit of `2`. The new barcode is "
"`2112345015002`."
msgstr ""
"Dernæst vejes en kundes skål pasta til at være `1,5` kilogram. Dette "
"genererer en ny stregkode for pastaen i henhold til vægten: `211234501500`, "
"som har et kontrolciffer på `2`. Den nye stregkode er `2112345015002`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:None
msgid "Generated barcode that includes a weight of 1.5 kg."
msgstr "Genereret stregkode, der inkluderer en vægt på 1,5 kg."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:109
msgid ""
"Ensure the products scan properly, by navigating to "
"the :menuselection:`Barcode app --> Operations`. Next, click any operation "
"type, such as :guilabel:`Receipts`. Then, click the :guilabel:`New` button "
"to create a draft stock move. Scan the product weight barcode, such as "
"`2112345015002`, and if the intended product appears, the barcode setup is "
"correct."
msgstr ""
"Kontroller, at produkterne scannes korrekt ved at gå "
"til :menuselection:`Stregkode-app --> Operationer`. Klik derefter på en "
"vilkårlig operationstype, såsom :guilabel:`Modtagelser`. Klik derefter på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Ny` for at oprette et udkast til lagerbevægelse. Scan "
"produktets vægtstregkode, såsom `2112345015002`, og hvis det ønskede produkt "
"vises, er stregkodeopsætningen korrekt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:None
msgid "Show successfully scanned barcode."
msgstr "Vis succesfuldt scannet stregkode."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:119
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/gs1_nomenclature.rst:96
msgid "Create rules"
msgstr "Opret regler"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:122
msgid ""
"Adding new rules is necessary for |UPC| and |EAN| formats that are **not** "
"in Odoo's default list, since barcodes cannot be read successfully if there "
"are unknown fields."
msgstr ""
"Tilføjelse af nye regler er nødvendig for |UPC|- og |EAN|-formater, der "
"**ikke** findes i Odoos standardliste, da stregkoder ikke kan læses korrekt, "
"hvis der er ukendte felter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:125
msgid ""
"While new rules can be created, Odoo fields do **not** auto-populate with "
"information from these rules. `Custom development <https://www.odoo.com/"
"appointment/132>`_ is required for this functionality."
msgstr ""
"Selvom nye regler kan oprettes, udfylder Odoo-felter **ikke** automatisk med "
"information fra disse regler. `Custom development <https://www.odoo.com/"
"appointment/132>`_ er påkrævet for denne funktionalitet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:129
msgid ""
"To create a rule, first enable :ref:`developer mode <developer-mode>`. Then, "
"navigate to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> Configuration --> Barcode "
"Nomenclatures`, and select :guilabel:`Default Nomenclature`."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette en regel skal du først aktivere :ref:`udviklertilstand "
"<developer-mode>`. Gå derefter til :menuselection:`Lager-app --> "
"Konfiguration --> Stregkodenomenklaturer` og "
"vælg :guilabel:`Standardnomenklatur`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:133
msgid "On this page, configure the following optional fields:"
msgstr "Konfigurer følgende valgfrie felter på denne side:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:135
msgid ""
":guilabel:`UPC/EAN Conversion`: determines if a |UPC|/|EAN| barcode should "
"be automatically converted when matching a rule with another encoding. "
"Options include :guilabel:`Always` (the default "
"option), :guilabel:`Never`, :guilabel:`EAN-13 to UPC-A`, and :guilabel:`UPC-"
"A to EAN-13`."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`UPC/EAN-konvertering`: bestemmer, om en |UPC|/|EAN|-stregkode "
"automatisk skal konverteres, når den matcher en regel med en anden kodning. "
"Valgmulighederne omfatter :guilabel:`Altid` "
"(standardindstillingen), :guilabel:`Aldrig`, :guilabel:`EAN-13 til UPC-A` "
"og :guilabel:`UPC-A til EAN-13`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:138
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Is GS1 Nomenclature`: ensure this checkbox is **not** ticked, as "
"the :guilabel:`Default Nomenclature` uses |UPC| and |EAN| encoding, *not* "
"GS1 encoding."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Er GS1-nomenklatur`: sørg for, at dette afkrydsningsfelt **ikke** "
"er markeret, da :guilabel:`Standardnomenklatur` bruger |UPC|- og |EAN|-"
"kodning, *ikke* GS1-kodning."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:None
msgid "Default Nomenclature page setting fields."
msgstr "Side med indstillingsfelter for standardnomenklatur."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:145
msgid ""
"On the :guilabel:`Default Nomenclature` page, click :guilabel:`Add a line` "
"at the bottom of the table, which opens a :guilabel:`Create Rules` pop-up "
"window to create a new rule."
msgstr ""
"På siden :guilabel:`Standardnomenklatur` skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj "
"en linje` nederst i tabellen, hvilket åbner et pop op-"
"vindue :guilabel:`Opret regler` for at oprette en ny regel."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:148
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Rule Name` field is used internally to identify what the "
"barcode represents."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`Regelnavn` bruges internt til at identificere, hvad "
"stregkoden repræsenterer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:150
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Sequence` field represents the priority of the rule; meaning "
"the smaller the value, the higher the rule appears on the table."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`Sekvens` repræsenterer regelens prioritet; hvilket "
"betyder, at jo mindre værdien er, jo højere vises reglen i tabellen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:153
msgid ""
"The barcode :guilabel:`Type` field represents different classifications of "
"information that can be understood by the system "
"(e.g., :guilabel:`Package`, :guilabel:`Lot`, :guilabel:`Location`, :guilabel:`Coupon`, "
"etc.)."
msgstr ""
"Stregkode-feltet :guilabel:`Type` repræsenterer forskellige klassifikationer "
"af information, der kan forstås af systemet "
"(f.eks. :guilabel:`Pakke`, :guilabel:`Lot`, :guilabel:`Lokation`, :guilabel:`Kupon` "
"osv.)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:157
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Encoding` field specifies which encoding the barcode uses. "
"This rule **only** applies if the barcode uses this specific encoding. The "
"available :guilabel:`Encoding` options "
"are: :guilabel:`EAN-13`, :guilabel:`EAN-8`, :guilabel:`UPC-A`, "
"and :guilabel:`GS1-28`."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`Kodning` specificerer, hvilken kodning stregkoden bruger. "
"Denne regel gælder **kun**, hvis stregkoden bruger denne specifikke kodning. "
"De tilgængelige :guilabel:`Kodning`-muligheder "
"er: :guilabel:`EAN-13`, :guilabel:`EAN-8`, :guilabel:`UPC-A` "
"og :guilabel:`GS1-28`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:161
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Barcode Pattern` field represents how the sequence of letters "
"or numbers is recognized by the system to contain information about the "
"product. Sometimes, when a certain amount of digits are required, the number "
"of `.` is shown. `N` represents whole number digits, and `D` represent "
"decimal digits."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`Stregkodemønster` repræsenterer, hvordan sekvensen af "
"bogstaver eller tal genkendes af systemet til at indeholde information om "
"produktet. Sommetider, når et bestemt antal cifre er påkrævet, vises "
"antallet af `.`. `N` repræsenterer hele talcifre, og `D` repræsenterer "
"decimalcifre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:167
msgid ""
"`1...` represents any 4-digit number that starts with 1. `NNDD` represents a "
"two digit number with two decimal points. For example, `14.25` is 1425."
msgstr ""
"`1...` repræsenterer et hvilket som helst 4-cifret tal, der starter med 1. "
"`NNDD` repræsenterer et tocifret tal med to decimaler. For eksempel er "
"`14.25` 1425."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:170
msgid ""
"After filling in the information, click the :guilabel:`Save & New` button to "
"save the rule, and instantly start creating another rule. Or, "
"click :guilabel:`Save & Close` to save the rule, and return to the table of "
"rules."
msgstr ""
"Efter udfyldning af informationen skal du klikke på knappen :guilabel:`Gem "
"og ny` for at gemme reglen og straks begynde at oprette en anden regel. "
"Eller klik på :guilabel:`Gem og luk` for at gemme reglen og vende tilbage "
"til tabellen med regler."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:177
msgid "Default nomenclature list"
msgstr "Liste over standardnomenklatur"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature.rst:179
msgid ""
"The table below contains Odoo's list of :guilabel:`Default Nomenclature` "
"rules. Barcode patterns are written in regular expressions."
msgstr ""
"Tabellen nedenfor indeholder Odoos liste over :guilabel:`Default "
"Nomenclature` regler. Stregkodemønstre er skrevet i regulære udtryk."

