#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:3
msgid "Maintenance requests"
msgstr "Vedligeholdelsesanmodninger"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:7
msgid ""
"In order to keep equipment and work centers functioning properly, it is "
"often necessary to perform maintenance on them. This can include preventive "
"maintenance, intended to prevent equipment from breaking down, or corrective "
"maintenance, which is used to fix equipment that is broken or otherwise "
"unusable."
msgstr ""
"For at holde udstyr og arbejdscentre funktionsdygtige er det ofte nødvendigt "
"at udføre vedligeholdelse på dem. Dette kan omfatte forebyggende "
"vedligeholdelse, der har til formål at forhindre udstyr i at gå i stykker, "
"eller korrigerende vedligeholdelse, som bruges til at reparere udstyr, der "
"er i stykker eller på anden måde ubrugeligt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:12
msgid ""
"In Odoo **Maintenance**, users can create *maintenance requests* to schedule "
"and track the progress of equipment and work center maintenance."
msgstr ""
"I Odoo **Vedligeholdelse** kan brugere oprette *vedligeholdelsesanmodninger* "
"for at planlægge og spore fremdriften af udstyr og "
"arbejdscentervedligeholdelse."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:16
msgid "Maintenance access rights"
msgstr "Adgangsrettigheder til vedligeholdelse"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:18
msgid ""
"To create a maintenance request for equipment, a user has to have access to "
"the equipment they are submitting the request for. This can be done in one "
"of two ways:"
msgstr ""
"For at oprette en vedligeholdelsesanmodning for udstyr skal en bruger have "
"adgang til det udstyr, som anmodningen gælder for. Dette kan gøres på en af "
"to måder:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:21
msgid ""
"If a user is granted :guilabel:`Equipment Manager` level access rights for "
"the **Maintenance** app, they have access to all of the equipment in the "
"app. To view or edit the access rights for a user, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Settings --> Manager Users` and click a user's profile to "
"open it. On the :guilabel:`Access Rights` tab, scroll to "
"the :guilabel:`Supply Chain` section, and in the :guilabel:`Maintenance` "
"field, select :guilabel:`Equipment Manager` from the drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"Hvis en bruger tildeles adgangsrettigheder på :guilabel:`Udstyrschef`-niveau "
"til applikationen **Vedligeholdelse**, har de adgang til alt udstyr i appen. "
"For at se eller redigere adgangsrettigheder for en bruger, gå "
"til :menuselection:`Indstillinger --> Administrér brugere` og klik på en "
"brugers profil for at åbne den. På fanen :guilabel:`Adgangsrettigheder` skal "
"du rulle ned til afsnittet :guilabel:`Forsyningskæde`, og i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Vedligeholdelse` skal du vælge :guilabel:`Udstyrschef` fra "
"rullemenuen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:0
msgid "The Supply Chain access rights on a user record."
msgstr "Adgangsrettighederne for forsyningskæden på en brugerregistrering."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:30
msgid ""
"If a user does not require full access to all equipment, they can be "
"assigned as a *Follower* to one or more pieces of equipment. This allows "
"them to create maintenance requests for that piece of equipment, without "
"altering access rights. To add a user as a follower, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Maintenance --> Equipment --> Machines & Tools`, and "
"click on a piece of equipment to open it. In the *chatter* for the record, "
"click on the :icon:`fa-user` :guilabel:`(user)` icon to open the list of "
"followers. Click :guilabel:`Add Followers`. On the :guilabel:`Add followers "
"to this document` pop-up, select the appropriate user from "
"the :guilabel:`Followers` drop-down. To send a message alerting users that "
"they have been added as a follower, slide the :guilabel:`Notify Recipients` "
"toggle to active. When finished, click :guilabel:`Add Followers`."
msgstr ""
"Hvis en bruger ikke kræver fuld adgang til alt udstyr, kan de tildeles som "
"*Følger* til et eller flere stykker udstyr. Dette giver dem mulighed for at "
"oprette vedligeholdelsesanmodninger for det pågældende udstyr uden at ændre "
"adgangsrettigheder. For at tilføje en bruger som følger, gå "
"til :menuselection:`Vedligeholdelse --> Udstyr --> Maskiner og værktøj`, og "
"klik på et stykke udstyr for at åbne det. I *chatten* for registreringen "
"skal du klikke på ikonet :icon:`fa-user` :guilabel:`(bruger)` for at åbne "
"listen over følgere. Klik :guilabel:`Tilføj følgere`. I pop op-"
"vinduet :guilabel:`Tilføj følgere til dette dokument` skal du vælge den "
"relevante bruger fra rullemenuen :guilabel:`Følgere`. For at sende en "
"besked, der informerer brugere om, at de er blevet tilføjet som følgere, "
"skal du aktivere :guilabel:`Underret modtagere`. Når du er færdig, skal du "
"klikke :guilabel:`Tilføj følgere`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:0
msgid ""
"The followers list on an equipment record, with the add followers button "
"highlighted."
msgstr ""
"Følgerlisten på en udstyrsregistrering med knappen Tilføj følgere fremhævet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:47
msgid ""
"To create a new maintenance request, navigate to :menuselection:`Maintenance "
"app --> Maintenance --> Maintenance Requests`, and click :guilabel:`New`."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette en ny vedligeholdelsesanmodning skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Vedligeholdelse-app --> Vedligeholdelse --> "
"Vedligeholdelsesanmodninger` og klikke på :guilabel:`Ny`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:50
msgid ""
"Begin filling out the form by entering a descriptive title in "
"the :guilabel:`Request` field (e.g., `Drill not working`)."
msgstr ""
"Begynd at udfylde formularen ved at indtaste en beskrivende titel i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Anmodning` (f.eks. `Bor virker ikke`)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:53
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Created By` field auto-populates with the user creating the "
"request, but a different user can be selected by clicking on the drop-down "
"menu."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`Oprettet af` udfyldes automatisk med den bruger, der "
"opretter anmodningen, men en anden bruger kan vælges ved at klikke på "
"rullemenuen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:56
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`For` drop-down menu, select :guilabel:`Equipment` if the "
"maintenance request is being created for a piece of equipment, "
"or :guilabel:`Work Center` if it is being created for a work center."
msgstr ""
"I rullemenuen :guilabel:`Til` skal du vælge :guilabel:`Udstyr`, hvis "
"vedligeholdelsesanmodningen oprettes for et udstyr, "
"eller :guilabel:`Arbejdscenter`, hvis den oprettes for et arbejdscenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:60
msgid ""
"Depending on the option selected in the :guilabel:`For` field, the next "
"field is titled either :guilabel:`Equipment` or :guilabel:`Work Center`. "
"Using the drop-down menu for either field, select a piece of equipment or a "
"work center."
msgstr ""
"Afhængigt af den valgte mulighed i feltet :guilabel:`Til` hedder det næste "
"felt enten :guilabel:`Udstyr` eller :guilabel:`Arbejdscenter`. Brug "
"rullemenuen for et af felterne til at vælge et udstyr eller et arbejdscenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:64
msgid ""
"If the *Custom Maintenance Worksheets* setting is enabled in the "
"**Maintenance** app's settings, a :guilabel:`Worksheet Template` field "
"appears below the :guilabel:`Equipment` or :guilabel:`Work Center` field. If "
"necessary, use this field to select a worksheet to be filled out by the "
"employee performing the maintenance."
msgstr ""
"Hvis indstillingen *Brugerdefinerede vedligeholdelsesark* er aktiveret i "
"applikationen **Vedligeholdelse**s indstillinger, vises et "
"felt :guilabel:`Arkskabelon` under feltet :guilabel:`Udstyr` "
"eller :guilabel:`Arbejdscenter`. Brug om nødvendigt dette felt til at vælge "
"et ark, der skal udfyldes af medarbejderen, der udfører vedligeholdelsen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:69
msgid ""
"The next field is titled :guilabel:`Request Date`, and is set by default to "
"the date on which the maintenance request is created. This date cannot be "
"changed by the user."
msgstr ""
"Det næste felt hedder :guilabel:`Anmodningsdato` og er som standard "
"indstillet til den dato, hvor vedligeholdelsesanmodningen oprettes. Denne "
"dato kan ikke ændres af brugeren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:72
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Maintenance Type` field, select the :guilabel:`Corrective` "
"option if the request is intended to fix an existing issue, or "
"the :guilabel:`Preventive` option if the request is intended to prevent "
"issues from occurring in the future."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Vedligeholdelsestype` skal du vælge "
"muligheden :guilabel:`Korrigerende`, hvis anmodningen er beregnet til at "
"løse et eksisterende problem, eller muligheden :guilabel:`Forebyggende`, "
"hvis anmodningen er beregnet til at forhindre problemer i at opstå i "
"fremtiden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:76
msgid ""
"If the request is being created to address an issue that arose during a "
"specific manufacturing order (MO), select it in the :guilabel:`Manufacturing "
"Order` field."
msgstr ""
"Hvis anmodningen oprettes for at håndtere et problem, der opstod under en "
"bestemt produktionsordre (MO), skal du vælge den i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Produktionsordre`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:79
msgid ""
"If an |MO| was selected in the :guilabel:`Manufacturing Order` field, "
"a :guilabel:`Work Order` field appears below it. If the issue arose during a "
"specific work order, specify it in this field."
msgstr ""
"Hvis en |MO| blev valgt i feltet :guilabel:`Produktionsordre`, vises et "
"felt :guilabel:`Arbejdsordre` nedenfor. Hvis problemet opstod under en "
"bestemt arbejdsordre, skal du angive den i dette felt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:82
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Team` field, select the maintenance team that is "
"responsible for managing the request. If a specific team member is "
"responsible, select them in the :guilabel:`Responsible` field."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Team` skal du vælge det vedligeholdelsesteam, der er "
"ansvarligt for at administrere anmodningen. Hvis et bestemt teammedlem er "
"ansvarligt, skal du vælge vedkommende i feltet :guilabel:`Ansvarlig`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:85
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Scheduled Date` field is used to specify the date on which "
"maintenance should take place, and the time it should begin. Choose a date "
"by clicking on the field to open a calendar in a pop-up window, and then "
"select a day on the calendar. Enter an hour and minute in the two fields "
"below the calendar, and click :guilabel:`Apply` to save the date and time."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`Planlagt dato` bruges til at angive den dato, hvor "
"vedligeholdelsen skal finde sted, og det tidspunkt, den skal begynde. Vælg "
"en dato ved at klikke på feltet for at åbne en kalender i et pop-up-vindue, "
"og vælg derefter en dag i kalenderen. Indtast time og minut i de to felter "
"under kalenderen, og klik på :guilabel:`Anvend` for at gemme dato og "
"tidspunkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:90
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Duration` field is used to specify the time it takes to "
"complete the maintenance request. Use the text-entry field to enter the time "
"in a `00:00` format."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`Varighed` bruges til at angive den tid, det tager at "
"fuldføre vedligeholdelsesanmodningen. Brug tekstindtastningsfeltet til at "
"indtaste tiden i formatet `00:00`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:93
msgid ""
"If :guilabel:`Work Center` was selected in the :guilabel:`For` field, "
"a :guilabel:`Block Workcenter` checkbox appears below "
"the :guilabel:`Duration` field. Enable the checkbox to prevent work orders "
"or other maintenance from being scheduled at the specified work center while "
"the maintenance request is being processed."
msgstr ""
"Hvis :guilabel:`Arbejdscenter` blev valgt i feltet :guilabel:`Til`, vises et "
"afkrydsningsfelt :guilabel:`Bloker arbejdscenter` under "
"feltet :guilabel:`Varighed`. Aktiver afkrydsningsfeltet for at forhindre, at "
"arbejdsordrer eller anden vedligeholdelse planlægges på det angivne "
"arbejdscenter, mens vedligeholdelsesanmodningen behandles."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:98
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Priority` field is used to communicate the importance (or "
"urgency) of the maintenance request. Assign the request a priority between "
"zero and three :icon:`fa-star` :guilabel:`(star)` icons, by clicking on the "
"desired star number. Requests assigned a higher priority appear above those "
"with a lower priority, on the Kanban board used to track the progression of "
"maintenance requests."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`Prioritet` bruges til at kommunikere vigtigheden (eller "
"hastigheden) af vedligeholdelsesanmodningen. Tildel anmodningen en prioritet "
"mellem nul og tre :icon:`fa-star` :guilabel:`(stjerne)` ikoner ved at klikke "
"på det ønskede stjernenummer. Anmodninger med højere prioritet vises over "
"dem med lavere prioritet på Kanban-tavlen, der bruges til at spore "
"udviklingen af vedligeholdelsesanmodninger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:104
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Notes` tab at the bottom of the form, enter any relevant "
"details about the maintenance request (why the maintenance issue arose, when "
"it occurred, etc.)."
msgstr ""
"I fanen :guilabel:`Noter` nederst i formularen skal du indtaste eventuelle "
"relevante detaljer om vedligeholdelsesanmodningen (hvorfor "
"vedligeholdelsesproblemet opstod, hvornår det skete osv.)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:107
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Instructions` tab is used to include instructions for how "
"maintenance should be performed. Select one of the three options, and then "
"include the instructions as detailed below:"
msgstr ""
"Fanen :guilabel:`Instruktioner` bruges til at inkludere instruktioner for, "
"hvordan vedligeholdelse skal udføres. Vælg en af de tre muligheder, og "
"medtag derefter instruktionerne som beskrevet nedenfor:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:110
msgid ""
":guilabel:`PDF`: click the :guilabel:`Upload your file` button to open the "
"device's file manager, and then select a file to upload."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`PDF`: klik på knappen :guilabel:`Upload din fil` for at åbne "
"enhedens filhåndtering, og vælg derefter en fil, der skal uploades."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:112
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Google Slide`: enter a :guilabel:`Google Slide link` in the text-"
"entry field that appears after the option is selected."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Google Slide`: indtast et :guilabel:`Google Slide-link` i "
"tekstindtastningsfeltet, der vises, når indstillingen er valgt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:114
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Text`: enter the instructions in the text-entry field that "
"appears after the option is selected."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Tekst`: indtast instruktionerne i tekstindtastningsfeltet, der "
"vises, når indstillingen er valgt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:None
msgid "A maintenance request form filled out for a piece of equipment."
msgstr "En vedligeholdelsesanmodningsformular udfyldt for et stykke udstyr."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:122
msgid "Process maintenance request"
msgstr "Behandle vedligeholdelsesanmodning"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:124
msgid ""
"Once a maintenance request has been created, it appears in the *New Request* "
"stage of the *Maintenance Requests* page, which can be accessed by "
"navigating to :menuselection:`Maintenance app --> Maintenance --> "
"Maintenance Requests`."
msgstr ""
"Når en vedligeholdelsesanmodning er oprettet, vises den i stadiet *Ny "
"anmodning* på siden *Vedligeholdelsesanmodninger*, som kan tilgås ved at "
"navigere til :menuselection:`Vedligeholdelse-app --> Vedligeholdelse --> "
"Vedligeholdelsesanmodninger`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:128
msgid ""
"Maintenance requests can be moved to different stages by dragging and "
"dropping them. They can also be moved by clicking on a request to open it in "
"a new page, and then selecting the desired stage from the stage indicator "
"bar, located above the top-right corner of the request's form."
msgstr ""
"Vedligeholdelsesanmodninger kan flyttes til forskellige stadier ved at "
"trække og slippe dem. De kan også flyttes ved at klikke på en anmodning for "
"at åbne den på en ny side og derefter vælge det ønskede stadie fra "
"stadieindikatoren placeret over øverste højre hjørne af anmodningens "
"formular."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:132
msgid ""
"Successful maintenance requests should be moved to the :guilabel:`Repaired` "
"stage, indicating that the specified piece of equipment or work center is "
"repaired."
msgstr ""
"Vellykkede vedligeholdelsesanmodninger bør flyttes til "
"stadiet :guilabel:`Repareret`, hvilket angiver, at det angivne stykke udstyr "
"eller arbejdscenter er repareret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_requests.rst:135
msgid ""
"Failed maintenance requests should be moved to the :guilabel:`Scrap` stage, "
"indicating the specified piece of equipment, or work center, could not be "
"repaired, and must instead be scrapped."
msgstr ""
"Mislykkede vedligeholdelsesanmodninger bør flyttes til "
"stadiet :guilabel:`Skrot`, hvilket angiver, at det angivne stykke udstyr "
"eller arbejdscenter ikke kunne repareres og i stedet skal skrottes."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:3
msgid "Maintenance setup"
msgstr "Opsætning af vedligeholdelse"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:8
msgid ""
"Odoo *Maintenance* helps companies schedule corrective and preventive "
"maintenance on equipment used in their warehouse. This helps companies avoid "
"equipment breakdowns, blocks in warehouse work centers, and emergency repair "
"costs."
msgstr ""
"Odoo *Vedligeholdelse* hjælper virksomheder med at planlægge korrigerende og "
"forebyggende vedligeholdelse af udstyr, der bruges i deres lager. Dette "
"hjælper virksomheder med at undgå udstyrsnedbrud, blokeringer i lagerets "
"arbejdscentre og nødreparationsomkostninger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:13
msgid "Maintenance teams"
msgstr "Vedligeholdelsesteams"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:15
msgid ""
"When creating maintenance requests, a *maintenance team* can be assigned to "
"the request as the team responsible for handling the request."
msgstr ""
"Ved oprettelse af vedligeholdelsesanmodninger kan et *vedligeholdelsesteam* "
"tildeles anmodningen som det team, der er ansvarligt for at håndtere "
"anmodningen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:18
msgid ""
"To view existing maintenance teams, navigate to :menuselection:`Maintenance "
"app --> Configuration --> Maintenance Teams`."
msgstr ""
"For at se eksisterende vedligeholdelsesteams skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Vedligeholdelse-app --> Konfiguration --> "
"Vedligeholdelsesteams`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:21
msgid ""
"From the resulting :guilabel:`Teams` page, a list of all existing teams (if "
"any) is displayed, with the :guilabel:`Team Name`, :guilabel:`Team Members`, "
"and :guilabel:`Company` listed in the columns, by default."
msgstr ""
"Fra den resulterende side :guilabel:`Teams` vises en liste over alle "
"eksisterende teams (hvis nogen) "
"med :guilabel:`Teamnavn`, :guilabel:`Teammedlemmer` "
"og :guilabel:`Virksomhed` angivet i kolonnerne som standard."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:None
msgid "List of Teams on Maintenance Teams page."
msgstr "Liste over teams på siden Vedligeholdelsesteams."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:29
msgid ""
"To add a new team, click :guilabel:`New`. This adds a blank line at the "
"bottom of the list of teams. In the blank field that appears below "
"the :guilabel:`Team Name` column, assign a name to the new maintenance team."
msgstr ""
"For at tilføje et nyt team skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Ny`. Dette tilføjer "
"en tom linje nederst på listen over teams. I det tomme felt, der vises under "
"kolonnen :guilabel:`Teamnavn`, skal du tildele et navn til det nye "
"vedligeholdelsesteam."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:33
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Team Members` column, click the field to reveal a drop-"
"down menu with existing users in the database. Choose which users should be "
"members of the new maintenance team."
msgstr ""
"I kolonnen :guilabel:`Teammedlemmer` skal du klikke på feltet for at få vist "
"en rullemenü med eksisterende brugere i databasen. Vælg, hvilke brugere der "
"skal være medlemmer af det nye vedligeholdelsesteam."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:36
msgid ""
"Click :guilabel:`Search More...` to open a :guilabel:`Search: Team Members` "
"pop-up window to search for users **not** shown on the initial drop-down "
"menu."
msgstr ""
"Klik på :guilabel:`Søg efter flere...` for at åbne et pop op-vindue "
"med :guilabel:`Søg: Teammedlemmer` for at søge efter brugere, der **ikke** "
"vises i den første rullemenü."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:None
msgid "Search: Team Members pop-up window."
msgstr "Pop op-vinduet Søg: Teammedlemmer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:43
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Company` column, if in a multi-company environment, click "
"the drop-down menu to select the company in the database to which this new "
"maintenance team belongs."
msgstr ""
"I kolonnen :guilabel:`Firma`, hvis der er et multi-firma miljø, skal du "
"klikke på rullemenuen for at vælge den firma i databasen, som dette nye "
"vedligeholdelsesteam tilhører."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:46
msgid "Once ready, click :guilabel:`Save` to save changes."
msgstr ""
"Når du er klar, skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Gem` for at gemme ændringerne."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:49
msgid ""
"The team members assigned to maintenance teams are also referred to as "
"*Technicians*, when viewing the *Maintenance Calendar*."
msgstr ""
"Teammedlemmerne, der er tildelt vedligeholdelseteams, omtales også som "
"*teknikere*, når du ser *vedligeholdelseskalenderen*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:52
msgid ""
"Navigate to :menuselection:`Maintenance app --> Maintenance --> Maintenance "
"Calendar`, and click on an existing maintenance request. From the resulting "
"popover, locate the :guilabel:`Technician` field. The name listed in the "
"field is the team member, and is the user responsible for that particular "
"request."
msgstr ""
"Naviger til :menuselection:`Vedligeholdelse app --> Vedligeholdelse --> "
"Vedligeholdelseskalender`, og klik på en eksisterende "
"vedligeholdelsesanmodning. Fra den resulterende popover skal du finde feltet "
":guilabel:`Tekniker`. Navnet i feltet er teammedlemmet og er den bruger, der "
"er ansvarlig for den pågældende anmodning."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:None
msgid "Maintenance request popover with Technician field shown."
msgstr "Vedligeholdelsesanmodnings-popover med Tekniker-felt vist."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:61
msgid ""
"At the far-right side of the page is a sidebar column, containing a "
"minimized calendar set to today's date, and a :guilabel:`Technician` list, "
"displaying all the technicians (or team members) with requests currently "
"open."
msgstr ""
"I højre side af siden er der en sidebjælkekolonne, der indeholder en "
"minimeret kalender indstillet til dags dato og en :guilabel:`Tekniker`-"
"liste, der viser alle teknikerne (eller teammedlemmerne) med anmodninger, "
"der i øjeblikket er åbne."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:66
msgid "Equipment"
msgstr "Udstyr"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:68
msgid ""
"In Odoo *Maintenance*, *equipment* refers to machines and tools used "
"internally in warehouse work centers. Equipment can include technology such "
"as computers or tablets, power tools, machines used for manufacturing, and "
"more."
msgstr ""
"I Odoo *Vedligeholdelse* refererer *udstyr* til maskiner og værktøj, der "
"bruges internt i lagerarbejdscentre. Udstyr kan omfatte teknologi såsom "
"computere eller tablets, elværktøj, maskiner, der bruges til produktion, og "
"mere."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:73
msgid "Equipment categories"
msgstr "Udstyrskategorier"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:75
msgid ""
"Each piece of equipment belongs to an *equipment category*. Before adding "
"new equipment, make sure that a fitting equipment category is created."
msgstr ""
"Hvert stykke udstyr tilhører en *udstyrkategori*. Før du tilføjer nyt "
"udstyr, skal du sikre dig, at en passende udstyrkategori er oprettet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:78
msgid ""
"To create a new equipment category, navigate to :menuselection:`Maintenance "
"app --> Configuration --> Equipment Categories`, and click :guilabel:`New`. "
"Doing so opens a blank equipment category form."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette en ny udstyrkategori skal du navigere til "
":menuselection:`Vedligeholdelse app --> Konfiguration --> Udstyrkategorier`, "
"og klikke på :guilabel:`Ny`. Dette åbner en tom udstyrkategoriformular."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:None
msgid "Equipment category form with various information filled out."
msgstr "Udstyrkategoriformular med forskellige oplysninger udfyldt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:86
msgid ""
"On the blank form, assign a name in the :guilabel:`Category Name` field."
msgstr ""
"På den tomme formular skal du tildele et navn i feltet "
":guilabel:`Kategorinavn`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:88
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Responsible` field, assign a user to be responsible for "
"the equipment in this category, if necessary. By default, the user who "
"creates the category is selected as :guilabel:`Responsible`, by default."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Ansvarlig` skal du tildele en bruger til at være "
"ansvarlig for udstyret i denne kategori, hvis det er nødvendigt. Som "
"standard vælges den bruger, der opretter kategorien, som "
":guilabel:`Ansvarlig`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:92
msgid ""
"If in a multi-company environment, click the drop-down menu in "
"the :guilabel:`Company` field, and select the company in the database to "
"whom the equipment in this category belongs."
msgstr ""
"Hvis der er et multi-firma miljø, skal du klikke på rullemenuen i feltet "
":guilabel:`Firma`, og vælge den firma i databasen, som udstyret i denne "
"kategori tilhører."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:95
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Email Alias` field, assign an email alias to this "
"category, if necessary."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`E-mail-alias` skal du tildele et e-mail-alias til denne "
"kategori, hvis det er nødvendigt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:97
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Comments` field, type any comments or notes for internal "
"users to reference in relation to this category, if necessary."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Kommentarer` skal du skrive eventuelle kommentarer eller "
"noter, som interne brugere kan referere til i relation til denne kategori, "
"hvis det er nødvendigt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:101
msgid ""
"Once a new equipment category is created, all equipment belonging to that "
"category, as well as any past or currently open maintenance requests, are "
"available from the equipment category form."
msgstr ""
"Når en ny udstyrkategori er oprettet, er alt udstyr, der tilhører den "
"kategori, samt eventuelle tidligere eller aktuelt åbne "
"vedligeholdelsesanmodninger, tilgængelige fra udstyrkategoriformularen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:104
msgid ""
"Navigate to :menuselection:`Maintenance app --> Configuration --> Equipment "
"Categories`, and select a category to view. Locate the :guilabel:`Equipment` "
"and :guilabel:`Maintenance` smart buttons at the top of the form."
msgstr ""
"Naviger til :menuselection:`Vedligeholdelse app --> Konfiguration --> "
"Udstyrkategorier`, og vælg en kategori at se. Find de smarte knapper "
":guilabel:`Udstyr` og :guilabel:`Vedligeholdelse` øverst på formularen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:None
msgid "Equipment and Maintenance smart buttons on equipment category form."
msgstr "Udstyr- og Vedligeholdelse-smarte knapper på udstyrkategoriformular."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:112
msgid ""
"Click the :guilabel:`Equipment` smart button to view all equipment belonging "
"to this category. Click the :guilabel:`Maintenance` smart button to view any "
"past, or currently open, maintenance requests."
msgstr ""
"Klik på den smarte knap :guilabel:`Udstyr` for at se alt udstyr, der "
"tilhører denne kategori. Klik på den smarte knap :guilabel:`Vedligeholdelse` "
"for at se eventuelle tidligere eller aktuelt åbne "
"vedligeholdelsesanmodninger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:117
msgid "Machines & tools"
msgstr "Maskiner & værktøj"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:119
msgid ""
"To add new equipment, navigate to :menuselection:`Maintenance app --> "
"Equipment --> Machines & Tools`, and click :guilabel:`New`. This opens a "
"blank equipment form."
msgstr ""
"For at tilføje nyt udstyr skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Vedligeholdelse-appen --> Udstyr --> Maskiner & værktøj` "
"og klikke på :guilabel:`Ny`. Dette åbner en tom udstyrsformular."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:122
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Name` field, assign a name for the new equipment. In "
"the :guilabel:`Equipment Category` field, click the drop-down menu and "
"select which category this new equipment should belong to."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Navn` tildeles et navn til det nye udstyr. I "
"feltet :guilabel:`Udstyrskategori` klikkes på rullemenuen, og der vælges, "
"hvilken kategori dette nye udstyr skal tilhøre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:126
msgid ""
"If in a multi-company environment, click the drop-down menu in "
"the :guilabel:`Company` field, and select the company in the database to "
"whom the new equipment belongs."
msgstr ""
"Hvis du er i et multifirma-miljø, skal du klikke på rullemenuen i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Firma` og vælge det firma i databasen, som det nye udstyr "
"tilhører."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:129
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Used By` field, select from one of three radio button "
"options: :guilabel:`Department`, :guilabel:`Employee`, or :guilabel:`Other`."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Bruges af` vælges en af tre radioknap-"
"muligheder: :guilabel:`Afdeling`, :guilabel:`Medarbejder` "
"eller :guilabel:`Andet`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:None
msgid "Left-hand side of information fields on new equipment form."
msgstr "Venstre side af informationsfelterne på ny udstyrsformular."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:136
msgid ""
"If :guilabel:`Department` is selected, a :guilabel:`Department` field "
"appears below the :guilabel:`Used By` field. Click the drop-down menu and "
"select the department that uses this equipment."
msgstr ""
"Hvis :guilabel:`Afdeling` er valgt, vises et :guilabel:`Afdeling`-felt under "
"feltet :guilabel:`Bruges af`. Klik på rullemenuen, og vælg den afdeling, der "
"bruger dette udstyr."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:140
msgid ""
"If :guilabel:`Employee` is selected, an :guilabel:`Employee` field appears "
"below the :guilabel:`Used By` field. Click the drop-down menu, and select "
"the employee who uses this equipment."
msgstr ""
"Hvis :guilabel:`Medarbejder` er valgt, vises et :guilabel:`Medarbejder`-felt "
"under feltet :guilabel:`Bruges af`. Klik på rullemenuen, og vælg den "
"medarbejder, der bruger dette udstyr."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:143
msgid ""
"If the :guilabel:`Other` option is selected, both the :guilabel:`Department` "
"and :guilabel:`Employee` fields appear below the :guilabel:`Used By` field. "
"Click the drop-down menus for the respective fields, and choose which "
"department and employee uses this equipment."
msgstr ""
"Hvis muligheden :guilabel:`Andet` er valgt, vises både "
"felterne :guilabel:`Afdeling` og :guilabel:`Medarbejder` under "
"feltet :guilabel:`Bruges af`. Klik på rullemenuerne for de respektive "
"felter, og vælg, hvilken afdeling og medarbejder der bruger dette udstyr."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:147
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Maintenance Team` field, select the team responsible for "
"this equipment. In the :guilabel:`Technician` field, select the team member/"
"user responsible for this equipment."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Vedligeholdelsesteam` vælges det team, der er ansvarligt "
"for dette udstyr. I feltet :guilabel:`Tekniker` vælges det teammedlem/"
"bruger, der er ansvarligt for dette udstyr."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:None
msgid "Right-hand side of information fields on new equipment form."
msgstr "Højre side af informationsfelterne på ny udstyrsformular."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:154
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Used in location` field, enter the location wherein this "
"equipment will be used, if not in an internal work center (e.g. in an "
"office)."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Bruges på placering` indtastes den placering, hvor dette "
"udstyr vil blive brugt, hvis det ikke er i et internt arbejdscenter (f.eks. "
"på et kontor)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:157
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Work Center` field, click the drop-down menu, and select "
"which work center this equipment will be used in."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Arbejdscenter` klikkes på rullemenuen, og der vælges, "
"hvilket arbejdscenter dette udstyr vil blive brugt i."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:160
msgid ""
"In the blank space under the :guilabel:`Description` tab at the bottom of "
"the form, add any relevant information describing the equipment for users to "
"reference."
msgstr ""
"I det tomme felt under fanen :guilabel:`Beskrivelse` nederst på formularen "
"tilføjes eventuelle relevante oplysninger, der beskriver udstyret, så "
"brugerne kan referere til dem."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:164
msgid "Product Information tab"
msgstr "Fanen Produktinformation"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:166
msgid ""
"To add any relevant information while creating a new piece of equipment, "
"from the equipment form, click the :guilabel:`Product Information` tab."
msgstr ""
"For at tilføje eventuelle relevante oplysninger, mens du opretter et nyt "
"stykke udstyr, skal du fra udstyrsformularen klikke på "
"fanen :guilabel:`Produktinformation`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:None
msgid "Product Information tab with available fields below it."
msgstr "Fanen Produktinformation med tilgængelige felter nedenfor."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:173
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Vendor` field, add the vendor from which the equipment was "
"purchased. In the :guilabel:`Vendor Reference` field, add the product "
"reference number obtained from the vendor, if applicable."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Leverandør` tilføjes den leverandør, som udstyret blev "
"købt hos. I feltet :guilabel:`Leverandørreference` tilføjes "
"produktreferencenummeret fra leverandøren, hvis relevant."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:177
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Model` field, specify which model this equipment is, if "
"applicable. If the equipment is serialized, add a serial number in "
"the :guilabel:`Serial Number` field."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Model` angives, hvilken model dette udstyr er, hvis "
"relevant. Hvis udstyret er serialiseret, tilføjes et serienummer i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Serienummer`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:180
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Effective Date` field, click the date to reveal a calendar "
"popover, and select a date. This date indicates when this equipment was "
"first put in use, and will be used to compute the Mean Time Between Failure "
"(MTBF) in the equipment's :guilabel:`Maintenance` tab."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Ikrafttrædelsesdato` klikkes på datoen for at vise en "
"kalenderpopover, og der vælges en dato. Denne dato angiver, hvornår dette "
"udstyr først blev taget i brug, og vil blive brugt til at beregne Mean Time "
"Between Failure (MTBF) i udstyrsobservatørens "
"fane :guilabel:`Vedligeholdelse`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:184
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Cost` field, specify how much the equipment cost to "
"acquire, if applicable."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Omkostning` skal du angive, hvor meget udstyret kostede "
"at anskaffe, hvis relevant."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:186
msgid ""
"If the equipment is covered under a warranty, specify "
"the :guilabel:`Warranty Expiration Date` by selecting a date from the "
"calendar popover in that field."
msgstr ""
"Hvis udstyret er dækket af en garanti, skal du angive :guilabel:`Garantiens "
"udløbsdato` ved at vælge en dato fra kalenderen i dette felt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:190
msgid "Maintenance tab"
msgstr "Fanen Vedligeholdelse"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:192
msgid ""
"Various maintenance metrics are available for each piece of equipment, and "
"are automatically computed, based on corrective maintenance, and planned "
"preventive maintenance."
msgstr ""
"Forskellige vedligeholdelsesmålinger er tilgængelige for hvert stykke udstyr "
"og beregnes automatisk baseret på korrigerende vedligeholdelse og planlagt "
"forebyggende vedligeholdelse."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:195
msgid ""
"To view the maintenance metrics for a specific piece of equipment, from the "
"equipment form, click the :guilabel:`Maintenance` tab."
msgstr ""
"For at se vedligeholdelsesmålingerne for et specifikt stykke udstyr skal du "
"fra udstyrsformularen klikke på fanen :guilabel:`Vedligeholdelse`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:None
msgid "Maintenance tab on equipment form showing computed metrics fields."
msgstr ""
"Fanen Vedligeholdelse på udstyrsformular, der viser beregnede målefelter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:202
msgid "Doing so reveals the following fields:"
msgstr "Dette viser følgende felter:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:204
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Expected Mean Time Between Failure`: the amount of time (in days) "
"before the next failure is expected. This is the **only** field not greyed-"
"out, and the **only** field users can edit."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Forventet gennemsnitlig tid mellem fejl`: tiden (i dage) før "
"næste fejl forventes. Dette er det **eneste** felt, der ikke er gråtonet, og "
"det **eneste** felt, brugere kan redigere."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:207
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Mean Time Between Failure`: the amount of time (in days) between "
"reported failures. This value is computed based on completed corrective "
"maintenances."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Gennemsnitlig tid mellem fejl`: tiden (i dage) mellem "
"rapporterede fejl. Denne værdi beregnes baseret på gennemført korrigerende "
"vedligeholdelse."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:209
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Estimated Next Failure`: the date on which the next failure is "
"expected. This date is computed as the Latest Failure Date + |MTBF|."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Estimeret næste fejl`: datoen, hvor næste fejl forventes. Denne "
"dato beregnes som seneste fejldato + |MTBF|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:211
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Latest Failure`: The date of the latest failure. The value in "
"this field updates once a failure is reported for this equipment."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Seneste fejl`: datoen for den seneste fejl. Værdien i dette felt "
"opdateres, når en fejl rapporteres for dette udstyr."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:213
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Mean Time To Repair`: the amount of time (in days) it takes to "
"repair this equipment upon failure. This value updates once a maintenance "
"request is completed for this equipment."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Gennemsnitlig tid til reparation`: tiden (i dage), det tager at "
"reparere dette udstyr ved fejl. Denne værdi opdateres, når en "
"vedligeholdelsesanmodning er gennemført for dette udstyr."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:217
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:3
msgid "Work centers"
msgstr "Arbejdscentre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:219
msgid ""
"To view the work centers where equipment is being used, and how the "
"equipment is being used in them, navigate to :menuselection:`Maintenance app "
"--> Equipment --> Work Centers`, and click into a work center."
msgstr ""
"For at se de arbejdscentre, hvor udstyr bruges, og hvordan udstyret bruges i "
"dem, skal du navigere til :menuselection:`Vedligeholdelsesapp --> Udstyr --> "
"Arbejdscentre` og klikke på et arbejdscenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:223
msgid ""
"From the resulting work center form, click the :guilabel:`Equipment` tab to "
"view all machines and tools being used in that specific work center."
msgstr ""
"Fra den resulterende arbejdscenterformular skal du klikke på "
"fanen :guilabel:`Udstyr` for at se alle maskiner og værktøjer, der bruges i "
"det specifikke arbejdscenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:226
msgid ""
"Each piece of equipment is listed with certain relevant information: "
"the :guilabel:`Equipment Name`, the responsible :guilabel:`Technician`, "
"the :guilabel:`Equipment Category` it belongs to, and a few important "
"maintenance metrics: its |MTBF|, |MTTR|, and :guilabel:`Est. Next Failure` "
"date."
msgstr ""
"Hvert stykke udstyr er opført med visse relevante "
"oplysninger: :guilabel:`Udstyrets navn`, den "
"ansvarlige :guilabel:`Tekniker`, den :guilabel:`Udstyrkategori`, det "
"tilhører, og nogle få vigtige vedligeholdelsesmålinger: dets |MTBF|, |MTTR| "
"og :guilabel:`Est. næste fejl`-dato."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:None
msgid "List of equipment included in a work center."
msgstr "Liste over udstyr inkluderet i et arbejdscenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:235
msgid ""
"To add new equipment to a work center directly from the work center form, "
"click :guilabel:`Add a line` under the :guilabel:`Equipment` tab. This opens "
"an :guilabel:`Add: Maintenance Equipment` pop-up window."
msgstr ""
"For at tilføje nyt udstyr til et arbejdscenter direkte fra "
"arbejdscenterformularen skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje` under "
"fanen :guilabel:`Udstyr`. Dette åbner et pop op-vindue "
"med :guilabel:`Tilføj: Vedligeholdelsesudstyr`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/maintenance/maintenance_setup.rst:239
msgid ""
"From the pop-up window, select the equipment that should be added to the "
"work center, and click :guilabel:`Select`."
msgstr ""
"Fra pop op-vinduet skal du vælge det udstyr, der skal tilføjes til "
"arbejdscentret, og klikke på :guilabel:`Vælg`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing.rst:9
msgid ""
"**Odoo Manufacturing** helps manufacturers schedule, plan, and process "
"manufacturing orders. With the work center control panel, put tablets on the "
"shop floor to control work orders in real-time and allow workers to trigger "
"maintenance operations, feedback loops, quality issues, etc."
msgstr ""
"**Odoo Produktion** hjælper producenter med at planlægge og behandle "
"produktionsordrer. Med arbejdscenterets kontrolpanel kan du placere tablets "
"på værkstedet for at styre arbejdsordrer i realtid og give arbejdere "
"mulighed for at udløse vedligeholdelsesoperationer, feedback-loops, "
"kvalitetsproblemer osv."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing.rst:14
msgid "`Odoo Tutorials: MRP <https://www.odoo.com/slides/mrp-29>`_"
msgstr "`Odoo-vejledninger: MRP <https://www.odoo.com/slides/mrp-29>`_"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing.rst:15
msgid ""
"`Odoo Tutorials: Barcode Scanner <https://www.odoo.com/slides/barcode-30>`_"
msgstr ""
"Odoo vejledninger: Stregkodescanner <https://www.odoo.com/slides/"
"barcode-30>`_"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing.rst:16
msgid ":doc:`IoT Boxes (MES) </applications/general/iot>`"
msgstr ":doc:`IoT-bokse (MES) </applications/general/iot>`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration.rst:5
msgid "Advanced configuration"
msgstr "Avanceret Konfiguration"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:3
msgid "Kits"
msgstr "Samlesæt-funktion"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:5
msgid ""
"In Odoo, a *kit* is a type of bill of materials (BoM) that can be "
"manufactured and sold. Kits are sets of unassembled components sold to "
"customers. They may be sold as standalone products, and are also useful "
"tools for managing more complex bills of materials (BoMs)."
msgstr ""
"I Odoo er et *kit* en type stykliste (BoM), der kan fremstilles og sælges. "
"Kits er sæt af usamlede komponenter, der sælges til kunder. De kan sælges "
"som selvstændige produkter og er også nyttige værktøjer til at håndtere mere "
"komplekse styklister (BoMs)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:10
msgid ""
"To use, manufacture, and sell kits, both the :guilabel:`Manufacturing` "
"and :guilabel:`Inventory` apps need to be installed."
msgstr ""
"For at bruge, fremstille og sælge kits skal både :guilabel:`Produktion`- "
"og :guilabel:`Lager`-appene være installeret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:16
msgid "Create the kit as a product"
msgstr "Opret kittet som et produkt"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:18
msgid ""
"To use a kit as a sellable product, or as a component organization tool, the "
"kit should first be created as a product."
msgstr ""
"For at bruge et kit som et salgbart produkt eller som et værktøj til "
"organisering af komponenter, bør kittet først oprettes som et produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:21
msgid ""
"To create a kit product, go to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> "
"Products --> Products`, and then click :guilabel:`New`."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette et kitprodukt skal du gå til :menuselection:`Produktion --> "
"Produkter --> Produkter` og derefter klikke på :guilabel:`Ny`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:24
msgid ""
"Then, assign a name to the new kit product. Next, set the kit's product type "
"depending on inventory tracking needs and accounting requirements. To do "
"this, under the :guilabel:`General Information` tab, set "
"the :guilabel:`Product Type` to :guilabel:`Goods` and either check the box "
"next :guilabel:`Track Inventory` if inventory tracking is required, or leave "
"it unchecked if inventory tracking for the kit is not necessary."
msgstr ""
"Tildel derefter et navn til det nye kit-produkt. Indstil dernæst kittets "
"produkttype afhængigt af behov for lagersporing og regnskabskrav. Gør dette "
"under fanen :guilabel:`Generelle oplysninger` ved at "
"indstille :guilabel:`Produkttype` til :guilabel:`Varer` og enten markér "
"afkrydsningsfeltet ved :guilabel:`Spor lager`, hvis lagersporing er "
"nødvendig, eller lad det være umarkeret, hvis lagersporing for kittet ikke "
"er nødvendigt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:31
msgid ""
"Learn more about :doc:`tracked versus untracked products <../../inventory/"
"product_management/configure/type>`."
msgstr ""
"Læs mere om :doc:`sporede versus ikke-sporede produkter <../../inventory/"
"product_management/configure/type>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:34
msgid ""
"The kit's components must also be configured as products "
"via :menuselection:`Inventory app --> Products --> Products`. These "
"components require no specific configuration."
msgstr ""
"Kittets komponenter skal også konfigureres som produkter "
"via :menuselection:`Lager-app --> Produkter --> Produkter`. Disse "
"komponenter kræver ingen specifik konfiguration."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:38
msgid "Untracked kit inventory setup details"
msgstr "Detaljer om opsætning af ikke-sporet kit-lager"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:40
msgid ""
"Consider leaving tracking for the kit's inventory untracked when the kit is "
"used in other manufacturing processes or when tracking inventory for the kit "
"itself is not needed."
msgstr ""
"Overvej at lade lagersporing for kittet være ikke-sporet, når kittet bruges "
"i andre produktionsprocesser, eller når sporing af lager for selve kittet "
"ikke er nødvendig."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:43
msgid ""
"**Recommended for Continental Accounting**: If costs are expensed "
"immediately upon purchase, then leaving the kit's inventory as untracked is "
"recommended."
msgstr ""
"**Anbefalet til kontinentalt regnskab**: Hvis omkostninger udgiftsføres "
"umiddelbart ved køb, anbefales det at lade kittets lager være ikke-sporet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:45
msgid ""
"**Replenishment via Components**: Inventory count is managed at the "
"component level, so reordering rules must be set to individual components."
msgstr ""
"**Genopfyldning via komponenter**: Lagertælling håndteres på "
"komponentniveau, så genbestillingsregler skal indstilles til individuelle "
"komponenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:47
msgid ""
"**Selling & Stock Constraints**: Kits cannot be sold if any required "
"component is out of stock. Since availability depends on individual "
"components, a sales order may appear valid, but delivery can be delayed if "
"components are unavailable."
msgstr ""
"**Salg og lagerbegrænsninger**: Kits kan ikke sælges, hvis nogen påkrævet "
"komponent er udsolgt. Da tilgængelighed afhænger af individuelle "
"komponenter, kan en salgsordre se gyldig ud, men levering kan blive "
"forsinket, hvis komponenter er utilgængelige."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:52
msgid "Tracked kit inventory setup details"
msgstr "Detaljer om opsætning af sporet kit-lager"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:54
msgid ""
"Consider turning on tracking for the kit's inventory when the kit is a "
"tangible product or warehouse and inventory tracking is essential."
msgstr ""
"Overvej at aktivere sporing for kittets lager, når kittet er et "
"håndgribeligt produkt, eller når lager- og lagersporing er essentiel."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:57
msgid ""
"**Recommended for Angle-Saxon Accounting**: If the Cost of Goods Sold (COGS) "
"needs to be recorded in journals, then tracking the kit's inventory is "
"recommended."
msgstr ""
"**Anbefalet til angelsaksisk regnskab**: Hvis omkostninger ved solgte varer "
"(COGS) skal registreres i kladder, anbefales det at spore kittets lager."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:59
msgid ""
"**Component Purchase Constraints**: Only the kit's minimum required "
"components can be added to an **eCommerce** cart unless the option "
"to :doc:`continue selling <../../../websites/ecommerce/configuration/"
"products>` is disabled."
msgstr ""
"**Begrænsninger for komponentkøb**: Kun kittets minimalt nødvendige "
"komponenter kan tilføjes til en **e-Handel**-kurv, medmindre muligheden for "
"at :doc:`fortsætte med at sælge <../../../websites/ecommerce/configuration/"
"products>` er deaktiveret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:62
msgid ""
"**No Kit Serial Numbers**: Serial number tracking does not track the kit, "
"only its shipped components."
msgstr ""
"**Ingen serienumre til kit**: Serienummersporing sporer ikke kittet, kun "
"dets afsendte komponenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:64
msgid ""
"**Reordering Rule Recommendation**: Reordering rules should be set at the "
"component-level."
msgstr ""
"**Anbefaling for genbestillingsregel**: Genbestillingsregler bør indstilles "
"på komponentniveau."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:65
msgid ""
"**Stock Replenishment Recommendation**: Stock replenishment should also be "
"done at the component-level."
msgstr ""
"**Anbefaling for lagergenopfyldning**: Lagergenopfyldning bør også udføres "
"på komponentniveau."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:69
msgid "Kit setup similarities"
msgstr "Ligheder i opsætning af kit"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:71
msgid ""
"Regardless of which setup is used, there are some similarities between the "
"two options."
msgstr ""
"Uanset hvilken opsætning der anvendes, er der nogle ligheder mellem de to "
"muligheder."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:73
msgid ""
"**No Kit-Level Stock Adjustments**: Stock adjustments cannot be handled at "
"the kit-level."
msgstr ""
"**Ingen lagerreguleringer på kitniveau**: Lagerreguleringer kan ikke "
"håndteres på kitniveau."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:74
msgid ""
"**Kit Value Does Not Change**: The stock's value is the same whether the "
"kit's is tracked."
msgstr ""
"**Kit-værdien ændres ikke**: Lagerets værdi er den samme, uanset om kittet "
"spores."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:75
msgid ""
"**Kit Internal Transfers**: An internal transfer for the kit breaks it into "
"components."
msgstr ""
"**Interne overførsler af kit**: En intern overførsel af kittet opdeler det i "
"komponenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:80
msgid "Set up the kit BoM"
msgstr "Opsæt kit-styklisten"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:82
msgid ""
"After fully configuring the kit product and its components, a new :abbr:`BoM "
"(bill of materials)` can be created for the kit product."
msgstr ""
"Når kitproduktet og dets komponenter er fuldt konfigureret, kan der oprettes "
"en ny :abbr:`stykliste (bill of materials)` til kitproduktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:85
msgid ""
"To do so, go to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Products --> Bills of "
"Materials`, and then click :guilabel:`New`. Next to the :guilabel:`Product` "
"field, click the drop-down menu to reveal a list of products, and then "
"select the previously configured kit product."
msgstr ""
"Gå til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Produkter --> Styklister`, og klik "
"derefter på :guilabel:`Opret`. Ved siden af feltet :guilabel:`Produkt` skal "
"du klikke på rullemenuen for at se en liste over produkter og derefter vælge "
"det tidligere konfigurerede kitprodukt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:89
msgid ""
"Then, for the :guilabel:`BoM Type` field, click the :guilabel:`Kit` option. "
"Finally, under the :guilabel:`Components` tab, click :guilabel:`Add a line`, "
"and add each desired component, and specify their quantities under "
"the :guilabel:`Quantity` column."
msgstr ""
"Klik derefter på indstillingen :guilabel:`Kit` for "
"feltet :guilabel:`Styklistetype`. Under fanen :guilabel:`Komponenter` skal "
"du til sidst klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje` og tilføje hver ønsket "
"komponent og angive deres mængder under kolonnen :guilabel:`Mængde`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:93
msgid ""
"Once ready, click :guilabel:`Save` to save the newly created :abbr:`BoM "
"(bill of materials)`."
msgstr ""
"Når du er klar, skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Gem` for at gemme den "
"nyoprettede :abbr:`stykliste (bill of materials)`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:None
msgid "Kit selection on the bill of materials."
msgstr "Valg af kit på styklisten."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:98
msgid ""
"If the kit is solely being used as a sellable product, then only components "
"need to be added under the :guilabel:`Components` tab, and configuring "
"manufacturing operations is not necessary."
msgstr ""
"Hvis kittet udelukkende bruges som et salgbart produkt, behøver der kun "
"tilføjes komponenter under fanen :guilabel:`Komponenter`, og konfigurering "
"af produktionsoperationer er ikke nødvendig."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:102
msgid ""
"When a kit is sold as a product, it appears as a single line item on the "
"quotation and sales order. However, on delivery orders, each component of "
"the kit is listed."
msgstr ""
"Når et kit sælges som et produkt, vises det som en enkelt linjepost på "
"tilbuddet og salgsordren. På leveringsordrer vises hver komponent i kittet "
"dog."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:106
msgid "Use kits to manage complex BoMs"
msgstr "Brug kits til at administrere komplekse styklister"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:108
msgid ""
"Kits can also be used for complex :abbr:`BoMs (Bills of Materials)`. This "
"method nests BoMs within other BoMs, organizing complex products while "
"simplifying manufacturing by defining each procurement and production step "
"separately."
msgstr ""
"Kits kan også bruges til komplekse :abbr:`styklister (bills of materials)`. "
"Denne metode indlejrer styklister i andre styklister og organiserer "
"komplekse produkter, samtidig med at produktionen forenkles ved at definere "
"hvert indkøbs- og produktionstrin separat."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:112
msgid ""
"Sublevel BoMs (subassemblies or semi-finished products) streamline these "
"workflows, helping with traceability efforts."
msgstr ""
"Styklister på underniveau (delsamlinger eller halvfærdige produkter) "
"effektiviserer disse arbejdsgange og hjælper med sporbarheden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/kit_shipping.rst:116
msgid ":doc:`sub_assemblies`"
msgstr ":doc:`sub_assemblies`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:3
msgid "Managing BoMs for product variants"
msgstr "Administrering af styklister for produktvarianter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:5
msgid ""
"Odoo allows one bill of materials (BoM) to be used for multiple variants of "
"the same product. Having a consolidated :abbr:`BoM (bill of materials)` for "
"a product with variants saves time by preventing the need to manage "
"multiple :abbr:`BoMs (bills of materials)`."
msgstr ""
"Odoo gør det muligt at bruge én stykliste til flere varianter af samme "
"produkt. At have en konsolideret :abbr:`stykliste (bill of materials)` for "
"et produkt med varianter sparer tid ved at forhindre behovet for at "
"administrere flere :abbr:`styklister (bills of materials)`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:10
msgid "Activate product variants"
msgstr "Aktivér produktvarianter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:12
msgid ""
"To activate the product variants feature, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> Configuration --> Settings`, and scroll "
"down to the :guilabel:`Products` section. Then, click the checkbox to enable "
"the :guilabel:`Variants` option. After that, click :guilabel:`Save` to apply "
"the setting."
msgstr ""
"For at aktivere produktvariantfunktionen skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Lager --> Konfiguration --> Indstillinger` og rulle ned "
"til sektionen :guilabel:`Produkter`. Klik derefter på afkrydsningsfeltet for "
"at aktivere indstillingen :guilabel:`Varianter`. Klik herefter "
"på :guilabel:`Gem` for at anvende indstillingen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:17
msgid ""
"For more information on configuring product variants, refer to "
"the :doc:`product variants <../../../sales/sales/products_prices/products/"
"variants>` documentation."
msgstr ""
"For mere information om konfiguration af produktvarianter, se "
"dokumentationen :doc:`produktvarianter <../../../sales/sales/products_prices/"
"products/variants>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:None
msgid "Selecting \"Variants\" from Inventory app settings."
msgstr "Valg af \"Varianter\" fra indstillingerne i Lager-appen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:25
msgid "Create custom product attributes"
msgstr "Opret brugerdefinerede produktattributter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:27
msgid ""
"Once the product variants feature is activated, create and edit product "
"attributes on the :guilabel:`Attributes` page."
msgstr ""
"Når produktvariantfunktionen er aktiveret, kan du oprette og redigere "
"produktattributter på siden :guilabel:`Attributter`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:30
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Attributes` page is accessible either "
"from :menuselection:`Inventory app --> Configuration --> Settings` by "
"clicking the :guilabel:`Attributes` button, or by "
"clicking :menuselection:`Inventory app --> Configuration --> Attributes`."
msgstr ""
"Siden :guilabel:`Attributter` er tilgængelig enten fra :menuselection:`Lager "
"--> Konfiguration --> Indstillinger` ved at klikke på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Attributter`, eller ved at klikke "
"på :menuselection:`Lager --> Konfiguration --> Attributter`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:34
msgid ""
"Once on the :guilabel:`Attributes` page, either click into an existing "
"attribute, or click :guilabel:`Create` to create a new one. "
"Clicking :guilabel:`Create` reveals a new, blank form for customizing an "
"attribute. For an existing attribute, click :guilabel:`Edit` on its form to "
"make changes."
msgstr ""
"Når du er på siden :guilabel:`Attributter`, skal du enten klikke på en "
"eksisterende attribut eller klikke på :guilabel:`Opret` for at oprette en "
"ny. Klik på :guilabel:`Opret` for at åbne en ny, tom formular til tilpasning "
"af en attribut. For en eksisterende attribut skal du klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Rediger` i formularen for at foretage ændringer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:39
msgid ""
"Assign an :guilabel:`Attribute Name`, and choose a category from "
"the :guilabel:`Category` field's drop-down menu. Then, select the desired "
"options next to the :guilabel:`Display Type` and :guilabel:`Variants "
"Creation Mode` fields. Once the desired options are selected, "
"click :guilabel:`Add a line` under the :guilabel:`Attribute Values` tab to "
"add a new value."
msgstr ""
"Tildel et :guilabel:`Attributnavn`, og vælg en kategori fra rullemenuen i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Kategori`. Vælg derefter de ønskede indstillinger ved "
"felterne :guilabel:`Visningstype` og :guilabel:`Variantoprettelsestilstand`. "
"Når de ønskede indstillinger er valgt, skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj "
"en linje` under fanen :guilabel:`Attributværdier` for at tilføje en ny værdi."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:45
msgid ""
"Included on the :guilabel:`Value` row is a :guilabel:`Is custom value` "
"checkbox. If selected, this value will be recognized as a custom value, "
"which allows customers to type special customization requests upon ordering "
"a custom variant of a product."
msgstr ""
"På rækken :guilabel:`Værdi` findes et afkrydsningsfelt :guilabel:`Er "
"brugerdefineret værdi`. Hvis dette er valgt, vil værdien blive genkendt som "
"en brugerdefineret værdi, hvilket giver kunder mulighed for at skrive "
"specielle tilpasningsanmodninger ved bestilling af en brugerdefineret "
"variant af et produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:0
msgid "Product variant attribute configuration screen."
msgstr "Konfigurationsskærm for produktvariantattribut."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:54
msgid ""
"Once all desired :guilabel:`Values` have been added, click :guilabel:`Save` "
"to save the new attribute."
msgstr ""
"Når alle ønskede :guilabel:`Værdier` er tilføjet, skal du klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Gem` for at gemme den nye attribut."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:60
msgid "Add product variants on the product form"
msgstr "Tilføj produktvarianter på produktformularen"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:62
msgid ""
"Created attributes can be applied on specific variants for particular "
"products. To add product variants to a product, navigate to the product form "
"by going to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> Products --> Products`. To "
"make changes to the product, click :guilabel:`Edit`. Then, click "
"the :guilabel:`Variants` tab."
msgstr ""
"Oprettede attributter kan anvendes på specifikke varianter for bestemte "
"produkter. For at tilføje produktvarianter til et produkt skal du navigere "
"til produktformularen ved at gå til :menuselection:`Lager --> Produkter --> "
"Produkter`. For at foretage ændringer i produktet skal du klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Rediger`. Klik derefter på fanen :guilabel:`Varianter`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:67
msgid ""
"Under the :guilabel:`Attribute` header, click :guilabel:`Add a line` to add "
"a new attribute, and select one to add from the drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"Under overskriften :guilabel:`Attribut` skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj "
"en linje` for at tilføje en ny attribut og vælge en at tilføje fra "
"rullemenuen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:70
msgid ""
"Then, under the :guilabel:`Values` header, click the drop-down menu to "
"choose from the list of existing values. Click on each desired value to add "
"them, and repeat this process for any additional attributes that should be "
"added to the product."
msgstr ""
"Derefter skal du under overskriften :guilabel:`Værdier` klikke på "
"rullemenuen for at vælge fra listen over eksisterende værdier. Klik på hver "
"ønsket værdi for at tilføje dem, og gentag denne proces for eventuelle "
"yderligere attributter, der skal tilføjes til produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:74
msgid "Once finished, click :guilabel:`Save` to save changes."
msgstr ""
"Når du er færdig, skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Gem` for at gemme ændringerne."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:None
msgid "Product form variants tab with values and attributes."
msgstr "Produktformularens variantfane med værdier og attributter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:81
msgid ""
":abbr:`BoM (bill of materials)` products with multiple variants that are "
"manufactured in-house should either have a **0,0 reordering rule** set up, "
"or have their replenishment routes set to *Replenish on Order (MTO)*."
msgstr ""
":abbr:`Stykliste`-produkter med flere varianter, der fremstilles internt, "
"bør enten have en **0,0 genbestillingsregel** sat op eller have deres "
"genopfyldningsruter sat til *Genbestil ved ordre (MTO)*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:86
msgid "Apply BoM components to product variants"
msgstr "Anvend styklistekomponenter på produktvarianter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:88
msgid ""
"Next, create a new :abbr:`BoM (bill of materials)`. Or, edit an existing "
"one, by going to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Products --> Bills of "
"Materials`. Then, click :guilabel:`Create` to open a new :guilabel:`Bills of "
"Materials` form to configure from scratch."
msgstr ""
"Opret derefter en ny :abbr:`stykliste`. Eller rediger en eksisterende ved at "
"gå til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Produkter --> Styklister`. Klik "
"derefter på :guilabel:`Opret` for at åbne en ny :guilabel:`Stykliste`-"
"formular, der kan konfigureres fra bunden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:92
msgid ""
"Add a product to the :abbr:`BoM (bill of materials)` by clicking the drop-"
"down menu in the :guilabel:`Product` field and selecting the desired product."
msgstr ""
"Tilføj et produkt til :abbr:`styklisten` ved at klikke på rullemenuen i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Produkt` og vælge det ønskede produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:95
msgid ""
"Then, add components by clicking :guilabel:`Add a line` under "
"the :guilabel:`Component` section of the :guilabel:`Components` tab, and "
"choosing the desired components from the drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"Tilføj derefter komponenter ved at klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje` "
"under afsnittet :guilabel:`Komponent` på fanen :guilabel:`Komponenter` og "
"vælge de ønskede komponenter fra rullemenuen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:98
msgid ""
"Choose the desired values in the :guilabel:`Quantity` and :guilabel:`Product "
"Unit of Measure` columns. Then, choose the desired values in "
"the :guilabel:`Apply on Variants` column."
msgstr ""
"Vælg de ønskede værdier i kolonnerne :guilabel:`Antal` "
"og :guilabel:`Produktenhed`. Vælg derefter de ønskede værdier i "
"kolonnen :guilabel:`Anvend på varianter`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:102
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Apply on Variants` option to assign components to specific "
"product variants on the :abbr:`BoM (bill of materials)` is available once "
"the :guilabel:`Variants` setting is activated from "
"the :menuselection:`Inventory` application. If the :guilabel:`Apply on "
"Variants` field is not immediately visible, activate it from the additional "
"options menu (three-dots icon, to the right of the header row)."
msgstr ""
"Indstillingen :guilabel:`Anvend på varianter` til at tildele komponenter til "
"specifikke produktvarianter på :abbr:`styklisten` er tilgængelig, når "
"indstillingen :guilabel:`Varianter` er aktiveret fra "
"applikationen :menuselection:`Lager`. Hvis feltet :guilabel:`Anvend på "
"varianter` ikke er synligt med det samme, kan det aktiveres fra menuen med "
"yderligere indstillinger (ikon med tre prikker til højre for "
"overskriftsrækken)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:None
msgid "\"Apply on Variants\" option on the additional options menu."
msgstr ""
"\"Anvend på varianter\"-indstilling i menuen med yderligere indstillinger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:112
msgid ""
"Each component can be assigned to multiple variants. Components with no "
"variants specified are used in every variant of the product. The same "
"principle applies when configuring operations and by-products."
msgstr ""
"Hver komponent kan tildeles flere varianter. Komponenter uden angivne "
"varianter bruges i alle varianter af produktet. Samme princip gælder ved "
"konfiguration af operationer og biprodukter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:116
msgid ""
"When defining variant :abbr:`BoMs (bills of material)` by component "
"assignment, the :guilabel:`Product Variant` field in the main section of "
"the :abbr:`BoM (bill of materials)` should be left blank. This field is "
"*only* used when creating a :abbr:`BoM (bill of materials)` specifically for "
"one product variant."
msgstr ""
"Når der defineres variant-:abbr:`styklister` ved komponenttildeling, skal "
"feltet :guilabel:`Produktvariant` i hovedafsnittet af :abbr:`styklisten` "
"efterlades tomt. Dette felt bruges *kun*, når der oprettes "
"en :abbr:`stykliste` specifikt til én produktvariant."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:121
msgid ""
"When all desired configurations have been made to the :abbr:`BoM (bill of "
"materials)`, click :guilabel:`Save` at the top of the form to save changes."
msgstr ""
"Når alle ønskede konfigurationer er foretaget på :abbr:`styklisten`, klik "
"på :guilabel:`Gem` øverst på formularen for at gemme ændringerne."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:125
msgid ""
"For components that only apply for specific variants, choose which "
"operations the components should be consumed in. If the :guilabel:`Consumed "
"in Operation` column is *not* immediately visible, activate it from the "
"additional options menu (three-dots icon, to the right of the header row)."
msgstr ""
"For komponenter, der kun gælder for specifikke varianter, skal du vælge, "
"hvilke operationer komponenterne skal forbruges i. Hvis "
"kolonnen :guilabel:`Forbrugt i operation` *ikke* er synlig med det samme, "
"kan den aktiveres fra menuen med yderligere indstillinger (ikon med tre "
"prikker til højre for overskriftsrækken)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:131
msgid "Sell and manufacture variants of BoM products"
msgstr "Sælg og fremstil varianter af styklisteprodukter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:133
msgid ""
"To sell and manufacture variants of :abbr:`BoM (bill of materials)` products "
"to order, navigate to :menuselection:`Sales app --> Create` to create a new "
"quotation."
msgstr ""
"For at sælge og fremstille varianter af :abbr:`styklisteprodukter` til "
"ordre, naviger til :menuselection:`Salg-app --> Opret` for at oprette et nyt "
"tilbud."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:137
msgid "Sell variant of BoM product"
msgstr "Sælg variant af styklisteprodukt"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:139
msgid ""
"Once on the blank :guilabel:`Quotation` form, click the drop-down next to "
"the :guilabel:`Customer` field to add a customer."
msgstr ""
"Når du er på den tomme :guilabel:`Tilbud`-formular, klik på rullemenuen ved "
"siden af feltet :guilabel:`Kunde` for at tilføje en kunde."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:142
msgid ""
"Then, under the :guilabel:`Order Lines` tab, click :guilabel:`Add a "
"product`, and select the previously-created :abbr:`BoM (bill of materials)` "
"product with variants from the drop-down menu. Doing so reveals "
"a :guilabel:`Configure a product` pop-up."
msgstr ""
"Under fanen :guilabel:`Ordrelinjer` klik derefter på :guilabel:`Tilføj et "
"produkt` og vælg det tidligere oprettede :abbr:`styklisteprodukt` med "
"varianter fra rullemenuen. Dette viser en pop-up med :guilabel:`Konfigurer "
"et produkt`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:146
msgid ""
"From the pop-up window, click the desired attribute options to configure the "
"correct variant of the product to manufacture. Then, click the "
"green :guilabel:`+` or :guilabel:`-` icons next to the `1` to change the "
"quantity to sell and manufacture, if desired."
msgstr ""
"Fra pop-up-vinduet skal du klikke på de ønskede attributindstillinger for at "
"konfigurere den korrekte variant af produktet, der skal fremstilles. Klik "
"derefter på de grønne ikoner :guilabel:`+` eller :guilabel:`-` ved siden af "
"`1` for at ændre antallet, der skal sælges og fremstilles, hvis ønsket."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:None
msgid "Configure a product pop-up for choosing variant attributes."
msgstr "Konfigurer et produkt pop-up til valg af variantattributter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:154
msgid ""
"Once all the specifications have been chosen, click :guilabel:`Add`. This "
"will change the pop-up to a second :guilabel:`Configure` pop-up, where "
"available optional products will appear, if they have been created "
"previously."
msgstr ""
"Når alle specifikationer er valgt, klik på :guilabel:`Tilføj`. Dette ændrer "
"pop-uppen til en anden :guilabel:`Konfigurer` pop-up, hvor tilgængelige "
"valgfrie produkter vises, hvis de er blevet oprettet tidligere."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:158
msgid "Once ready, click :guilabel:`Confirm` to close the pop-up."
msgstr "Når du er klar, klik på :guilabel:`Bekræft` for at lukke pop-uppen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:160
msgid ""
"Then, click :guilabel:`Save` to save all changes, and "
"click :guilabel:`Confirm` at the top of the :guilabel:`Quotation` form to "
"create and confirm a new sales order (SO)."
msgstr ""
"Klik derefter på :guilabel:`Gem` for at gemme alle ændringer, og klik "
"på :guilabel:`Bekræft` øverst på :guilabel:`Tilbud`-formularen for at "
"oprette og bekræfte en ny salgsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:164
msgid "Manufacture variant of BoM product"
msgstr "Fremstil variant af styklisteprodukt"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:166
msgid ""
"Once the :abbr:`SO (sales order)` is confirmed, a :guilabel:`Manufacturing` "
"smart button appears at the top of the :abbr:`SO (sales order)` form. Click "
"the :guilabel:`Manufacturing` smart button to open "
"the :guilabel:`Manufacturing Order` form."
msgstr ""
"Når :abbr:`salgsordren` er bekræftet, vises en smart "
"knap :guilabel:`Produktion` øverst i :abbr:`salgsordre`-formularen. Klik på "
"den smarte knap :guilabel:`Produktion` for at åbne "
"formularen :guilabel:`Produktionsordre`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:170
msgid ""
"On this form, under the :guilabel:`Components` tab, the appropriate "
"components for the chosen variant are listed. And, depending on the variant, "
"different components will be listed. To see any mandatory or "
"optional :guilabel:`Operation` steps, click the :guilabel:`Work Orders` tab."
msgstr ""
"På denne formular under fanen :guilabel:`Komponenter` vises de relevante "
"komponenter for den valgte variant. Og afhængigt af varianten vises "
"forskellige komponenter. For at se obligatoriske eller "
"valgfrie :guilabel:`Arbejdsgang`-trin skal du klikke på "
"fanen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:174
msgid ""
"To enter the tablet view work order screen, click the :guilabel:`tablet "
"icon` to the right of the row for the desired operation to be completed."
msgstr ""
"For at gå ind i tablet-visningens arbejdsordreoversigt skal du klikke "
"på :guilabel:`tablet-ikonet` til højre for rækken for den ønskede "
"arbejdsgang, der skal udføres."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:177
msgid ""
"From the tablet view, click :guilabel:`Mark as Done` as the operation "
"progresses to complete the operation steps."
msgstr ""
"Fra tablet-visningen skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Markér som udført`, mens "
"arbejdsgangen fortsætter, for at gennemføre arbejdsgangstrinene."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:180
msgid ""
"Alternatively, click the :guilabel:`Mark as Done` button at the top of the "
"manufacturing order form to complete the order."
msgstr ""
"Alternativt kan du klikke på knappen :guilabel:`Markér som udført` øverst i "
"produktionsordreformularen for at gennemføre ordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:None
msgid "Manufacturing order for variant of BoM product."
msgstr "Produktionsordre for variant af styklisteprodukt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:187
msgid ""
"Then, navigate back to the :abbr:`SO (sales order)` via the breadcrumbs at "
"the top of the page."
msgstr ""
"Gå derefter tilbage til :abbr:`salgsordren` via brødkrummerne øverst på "
"siden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:189
msgid ""
"Now that the product has been manufactured, click the :guilabel:`Delivery` "
"smart button to deliver the product to the customer. From "
"the :guilabel:`Delivery Order` form, click :guilabel:`Validate`, then "
"click :guilabel:`Apply` to deliver the product."
msgstr ""
"Nu hvor produktet er fremstillet, skal du klikke på den smarte "
"knap :guilabel:`Levering` for at levere produktet til kunden. Fra "
"formularen :guilabel:`Leveringsordre` skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Valider` "
"og derefter klikke på :guilabel:`Anvend` for at levere produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/product_variants.rst:193
msgid ""
"To finish the sale, click back to the :abbr:`SO (sales order)` via "
"the :guilabel:`breadcrumbs` at the top of the page again. Then, "
"click :guilabel:`Create Invoice` followed by :guilabel:`Create Invoice` "
"again to invoice the customer for the order."
msgstr ""
"For at afslutte salget skal du klikke tilbage til :abbr:`salgsordren` "
"via :guilabel:`brødkrummerne` øverst på siden igen. Klik derefter "
"på :guilabel:`Opret faktura` efterfulgt af :guilabel:`Opret faktura` igen "
"for at fakturere kunden for ordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:3
msgid "Multilevel BoMs"
msgstr "Flerniveau-styklister"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:9
msgid ""
"Use a multilevel bill of materials (BoM) when a manufactured product is part "
"of another assembly. This method nests |BOMs| within other |BOMs|, "
"organizing complex products while simplifying manufacturing by defining each "
"procurement and production step separately."
msgstr ""
"Brug en flerniveau-stykliste, når et fremstillet produkt er en del af en "
"anden samling. Denne metode indlejrer |BOMs| i andre |BOMs|, organiserer "
"komplekse produkter og forenkler produktionen ved at definere hvert indkøbs- "
"og produktionstrin separat."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:13
msgid ""
"Sublevel |BOMs| (subassemblies or semifinished products) streamline these "
"production workflows, and are beneficial when the subassembly is used across "
"multiple finished products (meaning they'd appear on multiple top-level |"
"BOMs|). The more complicated a product is to build or procure, the more "
"value a multilevel |BOM| can provide. Because of this, component and "
"subassembly replenishment planning is vital to ensuring multilevel |BOMs| "
"run smoothly."
msgstr ""
"Underniveau |BOMs| (undersamlinger eller halvfærdige produkter) strømline "
"disse produktionsarbejdsgange og er fordelagtige, når undersamlingen bruges "
"på tværs af flere færdige produkter (hvilket betyder, at de ville forekomme "
"på flere topniveau |BOMs|). Jo mere kompliceret et produkt er at bygge eller "
"indkøbe, jo mere værdi kan en flerniveau |BOM| give. På grund af dette er "
"planlægning af genopfyldning af komponenter og undersamlinger vital for at "
"sikre, at flerniveau |BOMs| kører glat."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:20
msgid "Why replenishment planning is important"
msgstr "Hvorfor planlægning af genopfyldning er vigtig"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:22
msgid ""
":doc:`Replenishment <../../inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment>` is "
"critical for multilevel BoMs to prevent bottlenecks, manage lead times, and "
"optimize inventory. Without it, missing components can halt production, "
"delay orders, and increase costs. A well-planned replenishment strategy "
"ensures :doc:`just-in-time availability <../../inventory/warehouses_storage/"
"replenishment/reordering_rules>`, :doc:`automates procurement <../../"
"inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/reordering_rules>`, balances "
"stock levels, and keeps supply chains efficient. This minimizes delays, "
"reduces manual effort, and ensures smooth manufacturing."
msgstr ""
":doc:`Genopfyldning <../../inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment>` er "
"kritisk for flerniveau-styklister for at forhindre flaskehalse, håndtere "
"leveringstider og optimere lageret. Uden det kan manglende komponenter "
"standse produktionen, forsinke ordrer og øge omkostningerne. En velplanlagt "
"genopfyldningsstrategi sikrer :doc:`just-in-time-tilgængelighed <../../"
"inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/"
"reordering_rules>`, :doc:`automatiserer indkøb <../../inventory/"
"warehouses_storage/replenishment/reordering_rules>`, balancerer "
"lagerniveauer og holder forsyningskæder effektive. Dette minimerer "
"forsinkelser, reducerer manuel indsats og sikrer jævn produktion."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:31
msgid ""
"Manufacturing orders (MO)s that come from a |BOM| require all components to "
"be available before the |MO| can be completed. The :guilabel:`Component "
"Status` for that |MO| provides this information. Learn how to :doc:`check an "
"MO's component status <../basic_setup/bill_configuration>`."
msgstr ""
"Produktionsordrer, der kommer fra en |BOM|, kræver, at alle komponenter er "
"tilgængelige, før |MO| kan gennemføres. :guilabel:`Komponentstatus` for den |"
"MO| giver disse oplysninger. Lær hvordan du :doc:`kontrollerer en "
"produktionsordres komponentstatus <../basic_setup/bill_configuration>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:38
msgid "Create a multilevel BoM"
msgstr "Opret en flerniveau-stykliste"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:40
msgid ""
"To set up a multilevel |BOM|, the top-level product and sublevel products's |"
"BOMs| must be created. If starting from scratch, build the |BOMs| from the "
"bottom up. Start with the lowest-level product |BOMs|, then include those "
"products as components in higher-level |BOMs|."
msgstr ""
"For at opsætte en flerniveau |BOM| skal topniveauproduktets og "
"underniveauprodukternes |BOMs| oprettes. Hvis du starter fra bunden, skal du "
"bygge |BOMs| nedefra og op. Start med produktet på det laveste niveau |"
"BOMs|, og inkluder derefter disse produkter som komponenter i |BOMs| på "
"højere niveau."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:45
msgid ""
"A printed circuit board (PCB) for a custom keyboard is composed of hundreds "
"of electronic components, such as transistors, resistors, and capacitors. "
"Instead of listing all of those components out, a sublevel product and |BOM| "
"for a `PCB` is created, to track the quantities of transistors and other "
"small components, without needing to overcrowd the top-level |BOM| for the "
"custom keyboard by listing them. Instead, the custom keyboard's |BOM| "
"consists of an assortment of components and sublevel |BOMs| alike, like key "
"caps, switches, the PCB, and keyboard plate."
msgstr ""
"Et printkort (PCB) til et tilpasset tastatur består af hundredvis af "
"elektroniske komponenter, såsom transistorer, modstande og kondensatorer. I "
"stedet for at liste alle disse komponenter op oprettes et underniveauprodukt "
"og |BOM| for et `PCB` for at spore mængderne af transistorer og andre små "
"komponenter uden at skulle overfylde topniveau |BOM| for det tilpassede "
"tastatur ved at liste dem. I stedet består det tilpassede tastaturs |BOM| af "
"et udvalg af komponenter og underniveau |BOMs|, som tastetrykkere, "
"kontakter, PCB'et og tastaturpladen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:52
msgid ""
":doc:`Learn how to build a simple bill of materials <../basic_setup/"
"bill_configuration>`. For the PCB, this would include the transistors, "
"resistors, and other components."
msgstr ""
":doc:`Lær hvordan du bygger en simpel stykliste <../basic_setup/"
"bill_configuration>`. For PCB'et vil dette omfatte transistorerne, "
"modstandene og andre komponenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:None
msgid "A bill of materials for a PCB."
msgstr "En stykliste for et printkort."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:58
msgid ""
"After the sublevel products (like the PCB, key caps, and keyboard plate) are "
"fully configured, create the top-level product by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Products --> Products`, and then "
"selecting :guilabel:`New`. From here, configure the product's specifications "
"as needed."
msgstr ""
"Når underprodukterne (som PCB, tastetryk og tastaturplade) er fuldt "
"konfigureret, oprettes topniveauproduktet ved at navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Produkter --> Produkter` og derefter "
"vælge :guilabel:`Ny`. Herfra konfigureres produktets specifikationer efter "
"behov."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:63
msgid ""
"Once the top-level product (the keyboard) is configured, click "
"the :guilabel:`Bill of Materials` smart button on the product form, and then "
"select :guilabel:`New` to make a |BOM| for the top-level product. Add the "
"sublevel products to this |BOM|, along with any other necessary components."
msgstr ""
"Når topniveauproduktet (tastaturet) er konfigureret, klikkes på den smarte "
"knap :guilabel:`Stykliste` på produktformularen, og derefter "
"vælges :guilabel:`Ny` for at lave en |BOM| til topniveauproduktet. Tilføj "
"underprodukterne til denne |BOM| sammen med alle andre nødvendige "
"komponenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:None
msgid ""
"A bill of materials for a keyboard, containing a bill of materials for a PCB."
msgstr "En stykliste for et tastatur, der indeholder en stykliste for et PCB."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:71
msgid "Manage production planning"
msgstr "Administrer produktionsplanlægning"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:73
msgid ""
"The two options below are two of the best ways to manage manufacturing order "
"automation for products with multilevel |BOMs|."
msgstr ""
"De to nedenstående muligheder er to af de bedste måder at administrere "
"automatisering af produktionsordrer for produkter med styklister på flere "
"niveauer |BOMs|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:77
msgid ""
"Complex |BOMs| are specifically used to manage products that require "
"manufactured components. If a BoM is being created to organize components or "
"bundle sellable products, :doc:`use a kit <kit_shipping>` instead."
msgstr ""
"Komplekse |BOMs| bruges specifikt til at administrere produkter, der kræver "
"fremstillede komponenter. Hvis der oprettes en stykliste for at organisere "
"komponenter eller samle salgbare produkter, :doc:`brug i stedet et kit "
"<kit_shipping>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:81
msgid ""
"To automatically trigger manufacturing orders for sublevel products after "
"confirming a manufacturing order for the main product, there are two options:"
msgstr ""
"For automatisk at udløse produktionsordrer for underprodukter efter "
"bekræftelse af en produktionsordre for hovedproduktet er der to muligheder:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:84
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:153
msgid ""
"**Option 1 (recommended):** Create *Reordering Rules* for the sublevel "
"products and set both the minimum and maximum needed stock quantities to `0`."
msgstr ""
"**Mulighed 1 (anbefalet):** Opret *genbestillingsregler* for "
"underprodukterne og sæt både minimum og maksimum nødvendige lagermængder til "
"`0`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:86
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:155
msgid ""
"**Option 2:** Activate the :guilabel:`Replenish on Order (MTO)` "
"and :guilabel:`Manufacture` routes under the :guilabel:`Inventory` tab of "
"the sublevel product's product form."
msgstr ""
"**Mulighed 2:** Aktiver ruterne :guilabel:`Genopfyld ved ordre (MTO)` "
"og :guilabel:`Fremstil` under fanen :guilabel:`Lager` på underproduktets "
"produktformular."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:90
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:159
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/purchase/products/reordering.rst:82
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/purchase/products/temporary_reordering.rst:27
msgid ""
":doc:`../../inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/reordering_rules`"
msgstr ""
":doc:`../../inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/reordering_rules`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:91
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:160
msgid ":doc:`../../inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/mto`"
msgstr ":doc:`../../inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/mto`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:93
msgid ""
"Option 1 is more flexible than Option 2 and is recommended. Reordering rules "
"do not directly link demand to replenishment, allowing stock to be "
"unreserved and reassigned as needed. The Replenish on Order (MTO) route, "
"however, uniquely links sublevel and top-level products, reserving "
"quantities for the confirmed top-level manufacturing order."
msgstr ""
"Mulighed 1 er mere fleksibel end mulighed 2 og anbefales. "
"Genbestillingsregler kobler ikke direkte efterspørgsel til genopfyldning, "
"hvilket gør det muligt at fjerne reservation af lager og tildele det efter "
"behov. Ruten Genopfyld ved ordre (MTO) kobler derimod underprodukter og "
"topniveauprodukter unikt sammen og reserverer mængder til den bekræftede "
"produktionsordre på topniveau."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:98
msgid ""
"In both methods, sublevel products must be fully manufactured before "
"starting the top-level product."
msgstr ""
"I begge metoder skal underprodukter være fuldt fremstillet, før der startes "
"på topniveauproduktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:101
msgid "Multilevel BoM setup flow"
msgstr "Opsætningsflow for stykliste på flere niveauer"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:103
msgid ""
"The following section details how to set up multilevel BoMs, set the initial "
"inventory, establish a :ref:`0/0/1 reordering rule <manufacturing/advanced/"
"procurement-method>` (the recommended production plan), configure lead "
"times, and set up production options."
msgstr ""
"Følgende afsnit beskriver, hvordan man opsætter styklister på flere "
"niveauer, indstiller det indledende lager, etablerer en :ref:`0/0/1 "
"genbestillingsregel <manufacturing/advanced/procurement-method>` (den "
"anbefalede produktionsplan), konfigurerer leveringstider og opsætter "
"produktionsmuligheder."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:107
msgid ""
"Creating a 0/0/1 reordering rule for the sublevel products (minimum stock "
"set at zero, maximum stock set at zero, reorder one automatically) "
"regardless of whether they are a component or subassembly is the recommended "
"approach for managing a multilevel |BOM|. This setup uses the **Inventory**, "
"**Manufacturing**, and **Purchase** apps."
msgstr ""
"Oprettelse af en 0/0/1 genbestillingsregel for underprodukterne "
"(minimumlager sat til nul, maksimumlager sat til nul, genbestil én "
"automatisk) uanset om de er en komponent eller delmontage, er den anbefalede "
"tilgang til at administrere en |BOM| på flere niveauer. Dette setup bruger "
"applikationerne **Lager**, **Produktion** og **Indkøb**."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:113
msgid ""
"This is only one example of how to set up a multilevel |BOM| in Odoo. "
"Consider any unique circumstances that need to be addressed during the "
"configuration, and make sure they are included in the setup. If any specific "
"help is needed during setup, consider purchasing a `success pack <https://"
"www.odoo.com/pricing-packs>`_."
msgstr ""
"Dette er kun ét eksempel på, hvordan man opsætter en |BOM| på flere niveauer "
"i Odoo. Overvej eventuelle unikke omstændigheder, der skal adresseres under "
"konfigurationen, og sørg for, at de inkluderes i opsætningen. Hvis der er "
"behov for specifik hjælp under opsætningen, kan du overveje at købe en "
"`succespakke <https://www.odoo.com/pricing-packs>`_."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:119
msgid "Create the BoMs"
msgstr "Opret styklisterne"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:121
msgid ""
"Follow the steps in the :ref:`Create a multilevel BoM <manufactuing/advanced/"
"create-multilevel-bom>` section to build the |BOMs|."
msgstr ""
"Følg trinnene i afsnittet :ref:`Opret en stykliste på flere niveauer "
"<manufactuing/advanced/create-multilevel-bom>` for at bygge |BOMs|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:124
msgid ""
"Make sure to build the multilevel |BOM| from the bottom up. Start by "
"creating the lowest-level component products in Odoo, then the subassembly "
"products that those are used for, then the |BOM| for that subassembly, and "
"repeat until every level of the multilevel |BOM| is created."
msgstr ""
"Sørg for at bygge |BOM| på flere niveauer nedefra og op. Start med at "
"oprette komponentprodukterne på laveste niveau i Odoo, derefter "
"delmontageprodukterne som disse bruges til, derefter |BOM| til den "
"delmontage, og gentag indtil hvert niveau af |BOM| på flere niveauer er "
"oprettet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:129
msgid "Set the initial inventory"
msgstr "Indstil det initiale lager"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:132
msgid ""
"If there's no initial inventory to configure, then skip this section and "
"begin configuring the procurement method for the multilevel |BOM|."
msgstr ""
"Hvis der ikke er noget initialt lager at konfigurere, så spring dette afsnit "
"over og begynd at konfigurere indkøbsmetoden for den flerniveau |BOM|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:135
msgid ""
"Update the quantity on hand for each of the products configured in the prior "
"step (both components, subassemblies, and the final product). To do this, "
"open the **Inventory** app, and then find the products with filters, the "
"search bar, or scrolling, and then click on them to open their product form. "
"From here, click the :guilabel:`On Hand` smart button, :doc:`select the "
"variant <../../../sales/sales/products_prices/products/variants>` if that "
"was configured, and then enter the quantity on hand."
msgstr ""
"Opdater behændningen for hvert af de produkter, der blev konfigureret i det "
"forrige trin (både komponenter, undermontager og det endelige produkt). For "
"at gøre dette skal du åbne **Lager**-appen og derefter finde produkterne med "
"filtre, søgelinjen eller ved at scrolle, og derefter klikke på dem for at "
"åbne deres produktformular. Klik herfra på :guilabel:`Behændning` smart-"
"knappen, :doc:`vælg varianten <../../../sales/sales/products_prices/products/"
"variants>`, hvis den blev konfigureret, og indtast derefter behændningen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:148
msgid "Configure the procurement method"
msgstr "Konfigurer indkøbsmetoden"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:150
msgid ""
"Now it is time to pick the procurement method this multilevel |BOM| uses. "
"The two options below are preferred, but unique circumstances may lead to "
"another procurement method making more sense."
msgstr ""
"Nu er det tid til at vælge den indkøbsmetode, som denne flerniveau |BOM| "
"bruger. De to muligheder nedenfor foretrækkes, men unikke omstændigheder kan "
"føre til, at en anden indkøbsmetode giver mere mening."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:162
msgid ""
"Reordering rules are recommended because they do not tie the manufactured "
"product to a specific sales order, allowing that manufactured product to "
"fulfill a different sales order if the original gets cancelled."
msgstr ""
"Genbestillingsregler anbefales, fordi de ikke binder det producerede produkt "
"til en specifik salgsordre, hvilket tillader, at det producerede produkt kan "
"opfylde en anden salgsordre, hvis den oprindelige bliver annulleret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:166
msgid ""
"Making the product to order is not recommended because the manufactured "
"product cannot be used to fulfill another sales order. However, this could "
"be helpful if strict tracking is necessary for the business."
msgstr ""
"At producere produktet til ordre anbefales ikke, fordi det producerede "
"produkt ikke kan bruges til at opfylde en anden salgsordre. Dette kan dog "
"være nyttigt, hvis streng sporing er nødvendig for virksomheden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:171
msgid "Enter vendor and manufacturing lead times"
msgstr "Indtast leverandør- og produktionsleveringstider"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:173
msgid ""
"Vendor and manufacturing lead times are used by Odoo to coordinate "
"production and procurement actions to fulfill orders on time. Set vendor "
"lead times for components that are purchased. These can appear at any level "
"in a multilevel |BOM| except the final product. Set manufacturing lead times "
"for products that are built using a |BOM|. These can appear at any level in "
"a multilevel |BOM| except the lowest level (when individual components are "
"procured)."
msgstr ""
"Leverandør- og produktionsleveringstider bruges af Odoo til at koordinere "
"produktions- og indkøbshandlinger for at opfylde ordrer til tiden. Indstil "
"leverandørleveringstider for komponenter, der købes. Disse kan forekomme på "
"ethvert niveau i en flerniveau |BOM| undtagen det endelige produkt. Indstil "
"produktionsleveringstider for produkter, der bygges ved hjælp af en |BOM|. "
"Disse kan forekomme på ethvert niveau i en flerniveau |BOM| undtagen det "
"laveste niveau (når individuelle komponenter indkøbes)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:180
msgid ":doc:`../../inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times`"
msgstr ":doc:`../../inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:183
msgid "Build out operations to handle the production flow"
msgstr "Byg operationer til at håndtere produktionsflowet"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:185
msgid ""
"First, determine the current manufacturing flow for the business, then match "
"the corresponding Odoo setup. The list below are only some of the "
"configuration pieces that could be involved in this step."
msgstr ""
"Først skal du bestemme det aktuelle produktionsflow for virksomheden, og "
"derefter matche den tilsvarende Odoo-opsætning. Listen nedenfor er kun nogle "
"af de konfigurationselementer, der kan være involveret i dette trin."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:188
msgid ""
"**Manufacturing Steps**: Consider how many manufacturing steps are taken "
"(one-, two-, or three-step manufacturing)."
msgstr ""
"**Produktionstrin**: Overvej hvor mange produktionstrin der tages (én-, to- "
"eller tre-trins produktion)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:190
msgid ""
"**Work Centers**: Decide if any :doc:`work centers <using_work_centers>` "
"need to be configured."
msgstr ""
"**Arbejdscentre**: Beslut om der skal konfigureres :doc:`arbejdscentre "
"<using_work_centers>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:191
msgid ""
"**Master Production Schedule**: If manually planned manufacturing orders are "
"needed (e.g., to handle seasonal demand), make a :doc:`master production "
"schedule <../workflows/use_mps>` (MPS)."
msgstr ""
"**Hovedproduktionsplan**: Hvis manuelt planlagte produktionsordrer er "
"nødvendige (f.eks. for at håndtere sæsonbestemt efterspørgsel), skal du lave "
"en :doc:`hovedproduktionsplan <../workflows/use_mps>` (MPS)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:195
msgid ""
"Manufacturing operations is an art and a science, so configuring an "
"established flow into Odoo is the recommended approach for this step. Read "
"more about :doc:`manufacturing in Odoo <../../manufacturing>`"
msgstr ""
"Produktionsoperationer er en kunst og en videnskab, så at konfigurere et "
"etableret flow i Odoo er den anbefalede fremgangsmåde for dette trin. Læs "
"mere om :doc:`produktion i Odoo <../../manufacturing>`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:200
msgid "Configuration summary"
msgstr "Konfigurationsoversigt"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:202
msgid ""
"At the end of this process, the multilevel |BOM| is configured, and the top-"
"level product has its inventory counts, procurement method set, procurement "
"lead times, and manufacturing operations configured. From here, sales orders "
"can include the top-level product, automatic procurement through vendors or "
"manufacturing can begin, the top-level product can be included in an "
"**eCommerce** store."
msgstr ""
"I slutningen af denne proces er flerniveau |BOM| konfigureret, og produktet "
"på øverste niveau har sine lagerbeholdninger, indkøbsmetode, "
"indkøbsleveringstider og produktionsoperationer konfigureret. Herfra kan "
"salgsordrer inkludere produktet på øverste niveau, automatisk indkøb gennem "
"leverandører eller produktion kan begynde, produktet på øverste niveau kan "
"inkluderes i en **Webshop**-butik."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/sub_assemblies.rst:209
msgid ":doc:`../../../websites/ecommerce/ecommerce_design/catalog`"
msgstr ":doc:`../../../websites/ecommerce/ecommerce_design/catalog`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:5
msgid ""
"*Work centers* are where **Manufacturing** work orders are processed, and "
"can be used to track costs, make schedules, plan capacity, organize "
"equipment, and track efficiency. Specifying a work center is required when a "
"work order is defined in the *Operations* tab of a bill of materials (BoM) "
"for a product."
msgstr ""
"*Arbejdscentre* er hvor **Produktion**s arbejdsordrer behandles, og kan "
"bruges til at spore omkostninger, lave tidsplaner, planlægge kapacitet, "
"organisere udstyr og spore effektivitet. At specificere et arbejdscenter er "
"påkrævet, når en arbejdsordre er defineret i fanen *Operationer* i en "
"stykliste (BoM) for et produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:11
msgid ""
"Work centers only appear if the :guilabel:`Work Orders` setting is enabled. "
"To do so, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Configuration --"
"> Settings`, then tick the :guilabel:`Work Orders` checkbox. Work orders can "
"be managed in the :guilabel:`Manufacturing` app by "
"selecting :menuselection:`Operations --> Work Orders`."
msgstr ""
"Arbejdscentre vises kun, hvis indstillingen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer` er "
"aktiveret. For at gøre dette skal du navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion-"
"appen --> Konfiguration --> Indstillinger` og derefter markere "
"afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer`. Arbejdsordrer kan "
"administreres i :guilabel:`Produktion`-appen ved at "
"vælge :menuselection:`Operationer --> Arbejdsordrer`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:17
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:55
msgid ":doc:`../basic_setup/bill_configuration`"
msgstr ":doc:`../basic_setup/bill_configuration`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:20
msgid "Work center configuration"
msgstr "Konfiguration af arbejdscenter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:25
msgid "Create a new work center"
msgstr "Opret et nyt arbejdscenter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:27
msgid ""
"In the **Manufacturing** app, select :menuselection:`Configuration --> Work "
"Centers` and click the :guilabel:`New` button to open a new work center form."
msgstr ""
"I **Produktion**-appen skal du vælge :menuselection:`Konfiguration --> "
"Arbejdscentre` og klikke på knappen :guilabel:`Ny` for at åbne en ny "
"arbejdscenterformular."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:None
msgid "An example of a fully configured work center form."
msgstr "Et eksempel på en fuldt konfigureret arbejdscenterformular."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:33
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Work Center Name`: the label for the work center used to select "
"it on a work order or on the reporting dashboards"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Arbejdscenternavn`: etiketten for arbejdscenteret, der bruges til "
"at vælge det på en arbejdsordre eller på rapporteringsdashboards"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:35
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Tag`: reusable labels that can be used to sort work centers in "
"list view"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Mærke`: genanvendelige etiketter, der kan bruges til at sortere "
"arbejdscentre i listevisning"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:36
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Alternative Workcenters`: where a work order should be carried "
"out if this work center is not available"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Alternative arbejdscentre`: hvor en arbejdsordre skal udføres, "
"hvis dette arbejdscenter ikke er tilgængeligt"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:38
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Code`: reference id for the work center that is displayed in the "
"list view"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Kode`: reference-id for arbejdscenteret, der vises i "
"listevisningen"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:39
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Working Hours`: the hours that work center can be used during the "
"week"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Arbejdstid`: de timer, hvor arbejdscenteret kan bruges i løbet af "
"ugen"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:44
msgid "Working hours"
msgstr "Arbejdstider"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:46
msgid ""
"*Working hours* define when a work center should operate, based on a one- or "
"two-week schedule. These hours also form the basis for calculating *overall "
"equipment efficiency* (OEE)."
msgstr ""
"*Arbejdstid* definerer, hvornår et arbejdscenter skal fungere, baseret på en "
"én- eller to-ugers tidsplan. Disse timer danner også grundlaget for "
"beregning af *samlet udstyrseffektivitet* (OEE)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:50
msgid ""
"By default, Odoo uses the `Standard 40 hours/week` working hours, which "
"expects work centers to operate between 8:00 AM and 5:00 PM on Monday "
"through Friday."
msgstr ""
"Som standard bruger Odoo `Standard 40 timer/uge` arbejdstid, som forventer, "
"at arbejdscentre fungerer mellem kl. 8:00 og 17:00 mandag til fredag."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:53
msgid ""
"To change the working hours, hover over the current :guilabel:`Working "
"Hours` value and click the :icon:`fa-arrow-right` (:guilabel:`Internal "
"link`) icon to open the working hours form."
msgstr ""
"For at ændre arbejdstiden skal du holde musen over den "
"aktuelle :guilabel:`Arbejdstid`-værdi og klikke på :icon:`fa-arrow-right` "
"(:guilabel:`Internt link`)-ikonet for at åbne arbejdstidsformularen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:None
msgid "The working hours form for Standard 40 hours/week."
msgstr "Arbejdstidsformularen for Standard 40 timer/uge."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:59
msgid ""
"To create a new set of working hours, click the :guilabel:`New` button and "
"give it a name. From here, edit any :guilabel:`Work from` or :guilabel:`Work "
"to` value to adjust the time range. Remove a line by clicking click "
"the :icon:`fa-trash-o` :guilabel:`(trash)` icon. To create a new time range, "
"click :guilabel:`Add a line` at the bottom of the list."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette et nyt sæt arbejdstider skal du klikke på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Ny` og give det et navn. Herfra kan du redigere "
"enhver :guilabel:`Arbejd fra`- eller :guilabel:`Arbejd til`-værdi for at "
"justere tidsintervallet. Fjern en linje ved at klikke på :icon:`fa-trash-"
"o` :guilabel:`(skraldespand)`-ikonet. For at oprette et nyt tidsinterval "
"skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje` nederst på listen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:65
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:95
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:205
msgid ":doc:`../reporting/oee`"
msgstr ":doc:`../reporting/oee`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:66
msgid ":doc:`../workflows/work_center_time_off`"
msgstr ":doc:`../workflows/work_center_time_off`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:69
msgid "Set productivity standards and allowed employees"
msgstr "Indstil produktivitetsstandarder og tilladte medarbejdere"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:71
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`General Information` tab on the work center form allows for "
"productivity goals to be assigned to a work center. These are used as the "
"basis for calculating how much of the potential time the work center is "
"being used and its operating costs."
msgstr ""
"Fanen :guilabel:`Generelle oplysninger` på arbejdscenterformularen giver "
"mulighed for at tildele produktivitetsmål til et arbejdscenter. Disse bruges "
"som grundlag for at beregne, hvor meget af den potentielle tid "
"arbejdscenteret bliver brugt, og dets driftsomkostninger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:None
msgid "The general information tab of the work center form."
msgstr "Fanen med generelle oplysninger i arbejdscenterformularen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:78
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Time Efficiency`: a multiplier for how using this work center "
"affects the normal speed of execution of a work order"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Time Efficiency`: en multiplikator for, hvordan brugen af dette "
"arbejdscenter påvirker den normale udførelseshastighed af en arbejdsordre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:82
msgid ""
"If a work center has older equipment and work orders take twice as long to "
"produce, the `Time Efficiency` would be `50.00%`."
msgstr ""
"Hvis et arbejdscenter har ældre udstyr, og arbejdsordrer tager dobbelt så "
"lang tid at producere, vil `Time Efficiency` være `50,00%`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:85
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Capacity`: the number of products that can be processed at the "
"work center simultaneously"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Capacity`: antallet af produkter, der kan behandles på "
"arbejdscenteret samtidigt"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:88
msgid ":guilabel:`OEE Target`: the target for efficiency at the work center"
msgstr ":guilabel:`OEE Target`: målet for effektivitet på arbejdscenteret"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:91
msgid ""
"If a work center is available for `8 hours per day` but is only expected to "
"be used for `7 hours per day`, the OEE would be "
"`87.50%`. :math:`7/8*100=87.5`"
msgstr ""
"Hvis et arbejdscenter er tilgængeligt i `8 timer om dagen`, men forventes "
"kun at blive brugt i `7 timer om dagen`, vil OEE være "
"`87,50%`. :math:`7/8*100=87.5`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:97
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Setup Time`: the time required before work can commence on a work "
"order"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Setup Time`: den tid, der kræves, før arbejdet kan påbegyndes på "
"en arbejdsordre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:98
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Cleanup Time`: breakdown or cleanup time required after a work "
"order is finished"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Cleanup Time`: nedbrudstid eller oprydningstid, der kræves, efter "
"en arbejdsordre er afsluttet"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:99
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Cost per hour`: the operating expense of that workstation. "
"The :guilabel:`per employee` value is for estimating the average cost per "
"employee."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Cost per hour`: driftsudgiften for den arbejdsstation. "
"Værdien :guilabel:`per employee` bruges til at estimere den gennemsnitlige "
"omkostning pr. medarbejder."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:103
msgid ":doc:`../basic_setup/mo_costs`"
msgstr ":doc:`../basic_setup/mo_costs`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:105
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Allowed Employees`: the employees who can perform work at the "
"work center. If blank, all employees are allowed."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Allowed Employees`: de medarbejdere, der kan udføre arbejde på "
"arbejdscenteret. Hvis feltet er tomt, er alle medarbejdere tilladt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:109
msgid ""
"If equipment at a work center requires a certification to "
"operate, :guilabel:`Allowed Employees` could list only those employees who "
"have the certification."
msgstr ""
"Hvis udstyr på et arbejdscenter kræver en certificering for at betjene det, "
"kan :guilabel:`Allowed Employees` kun angive de medarbejdere, der har "
"certificeringen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:113
msgid "Set production capacities"
msgstr "Indstil produktionskapaciteter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:115
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Capacity` setting on a work center creates a default value "
"for how many units can be produced at one time in a work center. To specify "
"that a work center can produce different quantities of different products, "
"select the :guilabel:`Specific Capacities` tab."
msgstr ""
"Indstillingen :guilabel:`Capacity` på et arbejdscenter opretter en "
"standardværdi for, hvor mange enheder der kan produceres ad gangen i et "
"arbejdscenter. For at angive, at et arbejdscenter kan producere forskellige "
"mængder af forskellige produkter, vælges fanen :guilabel:`Specific "
"Capacities`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:None
msgid ""
"A work center form with different capacities specified for different "
"products."
msgstr ""
"En arbejdscenterformular med forskellige kapaciteter angivet for forskellige "
"produkter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:123
msgid ""
"To specify production capacities in different measurements from a count of "
"units, enable the *Units of Measure* feature in the **Inventory** app."
msgstr ""
"For at angive produktionskapaciteter i forskellige målinger fra en optælling "
"af enheder, aktiver funktionen *Units of Measure* i appen **Lager**."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:127
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:153
msgid ":doc:`../../maintenance/add_new_equipment`"
msgstr ":doc:`../../maintenance/add_new_equipment`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:132
msgid "Integrate IoT devices"
msgstr "Integrer IoT-enheder"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:134
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`IoT Triggers` tab enables the integration of :abbr:`IoT "
"(Internet of Things)` devices with a work center:"
msgstr ""
"Fanen :guilabel:`IoT Triggers` muliggør integration af :abbr:`IoT (Internet "
"of Things)`-enheder med et arbejdscenter:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:137
msgid ":guilabel:`Device`: specifies the IoT device to be triggered"
msgstr ":guilabel:`Device`: angiver den IoT-enhed, der skal udløses"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:138
msgid ":guilabel:`Key`: the security key for the device"
msgstr ":guilabel:`Nøgle`: sikkerhedsnøglen til enheden"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:139
msgid ":guilabel:`Action`: the IoT device action triggered"
msgstr ":guilabel:`Handling`: IoT-enhedens handling, der udløses"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:None
msgid "The IoT Triggers tab of the work center form."
msgstr "Fanen IoT-udløsere på arbejdscenterformularen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:145
msgid "Assigning equipment to work centers"
msgstr "Tildeling af udstyr til arbejdscentre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:147
msgid ""
"The **Maintenance** app makes it possible to add specific equipment to a "
"work center and individually track its costs and productivity. It also adds "
"the :guilabel:`Equipment` and :guilabel:`Maintenance` tabs to the work "
"center form, used to list equipment and schedule maintenance activities."
msgstr ""
"Appen **Vedligeholdelse** gør det muligt at tilføje specifikt udstyr til et "
"arbejdscenter og individuelt spore dets omkostninger og produktivitet. Den "
"tilføjer også fanerne :guilabel:`Udstyr` og :guilabel:`Vedligeholdelse` til "
"arbejdscenterformularen, som bruges til at vise udstyr og planlægge "
"vedligeholdelsesaktiviteter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:156
msgid "Configure equipment"
msgstr "Konfigurer udstyr"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:158
msgid ""
"Using the :guilabel:`Equipment` tab, it is possible for specific pieces of "
"equipment to be assigned to a work center. The following information is "
"displayed for each piece of equipment added:"
msgstr ""
"Ved hjælp af fanen :guilabel:`Udstyr` er det muligt at tildele specifikke "
"stykker udstyr til et arbejdscenter. Følgende oplysninger vises for hvert "
"stykke udstyr, der tilføjes:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:161
msgid ":guilabel:`Equipment Name`: the name of the piece of equipment"
msgstr ":guilabel:`Udstyrets navn`: navnet på udstyret"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:162
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Technician`: the technician responsible for servicing the "
"equipment"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Tekniker`: teknikeren, der er ansvarlig for service af udstyret"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:163
msgid ":guilabel:`Equipment Category`: the category the equipment belongs to"
msgstr ":guilabel:`Udstyrskategori`: kategorien, som udstyret tilhører"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:164
msgid ""
":guilabel:`MTBF`: mean time between failures; the average time that the "
"piece of equipment will operate before failing"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`MTBF`: gennemsnitlig tid mellem fejl; den gennemsnitlige tid, som "
"udstyret vil fungere, før det fejler"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:166
msgid ""
":guilabel:`MTTR`: mean time to recovery; the average time it takes for the "
"equipment to become fully operational again"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`MTTR`: gennemsnitlig tid til genoprettelse; den gennemsnitlige "
"tid, det tager, før udstyret bliver fuldt operationelt igen"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:168
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Est. Next Failure`: an estimate of when the next equipment "
"failure will occur"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Forventet næste fejl`: et skøn over, hvornår den næste "
"udstyrsfejl vil forekomme"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:None
msgid "The equipment tab of the work center form."
msgstr "Udstyrsfanen på arbejdscenterformularen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:174
msgid ""
":guilabel:`MTBF`, :guilabel:`MTTR`, and :guilabel:`Est. Next Failure` are "
"all calculated automatically based on past failure data, if any exists."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`MTBF`, :guilabel:`MTTR` og :guilabel:`Forventet næste fejl` "
"beregnes alle automatisk baseret på tidligere fejldata, hvis der findes "
"nogen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:178
msgid "Work center planning"
msgstr "Planlægning af arbejdscenter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:180
msgid ""
"The currently scheduled work orders can be viewed by "
"accessing :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Planning --> Planning by "
"Workcenter`."
msgstr ""
"De aktuelt planlagte arbejdsordrer kan ses ved at gå "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion-app --> Planlægning --> Planlægning efter "
"arbejdscenter`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:None
msgid "The Gantt view of planning showing two assembly work centers."
msgstr "Gantt-visning af planlægning, der viser to samlearbejdscentre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:186
msgid ""
"Different views show how many individual work orders are scheduled, how many "
"minutes of each hour the work center is in production, and the dates and "
"times that are currently scheduled for work orders. Times and planned work "
"centers can be changed by clicking to access the individual work order."
msgstr ""
"Forskellige visninger viser, hvor mange individuelle arbejdsordrer der er "
"planlagt, hvor mange minutter af hver time arbejdscentret er i produktion, "
"og de datoer og tidspunkter, der aktuelt er planlagt til arbejdsordrer. "
"Tidspunkter og planlagte arbejdscentre kan ændres ved at klikke for at få "
"adgang til den individuelle arbejdsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:192
msgid "Work center performance"
msgstr "Arbejdscenterpræstation"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:194
msgid ""
"Performance for an individual work center can be viewed by "
"selecting :menuselection:`Configuration --> Work Centers`, and clicking on a "
"work center. Metrics are displayed in smart buttons at the top of the form."
msgstr ""
"Ydeevne for et individuelt arbejdscenter kan vises ved at "
"vælge :menuselection:`Konfiguration --> Arbejdscentre` og klikke på et "
"arbejdscenter. Nøgletal vises i smarte knapper øverst på formularen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:None
msgid "A work center form with smart buttons showing performance metrics."
msgstr ""
"En arbejdscenterformular med smarte knapper, der viser ydeevnemålinger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:201
msgid ""
":guilabel:`OEE`: overall equipment effectiveness, the percentage of time "
"that the work center has been productive out of its available work hours."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`OEE`: overall equipment effectiveness, den procentdel af tiden, "
"hvor arbejdscentret har været produktivt i forhold til dets tilgængelige "
"arbejdstimer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:207
msgid ":guilabel:`Lost`: the amount of time lost due to work stoppages"
msgstr ":guilabel:`Tabt`: mængden af tid tabt på grund af arbejdsstop"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:208
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Load`: the amount of time it will take to complete the current "
"workload"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Belastning`: den tid, det vil tage at gennemføre den aktuelle "
"arbejdsbyrde"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:209
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Performance`: the real duration of work time, shown as a "
"percentage of the expected duration"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Ydeevne`: den faktiske varighed af arbejdstid, vist som en "
"procentdel af den forventede varighed"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:213
msgid "Use case: measuring performance by shift using work centers"
msgstr "Use case: måling af ydeevne pr. skift ved hjælp af arbejdscentre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:215
msgid ""
"Work centers support defined working hours, enabling the tracking of "
"production efficiency by shift. To configure shift-based tracking, create "
"working hours for each of the shifts, then duplicate versions of each work "
"center for each of the shifts. With this setup, comparing shift productivity "
"can be done with any of the available :doc:`reporting <../../../essentials/"
"reporting>` tools."
msgstr ""
"Arbejdscentre understøtter definerede arbejdstimer, hvilket muliggør sporing "
"af produktionseffektivitet pr. skift. For at konfigurere skiftbaseret "
"sporing skal du oprette arbejdstimer for hvert skift og derefter duplikere "
"versioner af hvert arbejdscenter for hvert skift. Med denne opsætning kan "
"sammenligning af skiftproduktivitet udføres med ethvert af de "
"tilgængelige :doc:`rapporteringsværktøjer <../../../essentials/reporting>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:221
msgid "Working hours for multiple shifts"
msgstr "Arbejdstimer for flere skift"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:223
msgid ""
"To create working hours for multiple shifts, open a work center form and in "
"the :guilabel:`Working Hours` field click the :icon:`fa-arrow-right` "
"(:guilabel:`Internal link`), and then click the :guilabel:`New` button to "
"create a new set of hours for the second shift."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette arbejdstimer for flere skift skal du åbne en "
"arbejdscenterformular og i feltet :guilabel:`Arbejdstimer` klikke "
"på :icon:`fa-arrow-right` (:guilabel:`Internt link`) og derefter klikke på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Ny` for at oprette et nyt sæt timer for det andet skift."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:228
msgid ""
"A manufacturer has two shifts: a day shift from 5 AM to 1 PM and a night "
"shift from 1 PM to 9 PM. Starting from any existing work center, edit the "
"existing working hours to match the day shift."
msgstr ""
"En producent har to skift: et dagskift fra kl. 5 til kl. 13 og et natskift "
"fra kl. 13 til kl. 21. Start fra et eksisterende arbejdscenter og rediger de "
"eksisterende arbejdstimer, så de matcher dagskiftet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:0
msgid "The working hours for a day shift"
msgstr "Arbejdstimerne for et dagskift"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:234
msgid ""
"Once the day shift is saved, click the :icon:`fa-cog` :guilabel:`(cog)` icon "
"and select :guilabel:`Duplicate`. Rename this new schedule `Night Shift` and "
"change each :guilabel:`Work from` to 1 PM and :guilabel:`Work from` to 9 PM."
msgstr ""
"Når dagskiftet er gemt, skal du klikke på ikonet :icon:`fa-"
"cog` :guilabel:`(tandhjul)` og vælge :guilabel:`Dupliker`. Omdøb denne nye "
"tidsplan til `Natskift` og ændre hver :guilabel:`Arbejd fra` til kl. 13 "
"og :guilabel:`Arbejd til` til kl. 21."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:0
msgid "The working hours for a night shift"
msgstr "Arbejdstimerne for et natskift"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:242
msgid "Work centers for multiple shifts"
msgstr "Arbejdscentre for flere skift"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:244
msgid ""
"To create the duplicate work centers, return to the work center view by "
"navigating to :menuselection:`Configuration --> Work Centers` and "
"duplicating each of the work centers that are used by both shifts, either on "
"the individual work center forms, or directly from the list view."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette de duplikerede arbejdscentre skal du vende tilbage til "
"arbejdscentervisningen ved at navigere til :menuselection:`Konfiguration --> "
"Arbejdscentre` og duplikere hvert af de arbejdscentre, der bruges af begge "
"skift, enten på de enkelte arbejdscenterformularer eller direkte fra "
"listevisningen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:249
msgid ""
"To duplicate work centers directly from the list view, click the :icon:`fa-"
"check-square-o` :guilabel:`(checkbox)` that appears above the list items to "
"select all. Then, click the :icon:`fa-cog` :guilabel:`Actions` button at the "
"top of the list and select :guilabel:`Duplicate`."
msgstr ""
"For at duplikere arbejdscentre direkte fra listevisningen skal du klikke "
"på :icon:`fa-check-square-o` :guilabel:`(afkrydsningsfelt)`, der vises over "
"listeelementerne, for at vælge alle. Klik derefter på knappen :icon:`fa-"
"cog` :guilabel:`Handlinger` øverst på listen og vælg :guilabel:`Dupliker`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:255
msgid ""
"A manufacturer has two work centers, `Assembly Line 1` and `Assembly Line "
"2`, and two working hours, `Day Shift` and `Night Shift`."
msgstr ""
"En producent har to arbejdscentre, `Samlebånd 1` og `Samlebånd 2`, og to "
"arbejdstider, `Dagskift` og `Natskift`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:0
msgid "Work centers copied for day and night shifts."
msgstr "Arbejdscentre kopieret til dag- og natskift."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:261
msgid ""
"To create versions of `Assembly Line 1` and `Assembly Line 2` for each "
"shift, duplicate each of the work centers. Select the first work center and "
"add the shift name in that work center's name and assign it the appropriate "
"working hours. Optionally, configure each work center to use its opposite "
"shift counterpart as an alternate work center to make sure that "
"manufacturing orders get assigned to both. Tags can also help make a visual "
"distinction between each shift."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette versioner af `Samlebånd 1` og `Samlebånd 2` for hvert skift "
"skal du duplikere hvert af arbejdscentrene. Vælg det første arbejdscenter og "
"tilføj skiftnavnet i arbejdscentrets navn og tildel det de relevante "
"arbejdstimer. Valgfrit kan du konfigurere hvert arbejdscenter til at bruge "
"dets modsatte skift som et alternativt arbejdscenter for at sikre, at "
"produktionsordrer tildeles begge. Mærkater kan også hjælpe med at skabe en "
"visuel forskel mellem hvert skift."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:268
msgid ""
"Use the :icon:`oi-chevron-left` :guilabel:`(left arrow)` and :icon:`oi-"
"chevron-right` :guilabel:`(right arrow)` buttons in the top left corner to "
"move on to the next form in the list without returning to the list view."
msgstr ""
"Brug knapperne :icon:`oi-chevron-left` :guilabel:`(venstre pil)` "
"og :icon:`oi-chevron-right` :guilabel:`(højre pil)` i øverste venstre hjørne "
"til at gå videre til næste formular på listen uden at vende tilbage til "
"listevisningen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:273
msgid "Reports comparing different shifts"
msgstr "Rapporter, der sammenligner forskellige skiftehold"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:275
msgid ""
"With multiple work centers created to represent shifts, reports that sort by "
"work center will now compare shifts. This can be used to compare the number "
"of work orders that are being assigned each shift, the OEE, or actual time "
"that each shift is taking to produce a product."
msgstr ""
"Med flere arbejdscentre oprettet til at repræsentere skiftehold vil "
"rapporter, der sorterer efter arbejdscenter, nu sammenligne skiftehold. "
"Dette kan bruges til at sammenligne antallet af arbejdsordrer, der tildeles "
"hvert skift, OEE eller den faktiske tid, hvert skift bruger på at producere "
"et produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:280
msgid ""
"A report has been created to compare the time efficiency of two shifts "
"producing the same product in the same work center."
msgstr ""
"Der er oprettet en rapport til at sammenligne tidseffektiviteten for to "
"skiftehold, der producerer det samme produkt i det samme arbejdscenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:None
msgid ""
"A bar graph of two work centers with duration deviations of -6.50 and 15.00"
msgstr ""
"Et søjlediagram over to arbejdscentre med varighedsafvigelser på -6,50 og "
"15,00"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:286
msgid ""
"To create this report, go to :menuselection:`Reporting --> Work Orders` and "
"click to remove the :icon:`fa-filter` **Ready** *or* **Waiting** *or* "
"**Pending** *or* **In Progress** filter by clicking the :icon:`fa-"
"x` :guilabel:`Remove` icon on its right side. Next, click "
"the :guilabel:`Measures` button and select :guilabel:`Duration Deviation (%)`"
msgstr ""
"For at oprette denne rapport skal du gå til :menuselection:`Rapportering --> "
"Arbejdsordrer` og klikke for at fjerne filteret :icon:`fa-filter` **Klar** "
"*eller* **Venter** *eller* **Afventer** *eller* **I gang** ved at klikke på "
"ikonet :icon:`fa-x` :guilabel:`Fjern` på højre side. Klik derefter på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Mål` og vælg :guilabel:`Varighedsafvigelse (%)`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/using_work_centers.rst:291
msgid ""
"In this case, the day shift has on average taken more than the expected time "
"to produce products (-6.50%) while the night shift took less than the "
"expected time (15.00%)."
msgstr ""
"I dette tilfælde har dagholdet i gennemsnit brugt mere end den forventede "
"tid på at producere produkter (-6,50%), mens natholdet brugte mindre end den "
"forventede tid (15,00%)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:3
msgid "Work order dependencies"
msgstr "Arbejdsordreafhængigheder"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:7
msgid ""
"When manufacturing certain products, specific operations may need to be "
"completed before others can begin. To ensure operations are carried out in "
"the correct order, the **Manufacturing** app features a *work order "
"dependencies* setting. Enabling this setting allows for operations on a bill "
"of materials (BoM) to be blocked by other operations that should occur first."
msgstr ""
"Ved fremstilling af visse produkter kan specifikke operationer skulle "
"afsluttes, før andre kan begynde. For at sikre, at operationer udføres i den "
"korrekte rækkefølge, indeholder **Produktion**-appen en indstilling for "
"*arbejdsordreafhængigheder*. Aktivering af denne indstilling gør det muligt, "
"at operationer på en stykliste (BoM) kan blokeres af andre operationer, der "
"skal udføres først."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:15
msgid ""
"The *work order dependencies* setting is not enabled by default. To enable "
"it, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Configuration --> "
"Settings`. Then, enable the :guilabel:`Work Orders` setting, if it is not "
"already active."
msgstr ""
"Indstillingen *arbejdsordreafhængigheder* er ikke aktiveret som standard. "
"For at aktivere den, naviger til :menuselection:`Produktion-app --> "
"Konfiguration --> Indstillinger`. Aktiver derefter "
"indstillingen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer`, hvis den ikke allerede er aktiv."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:19
msgid ""
"After enabling the :guilabel:`Work Orders` setting, the :guilabel:`Work "
"Order Dependencies` setting appears below it. Enable :guilabel:`Work Order "
"Dependencies`, then click :guilabel:`Save` to confirm the changes."
msgstr ""
"Efter aktivering af indstillingen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer` vises "
"indstillingen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordreafhængigheder` nedenfor. "
"Aktivér :guilabel:`Arbejdsordreafhængigheder`, og klik derefter "
"på :guilabel:`Gem` for at bekræfte ændringerne."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:24
msgid "Add dependencies to BoM"
msgstr "Tilføj afhængigheder til stykliste"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:26
msgid ""
"Work order dependencies are configured on a product's |BOM|. To do so, "
"navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Products --> Bills of "
"Materials`, then select a |BOM|, or create a new one by "
"clicking :guilabel:`New`."
msgstr ""
"Arbejdsordreafhængigheder konfigureres på et produkts |BOM|. For at gøre "
"dette, naviger til :menuselection:`Produktion-app --> Produkter --> "
"Styklister`, vælg derefter en |BOM|, eller opret en ny ved at klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Ny`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:30
msgid ""
"On the |BOM|, open the *Miscellaneous* tab, then enable "
"the :guilabel:`Operation Dependencies` checkbox. The :guilabel:`Blocked By` "
"option becomes available under the :icon:`oi-settings-"
"adjust` :guilabel:`(settings)` menu of the *Operations* tab."
msgstr ""
"På |BOM| åbnes fanen *Diverse*, hvorefter "
"afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Operationsafhængigheder` aktiveres. "
"Indstillingen :guilabel:`Blokeret af` bliver tilgængelig under "
"menuen :icon:`oi-settings-adjust` :guilabel:`(indstillinger)` på fanen "
"*Operationer*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:None
msgid "The Operation Dependencies checkbox on the Miscellaneous tab of a BoM."
msgstr ""
"Afkrydsningsfeltet Operationsafhængigheder på fanen Diverse i en stykliste."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:37
msgid ""
"Open the *Operations* tab. Click the :icon:`oi-settings-"
"adjust` :guilabel:`(settings)` icon, then enable the :guilabel:`Blocked By` "
"checkbox. The :guilabel:`Blocked By` field appears for each operation in the "
"tab."
msgstr ""
"Åbn fanen *Operationer*. Klik på ikonet :icon:`oi-settings-"
"adjust` :guilabel:`(indstillinger)`, og aktivér derefter "
"afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Blokeret af`. Feltet :guilabel:`Blokeret af` "
"vises for hver operation på fanen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:None
msgid "The settings for the Operations tab on a BoM."
msgstr "Indstillingerne for fanen Operationer på en stykliste."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:44
msgid ""
"In the line of the operation that should be blocked by another operation, "
"click the :guilabel:`Blocked By` field. The *Open: Operations* pop-up window "
"opens. In the :guilabel:`Blocked By` field, select the blocking operation "
"that must be completed *before* the operation that is blocked."
msgstr ""
"I linjen for den operation, der skal blokeres af en anden operation, klikkes "
"på feltet :guilabel:`Blokeret af`. Pop op-vinduet *Åbn: Operationer* åbnes. "
"I feltet :guilabel:`Blokeret af` vælges den blokerende operation, der skal "
"fuldføres *før* den operation, der er blokeret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:None
msgid "The Blocked By drop-down field for an operation on a BoM."
msgstr "Rullefeltet Blokeret af for en operation på en stykliste."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:52
msgid ""
"Finally, save the |BOM| by clicking :icon:`fa-cloud-upload` :guilabel:`(Save "
"manually)`."
msgstr ""
"Til sidst gemmes |BOM| ved at klikke på :icon:`fa-cloud-"
"upload` :guilabel:`(Gem manuelt)`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:58
msgid "Plan work orders using dependencies"
msgstr "Planlæg arbejdsordrer ved hjælp af afhængigheder"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:60
msgid ""
"After work order dependencies are configured for a |BOM|, the "
"**Manufacturing** app can plan when work orders are scheduled based on those "
"dependencies. To plan the work orders for a manufacturing order, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Operations --> Manufacturing "
"Orders`."
msgstr ""
"Når arbejdsordreafhængigheder er konfigureret for en |BOM|, kan appen "
"**Produktion** planlægge, hvornår arbejdsordrer skal planlægges baseret på "
"disse afhængigheder. For at planlægge arbejdsordrerne for en "
"produktionsordre navigeres til :menuselection:`Produktion app --> "
"Operationer --> Produktionsordrer`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:64
msgid ""
"Next, select a manufacturing order for a product with work order "
"dependencies set on its |BOM|, or create a new manufacturing order by "
"clicking :guilabel:`New`. If a new manufacturing order is created, select a |"
"BOM| configured with work order dependencies from the :guilabel:`Bill of "
"Material` drop-down field, then click :guilabel:`Confirm`."
msgstr ""
"Vælg derefter en produktionsordre for et produkt med "
"arbejdsordreafhængigheder indstillet på dets |BOM|, eller opret en ny "
"produktionsordre ved at klikke på :guilabel:`Ny`. Hvis der oprettes en ny "
"produktionsordre, skal du vælge en |BOM| konfigureret med "
"arbejdsordreafhængigheder fra rullefeltet :guilabel:`Stykliste`, og derefter "
"klikke på :guilabel:`Bekræft`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:69
msgid ""
"After confirming the manufacturing order, open the *Work Orders* tab to view "
"the work orders required to complete it. Any work orders that are *not* "
"blocked by a different work order display a :guilabel:`To Do` tag in "
"the :guilabel:`Status` column."
msgstr ""
"Efter bekræftelse af produktionsordren åbnes fanen *Arbejdsordrer* for at se "
"de arbejdsordrer, der er nødvendige for at fuldføre den. Alle arbejdsordrer, "
"der *ikke* er blokeret af en anden arbejdsordre, viser et :guilabel:`At "
"gøre`-mærke i kolonnen :guilabel:`Status`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:73
msgid ""
"Work orders that are blocked by other work orders display "
"a :guilabel:`Blocked` tag instead. After the blocking work orders are "
"completed, the tag updates to :guilabel:`To Do`."
msgstr ""
"Arbejdsordrer, der er blokeret af andre arbejdsordrer, viser i stedet "
"et :guilabel:`Blokeret`-mærke. Når de blokerende arbejdsordrer er fuldført, "
"opdateres mærket til :guilabel:`At gøre`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:None
msgid "The status tags for work orders on a manufacturing order."
msgstr "Statusmærkerne for arbejdsordrer på en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:79
msgid ""
"To schedule the manufacturing order's work orders, click "
"the :guilabel:`Plan` button at the top of the page. After doing so, "
"the :guilabel:`Start` field for each work order on the *Work Orders* tab "
"populates with a scheduled start date and time. A blocked work order is "
"scheduled at the end of the time period specified in the :guilabel:`Expected "
"Duration` field of the work order that precedes it."
msgstr ""
"For at planlægge produktionsordrens arbejdsordrer klikkes på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Planlæg` øverst på siden. Efter dette udfyldes "
"feltet :guilabel:`Start` for hver arbejdsordre på fanen *Arbejdsordrer* med "
"en planlagt startdato og -tid. En blokeret arbejdsordre planlægges ved "
"slutningen af den tidsperiode, der er angivet i feltet :guilabel:`Forventet "
"varighed` for den arbejdsordre, der går forud for den."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:None
msgid ""
"The Scheduled Start Date field for work orders on a manufacturing order."
msgstr ""
"Feltet Planlagt starttidspunkt for arbejdsordrer på en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:88
msgid ""
"A manufacturing order is created for Product A. The manufacturing order has "
"two operations: Cut and Assemble. Each operation has an expected duration of "
"60 minutes, and the Assemble operation is blocked by the Cut operation."
msgstr ""
"Der oprettes en produktionsordre for produkt A. Produktionsordren har to "
"operationer: Skær og Saml. Hver operation har en forventet varighed på 60 "
"minutter, og operationen Saml er blokeret af operationen Skær."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:92
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Plan` button for the manufacturing order is clicked at 1:30 "
"pm, and the Cut operation is scheduled to begin immediately. Since the Cut "
"operation has an expected duration of 60 minutes, the Assemble operation is "
"scheduled to begin at 2:30 pm."
msgstr ""
"Knappen :guilabel:`Planlæg` for produktionsordren klikkes kl. 13.30, og "
"operationen Skær er planlagt til at begynde med det samme. Da operationen "
"Skær har en forventet varighed på 60 minutter, er operationen Saml planlagt "
"til at begynde kl. 14.30."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:97
msgid "Planning views"
msgstr "Planlægningsvisninger"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:99
msgid ""
"Two work order planning views are available to display a visual "
"representation of how work orders are planned:"
msgstr ""
"To arbejdsordreplanlægningsvisninger er tilgængelige for at vise en visuel "
"repræsentation af, hvordan arbejdsordrer planlægges:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:102
msgid ""
":menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Planning --> Planning by Production`"
msgstr ""
":menuselection:`Produktion app --> Planlægning --> Planlægning efter "
"produktion`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:103
msgid ""
":menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Planning --> Planning by Workcenter`"
msgstr ""
":menuselection:`Produktion app --> Planlægning --> Planlægning efter "
"arbejdscenter`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:105
msgid ""
"Both open a *Work Orders Planning* page. This page shows a timeline of all "
"the work orders scheduled for each operation."
msgstr ""
"Begge åbner en side med *Planlægning af arbejdsordrer*. Denne side viser en "
"tidslinje for alle de arbejdsordrer, der er planlagt for hver operation."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:108
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Planning by Production` is best used to view work orders grouped "
"by manufacturing order. This view is ideal for providing estimated delivery "
"times or determining if an order will be completed on schedule."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Planlægning efter produktion` bruges bedst til at se "
"arbejdsordrer grupperet efter produktionsordre. Denne visning er ideel til "
"at give estimerede leveringstider eller bestemme, om en ordre bliver "
"fuldført til tiden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:112
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Planning by Workcenter` is best used to view work orders grouped "
"by the work center at which they take place. This view can help identify "
"overloaded machines or bottlenecks in production."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Planlægning efter arbejdscenter` bruges bedst til at se "
"arbejdsordrer grupperet efter det arbejdscenter, hvor de finder sted. Denne "
"visning kan hjælpe med at identificere overbelastede maskiner eller "
"flaskehalse i produktionen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:115
msgid ""
"In both views, if one work order is blocked by the completion of another, "
"the work order that is blocked is shown as scheduled to start after the work "
"order that blocks it. In addition, a grey arrow connects the two work "
"orders, leading from the blocking operation to the blocked operation."
msgstr ""
"I begge visninger, hvis en arbejdsordre er blokeret af fuldførelsen af en "
"anden, vises den arbejdsordre, der er blokeret, som planlagt til at starte "
"efter den arbejdsordre, der blokerer den. Desuden forbinder en grå pil de to "
"arbejdsordrer, der fører fra den blokerende operation til den blokerede "
"operation."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:None
msgid ""
"The arrow connecting a blocked work order to the work order blocking it."
msgstr ""
"Pilen, der forbinder en blokeret arbejdsordre med den arbejdsordre, der "
"blokerer den."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:123
msgid "Rescheduling work orders"
msgstr "Omplanlægning af arbejdsordrer"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:125
msgid ""
"By default, linked work orders on the *Work Orders Planning* page can be "
"rescheduled automatically, ensuring that work orders cannot be moved out of "
"the order they are set in."
msgstr ""
"Som standard kan linkede arbejdsordrer på siden *Planlægning af "
"arbejdsordrer* omplanlægges automatisk, hvilket sikrer, at arbejdsordrer "
"ikke kan flyttes ud af den rækkefølge, de er angivet i."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:128
msgid ""
"Work orders can be scheduled with a buffer, or the time gap between "
"consecutive work orders. By default, this view is set to :guilabel:`Auto-"
"Reschedule (Keep Buffer)`. When the buffer is kept, the work orders are "
"moved, and the gap is maintained. If the buffer is important, use this "
"setting."
msgstr ""
"Arbejdsordrer kan planlægges med en buffer eller tidsgabet mellem på "
"hinanden følgende arbejdsordrer. Som standard er denne visning indstillet "
"til :guilabel:`Auto-omplanlæg (behold buffer)`. Når bufferen bevares, "
"flyttes arbejdsordrerne, og gabet bevares. Hvis bufferen er vigtig, skal "
"denne indstilling bruges."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:133
msgid "A manufacturing order for a table has two work orders:"
msgstr "En produktionsordre for et bord har to arbejdsordrer:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:135
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:166
msgid "Apply finish"
msgstr "Påfør finish"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:136
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:165
msgid "Assemble"
msgstr "Samle"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:138
msgid ""
"The first work order has a 24-hour buffer built in to allow for the finish "
"to cure. When a work order is rescheduled, the 24-hour buffer is maintained."
msgstr ""
"Den første arbejdsordre har en indbygget buffer på 24 timer for at give "
"finish tid til at hærde. Når en arbejdsordre omplanlægges, bibeholdes "
"bufferen på 24 timer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:141
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can use the :guilabel:`Auto-Reschedule (Use Buffer)` "
"setting by selecting it from the :guilabel:`Auto-Reschedule (Keep Buffer)` "
"drop-down menu. Select this option if the gaps were accidental and meeting a "
"due date is a priority."
msgstr ""
"Alternativt kan du bruge indstillingen :guilabel:`Auto-Reschedule (Use "
"Buffer)` ved at vælge den fra rullemenuen :guilabel:`Auto-Reschedule (Keep "
"Buffer)`. Vælg denne mulighed, hvis hullerne var utilsigtede, og det er en "
"prioritet at overholde en deadline."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:145
msgid ""
"For full control over rescheduling work orders, select :guilabel:`Manual "
"Reschedule`."
msgstr ""
"For fuld kontrol over omplanlægning af arbejdsordrer skal du "
"vælge :guilabel:`Manual Reschedule`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:148
msgid ""
"Unless there is a specific reason to compress the buffer, it is important to "
"maintain the :guilabel:`Auto-Reschedule (Keep Buffer)` setting. Other work "
"orders upstream from the work order being rescheduled could run late and "
"cause issues with the production schedule."
msgstr ""
"Medmindre der er en specifik grund til at komprimere bufferen, er det "
"vigtigt at bibeholde indstillingen :guilabel:`Auto-Reschedule (Keep "
"Buffer)`. Andre arbejdsordrer længere oppe i produktionen end den "
"arbejdsordre, der omplanlægges, kan løbe forsinket og forårsage problemer "
"med produktionsplanen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:153
msgid "Resolving inconsistencies"
msgstr "Løsning af uoverensstemmelser"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:155
msgid ""
"When the *Work Orders Planning* page is set to manually reschedule work "
"orders, it is possible to introduce inconsistencies in the manufacturing "
"order."
msgstr ""
"Når siden *Work Orders Planning* er indstillet til manuelt at omplanlægge "
"arbejdsordrer, er det muligt at indføre uoverensstemmelser i "
"produktionsordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:158
msgid ""
"The arrows on the *Work Orders Planning* page can also point out "
"inconsistencies in the manufacturing order and how to correct them. When the "
"arrow changes color, an inconsistency has been introduced."
msgstr ""
"Pilene på siden *Work Orders Planning* kan også påpege uoverensstemmelser i "
"produktionsordren og hvordan de rettes. Når pilen skifter farve, er der "
"indført en uoverensstemmelse."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:163
msgid "A workshop is manufacturing a table in three work orders:"
msgstr "Et værksted fremstiller et bord i tre arbejdsordrer:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:167
msgid "Dry"
msgstr "Tørre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:169
msgid ""
"If the third work order is moved before the second work order, the third "
"work order and the arrow pointing to it turn red to indicate that the "
"planned schedule violates the defined work order dependency."
msgstr ""
"Hvis den tredje arbejdsordre flyttes før den anden arbejdsordre, bliver den "
"tredje arbejdsordre og pilen, der peger på den, rød for at indikere, at den "
"planlagte tidsplan overtræder den definerede arbejdsordreafhængighed."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:0
msgid "A red line appears between two work orders."
msgstr "En rød linje vises mellem to arbejdsordrer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:176
msgid ""
"When hovering over the connecting line, an **X** (cancel) button appears. "
"When clicking this button, Odoo assumes the dependencies no longer apply due "
"to an exception, and the link between the steps is broken. To remove the "
"dependency, hover over the connecting line. Click the **X** (cancel) button "
"that appears, and the arrow between the two work orders disappears."
msgstr ""
"Når man holder musen over den forbindende linje, vises en **X**-knap "
"(annuller). Når man klikker på denne knap, antager Odoo, at afhængighederne "
"ikke længere gælder på grund af en undtagelse, og linket mellem trinene "
"brydes. For at fjerne afhængigheden skal du holde musen over den forbindende "
"linje. Klik på **X**-knappen (annuller), der vises, og pilen mellem de to "
"arbejdsordrer forsvinder."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:181
msgid ""
"To resolve the scheduling conflict and keep the dependency, select the red "
"work order. Click the :guilabel:`Edit` button, and the *Open* window "
"appears. Click the red :icon:`fa-exclamation-"
"triangle` :guilabel:`(exclamation triangle)` icon next to "
"the :guilabel:`Start Date`, and the *Scheduling Information* pop-up window "
"appears."
msgstr ""
"For at løse planlægningskonflikten og bevare afhængigheden skal du vælge den "
"røde arbejdsordre. Klik på knappen :guilabel:`Edit`, og vinduet *Open* "
"vises. Klik på det røde :icon:`fa-exclamation-"
"triangle` :guilabel:`(advarseltrekant)` ikon ved siden af :guilabel:`Start "
"Date`, og pop op-vinduet *Scheduling Information* vises."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:None
msgid "Click the Replan button to reschedule the inconsistent work order."
msgstr ""
"Klik på knappen Replan for at omplanlægge den uoverensstemmende arbejdsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies.rst:189
msgid ""
"Click the :guilabel:`Replan` button, then click :guilabel:`Save` to save the "
"changes to the work order. The work order is rescheduled after the previous "
"work order in a way that maintains the work order dependency."
msgstr ""
"Klik på knappen :guilabel:`Replan`, og klik derefter på :guilabel:`Save` for "
"at gemme ændringerne i arbejdsordren. Arbejdsordren omplanlægges efter den "
"forrige arbejdsordre på en måde, der bibeholder arbejdsordreafhængigheden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup.rst:5
msgid "Basic setup"
msgstr "Grundlæggende opsætning"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:3
msgid "Bill of materials"
msgstr "Stykliste"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:9
msgid ""
"A *bill of materials* (or *BoM* for short) documents specific components, "
"along with their respective quantities, that are needed to produce or repair "
"a product. In Odoo, |BoMs| serve as blueprints for manufactured goods and "
"kits, and often include production operations and step-by-step guidelines, "
"as well."
msgstr ""
"En *stykliste* (eller *BoM* som forkortelse) dokumenterer specifikke "
"komponenter sammen med deres respektive mængder, som er nødvendige for at "
"producere eller reparere et produkt. I Odoo fungerer |BoMs| som tegninger "
"for fremstillede varer og sæt og inkluderer ofte også produktionsoperationer "
"og trin-for-trin vejledninger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:17
msgid "BoM setup"
msgstr "Opsætning af stykliste"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:19
msgid ""
"To create a |BOM|, go to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Products --> "
"Bills of Materials` and click :guilabel:`New`."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette en |BOM|, gå til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Produkter --> "
"Styklister` og klik på :guilabel:`Ny`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:22
msgid ""
"Next, set the :guilabel:`BoM Type` to :guilabel:`Manufacture this Product`."
msgstr ""
"Indstil derefter :guilabel:`Styklistetype` til :guilabel:`Fremstil dette "
"produkt`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:24
msgid ""
"Then, specify :ref:`required components <manufacturing/basic_setup/setup-"
"components>` and, if necessary, define any :ref:`manufacturing operations "
"<manufacturing/basic_setup/setup-operations>`."
msgstr ""
"Angiv derefter :ref:`påkrævede komponenter <manufacturing/basic_setup/setup-"
"components>` og definer om nødvendigt "
"eventuelle :ref:`produktionsoperationer <manufacturing/basic_setup/setup-"
"operations>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:28
msgid ""
"Individual |BOMs| can also be quickly accessed or created by clicking "
"the :guilabel:`Bill of Materials` smart button on any product form, as "
"accessible through the *Sales*, *Inventory*, and *Manufacturing* apps, as "
"well as through any internal links where a product is referenced (such as in "
"a field or a line item)."
msgstr ""
"Individuelle |BOMs| kan også hurtigt tilgås eller oprettes ved at klikke på "
"smartknappen :guilabel:`Stykliste` på enhver produktformular, som er "
"tilgængelig via appene *Salg*, *Lager* og *Produktion*, samt via eventuelle "
"interne links, hvor et produkt er refereret (såsom i et felt eller en "
"linjepost)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:37
msgid "Show BoM for a product, with components listed."
msgstr "Vis stykliste for et produkt med komponenter anført."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:37
msgid "BoM for `Drawer`, displaying the **Components** tab."
msgstr "Stykliste for `Skuffe`, der viser fanen **Komponenter**."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:40
msgid ":doc:`../advanced_configuration/kit_shipping`"
msgstr ":doc:`../advanced_configuration/kit_shipping`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:41
msgid ":doc:`../subcontracting/subcontracting_basic`"
msgstr ":doc:`../subcontracting/subcontracting_basic`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:46
msgid "Components"
msgstr "Komponenter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:48
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Components` tab of a |BOM|, specify components used to "
"manufacture the product by clicking :guilabel:`Add a line`. From "
"the :guilabel:`Components` drop-down menu, select from existing products or "
"create a new product by typing the name and selecting either "
"the :guilabel:`Create \" \"` option to quickly add the line item, or "
"the :guilabel:`Create and edit...` option to add the component and continue "
"to its configuration form."
msgstr ""
"I fanen :guilabel:`Komponenter` i en |BOM|, angiv komponenter, der bruges "
"til at fremstille produktet, ved at klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje`. "
"Fra rullemenuen :guilabel:`Komponenter`, vælg fra eksisterende produkter "
"eller opret et nyt produkt ved at skrive navnet og vælge enten "
"indstillingen :guilabel:`Opret \" \"` for hurtigt at tilføje linjeposten, "
"eller indstillingen :guilabel:`Opret og rediger...` for at tilføje "
"komponenten og fortsætte til dens konfigurationsformular."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:None
msgid "Add a component by selecting it from the drop-down menu."
msgstr "Tilføj en komponent ved at vælge den fra rullemenuen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:58
msgid ""
"Optionally, access additional fields by clicking the :icon:`oi-settings-"
"adjust` :guilabel:`(settings adjust)` icon to the far-right of "
"the :guilabel:`Components` tab. Tick the checkboxes for the following "
"features to enable these columns:"
msgstr ""
"Valgfrit kan du få adgang til yderligere felter ved at klikke på "
"ikonet :icon:`oi-settings-adjust` :guilabel:`(indstillinger justér)` yderst "
"til højre i fanen :guilabel:`Komponenter`. Markér afkrydsningsfelterne for "
"følgende funktioner for at aktivere disse kolonner:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:62
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Apply on Variants`: specify which :doc:`product variant <../"
"advanced_configuration/product_variants>` each component is used in. When "
"the field is left blank, the component is used in all product variants."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Anvend på varianter`: angiv, hvilken :doc:`produktvariant <../"
"advanced_configuration/product_variants>` hver komponent bruges i. Når "
"feltet efterlades tomt, bruges komponenten i alle produktvarianter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:68
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Consumed in Operation`: specify the operation using the "
"component. Useful for determining :ref:`manufacturing readiness "
"<manufacturing/basic_setup/manufacturing-readiness>`."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Forbrugt i operation`: angiv operationen, der bruger komponenten. "
"Nyttigt til at bestemme :ref:`produktionsparathed <manufacturing/basic_setup/"
"manufacturing-readiness>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:70
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Manual Consumption`: tick the checkbox to force operators to "
"check the :guilabel:`Consumed` checkbox on a manufacturing order (MO)."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Manuel forbrug`: markér afkrydsningsfeltet for at tvinge "
"operatører til at markere afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Forbrugt` på en "
"produktionsordre (MO)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:0
msgid "Show a manufacturing order, highlighting the *Consumed* field."
msgstr "Vis en produktionsordre, der fremhæver feltet *Forbrugt*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:77
msgid ""
"Not doing so triggers the :guilabel:`Consumption Warning` error message, "
"where the consumed component quantity must be manually inputted. Otherwise, "
"the operation cannot be completed."
msgstr ""
"Hvis dette ikke gøres, udløses fejlmeddelelsen :guilabel:`Forbrugsadvarsel`, "
"hvor den forbrugte komponentmængde skal indtastes manuelt. Ellers kan "
"operationen ikke gennemføres."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:0
msgid "Show the consumption warning error message."
msgstr "Vis advarselsmeddelelse om forbrugsfejl."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:89
msgid ""
"Add an *operation* to a |BOM| to specify instructions for production and "
"register time spent on an operation. To use this feature, first enable the "
"*Work Orders* feature by going to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> "
"Configuration --> Settings`. In the :guilabel:`Operations` section, tick "
"the :guilabel:`Work Orders` checkbox to enable the feature."
msgstr ""
"Tilføj en *operation* til en |BOM| for at angive instruktioner til "
"produktion og registrere tid brugt på en operation. For at bruge denne "
"funktion skal du først aktivere funktionen *Arbejdsordrer* ved at gå "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion-app --> Konfiguration --> Indstillinger`. I "
"sektionen :guilabel:`Operationer` skal du markere "
"afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer` for at aktivere funktionen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:95
msgid ":doc:`../advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies`"
msgstr ":doc:`../advanced_configuration/work_order_dependencies`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:None
msgid "\"Work Orders\" feature in the Settings page."
msgstr "Funktionen \"Arbejdsordrer\" på siden Indstillinger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:101
msgid ""
"Next, navigate to the |BOM| by going to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --"
"> Products --> Bill of Materials` and selecting the desired |BOM|. To add a "
"new operation, go to the :guilabel:`Operations` tab, and "
"click :guilabel:`Add a line`."
msgstr ""
"Gå derefter til |BOM| ved at gå til :menuselection:`Produktion-app --> "
"Produkter --> Stykliste` og vælge den ønskede |BOM|. For at tilføje en ny "
"operation skal du gå til fanen :guilabel:`Operationer` og klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:105
msgid ""
"Doing so opens the :guilabel:`Create Operations` pop-up window, where the "
"various fields of the operation are configured:"
msgstr ""
"Dette åbner pop-up-vinduet :guilabel:`Opret operationer`, hvor de "
"forskellige felter i operationen konfigureres:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:108
msgid ":guilabel:`Operation`: name of the operation."
msgstr ":guilabel:`Operation`: navn på operationen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:109
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Work Center`: select existing locations to perform the operation, "
"or create a new work center by typing the name and selecting "
"the :guilabel:`Create \" \"` option."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Arbejdscenter`: vælg eksisterende steder til at udføre "
"operationen, eller opret et nyt arbejdscenter ved at indtaste navnet og "
"vælge indstillingen :guilabel:`Opret \" \"`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:111
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Apply on Variants`: specify if this operation is only available "
"for certain product variants. If the operation applies to all product "
"variants, leave this field blank."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Anvend på varianter`: angiv om denne operation kun er tilgængelig "
"for bestemte produktvarianter. Hvis operationen gælder for alle "
"produktvarianter, skal du lade dette felt stå tomt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:115
msgid ""
":doc:`Configuring BoMs for product variants <../advanced_configuration/"
"product_variants>`"
msgstr ""
":doc:`Konfiguration af styklister til produktvarianter <../"
"advanced_configuration/product_variants>`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:117
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Duration Computation`: choose how time spent on the operation is "
"tracked. Opt for :guilabel:`Compute based on tracked time` to use the "
"operation's time tracker or :guilabel:`Set duration manually` if operators "
"can record and modify time themselves."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Varighedsberegning`: vælg hvordan tid brugt på operationen "
"spores. Vælg :guilabel:`Beregn baseret på sporet tid` for at bruge "
"operationens tidssporing eller :guilabel:`Indstil varighed manuelt`, hvis "
"operatører selv kan registrere og ændre tid."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:121
msgid ""
"Choosing the :guilabel:`Compute based on tracked time` option enables "
"the :guilabel:`Based on last __ work orders` option, which automatically "
"estimates the time to complete this operation based on the last few "
"operations. Choosing :guilabel:`Set duration manually` enables "
"the :guilabel:`Default Duration` field instead."
msgstr ""
"Valg af indstillingen :guilabel:`Beregn baseret på sporet tid` aktiverer "
"indstillingen :guilabel:`Baseret på sidste __ arbejdsordrer`, som automatisk "
"estimerer tiden til at fuldføre denne operation baseret på de sidste par "
"operationer. Valg af :guilabel:`Indstil varighed manuelt` aktiverer i stedet "
"feltet :guilabel:`Standardvarighed`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:125
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Default Duration`: estimated amount of time to complete the "
"operation; used for `planning manufacturing orders <https://www.youtube.com/"
"watch?v=TK55jIq00pc>`_ and determining `work center availability <https://"
"www.youtube.com/watch?v=3YwFlD97Bio>`_."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Standardvarighed`: estimeret tid til at fuldføre operationen; "
"bruges til `planlægning af produktionsordrer <https://www.youtube.com/watch?"
"v=TK55jIq00pc>`_ og bestemmelse af `arbejdscentertilgængelighed <https://"
"www.youtube.com/watch?v=3YwFlD97Bio>`_."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:128
msgid ":guilabel:`Company`: specify the company the |BOM| is available in."
msgstr ":guilabel:`Virksomhed`: angiv virksomheden som |BOM| er tilgængelig i."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:130
msgid ""
"Include operation details in the :guilabel:`Work Sheet` tab. "
"Choose :guilabel:`PDF` to attach a file or :guilabel:`Google Slide` with "
"*public* access to share a link. Select :guilabel:`Text` to type "
"instructions in the :guilabel:`Description` text field."
msgstr ""
"Inkluder operationsdetaljer i fanen :guilabel:`Arbejdsark`. "
"Vælg :guilabel:`PDF` for at vedhæfte en fil eller :guilabel:`Google Slide` "
"med *offentlig* adgang for at dele et link. Vælg :guilabel:`Tekst` for at "
"skrive instruktioner i tekstfeltet :guilabel:`Beskrivelse`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:135
msgid ""
"Type `/` for a list of formatting options and features, including ChatGPT."
msgstr ""
"Skriv `/` for en liste over formateringsmuligheder og funktioner, inklusive "
"ChatGPT."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:0
msgid "Show ChatGPT feature to generate instructions for a work order."
msgstr ""
"Vis ChatGPT-funktionen til at generere instruktioner til en arbejdsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:None
msgid "Fill out the Create Operations pop-up window."
msgstr "Udfyld pop-op-vinduet Opret operationer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:145
msgid ""
"Finally, click :guilabel:`Save \\& Close` to close the pop-up window. To add "
"more operations, click :guilabel:`Save & New` and repeat the same steps "
"above to configure another operation."
msgstr ""
"Klik til sidst på :guilabel:`Gem \\& luk` for at lukke pop-op-vinduet. For "
"at tilføje flere operationer skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Gem \\& ny` og "
"gentage de samme trin ovenfor for at konfigurere en anden operation."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:149
msgid ""
"Each operation is unique, as it is always exclusively linked to one |BOM|."
msgstr ""
"Hver operation er unik, da den altid udelukkende er knyttet til én |BOM|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:152
msgid ""
"After creating an operation, click the :guilabel:`Copy Existing Operations` "
"button to choose an operation to duplicate."
msgstr ""
"Po vytvoření operace klikněte na tlačítko :guilabel:`Kopírovat existující "
"operace` a vyberte operaci k duplikování."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:0
msgid ""
"Show Operation tab, highlighting the \"Copy Existing Operations\" field."
msgstr ""
"Zobrazení karty Operace se zvýrazněným polem „Kopírovat existující operace\"."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:160
msgid "Instructions"
msgstr "Instruktioner"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:163
msgid ""
"To add detailed instructions to operations, the *Quality* app must be "
"installed."
msgstr ""
"Pro přidání podrobných pokynů k operacím musí být nainstalována aplikace "
"*Kvalitet*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:165
msgid ""
"Add specific instructions to an existing operation by clicking the "
"operation's :icon:`fa-list-ul` :guilabel:`(list)` icon in "
"the :guilabel:`Instructions` column. The number in "
"the :guilabel:`Instructions` column shows the number of existing detailed "
"instructions there are for the operation."
msgstr ""
"Přidejte konkrétní pokyny k existující operaci kliknutím na ikonu :icon:`fa-"
"list-ul` :guilabel:`(seznam)` operace ve sloupci :guilabel:`Pokyny`. Číslo "
"ve sloupci :guilabel:`Pokyny` zobrazuje počet existujících podrobných pokynů "
"pro danou operaci."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:None
msgid "Show the Instructions column, and list icon."
msgstr "Zobrazení sloupce Pokyny a ikony seznamu."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:174
msgid ""
"On the :guilabel:`Steps` dashboard, click :guilabel:`New` to open a blank "
"quality control point form where the new manufacturing step can be created. "
"Here, give the specific instruction a :guilabel:`Title` and set "
"the :guilabel:`Type` to :guilabel:`Instructions`. In "
"the :guilabel:`Instructions` tab of the form, write out the directions for "
"the step in the operation."
msgstr ""
"Na dashboardu :guilabel:`Kroky` klikněte na :guilabel:`Nový` a otevřete "
"prázdný formulář kontrolního bodu kvality, kde lze vytvořit nový výrobní "
"krok. Zde zadejte konkrétnímu pokynu :guilabel:`Název` a "
"nastavte :guilabel:`Typ` na :guilabel:`Pokyny`. Na kartě :guilabel:`Pokyny` "
"formuláře vypište směrnice pro krok v operaci."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:180
msgid ""
"Further customizations can be made here on this form, beyond ordinary "
"instructions, to also include specific types of quality control points that "
"carry specific (or complex) conditions. For more details about quality "
"control points refer the :doc:`Instruction check <../../quality/"
"quality_check_types/instructions_check>` documentation."
msgstr ""
"Další přizpůsobení lze provést v tomto formuláři nad rámec běžných pokynů, "
"aby zahrnovaly i konkrétní typy kontrolních bodů kvality s konkrétními (nebo "
"složitými) podmínkami. Další podrobnosti o kontrolních bodech kvality "
"najdete v dokumentaci :doc:`Kontrola pokynů <../../quality/"
"quality_check_types/instructions_check>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:None
msgid "Show the page to add a quality check."
msgstr "Zobrazení stránky pro přidání kontroly kvality."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:190
msgid "Miscellaneous"
msgstr "Diverse"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:192
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Miscellaneous` tab contains more |BoM| configurations to "
"customize procurement, calculate costs, and define how components are "
"consumed."
msgstr ""
"Karta :guilabel:`Různé` obsahuje další konfigurace |BoM|, které umožňují "
"přizpůsobit nákup, vypočítat náklady a definovat způsob spotřeby komponent."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:197
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Manufacturing Readiness`: choosing :guilabel:`When components for "
"the 1st operation are available` shows the :guilabel:`Component Status` as a "
"**green** :guilabel:`Not Available`, when only the components that are "
"consumed in the first operation are in stock. This indicates that although "
"not all components are available, operators can at least begin with the "
"first operation. Choosing :guilabel:`When all components are available` "
"displays a **red** :guilabel:`Not Available` component status unless all "
"components are in available."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Připravenost k výrobě`: výběr možnosti :guilabel:`Když jsou k "
"dispozici komponenty pro 1. operaci` zobrazí :guilabel:`Stav komponent` jako "
"**zelený** :guilabel:`Není k dispozici`, když jsou na skladě pouze "
"komponenty spotřebované v první operaci. To znamená, že ačkoli nejsou k "
"dispozici všechny komponenty, operátoři mohou alespoň začít s první operací. "
"Výběr možnosti :guilabel:`Když jsou k dispozici všechny komponenty` zobrazí "
"**červený** stav komponenty :guilabel:`Není k dispozici`, pokud nejsou k "
"dispozici všechny komponenty."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:205
msgid ""
"Specify which operation consumes each component on the |BoM| in "
"the :ref:`Manual Consumption field <manufacturing/basic_setup/consumed-in-"
"operation>`."
msgstr ""
"Určete, která operace spotřebovává každou komponentu v |BoM| v :ref:`poli "
"Ruční spotřeba <manufacturing/basic_setup/consumed-in-operation>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:0
msgid "Show the *Component Status* field on the manufacturing order dashboard."
msgstr "Zobrazení pole *Stav komponent* na dashboardu výrobní zakázky."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:212
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Version`: displays the current |BoM| version, visible with the "
"Odoo *PLM* app installed for managing |BoM| changes."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Verze`: zobrazí aktuální verzi |BoM|, která je viditelná s "
"nainstalovanou aplikací Odoo *PLM* pro správu změn |BoM|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:214
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Flexible Consumption`: specifies if components used can deviate "
"from the quantity defined on the |BoM|. Choose :guilabel:`Blocked` if "
"operators **must** adhere strictly to the |BoM| quantity. Otherwise, "
"choose :guilabel:`Allowed` or :guilabel:`Allowed with Warning`."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Flexibilní spotřeba`: určuje, zda použité komponenty mohou "
"odchylovat od množství definovaného v |BoM|. Vyberte :guilabel:`Blokováno`, "
"pokud se operátoři **musí** striktně držet množství |BoM|. Jinak "
"vyberte :guilabel:`Povoleno` nebo :guilabel:`Povoleno s varováním`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:217
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Routing`: select the preferred warehouse's manufacturing "
"operation type for products produced in multiple warehouses. If left blank, "
"this warehouse's `Manufacturing` operation type is used by default."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Směrování`: vyberte preferovaný typ výrobní operace skladu pro "
"produkty vyráběné ve více skladech. Pokud je ponecháno prázdné, použije se "
"ve výchozím nastavení typ operace `Výroba` tohoto skladu."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:220
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Analytic Distribution`: select pre-created :doc:`analytic "
"distribution models <../../../finance/accounting/reporting/"
"analytic_accounting>` from the list to automatically record the cost of "
"manufacturing products in the chosen journal."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Analytická distribuce`: vyberte ze seznamu předem "
"vytvořené :doc:`modely analytické distribuce <../../../finance/accounting/"
"reporting/analytic_accounting>`, abyste automaticky zaznamenali náklady na "
"výrobu produktů do vybraného deníku."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:223
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Manuf Lead Time`: define the number of days needed to complete a |"
"MO| from the date of confirmation."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Dodací lhůta výroby`: definujte počet dní potřebných k dokončení |"
"MO| od data potvrzení."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:225
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Days to prepare Manufacturing Order`: number of days needed to "
"replenish components, or manufacture sub-assemblies of the product."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Počet dní na přípravu výrobní zakázky`: počet dní potřebných k "
"doplnění komponent nebo výrobě podsestav produktu."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:229
msgid ""
":doc:`Analytic distribution <../../../finance/accounting/reporting/"
"analytic_accounting>`"
msgstr ""
":doc:`Analytická distribuce <../../../finance/accounting/reporting/"
"analytic_accounting>`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:230
msgid ""
":doc:`Lead times <../../inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/"
"lead_times>`"
msgstr ""
":doc:`Dodací lhůty <../../inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/"
"lead_times>`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:None
msgid "Show the *Miscellaneous* tab of the BoM."
msgstr "Vis fanen *Diverse* i styklisten."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:237
msgid "Add by-products to BoMs"
msgstr "Tilføj biprodukter til styklister"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:239
msgid ""
"A *by-product* is a residual product that is created during production in "
"addition to the main product of a |BOM|. Unlike the primary product, there "
"can be more than one by-product on a |BOM|."
msgstr ""
"Et *biprodukt* er et restprodukt, der opstår under produktionen ud over "
"hovedproduktet i en |BOM|. I modsætning til hovedproduktet kan der være mere "
"end ét biprodukt på en |BOM|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:242
msgid ""
"To add by-products to a |BOM|, first enable the *By-Products* feature "
"in :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Configuration --> Settings`. In "
"the :guilabel:`Operations` section, tick the checkbox for :guilabel:`By-"
"Products` to enable the feature."
msgstr ""
"For at tilføje biprodukter til en |BOM| skal du først aktivere funktionen "
"*Biprodukter* i :menuselection:`Produktion --> Konfiguration --> "
"Indstillinger`. I afsnittet :guilabel:`Operationer` skal du markere "
"afkrydsningsfeltet for :guilabel:`Biprodukter` for at aktivere funktionen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:None
msgid "\"By Products\" feature in the settings page."
msgstr "Funktionen \"Biprodukter\" på indstillingssiden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:250
msgid ""
"Once the feature is enabled, add by-products to a |BOM| by clicking "
"the :guilabel:`By-products` tab. Click :guilabel:`Add a line`, and fill in "
"the :guilabel:`By-product`, :guilabel:`Quantity`, and :guilabel:`Unit of "
"Measure`. Optionally, specify a :guilabel:`Produced in Operation` for the by-"
"product."
msgstr ""
"Når funktionen er aktiveret, tilføjes biprodukter til en |BOM| ved at klikke "
"på fanen :guilabel:`Biprodukter`. Klik på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje`, og "
"udfyld :guilabel:`Biprodukt`, :guilabel:`Antal` og :guilabel:`Måleenhed`. Du "
"kan eventuelt angive en :guilabel:`Produceret i operation` for biproduktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:256
msgid ""
"The by-product, `Mush`, is created in the `Grind grapes` operation when "
"producing `Red Wine`."
msgstr ""
"Biproduktet `Mush` oprettes i operationen `Grind grapes`, når der produceres "
"`Red Wine`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/bill_configuration.rst:0
msgid "Show sample by-product in the BoM."
msgstr "Vis eksempel på biprodukt i styklisten."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:5
msgid "Manufacturing product configuration"
msgstr "Konfiguration af produktionsprodukt"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:7
msgid ""
"Manufacturing products can be configured with lots or serial numbers "
"for :doc:`tracking <../../inventory/product_management/product_tracking>`, "
"and a bill of materials (BoM) for :doc:`replenishment <../../inventory/"
"warehouses_storage/replenishment/mto>`."
msgstr ""
"Produktionsprodukter kan konfigureres med lot- eller serienumre "
"til :doc:`sporing <../../inventory/product_management/product_tracking>` og "
"en stykliste (BoM) til :doc:`genopfyldning <../../inventory/"
"warehouses_storage/replenishment/mto>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:16
msgid ""
"To optionally :doc:`assign lots or serial numbers <../../inventory/"
"product_management/product_tracking>` to newly manufactured products, go "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Products --> Products`. Then, select an "
"existing product, or create a new one by clicking :guilabel:`New`. Go to "
"the :guilabel:`Inventory` tab, and open the :guilabel:`General Information` "
"tab. In the :guilabel:`Track Inventory` field, select :guilabel:`By Unique "
"Serial Number` or :guilabel:`By Lots`."
msgstr ""
"For eventuelt at :doc:`tildele lot- eller serienumre <../../inventory/"
"product_management/product_tracking>` til nyproducerede produkter skal du gå "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Produkter --> Produkter`. Vælg derefter "
"et eksisterende produkt, eller opret et nyt ved at klikke på :guilabel:`Ny`. "
"Gå til fanen :guilabel:`Lager` og åbn fanen :guilabel:`Generelle "
"oplysninger`. Vælg :guilabel:`Efter entydigt serienummer` "
"eller :guilabel:`Efter lot` i feltet :guilabel:`Spor lager`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:23
msgid ""
"Doing so enables the :guilabel:`Lot/Serial Number` field on a manufacturing "
"order, or the :guilabel:`Register Production` instruction on a work order "
"card in the **Shop Floor** app."
msgstr ""
"Dette aktiverer feltet :guilabel:`Lot-/serienummer` på en produktionsordre "
"eller instruktionen :guilabel:`Registrer produktion` på et arbejdsordrekort "
"i **Værksted**-appen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:29
msgid "\"Lot/Serial Number\" field on the MO."
msgstr "Feltet \"Lot/serienummer\" på produktionsordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:29
msgid "**Lot/Serial Number** field on the MO."
msgstr "Feltet **Lot/serienummer** på produktionsordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:34
msgid ""
"**Register Production** option to generate lot/serial number on a work order "
"card."
msgstr ""
"Indstillingen **Registrer produktion** til at generere lot/serienummer på et "
"arbejdsordrekort."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:39
msgid "Configure a bill of materials (BoM)"
msgstr "Konfigurere en stykliste"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:41
msgid ""
"Next, a |BOM| must be configured for the product so Odoo knows how it is "
"manufactured. A |BOM| is a list of the components and operations required to "
"manufacture a product."
msgstr ""
"Dernæst skal der konfigureres en |BOM| for produktet, så Odoo ved, hvordan "
"det fremstilles. En |BOM| er en liste over de komponenter og operationer, "
"der kræves for at fremstille et produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:44
msgid ""
"To create a |BOM| for a specific product, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Products --> Products`, then select the "
"product. On the product page, click the :guilabel:`Bill of Materials` smart "
"button at the top of the page, then select :guilabel:`New` to configure a "
"new |BOM|."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette en |BOM| for et bestemt produkt skal du gå "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Produkter --> Produkter` og vælge "
"produktet. På produktsiden skal du klikke på "
"smartknappen :guilabel:`Stykliste` øverst på siden og derefter "
"vælge :guilabel:`Ny` for at konfigurere en ny |BOM|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:None
msgid "The Bill of Materials smart button on a product page."
msgstr "Smartknappen Stykliste på en produktside."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:51
msgid ""
"On the |BOM|, the :guilabel:`Product` field auto-populates with the product. "
"In the :guilabel:`Quantity` field, specify the number of units that the BoM "
"produces."
msgstr ""
"På |BOM| udfyldes feltet :guilabel:`Produkt` automatisk med produktet. I "
"feltet :guilabel:`Antal` skal du angive antallet af enheder, som styklisten "
"producerer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:54
msgid ""
"Add a component to the |BOM| by selecting the :guilabel:`Components` tab and "
"clicking :guilabel:`Add a line`. Select a component from "
"the :guilabel:`Component` drop-down menu, then enter the quantity in "
"the :guilabel:`Quantity` field. Continue adding components on new lines "
"until all components have been added."
msgstr ""
"Tilføj en komponent til |BOM| ved at vælge fanen :guilabel:`Komponenter` og "
"klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje`. Vælg en komponent fra "
"rullemenuen :guilabel:`Komponent`, og angiv derefter antallet i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Antal`. Fortsæt med at tilføje komponenter på nye linjer, "
"indtil alle komponenter er blevet tilføjet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:None
msgid "The Components tab on a bill of materials."
msgstr "Fanen Komponenter på en stykliste."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:62
msgid ""
"Next, select the :guilabel:`Operations` tab. Click :guilabel:`Add a line` "
"and a :guilabel:`Create Operations` pop-up window appears. In "
"the :guilabel:`Operation` field, specify the name of the operation being "
"added (e.g. Assemble, Cut, etc.). Select the work center where the operation "
"will be carried out from the :guilabel:`Work Center` drop-down menu. "
"Finally, click :guilabel:`Save & Close` to finish adding operations, "
"or :guilabel:`Save & New` to add more."
msgstr ""
"Vælg derefter fanen :guilabel:`Operationer`. Klik på :guilabel:`Tilføj en "
"linje`, og et pop op-vindue :guilabel:`Opret operationer` vises. I "
"feltet :guilabel:`Operation` skal du angive navnet på den operation, der "
"tilføjes (f.eks. Samle, Skære osv.). Vælg det arbejdscenter, hvor "
"operationen skal udføres, fra rullemenuen :guilabel:`Arbejdscenter`. Klik "
"til sidst på :guilabel:`Gem og luk` for at afslutte tilføjelse af "
"operationer, eller :guilabel:`Gem og ny` for at tilføje flere."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:69
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Operations` tab only appears if the :guilabel:`Work Orders` "
"setting is enabled. To do so, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> "
"Configuration --> Settings`, then enable the :guilabel:`Work Orders` "
"checkbox."
msgstr ""
"Fanen :guilabel:`Operationer` vises kun, hvis "
"indstillingen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer` er aktiveret. For at gøre dette skal "
"du navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Konfiguration --> "
"Indstillinger` og derefter aktivere "
"afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:None
msgid "The Operations tab on a bill of materials."
msgstr "Fanen Operationer på en stykliste."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/configure_manufacturing_product.rst:77
msgid ":doc:`bill_configuration`."
msgstr ":doc:`bill_configuration`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:3
msgid "Manufacturing order costs"
msgstr "Omkostninger til produktionsordre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:11
msgid ""
"The ability to accurately calculate the cost of manufacturing a product is "
"critical when determining product profitability. Odoo's **Manufacturing** "
"app simplifies this calculation by automatically calculating the cost to "
"complete each manufacturing order (MO), as well as the average production "
"cost of a product, based on all completed |MOs|."
msgstr ""
"Evnen til præcist at beregne omkostningerne ved at fremstille et produkt er "
"afgørende, når produktets rentabilitet skal bestemmes. Odoos **Produktion**-"
"app forenkler denne beregning ved automatisk at beregne omkostningerne ved "
"at gennemføre hver produktionsordre (MO) samt den gennemsnitlige "
"produktionsomkostning for et produkt baseret på alle gennemførte |MOs|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:17
msgid ""
"Odoo's Manufacturing app distinguishes between the *MO cost* and the *real "
"cost* of an |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Odoos Produktion-app skelner mellem *MO-omkostningen* og den *reelle "
"omkostning* for en |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:19
msgid ""
"The |MO| cost represents how much it *should* cost to complete an |MO|, "
"based on the configuration of the product's bill of materials (BoM). This "
"takes into account the cost and quantity of components, as well as the cost "
"of completing the necessary operations."
msgstr ""
"|MO|-omkostningen repræsenterer, hvor meget det *burde* koste at gennemføre "
"en |MO| baseret på konfigurationen af produktets stykliste (BoM). Dette "
"tager højde for omkostningen og mængden af komponenter samt omkostningen ved "
"at gennemføre de nødvendige operationer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:23
msgid ""
"The real cost represents how much it *actually* costs to complete the |MO|. "
"A few factors can cause the real cost to differ from the |MO| cost. For "
"example, an operation may take longer to complete than estimated, a greater "
"component quantity might be needed than was specified on the |BoM|, or the "
"price of components may change during manufacturing."
msgstr ""
"Den reelle omkostning repræsenterer, hvor meget det *faktisk* koster at "
"gennemføre |MO|. Nogle få faktorer kan få den reelle omkostning til at "
"afvige fra |MO|-omkostningen. For eksempel kan en operation tage længere tid "
"at gennemføre end estimeret, der kan være behov for en større "
"komponentmængde end specificeret på |BoM|, eller prisen på komponenter kan "
"ændre sig under produktionen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:31
msgid "Cost configuration"
msgstr "Omkostningskonfiguration"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:33
msgid ""
"Odoo computes |MO| costs based on the configuration of the |BoM| used to "
"manufacture a product. This calculation includes the cost and quantity of "
"components and operations listed on the |BoM|, in addition to the operating "
"costs of the work centers where those operations are carried out, and the "
"amount paid to each employee who works on an operation."
msgstr ""
"Odoo beregner |MO|-omkostninger baseret på konfigurationen af den |BoM|, der "
"bruges til at fremstille et produkt. Denne beregning inkluderer omkostningen "
"og mængden af komponenter og operationer, der er anført på |BoM|, samt "
"driftsomkostningerne for de arbejdscentre, hvor disse operationer udføres, "
"og det beløb, der betales til hver medarbejder, der arbejder på en operation."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:41
msgid "Component cost"
msgstr "Komponentomkostning"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:43
msgid ""
"Component cost is calculated automatically, based on the average purchase "
"cost of a component across all purchase orders (POs). To view a component's "
"cost, navigate to :guilabel:`Inventory app --> Products --> Products`, and "
"select a component product. The cost is displayed in the :guilabel:`Cost` "
"field of the :guilabel:`General Information` tab, on the component's product "
"form."
msgstr ""
"Komponentomkostningen beregnes automatisk baseret på den gennemsnitlige "
"indkøbsomkostning for en komponent på tværs af alle indkøbsordrer (PO'er). "
"For at se en komponents omkostning skal du navigere til :guilabel:`Lager-app "
"--> Produkter --> Produkter` og vælge et komponentprodukt. Omkostningen "
"vises i feltet :guilabel:`Omkostning` på fanen :guilabel:`Generelle "
"oplysninger` på komponentens produktformular."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:48
msgid ""
"It is possible to set the cost of a component manually, by clicking "
"the :guilabel:`Cost` field on the component's product form and entering a "
"value. However, any future |POs| for the component override a manually "
"entered value, resetting the :guilabel:`Cost` field back to an automatically "
"computed value."
msgstr ""
"Det er muligt at indstille omkostningen for en komponent manuelt ved at "
"klikke på feltet :guilabel:`Omkostning` på komponentens produktformular og "
"indtaste en værdi. Dog vil eventuelle fremtidige |POs| for komponenten "
"tilsidesætte en manuelt indtastet værdi og nulstille "
"feltet :guilabel:`Omkostning` tilbage til en automatisk beregnet værdi."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:56
msgid "Work center cost"
msgstr "Omkostning for arbejdscenter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:58
msgid ""
"To set the operating cost for a specific work center, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Configuration --> Work Centers`, "
"and select a work center."
msgstr ""
"For at indstille driftsomkostningen for et specifikt arbejdscenter skal du "
"navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion-app --> Konfiguration --> "
"Arbejdscentre` og vælge et arbejdscenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:61
msgid ""
"To set the cost of operating the work center for one hour, enter a value in "
"the :guilabel:`per workcenter` field, located beside the :guilabel:`Cost per "
"hour` section on the work center's :guilabel:`General Information` tab."
msgstr ""
"For at indstille omkostningen ved at drive arbejdscentret i én time skal du "
"indtaste en værdi i feltet :guilabel:`pr. arbejdscenter`, der findes ved "
"siden af sektionen :guilabel:`Omkostning pr. time` på arbejdscentrets "
"fane :guilabel:`Generelle oplysninger`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:65
msgid ""
"To set the hourly cost of each employee that operates the work center, enter "
"a value in the :guilabel:`per employee` field, located beside "
"the :guilabel:`Cost per hour` section on the work "
"center's :guilabel:`General Information` tab. For example, if `25.00` is "
"entered in the :guilabel:`per employee` field, it costs $25.00 per hour for "
"*each* employee working at the work center."
msgstr ""
"For at indstille timeomkostningen for hver medarbejder, der betjener "
"arbejdscentret, skal du indtaste en værdi i feltet :guilabel:`pr. "
"medarbejder`, der findes ved siden af sektionen :guilabel:`Omkostning pr. "
"time` på arbejdscentrets fane :guilabel:`Generelle oplysninger`. For "
"eksempel, hvis `25.00` indtastes i feltet :guilabel:`pr. medarbejder`, "
"koster det $25,00 pr. time for *hver* medarbejder, der arbejder på "
"arbejdscentret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:72
msgid ""
"The value entered in the :guilabel:`per employee` field is only used to "
"calculate the |MO| cost, which is the estimated cost of completing the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Værdien indtastet i feltet :guilabel:`pr. medarbejder` bruges kun til at "
"beregne |MO|-omkostningen, som er den estimerede omkostning ved at "
"gennemføre |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:75
msgid ""
"The actual cost of completing the |MO| is represented by the real cost. "
"Instead of using the value entered in the :guilabel:`per employee` field, "
"the real cost is calculated using the hourly cost specific to each employee."
msgstr ""
"Den faktiske omkostning ved at gennemføre |MO| repræsenteres af den reelle "
"omkostning. I stedet for at bruge værdien indtastet i feltet :guilabel:`pr. "
"medarbejder`, beregnes den reelle omkostning ved hjælp af den "
"timeomkostning, der er specifik for hver medarbejder."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:79
msgid ""
"For example, if the :guilabel:`per employee` cost of a work center is "
"'$50.00', and an employee with an hourly cost of '$60.00' completes a work "
"order there, the |MO| cost (estimated) is calculated using the $50/hr cost, "
"while the real cost is calculated using the $60/hr cost."
msgstr ""
"For eksempel, hvis :guilabel:`pr. medarbejder`-omkostningen for et "
"arbejdscenter er '$50,00', og en medarbejder med en timeomkostning på "
"'$60,00' gennemfører en arbejdsordre der, beregnes |MO|-omkostningen "
"(estimeret) ved hjælp af $50/time-omkostningen, mens den reelle omkostning "
"beregnes ved hjælp af $60/time-omkostningen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:83
msgid ""
"See the :ref:`employee cost section <manufacturing/mo-costs/employee-cost>` "
"below for information on how to set the cost for specific employees."
msgstr ""
"Se :ref:`afsnittet om medarbejderomkostninger <manufacturing/mo-costs/"
"employee-cost>` nedenfor for oplysninger om, hvordan du indstiller "
"omkostningen for specifikke medarbejdere."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:89
msgid "Employee cost"
msgstr "Medarbejderomkostning"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:91
msgid ""
"To set the hourly cost for a specific employee, navigate to "
"the :menuselection:`Employees` app, and select an employee. On the "
"employee's form, select the :guilabel:`Settings` tab, and enter the "
"employee's rate in the :guilabel:`Hourly Cost` field of "
"the :guilabel:`Application Settings` section."
msgstr ""
"For at indstille timesatsen for en specifik medarbejder skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Medarbejdere`-appen og vælge en medarbejder. På "
"medarbejderens formular skal du vælge fanen :guilabel:`Indstillinger` og "
"indtaste medarbejderens sats i feltet :guilabel:`Timeomkostning` under "
"afsnittet :guilabel:`Applikationsindstillinger`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:97
msgid ""
"As detailed in the :ref:`work center cost section <manufacturing/mo-costs/"
"work-center-cost>` above, the value entered in the :guilabel:`Hourly Cost` "
"field on the employee's form is used to calculate the real cost of an |MO|. "
"The estimated cost of an |MO|, referred to as the |MO| cost, uses the per "
"employee cost set on each work center's form."
msgstr ""
"Som beskrevet i :ref:`afsnittet om arbejdscenteromkostninger <manufacturing/"
"mo-costs/work-center-cost>` ovenfor bruges værdien indtastet i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Timeomkostning` på medarbejderens formular til at beregne "
"den faktiske omkostning ved en |MO|. Den estimerede omkostning ved en |MO|, "
"kaldet |MO|-omkostningen, bruger medarbejderomkostningen pr. medarbejder, "
"der er angivet på hvert arbejdscenters formular."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:105
msgid "|BoM| configuration"
msgstr "|BoM|-konfiguration"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:107
msgid ""
"Configuring a |BoM| so Odoo can accurately calculate the cost of |MOs| that "
"use it requires two steps. First, components **must** be added, and the "
"required quantity specified. Second, operations **must** be added, along "
"with the work centers where they are carried out."
msgstr ""
"Konfiguration af en |BoM|, så Odoo nøjagtigt kan beregne omkostningerne ved |"
"MOs|, der bruger den, kræver to trin. Først **skal** komponenter tilføjes, "
"og den nødvendige mængde angives. For det andet **skal** operationer "
"tilføjes sammen med de arbejdscentre, hvor de udføres."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:111
msgid ""
"Begin by navigating to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Products --> "
"Bills of Materials`. Select a |BoM|, or create a new one by "
"clicking :guilabel:`New`."
msgstr ""
"Start med at navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion-app --> Produkter --> "
"Styklister`. Vælg en |BoM|, eller opret en ny ved at klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Ny`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:114
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Components` tab of the |BoM| form, add each component by "
"clicking :guilabel:`Add a line`, selecting the component from the drop-down "
"menu in the :guilabel:`Component` column, and entering the quantity in "
"the :guilabel:`Quantity` column."
msgstr ""
"I fanen :guilabel:`Komponenter` på |BoM|-formularen skal du tilføje hver "
"komponent ved at klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje`, vælge komponenten "
"fra rullemenuen i kolonnen :guilabel:`Komponent` og indtaste mængden i "
"kolonnen :guilabel:`Mængde`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:118
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Operations` tab, add an operation by "
"clicking :guilabel:`Add a line` to open the :guilabel:`Create Operations` "
"pop-up window. Enter a title for the operation in the :guilabel:`Operation` "
"field."
msgstr ""
"I fanen :guilabel:`Operationer` skal du tilføje en operation ved at klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje` for at åbne pop-up-vinduet :guilabel:`Opret "
"operationer`. Indtast en titel for operationen i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Operation`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:122
msgid ""
"Select the :guilabel:`Work Center` where the operation is carried out. Then, "
"add a :guilabel:`Default Duration`, which is the estimated amount of time "
"the operation takes to complete."
msgstr ""
"Vælg det :guilabel:`Arbejdscenter`, hvor operationen udføres. Tilføj "
"derefter en :guilabel:`Standardvarighed`, som er den estimerede tid, "
"operationen tager at gennemføre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:125
msgid ""
"By default, the :guilabel:`Duration Computation` field is set "
"to :guilabel:`Set duration manually`, which means that the number entered "
"in :guilabel:`Default Duration` field is always used as the expected "
"duration of the operation."
msgstr ""
"Som standard er feltet :guilabel:`Varighedsberegning` indstillet "
"til :guilabel:`Indstil varighed manuelt`, hvilket betyder, at det tal, der "
"indtastes i feltet :guilabel:`Standardvarighed`, altid bruges som den "
"forventede varighed af operationen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:129
msgid ""
"Selecting :guilabel:`Compute based on tracked time` causes Odoo to "
"automatically compute the :guilabel:`Default Duration` based on a certain "
"number of work orders, which is set in the :guilabel:`Based on` field. "
"Before there are work orders to compute this duration, the value in "
"the :guilabel:`Default Duration` field is used instead."
msgstr ""
"Valg af :guilabel:`Beregn baseret på registreret tid` får Odoo til "
"automatisk at beregne :guilabel:`Standardvarighed` baseret på et bestemt "
"antal arbejdsordrer, som indstilles i feltet :guilabel:`Baseret på`. Før der "
"er arbejdsordrer til at beregne denne varighed, bruges værdien i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Standardvarighed` i stedet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:134
msgid ""
"The hourly cost of operating the work center, and the duration of the "
"operation, are used to calculate the operation's cost."
msgstr ""
"Timeomkostningen ved drift af arbejdscentret og varigheden af operationen "
"bruges til at beregne operationens omkostning."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:137
msgid ""
"Finally, click :guilabel:`Save & Close` to add the operation to the |BoM|, "
"and close the :guilabel:`Create Operations` pop-up window. Alternatively, "
"click :guilabel:`Save & New` to add the operation to the |BoM|, and open a "
"blank :guilabel:`Create Operations` pop-up window to add another operation."
msgstr ""
"Klik til sidst på :guilabel:`Gem og luk` for at tilføje operationen til |"
"BoM| og lukke pop-up-vinduet :guilabel:`Opret operationer`. Alternativt kan "
"du klikke på :guilabel:`Gem og ny` for at tilføje operationen til |BoM| og "
"åbne et tomt pop-up-vindue :guilabel:`Opret operationer` for at tilføje en "
"anden operation."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:143
msgid ""
"For a full overview of |BoM| configuration, see the documentation "
"on :doc:`bills of materials <bill_configuration>`."
msgstr ""
"For en komplet oversigt over |BoM|-konfiguration, se dokumentationen "
"om :doc:`styklister <bill_configuration>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:149
msgid "|MO| overview"
msgstr "|MO|-oversigt"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:151
msgid ""
"Each |MO| has an *overview* page, which lists a variety of information about "
"the |MO|, including |MO| cost and real cost. To view the overview for an |"
"MO|, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Operations --> "
"Manufacturing Orders`, and select an |MO|. Then, click the :icon:`fa-"
"bars` :guilabel:`Overview` smart button at the top of the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Hver |MO| har en *oversigtsside*, som viser en række oplysninger om |MO|, "
"herunder |MO|-omkostning og faktisk omkostning. For at se oversigten for en |"
"MO| skal du navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion-app --> Operationer --> "
"Produktionsordrer` og vælge en |MO|. Klik derefter på den smarte "
"knap :icon:`fa-bars` :guilabel:`Oversigt` øverst på |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:156
msgid ""
"Both the |MO| cost and real cost take into account the cost and quantity of "
"components, as well as the cost of completing each work order. The overview "
"page lists a row for each of these values, with the sum of them listed at "
"the bottom of the :guilabel:`MO Cost` and :guilabel:`Real Cost` columns."
msgstr ""
"Både |MO|-omkostningen og den faktiske omkostning tager højde for "
"omkostningen og mængden af komponenter samt omkostningen ved at gennemføre "
"hver arbejdsordre. Oversigten viser en række for hver af disse værdier, med "
"summen af dem vist nederst i kolonnerne :guilabel:`PO-omkostning` "
"og :guilabel:`Faktisk omkostning`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:160
msgid ""
"Before work begins on an |MO|, the :guilabel:`MO Cost` and :guilabel:`Real "
"Cost` columns display the same costs. This is the *estimated* cost of "
"completing the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Før arbejdet begynder på en |MO|, viser kolonnerne :guilabel:`PO-omkostning` "
"og :guilabel:`Faktisk omkostning` de samme omkostninger. Dette er den "
"*estimerede* omkostning ved at gennemføre |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:163
msgid ""
"However, once work commences, the values in the :guilabel:`Real Cost` column "
"may begin to diverge from the values in the :guilabel:`MO Cost` column. This "
"happens if a different component quantity is used than was listed on the |"
"MO|, the duration of a work order is different than expected, or the hourly "
"cost of the employee performing a work order differs from the employee cost "
"set on the work center."
msgstr ""
"Når arbejdet begynder, kan værdierne i kolonnen :guilabel:`Faktisk "
"omkostning` imidlertid begynde at afvige fra værdierne i "
"kolonnen :guilabel:`PO-omkostning`. Dette sker, hvis en anden "
"komponentmængde bruges end den, der var angivet på |MO|, varigheden af en "
"arbejdsordre er anderledes end forventet, eller timeomkostningen for den "
"medarbejder, der udfører en arbejdsordre, afviger fra "
"medarbejderomkostningen angivet på arbejdscentret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:169
msgid ""
"Once the |MO| has been completed by clicking :guilabel:`Produce All`, the "
"values in the :guilabel:`MO Cost` column update to match those displayed in "
"the :guilabel:`Real Cost` column."
msgstr ""
"Når |MO| er blevet afsluttet ved at klikke på :guilabel:`Producér alt`, "
"opdateres værdierne i kolonnen :guilabel:`PO-omkostning`, så de matcher dem, "
"der vises i kolonnen :guilabel:`Faktisk omkostning`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:None
msgid "The MO Overview page."
msgstr "Siden MO-oversigt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:179
msgid "Average manufacturing cost"
msgstr "Gennemsnitlige produktionsomkostninger"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:181
msgid ""
"In addition to the cost of each individual |MO| for a product, Odoo also "
"tracks the average cost of manufacturing the product, taking into account "
"the cost of every completed |MO|. To view this, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> Products --> Products`, and select a "
"product."
msgstr ""
"Ud over omkostningerne for hver enkelt |MO| for et produkt sporer Odoo også "
"de gennemsnitlige omkostninger ved at producere produktet under hensyntagen "
"til omkostningerne for hver færdiggjort |MO|. For at se dette skal du "
"navigere til :menuselection:`Lager-appen --> Produkter --> Produkter` og "
"vælge et produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:185
msgid ""
"The manufacturing cost of the product is displayed per unit of measure in "
"the :guilabel:`Cost` field, located in the :guilabel:`General Information` "
"tab. The value continues to update as the costs of additional |MOs| are "
"factored into the average cost."
msgstr ""
"Produktets produktionsomkostninger vises pr. måleenhed i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Omkostning`, der findes under fanen :guilabel:`Generelle "
"oplysninger`. Værdien opdateres løbende, efterhånden som omkostningerne for "
"yderligere |MOs| indgår i de gennemsnitlige omkostninger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:189
msgid ""
"To the right of the :guilabel:`Cost` field is a :guilabel:`Compute Price "
"from BoM` button, which only appears for products with at least one |BoM|. "
"Click this button to reset the cost of the product to the expected cost, "
"which only takes into account the components and operations listed on the |"
"BoM|."
msgstr ""
"Til højre for feltet :guilabel:`Omkostning` findes en knap :guilabel:`Beregn "
"pris fra stykliste`, som kun vises for produkter med mindst én |BoM|. Klik "
"på denne knap for at nulstille omkostningen for produktet til de forventede "
"omkostninger, som kun tager hensyn til komponenterne og operationerne anført "
"på |BoM|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:196
msgid ""
"Be aware that clicking :guilabel:`Compute Price from BoM` does not set the "
"price permanently. The cost continues to update based on the average of the |"
"BoM| price and the real cost of any future |MOs|."
msgstr ""
"Vær opmærksom på, at klik på :guilabel:`Beregn pris fra stykliste` ikke "
"fastsætter prisen permanent. Omkostningen opdateres løbende baseret på "
"gennemsnittet af |BoM|-prisen og de faktiske omkostninger for eventuelle "
"fremtidige |MOs|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:200
msgid "Example workflow: manufacturing cost"
msgstr "Eksempel på arbejdsgang: produktionsomkostninger"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:203
msgid ""
"Golf product manufacturer *Fairway Fields* produces a variety of golf "
"products, including an indoor *putting green*. They have configured a |BoM| "
"for the putting green, so Odoo automatically calculates the manufacturing "
"cost of each putting green |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Golfproduktfabrikanten *Fairway Fields* producerer en række golfprodukter, "
"herunder en indendørs *putting green*. De har konfigureret en |BoM| til "
"putting green, så Odoo automatisk beregner produktionsomkostningerne for "
"hver putting green |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:207
msgid "The |BoM| lists two components:"
msgstr "|BoM| angiver to komponenter:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:209
msgid "One unit of *green felt*, which costs $20.00."
msgstr "Én enhed *grøn filt*, som koster 20,00 $."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:210
msgid "One unit of a *rubber pad*, which costs $30.00."
msgstr "Én enhed af en *gummipude*, som koster 30,00 $."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:212
msgid ""
"The |BoM| also lists four operations, all of which are carried out at "
"*Assembly Station 1*, which has an hourly operating cost of $30.00. Those "
"operations are as follows:"
msgstr ""
"|BoM| angiver også fire operationer, som alle udføres ved *samlestation 1*, "
"der har en driftsomkostning på 30,00 $ i timen. Disse operationer er som "
"følger:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:215
msgid ""
"*Cut felt*: default duration of seven minutes, for a total cost of $3.50."
msgstr ""
"*Klip filt*: standardvarighed på syv minutter for en samlet omkostning på "
"3,50 $."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:216
msgid ""
"*Cut rubber pad*: default duration of five minutes, for a total cost of "
"$2.50."
msgstr ""
"*Klip gummipude*: standardvarighed på fem minutter for en samlet omkostning "
"på 2,50 $."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:217
msgid ""
"*Attach pad to felt*: default duration of 15 minutes, for a total cost of "
"$7.50."
msgstr ""
"*Fastgør pude til filt*: standardvarighed på 15 minutter for en samlet "
"omkostning på 7,50 $."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:218
msgid ""
"*Cut holes*: default duration of three minutes, for a total cost of $1.50."
msgstr ""
"*Skær huller*: standardvarighed på tre minutter for en samlet omkostning på "
"1,50 $."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:220
msgid ""
"Altogether, the components required to produce one putting green cost "
"$50.00, and the operations required cost $15.00, for a total manufacturing "
"cost of $65.00. This cost is reflected in the :guilabel:`Cost` field on the "
"putting green's product form."
msgstr ""
"Samlet set koster de komponenter, der kræves for at producere én putting "
"green, 50,00 $, og de nødvendige operationer koster 15,00 $, til en samlet "
"produktionsomkostning på 65,00 $. Denne omkostning afspejles i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Omkostning` på putting greens produktformular."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:224
msgid ""
"Fairway Fields confirms an |MO| for one putting green. Before manufacturing "
"starts, the |MO| overview lists a cost of `$65.00` in both the :guilabel:`MO "
"Cost` and :guilabel:`Real Cost` fields."
msgstr ""
"Fairway Fields bekræfter en |MO| for én putting green. Før produktionen "
"starter, viser |MO|-oversigten en omkostning på `65,00 $` i både "
"felterne :guilabel:`MO-omkostning` og :guilabel:`Faktiske omkostninger`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:None
msgid "The MO Overview page for one putting green, before production starts."
msgstr "Siden MO-oversigt for én putting green før produktionen starter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:231
msgid ""
"Manufacturing begins, and the operations take ten minutes longer than "
"expected, for a total manufacturing time of 40 minutes. This deviation from "
"the |BoM| is reflected on the |MO| overview, which now lists "
"a :guilabel:`Real Cost` of `$70.00`."
msgstr ""
"Produktionen begynder, og operationerne tager ti minutter længere end "
"forventet med en samlet produktionstid på 40 minutter. Denne afvigelse fra |"
"BoM| afspejles i |MO|-oversigten, som nu viser :guilabel:`Faktiske "
"omkostninger` på `70,00 $`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:None
msgid "The MO Overview page for one putting green, during production."
msgstr ""
"Oversigten over produktionsordren for én putting green under produktion."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:238
msgid ""
"Once manufacturing is finished, and the |MO| is marked as *Done*, the |MO| "
"overview updates again, so the values in the :guilabel:`MO Cost` "
"and :guilabel:`Real Cost` columns match, each displaying a value of `$70.00`."
msgstr ""
"Når produktionen er færdig, og |MO| er markeret som *Udført*, opdateres |MO|-"
"oversigten igen, så værdierne i kolonnerne :guilabel:`PO-omkostning` "
"og :guilabel:`Faktisk omkostning` matcher, og hver viser en værdi på "
"`$70.00`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/mo_costs.rst:242
msgid ""
"On the putting green's product page, the :guilabel:`Cost` field now displays "
"a cost of `$67.50`, the average of the original cost of $65.00 and the real "
"cost of $70.00 from the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"På putting green-produktsiden viser feltet :guilabel:`Omkostning` nu en "
"omkostning på `$67.50`, gennemsnittet af den oprindelige omkostning på "
"$65.00 og den faktiske omkostning på $70.00 fra |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:3
msgid "One-step manufacturing"
msgstr "Produktion i ét trin"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:9
msgid ""
"Odoo *Manufacturing* allows users to manufacture products using one, two, or "
"three steps. When using one-step manufacturing, Odoo creates a manufacturing "
"order (MO), but does not generate transfers for the movement of components "
"out of inventory or finished products into stock. Inventory counts still "
"update based on the number of components used and products manufactured, but "
"the act of transferring them to and from inventory is not tracked."
msgstr ""
"Odoo *Produktion* giver brugere mulighed for at producere produkter ved "
"hjælp af ét, to eller tre trin. Når der anvendes produktion i ét trin, "
"opretter Odoo en produktionsordre (PO), men genererer ikke overførsler for "
"flytning af komponenter ud af lageret eller færdige produkter ind på "
"lageret. Lagerbeholdningerne opdateres stadig baseret på antallet af "
"anvendte komponenter og producerede produkter, men selve overførslen til og "
"fra lageret spores ikke."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:16
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:15
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:16
msgid ""
"The number of steps used in manufacturing is set at the warehouse level, "
"allowing for each warehouse to use a different number of steps. To change "
"the number of steps used for a specific warehouse, begin by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Inventory --> Configuration --> Warehouses`, and then "
"select a warehouse from the :guilabel:`Warehouses` screen."
msgstr ""
"Antallet af trin, der anvendes i produktionen, indstilles på lagerniveau, "
"hvilket gør det muligt for hvert lager at bruge et forskelligt antal trin. "
"For at ændre antallet af trin, der bruges til et bestemt lager, skal du "
"navigere til :menuselection:`Lager --> Konfiguration --> Lagre` og derefter "
"vælge et lager fra skærmbilledet :guilabel:`Lagre`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:21
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:20
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:21
msgid ""
"On the :guilabel:`Warehouse Configuration` tab, find "
"the :guilabel:`Manufacture` radio input field, and select one of the three "
"options: :guilabel:`Manufacture (1 step)`, :guilabel:`Pick components and "
"then manufacture (2 steps)`, or :guilabel:`Pick components, manufacture and "
"then store products (3 steps)`."
msgstr ""
"På fanen :guilabel:`Lagerkonfiguration` skal du finde "
"inputfeltet :guilabel:`Fremstil` og vælge en af de tre "
"muligheder: :guilabel:`Fremstil (1 trin)`, :guilabel:`Pluk komponenter og "
"fremstil derefter (2 trin)` eller :guilabel:`Pluk komponenter, fremstil og "
"gem derefter produkter (3 trin)`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:0
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:0
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:0
msgid "The Manufacture radio input field on a warehouse configuration page."
msgstr "Inputfeltet Fremstil på en lagerkonfigurationsside."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:33
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:30
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:31
msgid "Create manufacturing order"
msgstr "Opret produktionsordre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:35
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:32
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:33
msgid ""
"To manufacture a product in Odoo *Manufacturing*, begin by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders`, "
"and then click :guilabel:`New` to create a new |MO|."
msgstr ""
"For at producere et produkt i Odoo *Produktion* skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operationer --> Produktionsordrer` og "
"derefter klikke på :guilabel:`Ny` for at oprette en ny |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:39
msgid ""
"On the new |MO|, select the product to be produced from "
"the :guilabel:`Product` drop-down menu. The :guilabel:`Bill of Material` "
"field auto-populates with the associated bill of materials (BoM)."
msgstr ""
"På den nye |MO| skal du vælge det produkt, der skal produceres, fra "
"rullemenuen :guilabel:`Produkt`. Feltet :guilabel:`Stykliste` udfyldes "
"automatisk med den tilknyttede stykliste."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:42
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:39
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:40
msgid ""
"If a product has more than one |BOM| configured for it, the specific |BOM| "
"can be selected in the :guilabel:`Bill of Material` field, and "
"the :guilabel:`Product` field auto-populates with the associated product."
msgstr ""
"Hvis et produkt har mere end én |BOM| konfigureret til det, kan den "
"specifikke |BOM| vælges i feltet :guilabel:`Stykliste`, og "
"feltet :guilabel:`Produkt` udfyldes automatisk med det tilknyttede produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:46
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:43
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:44
msgid ""
"After a |BOM| has been selected, the :guilabel:`Components` "
"and :guilabel:`Work Orders` tabs auto-populate with the components and "
"operations specified on the |BOM|. If additional components or operations "
"are required for the |MO| being configured, add them to "
"the :guilabel:`Components` and :guilabel:`Work Orders` tabs by "
"clicking :guilabel:`Add a line`."
msgstr ""
"Efter at en |BOM| er blevet valgt, udfyldes fanerne :guilabel:`Komponenter` "
"og :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer` automatisk med de komponenter og operationer, "
"der er angivet på |BOM|. Hvis der kræves yderligere komponenter eller "
"operationer til den |MO|, der konfigureres, skal du tilføje dem til "
"fanerne :guilabel:`Komponenter` og :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer` ved at klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:51
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:48
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:49
msgid "Finally, click :guilabel:`Confirm` to confirm the |MO|."
msgstr "Klik til sidst på :guilabel:`Bekræft` for at bekræfte |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:54
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:75
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:72
msgid "Process manufacturing order"
msgstr "Behandl produktionsordre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:56
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:77
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:74
msgid ""
"An |MO| is processed by completing all of the work orders listed under "
"its :guilabel:`Work Orders` tab. This can be done on the |MO| itself, or "
"from the work order tablet view."
msgstr ""
"En |MO| behandles ved at fuldføre alle de arbejdsordrer, der er anført under "
"dens fane :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer`. Dette kan gøres på selve |MO| eller fra "
"arbejdsordre-tabletvisningen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:60
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:81
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:78
msgid "Basic workflow"
msgstr "Grundlæggende arbejdsgang"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:62
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:80
msgid ""
"To complete work orders from the |MO| itself, begin by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders`, "
"and then select an |MO|."
msgstr ""
"For at fuldføre arbejdsordrer fra selve |MO| skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operationer --> Produktionsordrer` og "
"derefter vælge en |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:65
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:86
msgid ""
"On the |MO| page, select the :guilabel:`Work Orders` tab. Once work begins "
"on the first work order that needs to be completed, click "
"the :guilabel:`Start` button for that work order. Odoo *Manufacturing* then "
"starts a timer that keeps track of how long the work order takes to complete."
msgstr ""
"På |MO|-siden skal du vælge fanen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer`. Når arbejdet "
"begynder på den første arbejdsordre, der skal fuldføres, skal du klikke på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Start` for den pågældende arbejdsordre. Odoo *Produktion* "
"starter derefter en timer, der holder styr på, hvor lang tid arbejdsordren "
"tager at fuldføre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:None
msgid "The Start button for an operation on a manufacturing order."
msgstr "Startknappen for en operation på en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:73
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:94
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:91
msgid ""
"When the work order is completed, click the :guilabel:`Done` button for that "
"work order. Repeat the same process for each work order listed on "
"the :guilabel:`Work Orders` tab."
msgstr ""
"Når arbejdsordren er færdig, klik på knappen :guilabel:`Færdig` for den "
"pågældende arbejdsordre. Gentag den samme proces for hver arbejdsordre, der "
"er angivet under fanen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:None
msgid "The Done button for an operation on a manufacturing order."
msgstr "Færdig-knappen for en operation på en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:80
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:101
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:98
msgid ""
"After completing all of the work orders, click :guilabel:`Produce All` at "
"the top of the screen to mark the |MO| as :guilabel:`Done`, and register the "
"manufactured product(s) into inventory."
msgstr ""
"Efter at have fuldført alle arbejdsordrer skal du klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Producér alle` øverst på skærmen for at markere |MO| "
"som :guilabel:`Færdig` og registrere det/de producerede produkt(er) på "
"lageret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:84
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:105
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:102
msgid "Shop Floor workflow"
msgstr "Værkstedsworkflow"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:86
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:107
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:104
msgid ""
"To complete the work orders for an |MO| using the *Shop Floor* module, begin "
"by navigating to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> "
"Manufacturing Orders`, and then select an |MO|."
msgstr ""
"For at fuldføre arbejdsordrerne for en |MO| ved hjælp af modulet *Værksted* "
"skal du starte med at gå til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operationer --> "
"Produktionsordrer` og derefter vælge en |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:89
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:110
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:107
msgid ""
"On the |MO|, click on the :guilabel:`Work Orders` tab, and then select "
"the :guilabel:`↗️ (square with arrow coming out of it)` button on the line of "
"the first work order to be processed. Doing so opens a :guilabel:`Work "
"Orders` pop-up window, with details and processing options for the work "
"order."
msgstr ""
"På |MO| skal du klikke på fanen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer` og derefter vælge "
"knappen :guilabel:`↗️ (firkant med pil, der kommer ud af den)` på linjen for "
"den første arbejdsordre, der skal behandles. Det åbner et pop op-vindue "
"med :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer`, der viser detaljer og behandlingsmuligheder "
"for arbejdsordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:94
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:115
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:112
msgid ""
"On the pop-up window, select the :guilabel:`Open Shop Floor` button at the "
"top-left of the window to open the *Shop Floor* module."
msgstr ""
"I pop op-vinduet skal du vælge knappen :guilabel:`Åbn værksted` øverst til "
"venstre i vinduet for at åbne modulet *Værksted*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:None
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:None
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:None
msgid "The Open Shop Floor button for a work order on a manufacturing order."
msgstr "Knappen Åbn værksted for en arbejdsordre på en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:101
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:122
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:119
msgid ""
"When accessed directly from a specific work order within an |MO|, *Shop "
"Floor* defaults to the page for the work center where the work order is "
"configured to be carried out. The page shows a card for the work order that "
"displays the |MO| number, the product and number of units to be produced, "
"and the steps required to complete the work order."
msgstr ""
"Når der åbnes direkte fra en bestemt arbejdsordre inden for en |MO|, er "
"*Værksted* som standard indstillet til siden for det arbejdscenter, hvor "
"arbejdsordren er konfigureret til at blive udført. Siden viser et kort for "
"arbejdsordren, der viser |MO|-nummeret, produktet og antallet af enheder, "
"der skal produceres, samt de trin, der kræves for at fuldføre arbejdsordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:None
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:None
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:None
msgid "A work order card on a work center page in the Shop Floor module."
msgstr "Et arbejdsordreskort på en arbejdscenterside i modulet Værksted."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:110
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:128
msgid ""
"A work order is processed by completing each step listed on its card. This "
"can be done by clicking on a step and following the instructions listed on "
"the pop-up window that appears. Once the step is completed, "
"click :guilabel:`Next` to move on to the next step, if any are required."
msgstr ""
"En arbejdsordre behandles ved at fuldføre hvert trin, der er angivet på dens "
"kort. Dette kan gøres ved at klikke på et trin og følge instruktionerne i "
"det pop op-vindue, der vises. Når trinnet er fuldført, klik "
"på :guilabel:`Næste` for at gå videre til næste trin, hvis der kræves nogen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:114
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:135
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:132
msgid ""
"Alternatively, work order steps can be completed by clicking the checkbox "
"that appears on the right side of the step's line on the work order card. "
"When using this method, the step is automatically marked as completed, "
"without a pop-up window appearing."
msgstr ""
"Alternativt kan arbejdsordrens trin fuldføres ved at klikke på "
"afkrydsningsfeltet, der vises på højre side af trinnets linje på "
"arbejdsordrekortet. Når du bruger denne metode, markeres trinnet automatisk "
"som fuldført uden et pop op-vindue."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:118
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:139
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:136
msgid ""
"The final step on a work order card is titled *Register Production*. This "
"step is used to register the number of product units that were produced. If "
"the number produced is equal to the number that the |MO| was created for, "
"click the :guilabel:`# Units` button on the right side of the line to "
"automatically register that number as the quantity produced."
msgstr ""
"Det sidste trin på et arbejdsordreskort hedder *Registrér produktion*. Dette "
"trin bruges til at registrere antallet af produktenheder, der blev "
"produceret. Hvis det producerede antal svarer til det antal, som |MO| blev "
"oprettet for, skal du klikke på knappen :guilabel:`# enheder` på højre side "
"af linjen for automatisk at registrere det antal som den producerede mængde."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:123
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:144
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:141
msgid ""
"If a different number must be entered, click the :guilabel:`Register "
"Production` step to open a pop-up window. Enter the number of units produced "
"in the :guilabel:`Units` field, and then click :guilabel:`Validate` to "
"register that number."
msgstr ""
"Hvis et andet antal skal indtastes, skal du klikke på "
"trinnet :guilabel:`Registrér produktion` for at åbne et pop op-vindue. "
"Indtast antallet af producerede enheder i feltet :guilabel:`Enheder`, og "
"klik derefter på :guilabel:`Validér` for at registrere det antal."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:128
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:149
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:146
msgid ""
"The *Register Production* step appears on every work order card. It must be "
"completed for the first work order that is processed. After doing so, the "
"step appears as already completed for each remaining work order in the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Trinnet *Registrér produktion* vises på hvert arbejdsordreskort. Det skal "
"fuldføres for den første arbejdsordre, der behandles. Efter at have gjort "
"det vises trinnet som allerede fuldført for hver resterende arbejdsordre i |"
"MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:132
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:153
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:150
msgid ""
"After completing all of the steps for a work order, a button appears on the "
"footer of the work order card. If any other work orders must be completed "
"before the |MO| can be closed, the button is titled :guilabel:`Mark as "
"Done`. If there are no additional work orders to complete, the button is "
"titled :guilabel:`Close Production`."
msgstr ""
"Efter at have fuldført alle trin for en arbejdsordre vises der en knap i "
"bunden af arbejdsordrekortet. Hvis der skal fuldføres andre arbejdsordrer, "
"før |MO| kan lukkes, hedder knappen :guilabel:`Markér som færdig`. Hvis der "
"ikke er flere arbejdsordrer at fuldføre, hedder knappen :guilabel:`Luk "
"produktion`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:137
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:158
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:155
msgid ""
"Clicking :guilabel:`Mark as Done` causes the work order card to fade away. "
"Once it disappears completely, the work order's status is marked as "
"*Finished* on the |MO|, and the next work order appears in the *Shop Floor* "
"module, on the page of the work center where it is configured to be carried "
"out. Any additional work orders can be processed using the instructions "
"detailed in this section."
msgstr ""
"Klik på :guilabel:`Markér som færdig` får arbejdsordrekortet til at falme. "
"Når det er forsvundet helt, markeres arbejdsordrens status som *Færdig* på |"
"MO|, og den næste arbejdsordre vises i modulet *Værksted* på siden for det "
"arbejdscenter, hvor den er konfigureret til at blive udført. Eventuelle "
"yderligere arbejdsordrer kan behandles ved hjælp af instruktionerne "
"beskrevet i dette afsnit."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:143
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:164
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:161
msgid ""
"Clicking :guilabel:`Close Production` causes the work order card to fade "
"away. Once it disappears, the |MO| is marked as *Done*, and the units of the "
"product that were produced are entered into inventory."
msgstr ""
"Klik på :guilabel:`Luk produktion` får arbejdsordrekortet til at falme. Når "
"det forsvinder, markeres |MO| som *Færdig*, og enhederne af det producerede "
"produkt indtastes på lageret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:147
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:168
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:165
msgid ""
"After clicking :guilabel:`Mark as Done` or :guilabel:`Close Production`, "
"each button is replaced by an :guilabel:`Undo` button. Click "
"the :guilabel:`Undo` button before the work order card fades away to keep "
"the work order open."
msgstr ""
"Efter at have klikket på :guilabel:`Markér som færdig` eller :guilabel:`Luk "
"produktion` erstattes hver knap af en :guilabel:`Fortryd`-knap. Klik på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Fortryd`, før arbejdsordrekortet falmer for at holde "
"arbejdsordren åben."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/one_step_manufacturing.rst:152
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:173
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:170
msgid ""
"This section details the basic workflow for processing an |MO| in the *Shop "
"Floor* module. For a more in-depth explanation of the module and all of its "
"features, please see the :doc:`../shop_floor/shop_floor_overview` "
"documentation."
msgstr ""
"Dette afsnit beskriver den grundlæggende arbejdsgang for behandling af en |"
"MO| i modulet *Shop Floor*. For en mere dybdegående forklaring af modulet og "
"alle dets funktioner, se venligst dokumentationen :doc:`../shop_floor/"
"shop_floor_overview`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:3
msgid "Three-step manufacturing"
msgstr "Tredelt produktion"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:9
msgid ""
"Odoo *Manufacturing* allows users to manufacture products using one, two, or "
"three steps. When using three-step manufacturing, Odoo creates a pick "
"components transfer, a manufacturing order (MO), and a store finished "
"products transfer, and updates inventory counts based on the number of "
"components removed, and finished products created."
msgstr ""
"Odoo *Produktion* giver brugere mulighed for at fremstille produkter ved "
"hjælp af et, to eller tre trin. Ved brug af fremstilling i tre trin opretter "
"Odoo en plukkomponentoverførsel, en produktionsordre (MO) og en overførsel "
"af færdige produkter til lager, og opdaterer lagerbeholdninger baseret på "
"antallet af fjernede komponenter og producerede færdige produkter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:36
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:37
msgid ""
"On the new |MO|, select the product to be produced from "
"the :guilabel:`Product` drop-down menu. The :guilabel:`Bill of Material` "
"field auto-populates with the associated Bill of Materials (BoM)."
msgstr ""
"På den nye |MO| skal du vælge det produkt, der skal produceres, fra "
"rullemenuen :guilabel:`Produkt`. Feltet :guilabel:`Stykliste` udfyldes "
"automatisk med den tilknyttede stykliste (BoM)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:51
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:52
msgid "Process pick components transfer"
msgstr "Behandle plukkomponentoverførsel"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:53
msgid ""
"After confirming a three-step |MO|, a :guilabel:`Transfers` smart button "
"appears at the top of the page. Click it to be taken to "
"the :guilabel:`Transfers` page for the |MO|. The page lists two transfers: "
"*WH/PC/XXXXX* (the pick components transfer), and *WH/SFP/XXXXX* (the store "
"finished products transfer)."
msgstr ""
"Efter bekræftelse af en |MO| i tre trin vises en "
"smartknap :guilabel:`Overførsler` øverst på siden. Klik på den for at komme "
"til siden :guilabel:`Overførsler` for |MO|. Siden viser to overførsler: *WH/"
"PC/XXXXX* (plukkomponentoverførslen) og *WH/SFP/XXXXX* (overførslen af "
"færdige produkter til lager)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:58
msgid ""
"Select :guilabel:`WH/PC/XXXXX` to open the pick components transfer for the |"
"MO|. This transfer is used to track the movement of components from the "
"locations where they are stored to the location where they are used to "
"manufacture the product."
msgstr ""
"Vælg :guilabel:`WH/PC/XXXXX` for at åbne plukkomponentoverførslen for |MO|. "
"Denne overførsel bruges til at spore flytningen af komponenter fra de "
"lokationer, hvor de opbevares, til den lokation, hvor de bruges til at "
"fremstille produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:62
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:59
msgid ""
"After transferring the components out of their storage location, "
"click :guilabel:`Validate` at the top of the transfer, followed "
"by :guilabel:`Apply` on the :guilabel:`Immediate Transfer?` pop-up window "
"that appears. Doing so marks the transfer as :guilabel:`Done`, and updates "
"inventory counts to reflect the quantity of components transferred."
msgstr ""
"Efter overførsel af komponenterne ud af deres opbevaringslokation skal du "
"klikke på :guilabel:`Valider` øverst på overførslen, efterfulgt "
"af :guilabel:`Anvend` i pop op-vinduet :guilabel:`Øjeblikkelig overførsel?`, "
"der vises. Dette markerer overførslen som :guilabel:`Udført` og opdaterer "
"lagerbeholdninger for at afspejle mængden af overførte komponenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:67
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:64
msgid ""
"Finally, return to the |MO| by clicking the :guilabel:`WH/MO/XXXXX` "
"breadcrumb at the top of the page."
msgstr ""
"Til sidst skal du vende tilbage til |MO| ved at klikke på "
"brødkrummen :guilabel:`WH/MO/XXXXX` øverst på siden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:None
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:None
msgid "The manufacturing order bread crumb on a pick components transfer."
msgstr "Produktionsordrens brødkrumme på en plukkomponentoverførsel."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:83
msgid ""
"To complete work orders from the |MO| itself, begin by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders`, "
"and then select a manufacturing order."
msgstr ""
"For at fuldføre arbejdsordrer fra selve |MO| skal du først navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operationer --> Produktionsordrer` og "
"derefter vælge en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:None
msgid "The Start button for a work order on a manufacturing order."
msgstr "Startknappen for en arbejdsordre på en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:None
msgid "The Done button for an work order on a manufacturing order."
msgstr "Udført-knappen for en arbejdsordre på en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:131
msgid ""
"A work order is processed by completing each step listed on its card. This "
"can be done by clicking on a step, and following the instructions listed on "
"the pop-up window that appears. Once the step is completed, "
"click :guilabel:`Next` to move on to the next step, if any are required."
msgstr ""
"En arbejdsordre behandles ved at fuldføre hvert trin, der er angivet på dens "
"kort. Dette kan gøres ved at klikke på et trin og følge instruktionerne i "
"pop op-vinduet, der vises. Når trinnet er fuldført, skal du klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Næste` for at gå videre til næste trin, hvis det er nødvendigt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:178
msgid "Process finished product transfer"
msgstr "Behandle overførsel af færdige produkter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:180
msgid ""
"After completing the |MO|, return to the order's :guilabel:`Transfers` page "
"by clicking the :guilabel:`Transfers` button at the top of the order. This "
"time, select :guilabel:`WH/SFP/XXXXX` to open the store finished products "
"transfer. This transfer is used to track the movement of finished products "
"from the location where they were manufactured to the location where they "
"are stored."
msgstr ""
"Efter fuldførelse af |MO| skal du vende tilbage til ordrens "
"side :guilabel:`Overførsler` ved at klikke på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Overførsler` øverst på ordren. Denne gang skal du "
"vælge :guilabel:`WH/SFP/XXXXX` for at åbne overførslen af færdige produkter "
"til lager. Denne overførsel bruges til at spore flytningen af færdige "
"produkter fra den lokation, hvor de blev fremstillet, til den lokation, hvor "
"de opbevares."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing.rst:185
msgid ""
"After transferring the finished products to their storage location, "
"click :guilabel:`Validate` at the top of the transfer, followed "
"by :guilabel:`Apply` on the :guilabel:`Immediate Transfer?` pop-up window "
"that appears. Doing so marks the transfer as :guilabel:`Done`, and updates "
"inventory counts to reflect the quantity of finished products transferred."
msgstr ""
"Efter overførsel af de færdige produkter til deres opbevaringslokation skal "
"du klikke på :guilabel:`Valider` øverst på overførslen, efterfulgt "
"af :guilabel:`Anvend` i pop op-vinduet :guilabel:`Øjeblikkelig overførsel?`, "
"der vises. Dette markerer overførslen som :guilabel:`Udført` og opdaterer "
"lagerbeholdninger for at afspejle mængden af overførte færdige produkter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:3
msgid "Two-step manufacturing"
msgstr "Fremstilling i to trin"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:9
msgid ""
"Odoo *Manufacturing* allows users to manufacture products using one, two, or "
"three steps. When using two-step manufacturing, Odoo creates a manufacturing "
"order (MO) and a pick components transfer, but does not generate a transfer "
"for the movement of finished products into stock. Inventory counts still "
"update based on the number of products manufactured, but the act of "
"transferring them to and from inventory is not tracked."
msgstr ""
"Odoo *Produktion* giver brugere mulighed for at fremstille produkter ved "
"hjælp af et, to eller tre trin. Ved brug af fremstilling i to trin opretter "
"Odoo en produktionsordre (MO) og en plukkomponentoverførsel, men genererer "
"ikke en overførsel for flytning af færdige produkter til lager. "
"Lagerbeholdninger opdateres stadig baseret på antallet af producerede "
"produkter, men flytningen af dem til og fra lager spores ikke."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:54
msgid ""
"After confirming a two-step |MO|, a :guilabel:`Transfers` smart button "
"appears at the top of the page. Click it to open the pick components "
"transfer for the |MO|. This transfer is used to track the movement of "
"components from the locations where they are stored to the location where "
"they are used to manufacture the product."
msgstr ""
"Efter bekræftelse af en |MO| i to trin vises en "
"smartknap :guilabel:`Overførsler` øverst på siden. Klik på den for at åbne "
"plukkomponentoverførslen for |MO|. Denne overførsel bruges til at spore "
"flytningen af komponenter fra de lokationer, hvor de opbevares, til den "
"lokation, hvor de bruges til at fremstille produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:83
msgid ""
"On the |MO| page, select the :guilabel:`Work Orders` tab. Once work begins "
"on the first work order that needs to be completed, click "
"the :guilabel:`Start` button for that operation. Odoo *Manufacturing* then "
"starts a timer that keeps track of how long the work order takes to complete."
msgstr ""
"På siden |MO| skal du vælge fanen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer`. Når arbejdet "
"begynder på den første arbejdsordre, der skal fuldføres, skal du klikke på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Start` for den operation. Odoo *Produktion* starter "
"derefter en timer, der holder styr på, hvor lang tid arbejdsordren tager at "
"fuldføre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:None
msgid "The Start button for an work order on a manufacturing order."
msgstr "Startknappen for en arbejdsordre på en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing.rst:None
msgid "The Done button for a work order on a manufacturing order."
msgstr "Knappen Udført for en arbejdsordre på en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:3
msgid "Work-in-progress costs"
msgstr "Omkostninger til igangværende arbejde"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:10
msgid ""
"When manufacturing processes take extended periods to complete, temporary "
"*work-in-progress (WIP)* :ref:`accounting journal entries <cheat_sheet/"
"journals>` can help to accurately reflect the value of partially completed "
"goods in financial statements, as well as potential insights on where cash "
"might be tied up in the manufacturing process."
msgstr ""
"Når produktionsprocesser tager længere tid at gennemføre, kan midlertidige "
"*work-in-progress (WIP)* :ref:`regnskabsposteringer <cheat_sheet/journals>` "
"hjælpe med at afspejle værdien af delvist færdige varer i regnskaber "
"nøjagtigt, samt give potentielle indsigter i, hvor likviditet kan være "
"bundet i produktionsprocessen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:15
msgid ""
"The **Manufacturing** app provides the option to manually post and reverse |"
"WIP| journal entries associated with an ongoing manufacturing order (MO) to "
"account for the *real cost* of components, work centers, and labor that have "
"already been incurred at the time the entry is posted."
msgstr ""
"**Produktion**-appen giver mulighed for manuelt at bogføre og tilbageføre |"
"WIP|-bogføringsposter knyttet til en igangværende produktionsordre (MO) for "
"at redegøre for de *faktiske omkostninger* ved komponenter, arbejdscentre og "
"arbejdskraft, der allerede er påløbet på tidspunktet for posteringens "
"bogføring."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:22
msgid "Costs included in WIP entries"
msgstr "Omkostninger inkluderet i igangværende arbejdsposter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:24
msgid ""
"Consumption that is factored into the |WIP| accounting entry can be viewed "
"in the |MO|. Those values are used to calculate the total *real cost* in the "
"|MO| overview."
msgstr ""
"Forbrug, der indgår i |WIP|-bogføringsposten, kan ses i |MO|. Disse værdier "
"bruges til at beregne den samlede *faktiske omkostning* i |MO|-oversigten."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:28
msgid ""
"To configure the unit prices and hourly rates used to calculate |WIP| costs, "
"see :doc:`Manufacturing order costs <mo_costs>`."
msgstr ""
"For at konfigurere enhedspriser og timesatser, der bruges til at beregne |"
"WIP|-omkostninger, se :doc:`Omkostninger ved produktionsordre <mo_costs>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:34
msgid "Consumption"
msgstr "Forbrug"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:36
msgid ""
"To view the *consumed* component quantities for a |WIP| order, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders`, "
"then select the |MO|. In the :guilabel:`Components` tab, "
"the :guilabel:`Consumed` column shows the quantity that has already been "
"consumed for each component in the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"For at se de *forbrugte* komponentmængder for en |WIP|-ordre skal du gå "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operationer --> Produktionsordrer` og "
"vælge |MO|. I fanen :guilabel:`Komponenter` viser "
"kolonnen :guilabel:`Forbrugt` den mængde, der allerede er forbrugt for hver "
"komponent i |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:None
msgid "MO Components tab with the quantity of components consumed."
msgstr "MO-fanen Komponenter med mængden af forbrugte komponenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:44
msgid ""
"To view the *real duration* of work order operations for a |WIP| order, "
"navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> Manufacturing "
"Orders`, then select the |MO|. In the :guilabel:`Work Orders` tab, "
"the :guilabel:`Real Duration` column shows the duration of work that has "
"already been carried out for each operation in the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"For at se den *faktiske varighed* af arbejdsordreoperationer for en |WIP|-"
"ordre skal du gå til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operationer --> "
"Produktionsordrer` og vælge |MO|. I fanen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer` viser "
"kolonnen :guilabel:`Faktisk varighed` varigheden af arbejde, der allerede er "
"udført for hver operation i |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:None
msgid "MO Work Orders tab with the real-world duration of operations."
msgstr "MO-fanen Arbejdsordrer med den faktiske varighed af operationer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:55
msgid "Real costs"
msgstr "Faktiske omkostninger"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:57
msgid ""
"To view the *real costs* of consumed components and labor, click "
"the :guilabel:`Overview` smart button to visit the *MO Overview*. "
"The :guilabel:`MO Cost` column represents planned costs based on the bill of "
"materials, while the :guilabel:`Real Cost` column reflects actual incurred "
"costs that will be recorded in the |WIP| entry. Work center overhead costs "
"and labor costs are grouped together under the *Operations* section. The "
"totals for both the :guilabel:`MO Cost` (expected) and :guilabel:`Real Cost` "
"(incurred) are displayed in the :guilabel:`Unit Cost` row at the bottom."
msgstr ""
"For at se de *faktiske omkostninger* ved forbrugte komponenter og "
"arbejdskraft skal du klikke på smartknappen :guilabel:`Oversigt` for at "
"besøge *MO-oversigten*. Kolonnen :guilabel:`MO-omkostning` repræsenterer "
"planlagte omkostninger baseret på styklisten, mens "
"kolonnen :guilabel:`Faktisk omkostning` afspejler faktiske påløbne "
"omkostninger, der vil blive registreret i |WIP|-posten. Arbejdscentrets "
"overheadomkostninger og lønomkostninger er grupperet sammen under afsnittet "
"*Operationer*. Totalerne for både :guilabel:`MO-omkostning` (forventet) "
"og :guilabel:`Faktisk omkostning` (påløbet) vises i "
"rækken :guilabel:`Enhedsomkostning` nederst."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:None
msgid ""
"Manufacturing overview with the real costs for components and operations."
msgstr ""
"Produktionsoversigt med de faktiske omkostninger for komponenter og "
"operationer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:67
msgid ""
"Amounts displayed in red or green highlight significant differences between "
"the :guilabel:`MO Cost` and :guilabel:`Real Cost` for each line item. This "
"can help identify potential issues in the manufacturing process, such as "
"unusually high component prices or slow operations."
msgstr ""
"Beløb vist i rødt eller grønt fremhæver væsentlige forskelle "
"mellem :guilabel:`MO-omkostning` og :guilabel:`Faktisk omkostning` for hver "
"linje. Dette kan hjælpe med at identificere potentielle problemer i "
"produktionsprocessen, såsom usædvanligt høje komponentpriser eller langsomme "
"operationer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:76
msgid ""
"By default, the Odoo database tracks the value of |WIP| costs under the "
"*Current Assets* :ref:`account type <chart-of-account/type>`. These default "
"accounts can be replaced with custom accounts."
msgstr ""
"Som standard sporer Odoo-databasen værdien af |WIP|-omkostninger "
"under :ref:`kontotypen <chart-of-account/type>` *Omsætningsaktiver*. Disse "
"standardkonti kan erstattes med brugerdefinerede konti."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:80
msgid ""
"To configure |WIP| accounts, navigate to :menuselection:`Accounting --> "
"Configuration --> Settings`, then scroll down to the *Inventory Valuation* "
"section. Under the *Manufacturing* section, select the accounts for both of "
"the drop-down fields:"
msgstr ""
"For at konfigurere |WIP|-konti skal du gå til :menuselection:`Regnskab --> "
"Konfiguration --> Indstillinger` og rulle ned til afsnittet "
"*Lagervurdering*. Under afsnittet *Produktion* skal du vælge kontiene for "
"begge rullegardinfelter:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:84
msgid ""
":guilabel:`WIP Account`: tracks the value of |WIP| goods. The default "
"account is **110500 Work in Progress**."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`IGA-konto`: sporer værdien af |WIP|-varer. Standardkontoen er "
"**110500 Igangværende arbejde**."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:86
msgid ""
":guilabel:`WIP Overhead Account`: tracks overhead costs. The default account "
"is **110400 Cost of Production**."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`IGA-overheadkonto`: sporer overheadomkostninger. Standardkontoen "
"er **110400 Produktionsomkostninger**."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:92
msgid "WIP entry workflow"
msgstr "Arbejdsgang for igangværende arbejdsposter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:94
msgid ""
"|WIP| accounting entries are not automatically tied to |MO| progress. They "
"reflect costs at the moment the entry is posted, based on what has already "
"been consumed. These entries must be :ref:`manually posted <manufacturing/"
"basic_setup/post-wip-entries>` in order to accurately reflect |WIP| "
"valuation in the **Accounting** app."
msgstr ""
"|WIP|-bogføringsposter er ikke automatisk knyttet til |MO|-fremskridt. De "
"afspejler omkostninger på det tidspunkt, hvor posten bogføres, baseret på "
"det, der allerede er forbrugt. Disse poster skal :ref:`bogføres manuelt "
"<manufacturing/basic_setup/post-wip-entries>` for nøjagtigt at afspejle |"
"WIP|-værdiansættelse i **Regnskab**-appen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:99
msgid ""
"|WIP| entries also need to be :ref:`reversed <manufacturing/basic_setup/"
"reverse-wip-entries>` once the manufacturing process is complete. These "
"entries are used to temporarily reflect manufacturing consumption and need "
"to be returned to an empty state in order to be used again in another "
"period. If needed, they can be reversed manually."
msgstr ""
"|WIP|-poster skal også :ref:`tilbageføres <manufacturing/basic_setup/reverse-"
"wip-entries>`, når produktionsprocessen er afsluttet. Disse poster bruges "
"til midlertidigt at afspejle produktionsforbrug og skal returneres til en "
"tom tilstand for at kunne bruges igen i en anden periode. Om nødvendigt kan "
"de tilbageføres manuelt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:107
msgid "Post WIP entries"
msgstr "Bogfør IGA-poster"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:109
msgid "To manually post |WIP| entries:"
msgstr "For manuelt at bogføre |WIP|-poster:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:111
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:126
msgid ""
"Go to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders` "
"and access the desired order."
msgstr ""
"Gå til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operationer --> Produktionsordrer` og "
"åbn den ønskede ordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:113
msgid ""
"Click the :icon:`fa-cog` icon and select :guilabel:`Post WIP Accounting "
"Entry`."
msgstr ""
"Klik på :icon:`fa-cog`-ikonet og vælg :guilabel:`Bogfør IGA-regnskabspost`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:114
msgid ""
"In the *Post WIP Accounting Entry* window, select the |WIP| accounting "
"journal."
msgstr ""
"I vinduet *Bogfør IGA-regnskabspost* skal du vælge |WIP|-regnskabskladden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:115
msgid "Adjust the dates and line items as needed, then click **Post WIP**."
msgstr ""
"Juster datoer og linjeposter efter behov, og klik derefter på **Bogfør IGA**."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:116
msgid ""
":ref:`Verify the entries are posted <manufacturing/basic_setup/verify-wip-"
"entries>` by reviewing the :guilabel:`Balance Sheet` report for that period."
msgstr ""
":ref:`Verificer, at posterne er bogført <manufacturing/basic_setup/verify-"
"wip-entries>` ved at gennemse rapporten :guilabel:`Statusopgørelse` for den "
"pågældende periode."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:122
msgid "Reverse WIP entries"
msgstr "Tilbagefør IGA-poster"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:124
msgid "To manually reverse |WIP| entries:"
msgstr "For manuelt at tilbageføre |WIP|-poster:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:128
msgid ""
"Click the :guilabel:`WIP` smart button to display the |WIP| entries "
"associated with it."
msgstr ""
"Klik på den smarte knap :guilabel:`IGA` for at vise de |WIP|-poster, der er "
"tilknyttet den."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:129
msgid ""
"Select the relevant reversal entry, click :icon:`fa-"
"cog` :guilabel:`Actions`, and select :guilabel:`Confirm Entries`."
msgstr ""
"Vælg den relevante tilbageførelsespost, klik på :icon:`fa-"
"cog` :guilabel:`Handlinger`, og vælg :guilabel:`Bekræft poster`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:131
msgid ""
":ref:`Verify the reversal is posted<manufacturing/basic_setup/verify-wip-"
"entries>` by reviewing the :guilabel:`Balance Sheet` report for that period."
msgstr ""
":ref:`Verificer, at tilbageførslen er bogført<manufacturing/basic_setup/"
"verify-wip-entries>` ved at gennemse rapporten :guilabel:`Statusopgørelse` "
"for den pågældende periode."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:135
msgid ""
"By default, an action is automatically scheduled for the next day to reverse "
"the initial |WIP| entries once they are posted. If needed, this can be "
"adjusted when :ref:`posting the initial WIP entry <manufacturing/basic_setup/"
"post-wip-entries>` using the :guilabel:`Reversal Date` field."
msgstr ""
"Som standard planlægges automatisk en handling for næste dag til at "
"tilbageføre de oprindelige |WIP|-poster, når de er bogført. Om nødvendigt "
"kan dette justeres ved :ref:`bogføring af den oprindelige IGA-post "
"<manufacturing/basic_setup/post-wip-entries>` ved hjælp af "
"feltet :guilabel:`Tilbageførselsdato`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:142
msgid "Verify WIP entries"
msgstr "Verificer IGA-poster"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:144
msgid ""
"To verify that |WIP| accounting entries are being :ref:`posted "
"<manufacturing/basic_setup/post-wip-entries>` and :ref:`reversed "
"<manufacturing/basic_setup/reverse-wip-entries>` correctly, go "
"to :menuselection:`Accounting --> Reporting --> Balance Sheet`. The values "
"should reflect manufacturing consumption at the time of posting and return "
"to zero once reversed."
msgstr ""
"For at verificere, at |WIP|-regnskabsposter bliver :ref:`bogført "
"<manufacturing/basic_setup/post-wip-entries>` og :ref:`tilbageført "
"<manufacturing/basic_setup/reverse-wip-entries>` korrekt, skal du gå "
"til :menuselection:`Regnskab --> Rapportering --> Statusopgørelse`. "
"Værdierne skal afspejle produktionsforbrug på bogføringstidspunktet og vende "
"tilbage til nul, når de er tilbageført."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/basic_setup/work_in_progress.rst:151
msgid ""
"If the |WIP| accounting entries do not appear as expected in the *Balance "
"Sheet*, double-check the dates and filters applied to ensure they align with "
"the posting and reversal dates of the |WIP| accounting entries."
msgstr ""
"Hvis |WIP|-regnskabsposterne ikke vises som forventet i *Statusopgørelse*, "
"skal du dobbelttjekke datoer og filtre for at sikre, at de stemmer overens "
"med bogførings- og tilbageførselsdatoerne for |WIP|-regnskabsposterne."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:3
msgid "Allocation reports"
msgstr "Allokeringsrapporter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:11
msgid ""
"When fulfilling sales orders (SOs), or sourcing components for manufacturing "
"orders (MOs), it is sometimes necessary to prioritize one |SO| or |MO| over "
"another. In situations where there is insufficient stock on-hand to fulfill "
"every |SO| or |MO|, ensuring that products and components are reserved for "
"priority orders is essential."
msgstr ""
"Når salgsordrer (SO'er) opfyldes, eller komponenter til produktionsordrer "
"(PO'er) indkøbes, er det nogle gange nødvendigt at prioritere én |SO| eller "
"|MO| over en anden. I situationer, hvor der ikke er tilstrækkelig "
"lagerbeholdning til at opfylde hver |SO| eller |MO|, er det essentielt at "
"sikre, at produkter og komponenter er reserveret til prioriterede ordrer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:16
msgid ""
"In Odoo *Manufacturing*, allocation reports are used on |MOs| to assign "
"products to specific sales orders |SOs|, or components to specific |MOs|. "
"This ensures the products or components are available for those orders, and "
"are not used by mistake."
msgstr ""
"I Odoo *Produktion* anvendes allokeringsrapporter på |MOs| til at tildele "
"produkter til specifikke salgsordrer |SOs|, eller komponenter til specifikke "
"|MOs|. Dette sikrer, at produkterne eller komponenterne er tilgængelige til "
"disse ordrer, og ikke anvendes ved en fejl."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:23
msgid ""
"To use allocation reports, the *Allocation Report for Manufacturing Orders* "
"feature **must** be enabled. To do so, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Configuration --> Settings`, and "
"tick the checkbox next to :guilabel:`Allocation Report for Manufacturing "
"Orders`. Then, click :guilabel:`Save`."
msgstr ""
"For at bruge allokeringsrapporter **skal** funktionen *Allokeringsrapport "
"for produktionsordrer* være aktiveret. For at gøre dette skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion-app --> Konfiguration --> Indstillinger`, og "
"sætte flueben ud for :guilabel:`Allokeringsrapport for produktionsordrer`. "
"Klik derefter på :guilabel:`Gem`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:28
msgid ""
"For products that are sold, it is also necessary to configure them so they "
"can be included in |SOs|. To do so, begin by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Inventory --> Products --> Products`, and select a "
"product. Under the :guilabel:`Product Name` field on the product form, make "
"sure that the :guilabel:`Can Be Sold` checkbox is ticked."
msgstr ""
"For produkter, der sælges, er det også nødvendigt at konfigurere dem, så de "
"kan inkluderes i |SOs|. For at gøre dette skal du begynde med at navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Lager --> Produkter --> Produkter`, og vælge et produkt. "
"Under feltet :guilabel:`Produktnavn` på produktformularen skal du sikre, at "
"afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Kan sælges` er markeret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:34
msgid "Allocate products"
msgstr "Alloker produkter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:36
msgid ""
"To allocate products or components from an |MO| to an |SO|, or to a "
"different |MO|, begin by navigating to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> "
"Operations --> Manufacturing Orders`. Click :guilabel:`New` to create a new |"
"MO|."
msgstr ""
"For at allokere produkter eller komponenter fra en |MO| til en |SO|, eller "
"til en anden |MO|, skal du begynde med at navigere til "
":menuselection:`Produktion-app --> Operationer --> Produktionsordrer`. Klik "
"på :guilabel:`Ny` for at oprette en ny |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:40
msgid ""
"On the |MO| form, select a product in the :guilabel:`Product` field, and "
"specify the quantity to be produced in the :guilabel:`Quantity` field. "
"Finally, click :guilabel:`Confirm` to confirm the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"På |MO|-formularen skal du vælge et produkt i feltet :guilabel:`Produkt`, og "
"angive mængden, der skal produceres, i feltet :guilabel:`Mængde`. Klik til "
"sidst på :guilabel:`Bekræft` for at bekræfte |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:43
msgid ""
"The rest of the allocation workflow depends on the current on-hand quantity "
"of the product being manufactured, and whether or not there are any |SOs| or "
"|MOs| which require the product, but have not already been allocated units."
msgstr ""
"Resten af allokeringsarbejdsgangen afhænger af den aktuelle lagerbeholdning "
"af det produkt, der fremstilles, og hvorvidt der er nogen |SOs| eller |MOs|, "
"som kræver produktet, men som endnu ikke har fået allokeret enheder."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:47
msgid ""
"If there **are** existing |SOs| and |MOs| that require the product, **and** "
"there are too few units of the product on-hand to fulfill those orders, then "
"an :icon:`fa-list` :guilabel:`Allocation` smart button appears at the top of "
"the page as soon as the |MO| is confirmed."
msgstr ""
"Hvis der **er** eksisterende |SOs| og |MOs|, der kræver produktet, **og** "
"der er for få enheder af produktet på lager til at opfylde disse ordrer, "
"vises der en :icon:`fa-list` :guilabel:`Allokering`-smartknap øverst på "
"siden, så snart |MO| er bekræftet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:51
msgid ""
"If there **are** existing |SOs| and |MOs| that require the product, **and** "
"there are enough units of the product on-hand to fulfill those orders, then "
"the :icon:`fa-list` :guilabel:`Allocation` smart button only appears at the "
"top of the page once the |MO| has been marked as done, by "
"clicking :guilabel:`Produce All`."
msgstr ""
"Hvis der **er** eksisterende |SOs| og |MOs|, der kræver produktet, **og** "
"der er nok enheder af produktet på lager til at opfylde disse ordrer, vises "
":icon:`fa-list` :guilabel:`Allokering`-smartknappen først øverst på siden, "
"når |MO| er blevet markeret som udført ved at klikke på :guilabel:`Producer "
"alle`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:None
msgid "The Allocation smart button at the top of an MO."
msgstr "Smartknappen Allokering øverst på en PO."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:61
msgid ""
"If there **are not** any existing |SOs| and |MOs| that require the product, "
"the :icon:`fa-list` :guilabel:`Allocation` smart button does not appear, "
"even when the |MO| has been marked as done."
msgstr ""
"Hvis der **ikke** er nogen eksisterende |SOs| og |MOs|, der kræver "
"produktet, vises :icon:`fa-list` :guilabel:`Allokering`-smartknappen ikke, "
"selv når |MO| er blevet markeret som udført."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:64
msgid ""
"Click the :icon:`fa-list` :guilabel:`Allocation` smart button to open "
"the :guilabel:`MRP Reception Report` for the |MO|. This report lists open "
"delivery orders or |MOs|, depending on the type of product produced in the "
"original |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Klik på :icon:`fa-list` :guilabel:`Allokering`-smartknappen for at åbne "
":guilabel:`MRP-modtagelsesrapport` for |MO|. Denne rapport viser åbne "
"leveringsordrer eller |MOs|, afhængigt af typen af produkt, der produceres i "
"den oprindelige |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:69
msgid "Allocate to delivery order"
msgstr "Alloker til leveringsordre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:71
msgid ""
"If the |MO| contains a finished product, the report lists any open delivery "
"orders for which quantities of the product have yet to be reserved."
msgstr ""
"Hvis |MO| indeholder et færdigt produkt, viser rapporten eventuelle åbne "
"leveringsordrer, for hvilke mængder af produktet endnu ikke er blevet "
"reserveret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:75
msgid ""
"An |MO| is created to produce three units of a *rocking chair*. Clicking "
"the :guilabel:`Allocation` smart button on the |MO| opens an allocation "
"report that lists open delivery orders that require one or more rocking "
"chairs."
msgstr ""
"Der oprettes en |MO| til at producere tre enheder af en *gyngestol*. Når du "
"klikker på :guilabel:`Allokering`-smartknappen på |MO|, åbnes en "
"allokeringsrapport, der viser åbne leveringsordrer, der kræver en eller "
"flere gyngestole."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:79
msgid ""
"Click the :guilabel:`Assign All` button to the right of a specific order to "
"assign products for each quantity required to fulfill that order."
msgstr ""
"Klik på knappen :guilabel:`Tildel alle` til højre for en specifik ordre for "
"at tildele produkter til hver mængde, der kræves for at opfylde den ordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:83
msgid ""
"If an order requires one quantity of four units of the product, and one "
"quantity of one unit of the product, clicking :guilabel:`Assign All` assigns "
"five units of the product to fulfill both quantities."
msgstr ""
"Hvis en ordre kræver én mængde på fire enheder af produktet og én mængde på "
"én enhed af produktet, tildeler klik på :guilabel:`Tildel alle` fem enheder "
"af produktet for at opfylde begge mængder."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:87
msgid ""
"Alternatively, click :guilabel:`Assign` next to a specific quantity to only "
"assign products to that quantity, and not any others in the order."
msgstr ""
"Alternativt kan du klikke på :guilabel:`Tildel` ved siden af et specifikt "
"antal for kun at tildele produkter til det pågældende antal og ikke til "
"andre i ordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:91
msgid ""
"If an order requires one quantity of four units of the product, and one "
"quantity of one unit of the product, clicking :guilabel:`Assign` next to the "
"quantity of one unit assigns a product to that quantity, but leaves the "
"quantity of four units without any products assigned."
msgstr ""
"Hvis en ordre kræver ét antal på fire enheder af produktet og ét antal på en "
"enhed af produktet, vil et klik på :guilabel:`Tildel` ved siden af antallet "
"på en enhed tildele et produkt til det pågældende antal, men efterlade "
"antallet på fire enheder uden tildelte produkter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:None
msgid "The MRP Reception Report for an MO containing finished products."
msgstr ""
"MRP-modtagelsesrapporten for en produktionsordre, der indeholder færdige "
"produkter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:100
msgid "Allocate to MO"
msgstr "Alloker til produktionsordre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:102
msgid ""
"If the |MO| contains a component, the report lists any open |MOs| for which "
"quantities of the component have yet to be reserved."
msgstr ""
"Hvis |MO| indeholder en komponent, viser rapporten alle åbne |MOs|, hvor "
"mængder af komponenten endnu ikke er reserveret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:106
msgid ""
"An |MO| is created to produce three units of *wood*, which is used as a "
"component for the *rocking chair* product. Clicking "
"the :guilabel:`Allocation` smart button on the |MO| opens an allocation "
"report that lists open rocking chair |MOs| that require one or more pieces "
"of wood."
msgstr ""
"Der oprettes en |MO| til at producere tre enheder *træ*, som bruges som "
"komponent til produktet *gyngestol*. Et klik på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Allokering` på |MO| åbner en allokeringsrapport, der "
"viser åbne gyngestols-|MOs|, som kræver et eller flere stykker træ."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:110
msgid ""
"Click the :guilabel:`Assign All` or :guilabel:`Assign` button to the right "
"of a specific |MO| to assign components to that |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Klik på knappen :guilabel:`Tildel alle` eller :guilabel:`Tildel` til højre "
"for en specifik |MO| for at tildele komponenter til den pågældende |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:None
msgid "The MRP Reception Report for an MO containing components."
msgstr ""
"MRP-modtagelsesrapporten for en produktionsordre, der indeholder komponenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:118
msgid "Unassign products"
msgstr "Fjern tildelte produkter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:120
msgid ""
"After assigning products to a quantity within a delivery order, or "
"components to an |MO|, the :guilabel:`Assign` button turns into "
"an :guilabel:`Unassign` button. Click :guilabel:`Unassign` to unreserve the "
"assigned products from that quantity, making them available for other "
"quantities."
msgstr ""
"Efter tildeling af produkter til et antal i en leveringsordre eller "
"komponenter til en |MO| ændres knappen :guilabel:`Tildel` til "
"en :guilabel:`Fjern tildeling`-knap. Klik på :guilabel:`Fjern tildeling` for "
"at fjerne reservationen af de tildelte produkter fra det pågældende antal og "
"gøre dem tilgængelige for andre antal."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:125
msgid "Print labels"
msgstr "Udskriv etiketter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:127
msgid ""
"After clicking :guilabel:`Assign All` or :guilabel:`Assign`, "
"the :guilabel:`Print Labels` or :guilabel:`Print Label` button to the right "
"of either button becomes selectable. Selecting either button generates and "
"downloads a PDF document with one label for each product that was assigned. "
"These labels are used to designate each product as being reserved for that "
"specific order."
msgstr ""
"Efter at have klikket på :guilabel:`Tildel alle` eller :guilabel:`Tildel` "
"bliver knappen :guilabel:`Udskriv etiketter` eller :guilabel:`Udskriv "
"etiket` til højre for begge knapper valgbar. Valg af en af knapperne "
"genererer og downloader et PDF-dokument med en etiket for hvert produkt, der "
"blev tildelt. Disse etiketter bruges til at markere hvert produkt som "
"reserveret til den specifikke ordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/allocation.rst:None
msgid ""
"The assignment labels generated by clicking Print Labels or Print Label."
msgstr ""
"Tildelingsetiketterne genereret ved at klikke på Udskriv etiketter eller "
"Udskriv etiket."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:3
msgid "Delays"
msgstr "Forsinkelser"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:11
msgid ""
"Odoo's *Manufacturing* app displays *delays* in manufacturing orders through "
"the :guilabel:`Delayed Productions` filter. If the |MO|'s end date exceeds "
"its deadline, the deadline is highlighted in red to draw attention to the "
"delay."
msgstr ""
"Odoo's *Produktion*-app viser *forsinkelser* i produktionsordrer gennem "
"filteret :guilabel:`Forsinkede produktioner`. Hvis |MO|'s slutdato "
"overskrider dens deadline, fremhæves deadlinen med rødt for at gøre "
"opmærksom på forsinkelsen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:None
msgid "The delayed production filter in Odoo."
msgstr "Filteret for forsinket produktion i Odoo."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:19
msgid "Deadline calculation"
msgstr "Beregning af deadline"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:21
msgid ""
"The |MO| deadline depends on how the |MO| was created, and is calculated as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""
"|MO|-deadlinenafhænger af, hvordan |MO| blev oprettet, og beregnes som "
"følger:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:23
msgid ""
"**Make To Order**: the |MO| deadline is the *Sales Order Delivery Date*."
msgstr ""
"**Fremstil til ordre**: |MO|-deadlinen er *leveringsdatoen for salgsordren*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:24
msgid ""
"**Replenishment**: the |MO| deadline is *today + Manufacturing Lead Time*."
msgstr "**Genopfyldning**: |MO|-deadlinen er *i dag + produktionsledetid*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:25
msgid "**Manually created MO**: the deadline field remains empty."
msgstr "**Manuelt oprettet produktionsordre**: fristfeltet forbliver tomt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:28
msgid "The |MO| *deadline* is not the same as the |MO| *end date*."
msgstr "|MO| *fristen* er ikke det samme som |MO| *slutdatoen*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:30
msgid "The end date is computed as:"
msgstr "Slutdatoen beregnes som:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:32
msgid ""
"\\text{End date} =\n"
" \\text{Scheduled start date}\n"
" +\\text{Total duration of all operations}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\\text{Slutdato} =\n"
" \\text{Planlagt startdato}\n"
" +\\text{Samlet varighed af alle operationer}\n"
"\n"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:40
msgid "Several additional filters are available to help track delays:"
msgstr ""
"Flere yderligere filtre er tilgængelige til at hjælpe med at spore "
"forsinkelser:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:42
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Delayed Productions`: the |MO|'s *scheduled start date* is later "
"than the deadline."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Forsinkede produktioner`: |MO|'s *planlagte startdato* er senere "
"end fristen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:43
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Late`: the |MO|'s *scheduled end date* exceeds the deadline, "
"highlighted in red."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Forsinket`: |MO|'s *planlagte slutdato* overskrider fristen, "
"fremhævet med rødt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:44
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Late Availability`: one or more required components are not "
"available before the deadline. For example, a confirmed purchase order or "
"manufacturing order for components is scheduled to end *after* the |MO| "
"deadline."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Forsinket tilgængelighed`: en eller flere nødvendige komponenter "
"er ikke tilgængelige før fristen. For eksempel er en bekræftet indkøbsordre "
"eller produktionsordre for komponenter planlagt til at slutte *efter* |MO| "
"fristen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:47
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Components Available`: all components are available to begin "
"production."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Komponenter tilgængelige`: alle komponenter er tilgængelige til "
"at påbegynde produktion."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:50
msgid "Use case"
msgstr "Anvendelseseksempel"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:52
msgid "Consider an |MO| with a deadline of **September 17th**:"
msgstr "Overvej en |MO| med en frist den **17. september**:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:54
msgid ""
"If production on the |MO| starts after September 17th, it appears in "
"the :guilabel:`Delayed Productions` filter."
msgstr ""
"Hvis produktion på |MO| starter efter 17. september, vises den i filteret "
":guilabel:`Forsinkede produktioner`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:56
msgid ""
"If required components are scheduled to arrive after September 17th, the |"
"MO| appears in the :guilabel:`Late Availability` filter."
msgstr ""
"Hvis nødvendige komponenter er planlagt til at ankomme efter 17. september, "
"vises |MO| i filteret :guilabel:`Forsinket tilgængelighed`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:58
msgid ""
"If the |MO| has a scheduled end date after September 17th, it appears in "
"the :guilabel:`Late` filter."
msgstr ""
"Hvis |MO| har en planlagt slutdato efter 17. september, vises den i filteret "
":guilabel:`Forsinket`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:None
msgid "An MO with the deadline emphasized."
msgstr "En produktionsordre med fremhævet frist."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/delayed.rst:64
msgid ""
"By combining these indicators, planners can quickly identify where "
"production is at risk of missing delivery commitments."
msgstr ""
"Ved at kombinere disse indikatorer kan planlæggere hurtigt identificere, "
"hvor produktionen risikerer at misse leveringsforpligtelser."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:3
msgid "Overall equipment effectiveness"
msgstr "Samlet udstyrseffektivitet"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:9
msgid ""
"In Odoo's *Manufacturing* app, *overall equipment effectiveness* (OEE) "
"represents the amount of time a work center is fully productive. |OEE| is "
"displayed as a percentage of the total time a work center is active."
msgstr ""
"I Odoos *Produktion*-app repræsenterer *samlet udstyrseffektivitet* (OEE) "
"den tid, hvor et arbejdscenter er fuldt produktivt. |OEE| vises som en "
"procentdel af den samlede tid, et arbejdscenter er aktivt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:13
msgid ""
"Fully productive time is considered to be time when the work center is "
"operational **and** processing work orders that have not exceeded their "
"*expected duration*."
msgstr ""
"Fuldt produktiv tid betragtes som tid, hvor arbejdscenteret er operationelt "
"**og** behandler arbejdsordrer, der ikke har overskredet deres *forventede "
"varighed*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:16
msgid ""
"|OEE| helps manufacturing teams understand the efficiency of work centers, "
"and the causes of manufacturing downtime."
msgstr ""
"|OEE| hjælper produktionsteams med at forstå effektiviteten af arbejdscentre "
"og årsagerne til produktionsstop."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:20
msgid ""
"Since |OEE| tracks work center productivity, using it requires enabling the "
"work centers feature in the settings of the Manufacturing app."
msgstr ""
"Da |OEE| sporer arbejdscenterets produktivitet, kræver brugen af det, at "
"funktionen arbejdscentre aktiveres i indstillingerne for Produktion-appen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:23
msgid ""
"To do so, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Configuration --"
"> Settings`, and tick the checkbox next to :guilabel:`Work Orders`, under "
"the :guilabel:`Operations` heading. Then, click :guilabel:`Save`."
msgstr ""
"For at gøre dette skal du navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion-appen --> "
"Konfiguration --> Indstillinger` og sætte flueben "
"ved :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer` under overskriften :guilabel:`Operationer`. "
"Klik derefter på :guilabel:`Gem`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:28
msgid "Efficiency standards"
msgstr "Effektivitetsstandarder"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:30
msgid ""
"For |OEE| to accurately reflect the percentage of fully productive time for "
"a work center, the work center **must** be properly configured with the "
"correct productivity metrics. These include the work center's *time "
"efficiency*, *capacity*, and *OEE target*."
msgstr ""
"For at |OEE| præcist afspejler procentdelen af fuldt produktiv tid for et "
"arbejdscenter, **skal** arbejdscentret være korrekt konfigureret med de "
"rigtige produktivitetsmålinger. Disse omfatter arbejdscenterets "
"*tidseffektivitet*, *kapacitet* og *OEE-mål*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:35
msgid "Time efficiency"
msgstr "Tidseffektivitet"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:37
msgid ""
"Time efficiency represents the efficiency of a work center when processing "
"work orders, and is represented as a percentage. A time efficiency value of "
"100% signifies that the work center processes work orders at the speed of "
"the expected duration, as listed on a product's |BoM|. A value less than or "
"greater than 100% signifies that the work center processes work orders "
"slower or faster than an operation's expected duration, respectively."
msgstr ""
"Tidseffektivitet repræsenterer effektiviteten af et arbejdscenter ved "
"behandling af arbejdsordrer og vises som en procentdel. En "
"tidseffektivitetsværdi på 100% betyder, at arbejdscentret behandler "
"arbejdsordrer med hastigheden af den forventede varighed, som angivet på et "
"produkts |BoM|. En værdi mindre end eller større end 100% betyder, at "
"arbejdscentret behandler arbejdsordrer henholdsvis langsommere eller "
"hurtigere end en operations forventede varighed."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:43
msgid ""
"To set the time efficiency for a work center, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Configuration --> Work Centers`, "
"and select a work center. On the :guilabel:`General Information` tab, enter "
"a numerical value in the :guilabel:`Time Efficiency` field."
msgstr ""
"For at indstille tidseffektiviteten for et arbejdscenter skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion-appen --> Konfiguration --> Arbejdscentre` og "
"vælge et arbejdscenter. På fanen :guilabel:`Generelle oplysninger` skal du "
"indtaste en numerisk værdi i feltet :guilabel:`Tidseffektivitet`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:48
msgid ""
"Manufacturing a *chair* product requires two operations: *cut* and "
"*assemble*. The product's |BoM| lists an expected duration of 30 minutes for "
"each operation."
msgstr ""
"Fremstilling af et *stol*-produkt kræver to operationer: *klip* og "
"*samling*. Produktets |BoM| angiver en forventet varighed på 30 minutter for "
"hver operation."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:51
msgid ""
"The cut operation is carried out at the *cut station* work center, which has "
"a time efficiency value of 50%. This means it takes twice as long to "
"complete the operation, for a total time of one hour."
msgstr ""
"Klipoperationen udføres ved arbejdscentret *klipstation*, som har en "
"tidseffektivitetsværdi på 50%. Det betyder, at det tager dobbelt så lang tid "
"at gennemføre operationen, for en samlet tid på en time."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:55
msgid ""
"The assemble operation is carried out at the *assembly line* work center, "
"which has a time efficiency value of 200%. This means it takes half as long "
"to complete the operation, for a total time of 15 minutes."
msgstr ""
"Samlingsoperationen udføres ved arbejdscentret *samlebånd*, som har en "
"tidseffektivitetsværdi på 200%. Det betyder, at det tager halvt så lang tid "
"at gennemføre operationen, for en samlet tid på 15 minutter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:60
msgid "Capacity"
msgstr "Kapacitet"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:62
msgid ""
"Capacity represents how many units of a product can be produced in parallel "
"at a work center. The duration of work orders for multiple units increases "
"or decreases, based on how many units the work center can handle."
msgstr ""
"Kapacitet repræsenterer, hvor mange enheder af et produkt der kan produceres "
"parallelt ved et arbejdscenter. Varigheden af arbejdsordrer for flere "
"enheder stiger eller falder baseret på, hvor mange enheder arbejdscentret "
"kan håndtere."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:66
msgid ""
"To set the capacity for a work center, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Configuration --> Work Centers`, "
"and select a work center. On the :guilabel:`General Information` tab, enter "
"a numerical value in the :guilabel:`Capacity` field."
msgstr ""
"For at indstille kapaciteten for et arbejdscenter skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion-appen --> Konfiguration --> Arbejdscentre` og "
"vælge et arbejdscenter. På fanen :guilabel:`Generelle oplysninger` skal du "
"indtaste en numerisk værdi i feltet :guilabel:`Kapacitet`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:71
msgid ""
"A *drill station* work center has a capacity of one unit. An |MO| is "
"confirmed for 10 units of a *chair*, a product manufactured using the drill "
"station."
msgstr ""
"Et arbejdscenter *borestation* har en kapacitet på én enhed. En |MO| "
"bekræftes for 10 enheder af en *stol*, et produkt fremstillet ved hjælp af "
"borestationen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:74
msgid ""
"Since there are ten times as many units to produce than the work center can "
"handle at once, the operation time is ten times the duration listed on the "
"product's |BoM|."
msgstr ""
"Da der er ti gange så mange enheder at producere, som arbejdscentret kan "
"håndtere på én gang, er operationstiden ti gange varigheden angivet på "
"produktets |BoM|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:78
msgid "|OEE| target"
msgstr "|OEE|-mål"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:80
msgid ""
"The |OEE| target is the goal for how much of a work center's operating time "
"should be fully productive time. It is displayed as a percentage, and should "
"only be set as high as `100%`."
msgstr ""
"|OEE|-målet er målet for, hvor meget af et arbejdscenters driftstid der skal "
"være fuldt produktiv tid. Det vises som en procentdel og bør kun sættes så "
"højt som `100%`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:83
msgid ""
"To set the |OEE| target for a work center, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Configuration --> Settings --> Work "
"Centers`, and select a work center. On the :guilabel:`General Information` "
"tab, enter a numerical value of `100.00` or less in the :guilabel:`OEE "
"Target` field."
msgstr ""
"For at indstille |OEE|-målet for et arbejdscenter skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion-appen --> Konfiguration --> Indstillinger --> "
"Arbejdscentre` og vælge et arbejdscenter. På fanen :guilabel:`Generelle "
"oplysninger` skal du indtaste en numerisk værdi på `100.00` eller mindre i "
"feltet :guilabel:`OEE-mål`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:88
msgid "Calculating |OEE|"
msgstr "Beregning af |OEE|"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:90
msgid ""
"|OEE| is represented as a percentage value between zero and 100. The value "
"signifies the amount of time that a work center was fully productive. The "
"remainder signifies the amount of time that the work center was operating at "
"less than full efficiency. This can occur for a number of reasons, including "
"*reduced speed*, *material availability*, and *equipment failure*."
msgstr ""
"|OEE| repræsenteres som en procentværdi mellem nul og 100. Værdien angiver "
"den tid, hvor et arbejdscenter var fuldt produktivt. Resten angiver den tid, "
"hvor arbejdscentret opererede med mindre end fuld effektivitet. Dette kan "
"ske af en række årsager, herunder *reduceret hastighed*, "
"*materialetilgængelighed* og *udstyrsfejl*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:96
msgid "Fully productive time"
msgstr "Fuldt produktiv tid"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:98
msgid ""
"For a work center to be considered fully productive, it must be able to "
"receive work orders, have the components necessary to process work orders, "
"and be operating within the expected duration of the work order it is "
"processing."
msgstr ""
"For at et arbejdscenter kan betragtes som fuldt produktivt, skal det kunne "
"modtage arbejdsordrer, have de nødvendige komponenter til at behandle "
"arbejdsordrer og være i drift inden for den forventede varighed af den "
"arbejdsordre, det behandler."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:103
msgid ""
"An *assembly line* work center is not blocked, and receives a work order to "
"assemble a *bicycle*. The required components are available, so production "
"begins as soon as they are picked and delivered to the work center. The work "
"order has an expected duration of 30 minutes, and is completed in 27 "
"minutes. All of this time is considered fully productive time."
msgstr ""
"Et arbejdscenter med *samlebånd* er ikke blokeret og modtager en "
"arbejdsordre til at samle en *cykel*. De nødvendige komponenter er "
"tilgængelige, så produktionen begynder, så snart de er plukket og leveret "
"til arbejdscentret. Arbejdsordren har en forventet varighed på 30 minutter "
"og er afsluttet på 27 minutter. Hele denne tid betragtes som fuldt produktiv "
"tid."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:109
msgid "Reduced speed"
msgstr "Reduceret hastighed"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:111
msgid ""
"When a work center is operating at reduced speed, it means that it is "
"processing a work order that has exceeded its expected duration. While the "
"work center may be operational, this is not considered fully productive time."
msgstr ""
"Når et arbejdscenter kører med reduceret hastighed, betyder det, at det "
"behandler en arbejdsordre, der har overskredet sin forventede varighed. "
"Selvom arbejdscentret kan være operationelt, betragtes dette ikke som fuldt "
"produktiv tid."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:116
msgid ""
"A *cutting station* work center receives a work order to cut boards for a "
"*table*. The expected duration of the work order is 15 minutes. The work "
"order ends up taking 18 minutes to complete. The work center is considered "
"to have been operating at reduced speed during the three minutes that "
"exceeded the expected duration."
msgstr ""
"Et arbejdscenter med *skærestation* modtager en arbejdsordre til at skære "
"brædder til et *bord*. Den forventede varighed af arbejdsordren er 15 "
"minutter. Arbejdsordren ender med at tage 18 minutter at fuldføre. "
"Arbejdscentret betragtes som at have kørt med reduceret hastighed i de tre "
"minutter, der overskred den forventede varighed."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:122
msgid "Material availability"
msgstr "Materialetilgængelighed"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:124
msgid ""
"Material availability refers to situations where a work center is able to "
"accept a work order, but the required components are not available. This can "
"occur because the components are not in stock, or are reserved for a "
"different order."
msgstr ""
"Materialetilgængelighed refererer til situationer, hvor et arbejdscenter er "
"i stand til at acceptere en arbejdsordre, men de nødvendige komponenter ikke "
"er tilgængelige. Dette kan forekomme, fordi komponenterne ikke er på lager "
"eller er reserveret til en anden ordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:129
msgid ""
"Manufacturing of a *bench* requires 20 units of *wood*. A manufacturing "
"order (MO) is confirmed for 10 units of the bench, but there is not enough "
"wood in stock to begin manufacturing. The time it takes to acquire the wood "
"is recorded as material availability downtime."
msgstr ""
"Produktion af en *bænk* kræver 20 enheder *træ*. En produktionsordre (MO) "
"bekræftes for 10 enheder af bænken, men der er ikke nok træ på lager til at "
"begynde produktionen. Den tid, det tager at anskaffe træet, registreres som "
"nedetid på grund af materialetilgængelighed."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:134
msgid "Equipment failure"
msgstr "Udstyrssvigt"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:136
msgid ""
"Equipment failure signifies any period of time when a work center is "
"unusable due to maintenance issues with its equipment. This can be due to "
"equipment breaking down, or when a work center is shut down for scheduled "
"maintenance. In these cases, a work center can be blocked using "
"a :doc:`maintenance request <../../maintenance/maintenance_requests>`."
msgstr ""
"Udstyrssvigt betyder enhver periode, hvor et arbejdscenter er ubrugeligt på "
"grund af vedligeholdelsesproblemer med dets udstyr. Dette kan skyldes, at "
"udstyr går i stykker, eller når et arbejdscenter lukkes ned for planlagt "
"vedligeholdelse. I disse tilfælde kan et arbejdscenter blokeres ved hjælp af "
"en :doc:`vedligeholdelsesanmodning <../../maintenance/maintenance_requests>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:142
msgid ""
"The drill at a *drill station* work center breaks down, causing the work "
"center to be unusable. A maintenance request is created to fix the drill, "
"and the work center is blocked from receiving work orders. It takes two "
"hours to fix the drill, and make the work center available again. This two-"
"hour period is recorded as equipment failure downtime."
msgstr ""
"Boret på et arbejdscenter med *borestation* går i stykker, hvilket gør "
"arbejdscentret ubrugeligt. Der oprettes en vedligeholdelsesanmodning for at "
"reparere boret, og arbejdscentret blokeres fra at modtage arbejdsordrer. Det "
"tager to timer at reparere boret og gøre arbejdscentret tilgængeligt igen. "
"Denne to-timers periode registreres som nedetid på grund af udstyrssvigt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:148
msgid "|OEE| reporting"
msgstr "|OEE|-rapportering"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:150
msgid ""
"To view |OEE| reporting metrics for every work center, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Reporting --> Overall Equipment "
"Effectiveness`. This page shows the metrics for each work center with |OEE| "
"data."
msgstr ""
"For at se |OEE|-rapporteringsmålinger for hvert arbejdscenter skal du "
"navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Rapportering --> Samlet "
"udstyrseffektivitet`. Denne side viser målingerne for hvert arbejdscenter "
"med |OEE|-data."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:154
msgid ""
"Alternatively, to see |OEE| reporting metrics for a single work center, "
"navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Configuration --> Work "
"Centers`, and select a work center. At the top of the work center's form, "
"click the :icon:`fa-pie-chart` :guilabel:`OEE` smart button."
msgstr ""
"Alternativt kan du se |OEE|-rapporteringsmålinger for et enkelt "
"arbejdscenter ved at navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion --> "
"Konfiguration --> Arbejdscentre` og vælge et arbejdscenter. Øverst på "
"arbejdscentrets formular skal du klikke på den smarte knap :icon:`fa-pie-"
"chart` :guilabel:`OEE`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:158
msgid ""
"By default, the main |OEE| reporting page shows data in a bar chart, while "
"the page for a specific work center shows it in a pie chart. To select a "
"different chart type on either page, click the :icon:`fa-bar-"
"chart` :guilabel:`(bar chart)`, :icon:`fa-line-chart` :guilabel:`(line "
"chart)`, or :icon:`fa-pie-chart` :guilabel:`(pie chart)` button above the "
"displayed chart."
msgstr ""
"Som standard viser hoved-|OEE|-rapporteringssiden data i et søjlediagram, "
"mens siden for et specifikt arbejdscenter viser det i et cirkeldiagram. For "
"at vælge en anden diagramtype på begge sider skal du klikke på "
"knappen :icon:`fa-bar-chart` :guilabel:`(søjlediagram)`, :icon:`fa-line-"
"chart` :guilabel:`(kurvediagram)` eller :icon:`fa-pie-"
"chart` :guilabel:`(cirkeldiagram)` over det viste diagram."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:163
msgid ""
"It is also possible to see |OEE| data in a pivot view, or a list displaying "
"each time entry, by clicking the :icon:`oi-view-pivot` :guilabel:`(pivot "
"view)` or :icon:`oi-view-list` :guilabel:`(list view)` buttons at the top-"
"right corner of the page."
msgstr ""
"Det er også muligt at se |OEE|-data i en pivotvisning eller en liste, der "
"viser hver tidsindtastning, ved at klikke på knapperne :icon:`oi-view-"
"pivot` :guilabel:`(pivotvisning)` eller :icon:`oi-view-"
"list` :guilabel:`(listevisning)` i øverste højre hjørne af siden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/oee.rst:None
msgid "The dashboard of the OEE report."
msgstr "Dashboardet for OEE-rapporten."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:3
msgid "Production analysis"
msgstr "Produktionsanalyse"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:8
msgid ""
"The *Production Analysis* report provides statistics about products "
"manufactured using Odoo's *Manufacturing* app. The report is useful when "
"trying to understand production costs, manufacturing durations, and other "
"important statistics about manufactured products."
msgstr ""
"*Produktionsanalyse*-rapporten giver statistik om produkter fremstillet ved "
"hjælp af Odoos *Produktion*-app. Rapporten er nyttig, når man forsøger at "
"forstå produktionsomkostninger, produktionsvarigheder og andre vigtige "
"statistikker om fremstillede produkter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:12
msgid ""
"To open the Production Analysis report, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Reporting --> Production Analysis`."
msgstr ""
"For at åbne Produktionsanalyse-rapporten skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Rapportering --> Produktionsanalyse`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:16
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Production Analysis` report is one of many reports available "
"across the Odoo app suite. This documentation only covers the measures "
"specific to the :guilabel:`Production Analysis` report, along with a few use "
"case examples."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Produktionsanalyse`-rapporten er en af mange rapporter "
"tilgængelige på tværs af Odoo-apppakken. Denne dokumentation dækker kun de "
"målinger, der er specifikke for :guilabel:`Produktionsanalyse`-rapporten, "
"sammen med nogle få eksempler på anvendelsestilfælde."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:20
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/purchase/advanced/analyze.rst:21
msgid ""
"For a full overview of the basic features available in most Odoo reports, "
"see the documentation on :doc:`reporting essentials <../../../essentials/"
"reporting>`."
msgstr ""
"For en fuld oversigt over de grundlæggende funktioner, der er tilgængelige i "
"de fleste Odoo-rapporter, se dokumentationen om :doc:`rapporteringsgrundlag "
"<../../../essentials/reporting>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:24
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/purchase/advanced/analyze.rst:25
msgid "Measures"
msgstr "Mål"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:26
msgid ""
"*Measures* are the datasets that can be selected in "
"the :guilabel:`Production Analysis` report. Each dataset represents a "
"specific statistic about |MOs| in the database. Choose a measure by clicking "
"the :guilabel:`Measures` :icon:`fa-caret-down` button, and selecting one of "
"the options from the drop-down menu:"
msgstr ""
"*Målinger* er de datasæt, der kan vælges i :guilabel:`produktionsanalyse`-"
"rapporten. Hvert datasæt repræsenterer en specifik statistik om |MOs| i "
"databasen. Vælg en måling ved at klikke på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Målinger` :icon:`fa-caret-down`, og vælg en af "
"mulighederne fra rullemenuen:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:31
msgid ""
"The options displayed in the :guilabel:`Measures` :icon:`fa-caret-down` drop-"
"down menu, and the order they appear in, differ depending on the filters, "
"groupings, and comparisons enabled in the :guilabel:`Search...` bar. By "
"default, the available measures appear as follows:"
msgstr ""
"De muligheder, der vises i :guilabel:`Målinger` :icon:`fa-caret-down` "
"rullemenuen, og den rækkefølge, de vises i, varierer afhængigt af de filtre, "
"grupperinger og sammenligninger, der er aktiveret i :guilabel:`Søg...`-"
"bjælken. Som standard vises de tilgængelige målinger som følger:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:35
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Average Employee Cost/Unit`: the average cost paid to employees "
"to produce one unit of the product."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Gennemsnitlig medarbejderomkostning/enhed`: den gennemsnitlige "
"omkostning betalt til medarbejdere for at producere en enhed af produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:37
msgid ""
":guilabel:`By-Products Total Cost`: the total value of all by-products "
"created by manufacturing the product."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Biprodukter samlet omkostning`: den samlede værdi af alle "
"biprodukter skabt ved fremstilling af produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:39
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Component Cost/Unit`: the average cost of the components required "
"to produce one unit of the product."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Komponentomkostning/enhed`: den gennemsnitlige omkostning af de "
"komponenter, der kræves for at producere en enhed af produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:41
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Cost/Unit`: the average cost of producing one unit of the "
"product, including component, employee, operation, and subcontracting costs."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Omkostning/enhed`: den gennemsnitlige omkostning ved at producere "
"en enhed af produktet, inklusive komponent-, medarbejder-, operations- og "
"underleverandøromkostninger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:43
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Duration of Operations/Unit`: the average total duration of "
"operations required to produce one unit of the product."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Varighed af operationer/enhed`: den gennemsnitlige samlede "
"varighed af operationer, der kræves for at producere en enhed af produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:45
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Quantity Demanded`: the total number of units of the product "
"included in |MOs|."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Ønsket antal`: det samlede antal enheder af produktet inkluderet "
"i |MOs|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:46
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Quantity Produced`: the total number of units of the product that "
"have actually been produced."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Produceret antal`: det samlede antal enheder af produktet, der "
"faktisk er blevet produceret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:48
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Total Component Cost`: the total amount spent on the product's "
"components, across every |MO| for the product."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Samlet komponentomkostning`: det samlede beløb brugt på "
"produktets komponenter, på tværs af alle |MO| for produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:50
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Total Cost`: the total amount spent manufacturing every unit of "
"the product produced so far."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Samlet omkostning`: det samlede beløb brugt på at fremstille hver "
"enhed af produktet produceret indtil videre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:52
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Total Duration of Operations`: the cumulative duration of every "
"operation completed while manufacturing the product."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Samlet varighed af operationer`: den kumulative varighed af hver "
"operation afsluttet under fremstilling af produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:54
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Total Employee Cost`: the cumulative amount paid to employees to "
"manufacture the product."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Samlet medarbejderomkostning`: det kumulative beløb betalt til "
"medarbejdere for at fremstille produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:56
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Total Operation Cost`: the cumulative amount spent on operations "
"required to produce the product."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Samlet operationsomkostning`: det kumulative beløb brugt på "
"operationer, der kræves for at producere produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:58
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Total Operation Cost/Unit`: the average cost of the operations "
"required to produce one unit of the product."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Samlet operationsomkostning/enhed`: den gennemsnitlige omkostning "
"af de operationer, der kræves for at producere en enhed af produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:60
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Total Subcontracting Cost`: the cumulative amount paid to "
"subcontractors to produce the product."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Samlet underleverandøromkostning`: det kumulative beløb betalt "
"til underleverandører for at producere produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:62
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Total Subcontracting Cost/Unit`: the average cost of engaging a "
"subcontractor to produce one unit of the product."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Samlet underleverandøromkostning/enhed`: den gennemsnitlige "
"omkostning ved at engagere en underleverandør til at producere en enhed af "
"produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:64
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Yield Percentage (%)`: the total quantity of the product produced "
"versus the total quantity demanded, represented as a percentage."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Udbytteprocent (%)`: den samlede mængde af produktet produceret "
"versus den samlede ønskede mængde, repræsenteret som en procentsats."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:66
msgid ":guilabel:`Count`: the total count of |MOs| created for the product."
msgstr ":guilabel:`Antal`: det samlede antal |MOs| oprettet for produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:69
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/purchase/advanced/analyze.rst:51
msgid ""
"Only one measure can be selected at a time when one of the :icon:`fa-area-"
"chart` :guilabel:`(graph view)` options is enabled. However, multiple "
"measures, and varying group-by criteria (on the x and y axes), can be "
"selected when using the :icon:`oi-view-pivot` :guilabel:`(pivot table)`."
msgstr ""
"Kun én måling kan vælges ad gangen, når en af :icon:`fa-area-"
"chart` :guilabel:`grafvisning`-indstillingerne er aktiveret. Dog kan flere "
"målinger og varierende grupperingskriterier (på x- og y-akserne) vælges, "
"når :icon:`oi-view-pivot` :guilabel:`pivottabel` bruges."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:75
msgid "Use case: compare products"
msgstr "Brugsscenarie: sammenlign produkter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:77
msgid ""
"One of the best uses for the :guilabel:`Production Analysis` report is "
"comparing statistics about two or more products. This is accomplished by "
"entering the products into the :guilabel:`Search...` bar, then selecting the "
"necessary measure, filter, and grouping, to see the desired data."
msgstr ""
"En af de bedste anvendelser af :guilabel:`Produktionsanalyse`-rapporten er "
"at sammenligne statistikker om to eller flere produkter. Dette gøres ved at "
"indtaste produkterne i :guilabel:`Søg...`-linjen og derefter vælge den "
"nødvendige måling, filter og gruppering for at se de ønskede data."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:82
msgid ""
"Toy manufacturer *Tommy's Toys* is trying to reduce their manufacturing "
"operation costs. To accomplish this, they have decided to identify redundant "
"products and cease manufacturing the ones with higher operational costs."
msgstr ""
"Legetøjsproducenten *Tommy's Toys* forsøger at reducere deres "
"produktionsomkostninger. For at opnå dette har de besluttet at identificere "
"overflødige produkter og ophøre med at producere dem med højere "
"driftsomkostninger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:86
msgid ""
"Two of the toys that have been singled out for analysis are the *pogo stick* "
"and *moon shoes*. Tommy's Toys believes these two toys are so similar that "
"they can stop manufacturing one, without significantly impacting their "
"product offering."
msgstr ""
"To af de legetøj, der er blevet udvalgt til analyse, er *pogo stick* og "
"*moon shoes*. Tommy's Toys mener, at disse to legetøj er så ens, at de kan "
"stoppe produktionen af det ene uden at påvirke deres produktudbud væsentligt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:90
msgid ""
"To compare operation costs for the toys, business analyst Mike opens "
"the :menuselection:`Manufacturing` app, and navigates to "
"the :guilabel:`Production Analysis` page. In the :guilabel:`Search...` bar, "
"he enters the names of both products. Then, he opens "
"the :guilabel:`Search...` bar drop-down menu, and clicks :guilabel:`Product` "
"in the :guilabel:`Group By` section."
msgstr ""
"For at sammenligne driftsomkostninger for legetøjet åbner "
"forretningsanalytiker Mike :menuselection:`Produktion`-appen og navigerer "
"til siden :guilabel:`Produktionsanalyse`. I :guilabel:`Søg...`-linjen "
"indtaster han navnene på begge produkter. Derefter åbner han "
"rullemenuen :guilabel:`Søg...` og klikker på :guilabel:`Produkt` i "
"afsnittet :guilabel:`Gruppér efter`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:96
msgid ""
"Below the :guilabel:`Search...` bar, Mike clicks on "
"the :guilabel:`Measures` :icon:`fa-caret-down` drop-down menu, and selects "
"the :guilabel:`Total Operation Cost/Unit` option. Finally, he selects "
"the :icon:`fa-bar-chart` :guilabel:`(bar chart)` graph type."
msgstr ""
"Under :guilabel:`Søg...`-linjen klikker Mike på "
"rullemenuen :guilabel:`Målinger` :icon:`fa-caret-down` og vælger "
"indstillingen :guilabel:`Samlet driftsomkostning/enhed`. Endelig vælger han "
"graftypen :icon:`fa-bar-chart` :guilabel:`søjlediagram`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:100
msgid ""
"With these options selected, the :guilabel:`Production Analysis` report "
"shows a bar chart for the current year, with one bar for each product, "
"signifying the average operation cost for one unit of the product."
msgstr ""
"Med disse indstillinger valgt viser :guilabel:`Produktionsanalyse`-rapporten "
"et søjlediagram for det aktuelle år med én søjle for hvert produkt, der "
"angiver den gennemsnitlige driftsomkostning for én enhed af produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:104
msgid ""
"With this data, Mike is able to see that the average operation cost for the "
"moon shoes is almost twice the cost of the pogo stick. Using this insight, "
"Tommy's Toys decides to cease production of moon shoes, thus lowering their "
"average cost of manufacturing operations."
msgstr ""
"Med disse data kan Mike se, at den gennemsnitlige driftsomkostning for moon "
"shoes er næsten dobbelt så høj som for pogo stick. Ved hjælp af denne "
"indsigt beslutter Tommy's Toys at ophøre med produktionen af moon shoes og "
"dermed sænke deres gennemsnitlige produktionsomkostninger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:0
msgid ""
"The bar chart comparing the operation costs of the pogo stick and moon shoes."
msgstr ""
"Søjlediagrammet, der sammenligner driftsomkostningerne for pogo stick og "
"moon shoes."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:113
msgid "Use case: compare time periods"
msgstr "Brugsscenarie: sammenlign tidsperioder"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:115
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Production Analysis` report can also be used to compare data "
"for two different time periods. This is accomplished using the options in "
"the :guilabel:`Comparison` section of the :guilabel:`Search...` bar."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Produktionsanalyse`-rapporten kan også bruges til at sammenligne "
"data for to forskellige tidsperioder. Dette gøres ved hjælp af "
"indstillingerne i afsnittet :guilabel:`Sammenligning` i :guilabel:`Søg...`-"
"linjen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:120
msgid ""
"Furniture company *Fanny's Furnishings* wants to compare their production "
"costs for the first and second quarters of 2024, to see which products they "
"spent the most money producing in each quarter."
msgstr ""
"Møbelfirmaet *Fanny's Furnishings* ønsker at sammenligne deres "
"produktionsomkostninger for første og andet kvartal af 2024 for at se, "
"hvilke produkter de brugte flest penge på at producere i hvert kvartal."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:124
msgid ""
"To compare the two time periods, shop floor supervisor Adam opens "
"the :menuselection:`Manufacturing` app, and navigates to "
"the :guilabel:`Production Analysis` page. He begins by selecting "
"the :icon:`fa-pie-chart` :guilabel:`(pie chart)` graph type option at the "
"top of the page."
msgstr ""
"For at sammenligne de to tidsperioder åbner værkstedsleder "
"Adam :menuselection:`Produktion`-appen og navigerer til "
"siden :guilabel:`Produktionsanalyse`. Han begynder med at vælge "
"graftypen :icon:`fa-pie-chart` :guilabel:`cirkeldiagram` øverst på siden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:130
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Comparison` feature is meant to be used with the :icon:`fa-"
"pie-chart` :guilabel:`(pie chart)` graph type, or the :icon:`oi-view-"
"pivot` :guilabel:`(pivot)` view."
msgstr ""
"Funktionen :guilabel:`Sammenligning` er beregnet til at blive brugt med "
"graftypen :icon:`fa-pie-chart` :guilabel:`cirkeldiagram` eller "
"visningen :icon:`oi-view-pivot` :guilabel:`pivot`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:133
msgid ""
"A :guilabel:`Comparison` option can still be selected with the other view "
"types enabled, but doing so does not change the way data is displayed on the "
"report."
msgstr ""
"En :guilabel:`Sammenligning`-indstilling kan stadig vælges med de andre "
"visningstyper aktiveret, men det ændrer ikke måden, data vises på i "
"rapporten."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:136
msgid ""
"Next, Adam selects the :guilabel:`Total Cost` option from "
"the :guilabel:`Measures` :icon:`fa-caret-down` drop-down menu. This option "
"displays the total amount spent producing each product."
msgstr ""
"Derefter vælger Adam indstillingen :guilabel:`Samlet omkostning` fra "
"rullemenuen :guilabel:`Målinger` :icon:`fa-caret-down`. Denne indstilling "
"viser det samlede beløb brugt på at producere hvert produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:140
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Search...` bar drop-down menu, he leaves "
"the :guilabel:`2024` filter enabled in the :guilabel:`End Date` section, and "
"enables the :guilabel:`Q2` filter as well. With both of these time periods "
"selected, the pie chart shows data for the second quarter of 2024."
msgstr ""
"I rullemenuen :guilabel:`Søg...` lader han filtret :guilabel:`2024` forblive "
"aktiveret i afsnittet :guilabel:`Slutdato` og aktiverer også "
"filtret :guilabel:`Q2`. Med begge disse tidsperioder valgt viser "
"cirkeldiagrammet data for andet kvartal af 2024."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:144
msgid ""
"Finally, Adam selects the :guilabel:`End Date: Previous Period` option in "
"the :guilabel:`Comparison` section of the :guilabel:`Search...` bar. Doing "
"so causes the pie chart to be split into an inner circle, and an outer ring."
msgstr ""
"Endelig vælger Adam indstillingen :guilabel:`Slutdato: Forrige periode` i "
"afsnittet :guilabel:`Sammenligning` i :guilabel:`Søg...`-linjen. Dette "
"medfører, at cirkeldiagrammet opdeles i en indre cirkel og en ydre ring."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:148
msgid ""
"The outer ring shows data for the selected time period, quarter two of 2024. "
"The inner circle shows data for the previous time period, quarter one of "
"2024."
msgstr ""
"Den ydre ring viser data for den valgte tidsperiode, andet kvartal af 2024. "
"Den indre cirkel viser data for den forrige tidsperiode, første kvartal af "
"2024."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:152
msgid ""
"If :guilabel:`End Date: Previous Year` is selected instead of :guilabel:`End "
"Date: Previous Period`, the inner circle shows data for the selected time "
"period, one *year* previous."
msgstr ""
"Hvis :guilabel:`Slutdato: Forrige år` er valgt i stedet "
"for :guilabel:`Slutdato: Forrige periode`, viser den indre cirkel data for "
"den valgte tidsperiode, et *år* tidligere."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:155
msgid ""
"In the case of this example, it would show data for quarter two of 2023."
msgstr "I dette eksempel ville det vise data for andet kvartal af 2023."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:157
msgid ""
"Using this report, Adam can see that the products with the highest total "
"cost for quarter two are the *bicycle* and *tricycle*. On the other hand, in "
"quarter one, the *roller skates* had the highest total cost."
msgstr ""
"Ved hjælp af denne rapport kan Adam se, at produkterne med de højeste "
"samlede omkostninger for andet kvartal er *cyklen* og *trehjulet*. I første "
"kvartal havde *rulleskøjterne* derimod de højeste samlede omkostninger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/reporting/production_analysis.rst:0
msgid ""
"The pie chart view of the Production Analysis report, with a comparison "
"filter enabled."
msgstr ""
"Cirkeldiagramvisningen af produktionsanalyserapporten med et sammenlignende "
"filter aktiveret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor.rst:5
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:60
msgid "Shop Floor"
msgstr "Værksted"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:3
msgid "Shop Floor overview"
msgstr "Værkstedsoversigt"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:8
msgid ""
"The *Shop Floor* module is a companion module to the *Manufacturing* app. "
"*Shop Floor* provides a visual interface for processing manufacturing orders "
"(MOs) and work orders. It also allows manufacturing employees to track the "
"amount of time spent working on manufacturing and work orders."
msgstr ""
"*Værksted*-modulet er et ledsagermodul til *Produktion*-appen. *Værksted* "
"giver en visuel grænseflade til behandling af produktionsordrer (MO'er) og "
"arbejdsordrer. Det giver også produktionsmedarbejdere mulighed for at spore "
"den tid, der er brugt på at arbejde med produktions- og arbejdsordrer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:12
msgid ""
"The *Shop Floor* module is :ref:`installed <general/install>` alongside the "
"*Manufacturing* app."
msgstr ""
"Modulet *Værksted* er :ref:`installeret <general/install>` sammen med appen "
"*Produktion*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:15
msgid "Access Shop Floor"
msgstr "Åbn Værksted"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:17
msgid "*Shop Floor* can be opened in the following ways:"
msgstr "*Værksted* kan åbnes på følgende måder:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:19
msgid ""
"Click the :guilabel:`Shop Floor` module icon from the main Odoo dashboard."
msgstr "Klik på modulikonet :guilabel:`Værksted` fra Odoos hoveddashboard."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:20
msgid ""
"Click the :icon:`oi-view-kanban` :guilabel:`Shop Floor` smart button on a "
"manufacturing order. This will open the manufacturing order in the *Shop "
"Floor* module."
msgstr ""
"Klik på :icon:`oi-view-kanban` :guilabel:`Værksted` smart-knappen på en "
"produktionsordre. Dette åbner produktionsordren i *Værksted*-modulet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:24
msgid "Activating work centers"
msgstr "Aktivering af arbejdscentre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:26
msgid ""
"When *Shop Floor* is opened on a workstation, it is possible to select work "
"centers to assign to it."
msgstr ""
"Når *Værksted* er åbnet på en arbejdsstation, er det muligt at vælge "
"arbejdscentre, der skal tildeles den."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:28
msgid ""
"Open the *Shop Floor* app from either the main Odoo dashboard or from "
"the :icon:`oi-view-kanban` :guilabel:`Shop Floor` smart button on a "
"manufacturing order."
msgstr ""
"Åbn *Værksted*-appen fra enten Odoo-hovedoverblikket eller fra :icon:`oi-"
"view-kanban` :guilabel:`Værksted` smart-knappen på en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:31
msgid ""
"If it is the workstation's first time opening *Shop Floor*, click "
"the :guilabel:`Activate your Work Centers` button that appears, and an "
"*Activate your Work Centers* pop-up window loads."
msgstr ""
"Hvis det er første gang, arbejdsstationen åbner *Værksted*, skal du klikke "
"på knappen :guilabel:`Aktiver dine arbejdscentre`, der vises, og et pop op-"
"vindue *Aktiver dine arbejdscentre* indlæses."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:34
msgid ""
"Select the work centers to assign to the workstation by clicking the "
"respective checkboxes, then click :guilabel:`Confirm`."
msgstr ""
"Vælg de arbejdscentre, der skal tildeles arbejdsstationen, ved at klikke på "
"de respektive afkrydsningsfelter, og klik derefter på :guilabel:`Bekræft`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:None
msgid "Select at least one work center to assign to the workstation."
msgstr "Vælg mindst ét arbejdscenter, der skal tildeles arbejdsstationen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:41
msgid "Installing Shop Floor on a workstation"
msgstr "Installation af Værksted på en arbejdsstation"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:43
msgid ""
"*Shop Floor* can be installed in the Chrome browser of a workstation to "
"limit its access to other Odoo applications."
msgstr ""
"*Værksted* kan installeres i Chrome-browseren på en arbejdsstation for at "
"begrænse dens adgang til andre Odoo-applikationer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:46
msgid ""
"First, open the *Shop Floor* app from either the main Odoo dashboard or from "
"the :icon:`oi-view-kanban` :guilabel:`Shop Floor` smart button on a "
"manufacturing order."
msgstr ""
"Åbn først *Værksted*-appen fra enten Odoo-hovedoverblikket eller "
"fra :icon:`oi-view-kanban` :guilabel:`Værksted` smart-knappen på en "
"produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:49
msgid ""
"Click the :icon:`fa-navicon` :guilabel:`(menu)` icon, then click :icon:`fa-"
"arrow-circle-down` :guilabel:`Install App`. A new window will open. Click "
"the :guilabel:`Install` button to install the app in the workstation's "
"browser."
msgstr ""
"Klik på :icon:`fa-navicon` :guilabel:`(menu)` ikonet, klik derefter "
"på :icon:`fa-arrow-circle-down` :guilabel:`Installer app`. Et nyt vindue "
"åbnes. Klik på knappen :guilabel:`Installer` for at installere appen i "
"arbejdsstationens browser."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:54
msgid "Navigation"
msgstr "Navigation"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:56
msgid ""
"*Shop Floor* is broken down into three main views, which can be selected "
"from the navigation bar at the top of the module:"
msgstr ""
"*Værksted* er opdelt i tre hovedvisninger, som kan vælges fra "
"navigationsbjælken øverst i modulet:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:59
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Overview`: *Shop Floor*'s main dashboard and displays information "
"cards for |MOs|. Learn more about the Overview in the :ref:`manufacturing/"
"shop_floor/overview` documentation."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Oversigt`: *Værktøj*s hoveddashboard og viser informationskort "
"for |MOs|. Lær mere om oversigten i :ref:`manufacturing/shop_floor/overview` "
"dokumentationen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:62
msgid ""
":guilabel:`My WO`: shows information cards for all work orders assigned to "
"the employee whose profile is currently active in the operator panel on the "
"left side of the module. This view functions largely the same as the views "
"for each work center, but it only shows work orders assigned to the active "
"employee."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Mine AO`: viser informationskort for alle arbejdsordrer tildelt "
"medarbejderen, hvis profil aktuelt er aktiv i operatørpanelet på venstre "
"side af modulet. Denne visning fungerer stort set på samme måde som "
"visningerne for hvert arbejdscenter, men den viser kun arbejdsordrer tildelt "
"den aktive medarbejder."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:66
msgid ""
"Each work center has a dedicated view that displays information cards for "
"the work orders assigned to it. Learn more about these views in "
"the :ref:`manufacturing/shop_floor/work-centers` documentation. Select a "
"work center to see the work orders assigned to it. The view for each work "
"center organizes work orders, based on the scheduled dates of their "
"corresponding |MOs|."
msgstr ""
"Hvert arbejdscenter har en dedikeret visning, der viser informationskort for "
"de arbejdsordrer, der er tildelt det. Lær mere om disse visninger "
"i :ref:`manufacturing/shop_floor/work-centers` dokumentationen. Vælg et "
"arbejdscenter for at se de arbejdsordrer, der er tildelt det. Visningen for "
"hvert arbejdscenter organiserer arbejdsordrer baseret på de planlagte datoer "
"for deres tilsvarende |MOs|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:72
msgid ""
"To isolate an |MO| or work order, so that no other orders appear, search the "
"reference number of the |MO| in the :guilabel:`Search` bar at the top of the "
"module. This search filter remains active while switching between the "
"different module views."
msgstr ""
"For at isolere en |MO| eller arbejdsordre, så ingen andre ordrer vises, skal "
"du søge efter referencenummeret for |MO| i :guilabel:`Søg` feltet øverst i "
"modulet. Dette søgefilter forbliver aktivt, når der skiftes mellem de "
"forskellige modulvisninger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:76
msgid ""
"On the left side of the module is the :ref:`manufacturing/shop_floor/"
"operator-panel`, which shows all of the employees currently signed in to "
"*Shop Floor* and allows new employees to sign in. The operator panel is "
"always available in the module, regardless of the selected view."
msgstr ""
"På venstre side af modulet er :ref:`manufacturing/shop_floor/operator-"
"panel`, som viser alle medarbejdere, der aktuelt er logget ind på "
"*Værksted*, og giver nye medarbejdere mulighed for at logge ind. "
"Operatørpanelet er altid tilgængeligt i modulet, uanset den valgte visning."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:83
msgid "Overview view"
msgstr "Oversigtsvisning"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:85
msgid ""
"By default, the *Overview* is displayed when opening *Shop Floor*. This "
"shows an information card for every |MO| that is *ready to start*. An |MO| "
"is considered ready to start once it has been confirmed, and all required "
"components are available."
msgstr ""
"Som standard vises *Oversigten*, når *Værksted* åbnes. Dette viser et "
"informationskort for hver |MO|, der er *klar til at starte*. En |MO| "
"betragtes som klar til at starte, når den er blevet bekræftet, og alle "
"nødvendige komponenter er tilgængelige."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:89
msgid ""
"To view every confirmed |MO| regardless of readiness, click the :icon:`oi-"
"close` :guilabel:`(remove)` icon on the :guilabel:`MO Ready` filter to "
"remove it from the :guilabel:`Search` bar."
msgstr ""
"For at se alle bekræftede |MO| uanset parathed skal du klikke på :icon:`oi-"
"close` :guilabel:`(fjern)` ikonet på :guilabel:`PO klar` filteret for at "
"fjerne det fra :guilabel:`Søg` feltet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:94
msgid "MO information card"
msgstr "MO-informationskort"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:96
msgid ""
"Each |MO| information card on the *Overview* displays all of the relevant "
"details of the associated |MO|, and also provides employees with options for "
"processing the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Hvert |MO| informationskort på *Oversigten* viser alle relevante detaljer "
"for den tilknyttede |MO| og giver også medarbejdere muligheder for at "
"behandle |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:99
msgid ""
"The header for an |MO| card shows the |MO| number, the product and number of "
"units being produced, and the |MO| status. If work on the MO has not yet "
"begun, the status is :guilabel:`Confirmed`. When work has begun, the status "
"updates to :guilabel:`In Progress`."
msgstr ""
"Hlavička karty |MO| zobrazuje číslo |MO|, produkt a počet vyráběných "
"jednotek a stav |MO|. Pokud práce na VZ ještě nezačala, je "
"stav :guilabel:`Potvrzeno`. Jakmile práce začne, stav se aktualizuje "
"na :guilabel:`Probíhá`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:103
msgid ""
"The main body of an |MO| card shows a line for each completed work order, if "
"any, followed by the current work order to be completed. Completed work "
"orders appear in grey with a :icon:`fa-check` :guilabel:`(checkmark)` icon "
"next to it. The current work order is indicated by a :icon:`oi-chevron-"
"right` :guilabel:`(right chevron)` button that opens the view for the work "
"center to which the order is assigned."
msgstr ""
"Hlavní část karty |MO| zobrazuje řádek pro každý dokončený pracovní příkaz, "
"pokud existuje, následovaný aktuálním pracovním příkazem, který je třeba "
"dokončit. Dokončené pracovní příkazy se zobrazují šedě s ikonou :icon:`fa-"
"check` :guilabel:`(zatržítko)` vedle nich. Aktuální pracovní příkaz je "
"označen tlačítkem :icon:`oi-chevron-right` :guilabel:`(pravá šipka)`, které "
"otevře zobrazení pracovního centra, ke kterému je příkaz přiřazen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:109
msgid ""
"If a lot or serial number is required for the product, below the current "
"work order is a line titled :guilabel:`Register Production`, which records "
"lot or serial numbers for the units produced. Click the :guilabel:`Register "
"Production` line to specify a lot or serial number for the produced units, "
"then click :guilabel:`Validate`."
msgstr ""
"Pokud je pro produkt vyžadováno číslo šarže nebo sériové číslo, pod "
"aktuálním pracovním příkazem je řádek s názvem :guilabel:`Zaznamenat "
"výrobu`, který zaznamenává čísla šarží nebo sériová čísla pro vyrobené "
"jednotky. Klikněte na řádek :guilabel:`Zaznamenat výrobu` pro zadání čísla "
"šarže nebo sériového čísla vyrobených jednotek a poté klikněte "
"na :guilabel:`Potvrdit`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:114
msgid ""
"The footer of the |MO| card displays a :guilabel:`Close Production` button. "
"This is used to close the |MO| once production is completed. However, if any "
"quality checks are required for the |MO| as a whole (not the work orders "
"within it), a :guilabel:`Quality Checks` button appears instead. "
"Clicking :guilabel:`Quality Checks` opens a pop-up window where any required "
"quality checks can be completed."
msgstr ""
"Patička karty |MO| zobrazuje tlačítko :guilabel:`Uzavřít výrobu`. To se "
"používá k uzavření |MO|, jakmile je výroba dokončena. Pokud jsou však pro |"
"MO| jako celek (nikoli pro pracovní příkazy v něm) vyžadovány jakékoli "
"kontroly kvality, zobrazí se místo toho tlačítko :guilabel:`Kontroly "
"kvality`. Kliknutím na :guilabel:`Kontroly kvality` se otevře vyskakovací "
"okno, kde lze dokončit všechny požadované kontroly kvality."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:119
msgid ""
"After clicking :guilabel:`Close Production`, the |MO| card disappears and "
"the work order is closed."
msgstr ""
"Po kliknutí na :guilabel:`Uzavřít výrobu` karta |MO| zmizí a pracovní příkaz "
"je uzavřen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:121
msgid ""
"On the right side of the footer is a :icon:`fa-ellipsis-"
"v` :guilabel:`(vertical ellipsis)` button, which opens an *Options* pop-up "
"window with additional options for the |MO|:"
msgstr ""
"Na pravé straně patičky je tlačítko :icon:`fa-ellipsis-v` :guilabel:`(svislé "
"tři tečky)`, které otevře vyskakovací okno *Možnosti* s dalšími možnostmi "
"pro |MO|:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:124
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Register Production / Serial`: Record lots of serial numbers for "
"the units produced."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Zaznamenat výrobu / sériová čísla`: Zaznamenejte šarže nebo "
"sériová čísla pro vyrobené jednotky."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:125
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:208
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Scrap`: Send components to a scrap location when they are found "
"to be defective. Learn more about the scrap order form in :ref:`inventory/"
"scrap-from-stock`."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Odpad`: Odešlete komponenty na místo odpadu, pokud jsou zjištěny "
"jako vadné. Více o formuláři příkazu odpadu se dozvíte v :ref:`inventory/"
"scrap-from-stock`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:127
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Add Work Order`: Add an additional work order to the |MO|. "
"Specify the operation after which the work order should be inserted, a "
"title, the work center at which it should take place, and the expected "
"duration. Optionally assign a start date and the employee who should "
"complete it."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Přidat pracovní příkaz`: Přidejte další pracovní příkaz k |MO|. "
"Určete operaci, po které má být pracovní příkaz vložen, název, pracovní "
"centrum, kde má proběhnout, a očekávanou dobu trvání. Volitelně přiřaďte "
"datum zahájení a zaměstnance, který jej má dokončit."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:130
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Add Component`: Add an additional component to the |MO|. Select "
"products to add to the work order, then click the :guilabel:`Back to "
"ShopFloor` button."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Přidat komponentu`: Přidejte další komponentu k |MO|. Vyberte "
"produkty, které chcete přidat k pracovnímu příkazu, a poté klikněte na "
"tlačítko :guilabel:`Zpět do dílny`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:134
msgid ""
"Additional components are consumed in the *Shop Floor* module, but their "
"stock moves will not be validated until the |MO| is closed."
msgstr ""
"Další komponenty jsou spotřebovány v modulu *Dílna*, ale jejich skladové "
"pohyby nebudou potvrzeny, dokud nebude |MO| uzavřen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:137
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Add By-product`: Add a product that will be created as a "
"byproduct of this work order. This displays when the :guilabel:`By-Products` "
"setting is enabled in the *Manufacturing* app."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Přidat vedlejší produkt`: Přidejte produkt, který bude vytvořen "
"jako vedlejší produkt tohoto pracovního příkazu. Zobrazí se, když je v "
"aplikaci *Produktion* povoleno nastavení :guilabel:`Vedlejší produkty`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:139
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Open Manufacturing Order`: opens the |MO| in the *Manufacturing* "
"app."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Otevřít výrobní zakázku`: otevře |MO| v aplikaci *Produktion*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:140
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Log Note`: Enter a note that will be visible in the *Shop Floor* "
"module and throughout all steps on the shop floor."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Zaznamenat poznámku`: Zadejte poznámku, která bude viditelná v "
"modulu *Dílna* a ve všech krocích v dílně."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:None
msgid "An information card for an MO on the Overview of the Shop Floor module."
msgstr "Informační karta pro VZ v přehledu modulu Dílna."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:149
msgid "Work center views"
msgstr "Zobrazení pracovních center"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:151
msgid ""
"The work center views list a number next to them. This number is the "
"quantity of work orders currently *ready to start* in the work center. A "
"work order is considered ready to start when the |MO| it is a part of is "
"ready to start, and any preceding work orders have been completed."
msgstr ""
"Zobrazení pracovních center mají vedle sebe uvedeno číslo. Toto číslo je "
"množství pracovních příkazů aktuálně *připravených ke spuštění* v pracovním "
"centru. Pracovní příkaz je považován za připravený ke spuštění, když je |"
"MO|, jehož je součástí, připraven ke spuštění a všechny předchozí pracovní "
"příkazy byly dokončeny."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:155
msgid ""
"By default, the view for each work center shows an information card for "
"every work order assigned to it that is ready to start."
msgstr ""
"Ve výchozím nastavení zobrazuje zobrazení každého pracovního centra "
"informační kartu pro každý pracovní příkaz, který je mu přiřazen a je "
"připraven ke spuštění."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:158
msgid ""
"To view every confirmed work order assigned to a work center regardless of "
"readiness, click the :icon:`oi-close` :guilabel:`(remove)` icon on "
"the :guilabel:`MO Ready` filter to remove it from the search bar."
msgstr ""
"Chcete-li zobrazit každý potvrzený pracovní příkaz přiřazený k pracovnímu "
"centru bez ohledu na připravenost, klikněte na ikonu :icon:`oi-"
"close` :guilabel:`(odebrat)` u filtru :guilabel:`VZ připravena` a odeberte "
"jej z vyhledávacího pole."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:163
msgid "Managing work centers"
msgstr "Správa pracovních center"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:165
msgid ""
"Work center views can be toggled on or off by clicking the :guilabel:`Add` "
"icon in the navigation bar, selecting or deselecting them on the pop-up "
"window that appears, and then clicking :guilabel:`Confirm`."
msgstr ""
"Arbejdscentervisninger kan slås til eller fra ved at klikke på "
":guilabel:`Tilføj` ikonet i navigationslinjen, markere eller afmarkere dem i "
"pop op-vinduet der vises, og derefter klikke på :guilabel:`Bekræft`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:170
msgid "Work order information card"
msgstr "Arbejdsordre-informationskort"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:172
msgid ""
"The work order information cards on a work center's view show all of the "
"relevant details of the associated work order and also provide employees "
"with options for processing it."
msgstr ""
"Arbejdsordre-informationskortene på et arbejdscenters visning viser alle "
"relevante detaljer for den tilknyttede arbejdsordre og giver også "
"medarbejdere muligheder for at behandle den."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:175
msgid ""
"The header for a work order card shows the reference number of the |MO| that "
"the work order is a part of, the product and number of units being produced. "
"Click the :guilabel:`Start` button to start work on a work order. When work "
"has begun, the status updates to display a timer showing the total time the "
"work order has been worked on. The instructions for each work order open "
"automatically when the timer starts."
msgstr ""
"Overskriften på et arbejdsordrekort viser referencenummeret for den |MO|, "
"som arbejdsordren er en del af, produktet og antallet af enheder der "
"produceres. Klik på :guilabel:`Start` knappen for at starte arbejdet på en "
"arbejdsordre. Når arbejdet er begyndt, opdateres status til at vise en timer "
"der viser den samlede tid arbejdsordren er blevet arbejdet på. "
"Instruktionerne for hver arbejdsordre åbnes automatisk når timeren starter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:181
msgid ""
"The main body of a work order card shows a line for each step required to "
"complete the work order. Work order steps can be completed by clicking the "
"button for the line, then following the instructions on the pop-up window "
"that appears."
msgstr ""
"Hovedindholdet af et arbejdsordrekort viser en linje for hvert trin der "
"kræves for at fuldføre arbejdsordren. Arbejdsordretrin kan fuldføres ved at "
"klikke på knappen for linjen og derefter følge instruktionerne i pop op-"
"vinduet der vises."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:185
msgid ""
"If the work order being processed is the final work order for the |MO|, "
"a :guilabel:`Close Production` button appears on the footer of the work "
"order card. Clicking :guilabel:`Close Production` closes both the work order "
"and the |MO|, unless a quality check is required for the Production` button "
"appears on the footer of the work order card. Click the :guilabel:`Close "
"Production` to close both the work order and the |MO|, unless a quality "
"check is required for the |MO|. In this case, the quality check must be "
"completed from the |MO| card before the |MO| can be closed."
msgstr ""
"Hvis den arbejdsordre der behandles er den endelige arbejdsordre for |MO|, "
"vises en :guilabel:`Luk produktion` knap i bunden af arbejdsordrekortet. "
"Klik på :guilabel:`Luk produktion` for at lukke både arbejdsordren og |MO|, "
"medmindre der kræves en kvalitetskontrol for Produktion` knappen vises i "
"bunden af arbejdsordrekortet. Klik på :guilabel:`Luk produktion` for at "
"lukke både arbejdsordren og |MO|, medmindre der kræves en kvalitetskontrol "
"for |MO|. I dette tilfælde skal kvalitetskontrollen fuldføres fra |MO| "
"kortet før |MO| kan lukkes."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:193
msgid ""
"Alternatively, if the |MO| requires the completion of additional work "
"orders, a :guilabel:`Mark as Done` button appears instead. "
"Clicking :guilabel:`Mark as Done` marks the current work order as completed, "
"and causes the next work order to appear on the view for the work center it "
"is assigned Done` button appears instead. Click :guilabel:`Mark as Done` to "
"mark the current work order as completed, and the next work order appears on "
"the view for the work center it is assigned to."
msgstr ""
"Alternativt, hvis |MO| kræver fuldførelse af yderligere arbejdsordrer, vises "
"en :guilabel:`Markér som udført` knap i stedet. Klik på :guilabel:`Markér "
"som udført` for at markere den aktuelle arbejdsordre som fuldført, og den "
"næste arbejdsordre vises på visningen for det arbejdscenter den er tildelt "
"Udført` knappen vises i stedet. Klik på :guilabel:`Markér som udført` for at "
"markere den aktuelle arbejdsordre som fuldført, og den næste arbejdsordre "
"vises på visningen for det arbejdscenter den er tildelt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:200
msgid ""
"After clicking :guilabel:`Close Production` or :guilabel:`Mark as Done`, the "
"work order card fades away. When the work order card disappears completely, "
"the work order is marked as :guilabel:`Finished` on the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Efter at have klikket på :guilabel:`Luk produktion` eller :guilabel:`Markér "
"som udført`, falmer arbejdsordrekortet. Når arbejdsordrekortet forsvinder "
"helt, markeres arbejdsordren som :guilabel:`Afsluttet` på |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:204
msgid ""
"On the right side of the footer is a :icon:`fa-ellipsis-"
"v` :guilabel:`(vertical ellipsis)` button, which opens a pop-up window with "
"additional options for the work order:"
msgstr ""
"På højre side af bunden er der en :icon:`fa-ellipsis-v` :guilabel:`(lodret "
"ellipse)` knap, som åbner et pop op-vindue med yderligere muligheder for "
"arbejdsordren:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:207
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Register Production/Serial`: Record a lot or serial numbers for "
"the units produced."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Registrér produktion/serienummer`: Registrer lot- eller "
"serienumre for de producerede enheder."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:210
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Modify Routing`: Move the work order to another work center or "
"add another work order."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Modificér rute`: Flyt arbejdsordren til et andet arbejdscenter "
"eller tilføj en anden arbejdsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:211
msgid ":guilabel:`Add Component`: Adds an additional component to the |MO|."
msgstr ":guilabel:`Tilføj komponent`: Tilføjer en ekstra komponent til |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:212
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Open Manufacturing Order`: Open the associated |MO| in the "
"*Manufacturing* app."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Åbn produktionsordre`: Åbn den tilknyttede |MO| i *Produktion* "
"appen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:213
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Update instructions`: Propose a change to the work order's "
"instructions or steps."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Opdatér instruktioner`: Foreslå en ændring til arbejdsordrens "
"instruktioner eller trin."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:214
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Create a Quality Alert`: Open a quality alert form that can be "
"filled out to alert a quality team about a potential issue."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Opret kvalitetsalarm`: Åbn en kvalitetsalarmformular der kan "
"udfyldes for at alarmere et kvalitetsteam om et potentielt problem."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:216
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Request Maintenance`: Create a maintenance request for the work "
"center."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Anmod om vedligeholdelse`: Opret en vedligeholdelsesanmodning for "
"arbejdscentret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:217
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Block`: Stop all work on the immediate operation and block future "
"work orders from being started until the work order is unblocked."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Bloker`: Stop alt arbejde på den umiddelbare operation og bloker "
"fremtidige arbejdsordrer fra at blive startet indtil arbejdsordren er "
"afblokeret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:None
msgid "An information card for a work order in the Shop Floor module."
msgstr "Et informationskort for en arbejdsordre i Værksted-modulet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:226
msgid "Operator panel"
msgstr "Operatørpanel"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:228
msgid ""
"The operator panel is used to manage the employees who are signed in to the "
"*Shop Floor* module. The panel displays the name and profile picture of "
"every employee currently signed in across all database instances."
msgstr ""
"Operatørpanelet bruges til at administrere de medarbejdere der er logget ind "
"på *Værksted* modulet. Panelet viser navn og profilbillede for alle "
"medarbejdere der aktuelt er logget ind på tværs af alle databaseinstanser."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:232
msgid ""
"To interact with *Shop Floor* as a specific employee, click the employee's "
"name to activate their profile. Inactive profiles appear with their names "
"and profile pictures greyed out."
msgstr ""
"For at interagere med *Værksted* som en bestemt medarbejder, klik på "
"medarbejderens navn for at aktivere deres profil. Inaktive profiler vises "
"med deres navne og profilbilleder gråtonet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:235
msgid ""
"When an employee is selected in the operator panel, they can begin working "
"on a work order by clicking the work order's heading. If an employee is "
"working on one or more work orders, the work order titles appear under their "
"name, as well as a timer showing how long they've been working on each order."
msgstr ""
"Når en medarbejder er valgt i operatørpanelet, kan de begynde at arbejde på "
"en arbejdsordre ved at klikke på arbejdsordrens overskrift. Hvis en "
"medarbejder arbejder på en eller flere arbejdsordrer, vises "
"arbejdsordretitlerne under deres navn, samt en timer der viser hvor længe de "
"har arbejdet på hver ordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:240
msgid ""
"To add new employees to the operator panel, click the :guilabel:`Edit "
"Operators` button at the bottom of the panel. Then, select employees from "
"the *Edit Operators* pop-up window. Click :guilabel:`Done` to save the list "
"of operators."
msgstr ""
"For at tilføje nye medarbejdere til operatørpanelet, klik på "
":guilabel:`Rediger operatører` knappen i bunden af panelet. Vælg derefter "
"medarbejdere fra *Rediger operatører* pop op-vinduet. Klik på "
":guilabel:`Udført` for at gemme listen over operatører."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:244
msgid ""
"To remove an employee from the operator panel, click the :guilabel:`Edit "
"Operators` button, deselect the employee, then click :guilabel:`Done`."
msgstr ""
"For at fjerne en medarbejder fra operatørpanelet, klik på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Rediger operatører`, fravælg medarbejderen og klik "
"derefter på :guilabel:`Udført`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:None
msgid ""
"The operator panel of the Shop Floor module, showing four employees signed "
"in."
msgstr ""
"Operatørpanelet i værkstedsmodulet, der viser fire medarbejdere logget ind."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:251
msgid "MO/WO prioritization"
msgstr "MO/WO-prioritering"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:253
msgid ""
"The *Shop Floor* module prioritizes orders based on their *scheduled date*, "
"set in the |MO|. An order can be moved to the top of the list by clicking "
"the :icon:`fa-star-o` :guilabel:`(star)` icon in the |MO| form. |MOs| and "
"work orders scheduled sooner are more highly prioritized and appear before "
"orders which are scheduled further out."
msgstr ""
"*Værksted*-modulet prioriterer ordrer baseret på deres *planlagte dato*, som "
"er angivet i |MO|. En ordre kan flyttes til toppen af listen ved at klikke "
"på :icon:`fa-star-o` :guilabel:`(stjerne)` ikonet i |MO| formularen. |MOs| "
"og arbejdsordrer, der er planlagt tidligere, prioriteres højere og vises før "
"ordrer, der er planlagt længere ude i fremtiden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:258
msgid ""
"To specify the scheduled date on an |MO|, begin by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Operations --> Manufacturing "
"Orders`, and click :guilabel:`New` to create a new |MO|."
msgstr ""
"For at angive den planlagte dato på en |MO|, start med at navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion-app --> Operationer --> Produktionsordrer`, "
"og klik på :guilabel:`Ny` for at oprette en ny |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:261
msgid ""
"To learn more about the fields on the |MO| form, see :ref:`manufacturing/"
"basic_setup/create-mo`."
msgstr ""
"For at lære mere om felterne i |MO| formularen, se :ref:`manufacturing/"
"basic_setup/create-mo`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:263
msgid ""
"Click on the :guilabel:`Scheduled Date` field to open a calendar popover "
"window. By default, the :guilabel:`Scheduled Date` field and its "
"corresponding pop-up window show the current date and time."
msgstr ""
"Klik på feltet :guilabel:`Planlagt dato` for at åbne et kalender-popover-"
"vindue. Som standard viser feltet :guilabel:`Planlagt dato` og dets "
"tilsvarende pop-up-vindue den aktuelle dato og tid."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:266
msgid ""
"Use the calendar to select the date on which processing should begin for the "
"|MO|. In the two fields at the bottom of the popover window, enter the hour "
"and minute at which processing should begin, using the 24-hour clock format."
msgstr ""
"Brug kalenderen til at vælge datoen, hvor behandlingen skal begynde for |"
"MO|. I de to felter nederst i pop op-vinduet skal du indtaste time og minut, "
"hvor behandlingen skal begynde, ved hjælp af 24-timers uret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:270
msgid ""
"Finally, click :guilabel:`Apply` at the bottom of the popover window to set "
"the date and time for the :guilabel:`Scheduled Date` field. Then, click "
"the :guilabel:`Confirm` button at the top of the |MO| to confirm it."
msgstr ""
"Klik til sidst på :guilabel:`Anvend` nederst i pop op-vinduet for at "
"indstille dato og tidspunkt for feltet :guilabel:`Planlagt dato`. Klik "
"derefter på knappen :guilabel:`Bekræft` øverst på |MO| for at bekræfte den."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:274
msgid ""
"Once the |MO| is confirmed, it appears in the *Shop Floor* module, as long "
"is it has the :guilabel:`Ready` status, which means all components are "
"available."
msgstr ""
"Når |MO| er bekræftet, vises den i *Værksted*-modulet, så længe den har "
"status :guilabel:`Klar`, hvilket betyder, at alle komponenter er "
"tilgængelige."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:277
msgid ""
"On the Odoo dashboard, click on the :menuselection:`Shop Floor` module to "
"open it. The *Overview* of the dashboard displays *Ready* |MOs|, organized "
"in order of priority on their |MO| form, then their scheduled dates."
msgstr ""
"Klik på :menuselection:`Værksted` modulet på Odoo-dashboardet for at åbne "
"det. *Oversigten* på dashboardet viser *Klar* |MOs|, organiseret i "
"rækkefølge efter prioritet på deres |MO| formular og derefter deres "
"planlagte datoer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:None
msgid "The Overview dashboard with prioritized orders appearing first."
msgstr "Oversigts-dashboardet med prioriterede ordrer, der vises først."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:285
msgid "Three |MOs| are confirmed for a *Table* product:"
msgstr "Tre |MOs| er bekræftet for et *Bord* produkt:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:287
msgid "WH/MO/00018 has a :guilabel:`Scheduled Date` of March 31."
msgstr "WH/MO/00018 har en :guilabel:`Planlagt dato` den 31. marts."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:288
msgid "WH/MO/00019 has a :guilabel:`Scheduled Date` of April 9."
msgstr "WH/MO/00019 har en :guilabel:`Planlagt dato` den 9. april."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:289
msgid "WH/MO/00020 has a :guilabel:`Scheduled Date` of April 3."
msgstr "WH/MO/00020 har en :guilabel:`Planlagt dato` den 3. april."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:291
msgid ""
"On the *Overview* of the *Shop Floor* module, the cards for each |MO| appear "
"in this order: WH/MO/00018, WH/MO/00020, WH/MO/00019."
msgstr ""
"I *Oversigten* i *Værksted*-modulet vises kortene for hver |MO| i denne "
"rækkefølge: WH/MO/00018, WH/MO/00020, WH/MO/00019."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:None
msgid "MOs in the Shop Floor module, ordered by their scheduled date."
msgstr "MO'er i Værksted-modulet, sorteret efter deres planlagte dato."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_overview.rst:297
msgid ""
"Each |MO| requires one work order, carried out at :guilabel:`Assembly 1`. "
"Clicking on the :guilabel:`Assembly 1` button at the top of the screen opens "
"the view for the work center, which displays one card for each work order, "
"appearing in the same order as their corresponding |MOs|."
msgstr ""
"Hver |MO| kræver én arbejdsordre, der udføres ved :guilabel:`Assembly 1`. "
"Klik på knappen :guilabel:`Assembly 1` øverst på skærmen for at åbne "
"visningen for arbejdscentret, som viser ét kort for hver arbejdsordre, der "
"vises i samme rækkefølge som deres tilsvarende |MOs|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:3
msgid "Shop Floor time tracking"
msgstr "Tidsregistrering i Værksted"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:9
msgid ""
"By signing in to the Odoo *Shop Floor* module as *operators*, employees are "
"able to track the amount of time they spend working on each work order. Odoo "
"tracks the time it takes to complete each work order as well as the time "
"each operator spends on each work order."
msgstr ""
"Ved at logge ind på Odoo *Værksted*-modulet som *operatører* kan "
"medarbejdere spore den tid, de bruger på at arbejde på hver arbejdsordre. "
"Odoo sporer den tid, det tager at fuldføre hver arbejdsordre, samt den tid "
"hver operatør bruger på hver arbejdsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:16
msgid "Manage operators"
msgstr "Administrer operatører"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:18
msgid ""
"When the *Shop Floor* module is first opened, the employee profile that is "
"signed in to the database is automatically signed in as an operator."
msgstr ""
"Når *Værksted*-modulet åbnes første gang, logges medarbejderprofilen, der er "
"logget ind på databasen, automatisk ind som operatør."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:21
msgid ""
"All operators for the current session are listed in the operator panel on "
"the left side of the screen. While the panel can list multiple employee "
"profiles, only one employee can be active at once. The active profile "
"highlighted in the operator panel is used for :ref:`time tracking "
"<manufacturing/shop_floor/track-work-order-duration>`."
msgstr ""
"Alle operatører for den aktuelle session er angivet i operatørpanelet på "
"venstre side af skærmen. Selvom panelet kan liste flere medarbejderprofiler, "
"kan kun én medarbejder være aktiv ad gangen. Den aktive profil, der er "
"fremhævet i operatørpanelet, bruges til :ref:`tidssporing <manufacturing/"
"shop_floor/track-work-order-duration>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:None
msgid "The operator panel in the Shop Floor module."
msgstr "Operatørpanelet i Værksted-modulet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:30
msgid "Add an operator"
msgstr "Tilføj en operatør"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:32
msgid ""
"To add employees to the operator panel, click the :guilabel:`Edit Operators` "
"button at the bottom of the panel. In the *Edit Operators* pop-up window, "
"select the employees that should be added as operators for the current "
"session, then click :guilabel:`Done`."
msgstr ""
"For at tilføje medarbejdere til operatørpanelet skal du klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Rediger operatører`-knappen nederst i panelet. I pop op-"
"vinduet *Rediger operatører* skal du vælge de medarbejdere, der skal "
"tilføjes som operatører for den aktuelle session, og derefter klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Udført`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:None
msgid "The Edit Operators pop-up window with four operators selected."
msgstr "Pop op-vinduet Rediger operatører med fire valgte operatører."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:40
msgid "Switch profiles"
msgstr "Skift profiler"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:42
msgid ""
"To sign in to *Shop Floor* as a different employee, click their name in the "
"operator panel to sign in using their profile. If a |PIN| has not been set "
"for the employee, the profile is signed in automatically. If a |PIN| has "
"been set for the employee, an :guilabel:`Enter your pin` pop-up window "
"appears. Enter the code using the number pad or keyboard, then "
"click :guilabel:`Confirm` to sign in to the *Shop Floor* module."
msgstr ""
"For at logge ind på *Værksted* som en anden medarbejder, skal du klikke på "
"deres navn i operatørpanelet for at logge ind ved hjælp af deres profil. "
"Hvis der ikke er angivet en |PIN| for medarbejderen, logges profilen ind "
"automatisk. Hvis der er angivet en |PIN| for medarbejderen, vises et pop op-"
"vindue med :guilabel:`Indtast din pin`. Indtast koden ved hjælp af "
"taltastaturet eller tastaturet, og klik derefter på :guilabel:`Bekræft` for "
"at logge ind på *Værksted*-modulet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:49
msgid ""
"Each employee can be assigned a PIN, which must be entered when signing in "
"to the *Shop Floor* module. Badges can also be generated and printed for "
"checking in and out with *Kiosk Mode* in the **Attendances** app. See "
"the :ref:`employee settings section <employees/hr-attn-pos>` to learn more."
msgstr ""
"Hver medarbejder kan tildeles en PIN-kode, som skal indtastes ved login til "
"*Værksted*-modulet. Der kan også genereres og udskrives badges til ind- og "
"udtjekning med *Kiosk-tilstand* i **Fremmøde**-appen. Se :ref:`afsnittet om "
"medarbejderindstillinger <employees/hr-attn-pos>` for at lære mere."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:55
msgid "Remove an operator"
msgstr "Fjern en operatør"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:57
msgid ""
"To remove employees from the operator panel, click the :guilabel:`Edit "
"Operators` button, and click the profiles that should be removed from the "
"panel. Confirm that the profiles have been unchecked, then "
"click :guilabel:`Done`."
msgstr ""
"For at fjerne medarbejdere fra operatørpanelet skal du klikke på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Rediger operatører` og klikke på de profiler, der skal "
"fjernes fra panelet. Bekræft, at profilerne er fravalgt, og klik derefter "
"på :guilabel:`Udført`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:64
msgid "Track work order duration"
msgstr "Spor arbejdsordrevarighed"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:66
msgid ""
"To track the time spent on a work order, select the work center where the "
"work order is scheduled to be carried out. This can be done by selecting the "
"work center from the top of the page in the *Shop Floor* module or by "
"clicking the name of the work center in the form for the manufacturing order "
"(MO) that the work order is a part of."
msgstr ""
"For at spore den tid, der bruges på en arbejdsordre, skal du vælge det "
"arbejdscenter, hvor arbejdsordren er planlagt til at blive udført. Dette kan "
"gøres ved at vælge arbejdscenteret fra toppen af siden i *Værksted*-modulet "
"eller ved at klikke på navnet på arbejdscenteret i formularen for "
"produktionsordren (MO), som arbejdsordren er en del af."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:71
msgid ""
"When work begins, click the :guilabel:`Start` button on the work order card "
"to start tracking the duration. The :guilabel:`Start` button is replaced by "
"a timer which displays the total duration that all operators have spent on "
"the work order."
msgstr ""
"Når arbejdet begynder, skal du klikke på knappen :guilabel:`Start` på "
"arbejdsordrens kort for at begynde at spore varigheden. "
"Knappen :guilabel:`Start` erstattes af et ur, der viser den samlede "
"varighed, som alle operatører har brugt på arbejdsordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:None
msgid "A work order card with an active timer."
msgstr "Et arbejdsordrekort med en aktiv timer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:79
msgid "View active profile work orders"
msgstr "Se aktiv profils arbejdsordrer"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:81
msgid ""
"The operator panel displays the work center location and individual time "
"spent for each work order an operator is working on. This timer only "
"reflects work done during the current session, even if the operator has "
"previously worked on the work order."
msgstr ""
"Operatørpanelet viser arbejdscenterets placering og individuel tidsforbrug "
"for hver arbejdsordre, en operatør arbejder på. Dette ur afspejler kun "
"arbejde udført under den aktuelle session, selvom operatøren tidligere har "
"arbejdet på arbejdsordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:85
msgid ""
"Operators can work on multiple work orders simultaneously and track their "
"time for each. Click :guilabel:`My WO` at the top of the page to see all of "
"the work orders the active profile is working on."
msgstr ""
"Operatører kan arbejde på flere arbejdsordrer samtidigt og spore deres tid "
"for hver. Klik på :guilabel:`Mine arbejdsordrer` øverst på siden for at se "
"alle de arbejdsordrer, den aktive profil arbejder på."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:None
msgid "An employee card in the operator panel, showing two work order timers."
msgstr "Et medarbejderkort i operatørpanelet, der viser to arbejdsordretimere."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:93
msgid "Pause and stop timer"
msgstr "Pause og stop ur"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:95
msgid ""
"To pause the timer on a work order, click the work order card a second time."
msgstr ""
"For at sætte uret på pause på en arbejdsordre skal du klikke på "
"arbejdsordrens kort endnu en gang."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:97
msgid ""
"Once a work order is complete, click the :guilabel:`Mark as Done` button at "
"the bottom of the work order card, and it disappears from the work center "
"page."
msgstr ""
"Når en arbejdsordre er fuldført, skal du klikke på knappen :guilabel:`Marker "
"som udført` nederst på arbejdsordrens kort, hvorefter den forsvinder fra "
"arbejdscenter-siden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:101
msgid ""
"If there are no additional work orders for the |MO|, the button "
"says :guilabel:`Close Production` instead. Clicking :guilabel:`Close "
"Production` marks the entire |MO| as *Done* and removes it from the *Shop "
"Floor* module."
msgstr ""
"Hvis der ikke er flere arbejdsordrer for |MO|, står der i "
"stedet :guilabel:`Luk produktion` på knappen. Ved at klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Luk produktion` markeres hele |MO| som *Udført* og fjernes fra "
"*Værksted*-modulet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:105
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Close Production` button is always visible on the "
"manufacturing order card in the :guilabel:`Overview` tab."
msgstr ""
"Knappen :guilabel:`Luk produktion` er altid synlig på produktionsordrens "
"kort i fanen :guilabel:`Oversigt`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:112
msgid "View work order duration"
msgstr "Vis arbejdsordrevarighed"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:115
msgid "By individual work order"
msgstr "Efter individuel arbejdsordre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:117
msgid ""
"To view the duration of a work order, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Operations --> Work Orders`."
msgstr ""
"For at se varigheden af en arbejdsordre skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktionsapp --> Operationer --> Arbejdsordrer`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:120
msgid ""
"By default, the search bar has a filter applied to display incomplete work "
"orders only. To view work orders that have been completed and marked as "
"*Done*, remove the filter from the search bar by clicking on the :icon:`oi-"
"close` :guilabel:`(Remove)` button on the right side of the filter."
msgstr ""
"Som standard har søgefeltet et filter anvendt til kun at vise ufuldstændige "
"arbejdsordrer. For at se arbejdsordrer, der er blevet fuldført og markeret "
"som *Udført*, skal du fjerne filteret fra søgefeltet ved at klikke på "
"knappen :icon:`oi-close` :guilabel:`(Fjern)` i højre side af filteret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:124
msgid ""
"The actual time it took to complete each work order is displayed in "
"the :guilabel:`Real Duration` column. This value represents the total time "
"spent on the work order by all operators who worked on it. It includes time "
"tracked in the *Shop Floor* module as well as time tracked in the work order "
"form or the :guilabel:`Work Orders` tab of the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Den faktiske tid, det tog at fuldføre hver arbejdsordre, vises i "
"kolonnen :guilabel:`Reel varighed`. Denne værdi repræsenterer den samlede "
"tid brugt på arbejdsordren af alle operatører, der har arbejdet på den. Den "
"inkluderer tid sporet i *Værksted*-modulet samt tid sporet i "
"arbejdsordreformularen eller i fanen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer` i |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:129
msgid ""
"To view detailed time tracking information, select a work order. In the work "
"order form, go to the :guilabel:`Time Tracking` tab to see a detailed list "
"of all operators who have worked on the work order and the amount of time "
"they spent on it."
msgstr ""
"For at se detaljerede tidssporingsoplysninger skal du vælge en arbejdsordre. "
"Gå i arbejdsordreformularen til fanen :guilabel:`Tidssporing` for at se en "
"detaljeret liste over alle operatører, der har arbejdet på arbejdsordren, og "
"den tid, de har brugt på den."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:134
msgid "By manufacturing order"
msgstr "Efter produktionsordre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:136
msgid ""
"To view the duration of all work orders in a specific |MO|, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Operations --> Manufacturing "
"Orders`."
msgstr ""
"Hvis du vil se varigheden af alle arbejdsordrer i en specifik |MO|, skal du "
"gå til :menuselection:`Produktion app --> Handlinger --> Produktionsordrer`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:139
msgid ""
"By default, the search bar has a filter applied to display incomplete |MOs| "
"only. To view |MOs| that have been completed and marked as *Done*, remove "
"the filter from the search bar by clicking on the :icon:`oi-"
"close` :guilabel:`(Remove)` button on the right side of the filter."
msgstr ""
"Som standard har søgefeltet et filter anvendt til kun at vise ufuldstændige |"
"MOs|. For at se |MOs|, der er blevet fuldført og markeret som *Færdig*, skal "
"du fjerne filteret fra søgefeltet ved at klikke på :icon:`oi-"
"close` :guilabel:`(Fjern)` knappen i højre side af filteret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/shop_floor/shop_floor_tracking.rst:143
msgid ""
"Select an |MO|. In the |MO| form, go to the :guilabel:`Work Orders` tab to "
"see a list of all work orders included in the |MO|. To view details for a "
"specific work order, click anywhere on the entry line and the work order "
"form opens."
msgstr ""
"Vælg en |MO|. I |MO| formularen skal du gå til "
"fanen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer` for at se en liste over alle arbejdsordrer "
"inkluderet i |MO|. For at se detaljer for en specifik arbejdsordre skal du "
"klikke hvor som helst på linjen, og arbejdsordreformularen åbnes."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:5
msgid "Subcontracting"
msgstr "Underlevering"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:9
msgid ""
"In manufacturing, *subcontracting* is the process of a company engaging a "
"third-party manufacturer, or subcontractor, to manufacture products that are "
"then sold by the contracting company."
msgstr ""
"I produktion er *underleverandørarbejde* processen, hvor en virksomhed "
"engagerer en tredjepartsproducent, eller underleverandør, til at fremstille "
"produkter, som derefter sælges af den kontraherende virksomhed."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:12
msgid ""
"Subcontracting provides a variety of benefits for both the contracting "
"company and the subcontractor."
msgstr ""
"Underleverandørarbejde giver en række fordele for både den kontraherende "
"virksomhed og underleverandøren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:15
msgid ""
"For the contracting company, subcontracting allows them to sell a wide "
"variety of manufactured products, without having to worry about investing in "
"and maintaining the equipment and labor required to handle the manufacturing "
"themselves."
msgstr ""
"For den kontraherende virksomhed gør underleverandørarbejde det muligt at "
"sælge en bred vifte af fremstillede produkter uden at skulle bekymre sig om "
"at investere i og vedligeholde det udstyr og den arbejdskraft, der kræves "
"for selv at håndtere produktionen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:19
msgid ""
"This helps contracting companies stay flexible throughout economic cycles, "
"as they can easily increase or decrease their engagements with "
"subcontractors, as necessitated by the current moment. It also means they "
"are able to focus on tasks they excel at, while delegating more specialized "
"work to subcontractors."
msgstr ""
"Dette hjælper kontraherende virksomheder med at forblive fleksible gennem "
"økonomiske cyklusser, da de nemt kan øge eller mindske deres engagement med "
"underleverandører, alt efter hvad den aktuelle situation kræver. Det betyder "
"også, at de kan fokusere på opgaver, de er gode til, mens de uddelegerer "
"mere specialiseret arbejde til underleverandører."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:24
msgid ""
"On the other side of the relationship, subcontracting allows subcontractors "
"to specialize in more niche areas of production, which might not be as "
"profitable outside the bounds of a subcontracting engagement. In certain "
"arrangements, it also provides them with the flexibility to choose which "
"projects they accept or decline, and how many they work on at any given time."
msgstr ""
"På den anden side af forholdet giver underleverandørarbejde "
"underleverandørerne mulighed for at specialisere sig i mere nicheprægede "
"produktionsområder, som måske ikke ville være lige så rentable uden for "
"rammerne af et underleverandørengagement. I visse aftaler giver det dem også "
"fleksibiliteten til at vælge, hvilke projekter de accepterer eller afviser, "
"og hvor mange de arbejder på på et givet tidspunkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:29
msgid ""
"In Odoo, companies can configure their subcontracting workflows based on a "
"variety of different factors, including how components are sourced, and what "
"happens to finished products once they are manufactured."
msgstr ""
"I Odoo kan virksomheder konfigurere deres underleverandørarbejdsgange "
"baseret på en række forskellige faktorer, herunder hvordan komponenter "
"indkøbes, og hvad der sker med færdige produkter, når de er fremstillet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:35
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:3
msgid "Basic subcontracting"
msgstr "Základní subdodavatelství"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:35
msgid ""
"Subcontract products without supplying the subcontractor with components."
msgstr "Subdodávat produkty bez dodávání komponent subdodavateli."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:40
msgid "Resupply subcontractor"
msgstr "Genforsyning af underleverandør"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:40
msgid ""
"Ship components to a subcontractor each time a PO for a subcontracted "
"product is confirmed."
msgstr ""
"Odeslat komponenty subdodavateli pokaždé, když je potvrzena nákupní "
"objednávka na subdodávaný produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:45
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:3
msgid "Dropship to subcontractor"
msgstr "Dropshipping subdodavateli"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:45
msgid ""
"Dropship components to a subcontractor each time a PO for a subcontracted "
"product is confirmed."
msgstr ""
"Dropshipovat komponenty subdodavateli pokaždé, když je potvrzena nákupní "
"objednávka na subdodávaný produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:54
msgid ""
"To enable subcontracting in Odoo, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing "
"app --> Configuration --> Settings`, and tick the checkbox next to "
"the :guilabel:`Subcontracting` setting, under the :guilabel:`Operations` "
"heading. Then, click :guilabel:`Save`."
msgstr ""
"For at aktivere underleverandørarbejde i Odoo skal du gå "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Konfiguration --> Indstillinger` og sætte "
"kryds ud for indstillingen :guilabel:`Underleverandørarbejde` under "
"overskriften :guilabel:`Operationer`. Klik derefter på :guilabel:`Gem`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:None
msgid "The Subcontracting setting in the manufacturing app."
msgstr "Indstillingen for underleverandørarbejde i produktionsappen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:62
msgid ""
"With subcontracting enabled, a few different features become available in "
"Odoo:"
msgstr ""
"Når underleverandørarbejde er aktiveret, bliver et par forskellige "
"funktioner tilgængelige i Odoo:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:64
msgid ""
"On bills of materials (BoMs), the *BoM Type* field now includes a "
"*Subcontracting* option. Enabling the *Subcontracting* |BoM| type designates "
"the |BoM|'s product as a subcontracted product, which means Odoo knows that "
"it is produced by a subcontractor, and not by the company that owns the Odoo "
"database."
msgstr ""
"På styklister (BoM'er) inkluderer feltet *BoM-type* nu en "
"*Underleverandørarbejde*-indstilling. Aktivering af *Underleverandørarbejde* "
"|BoM|-typen udpeger |BoM|'s produkt som et underleverandørprodukt, hvilket "
"betyder, at Odoo ved, at det produceres af en underleverandør og ikke af den "
"virksomhed, der ejer Odoo-databasen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:68
msgid ""
"Two subcontracting routes become available in the *Inventory* app, and can "
"be assigned to specific products, on the *Inventory* tab of their product "
"pages:"
msgstr ""
"To underleverandørruter bliver tilgængelige i *Lager*-appen og kan tildeles "
"til specifikke produkter på fanen *Lager* på deres produktsider:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:71
msgid "*Resupply Subcontractor on Order*"
msgstr "*Forsy underleverandør ved ordre*"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:72
msgid "*Dropship Subcontractor on Order*"
msgstr "*Dropship underleverandør ved ordre*"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:75
msgid "Subcontracting workflows"
msgstr "Underleverandørarbejdsgange"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:77
msgid ""
"In Odoo, there are three subcontracting workflows, the main difference "
"between them being *how* the subcontractor obtains the necessary components:"
msgstr ""
"I Odoo er der tre underleverandørarbejdsgange, hvor hovedforskellen mellem "
"dem er, *hvordan* underleverandøren får fat i de nødvendige komponenter:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:80
msgid ""
"In the *basic* subcontracting workflow, the subcontractor is fully "
"responsible for obtaining the components. This workflow is outlined in "
"the :doc:`subcontracting/subcontracting_basic` documentation."
msgstr ""
"I den *grundlæggende* underleverandørarbejdsgang er underleverandøren fuldt "
"ansvarlig for at skaffe komponenterne. Denne arbejdsgang er beskrevet "
"i :doc:`subcontracting/subcontracting_basic`-dokumentationen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:83
msgid ""
"In the *Resupply Subcontractor on Order* workflow, the contracting company "
"sends the components from their warehouse to the subcontractor. This "
"workflow is outlined in the :doc:`subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply` "
"documentation."
msgstr ""
"I *Forsy underleverandør ved ordre*-arbejdsgangen sender den kontraherende "
"virksomhed komponenterne fra deres lager til underleverandøren. Denne "
"arbejdsgang er beskrevet i :doc:`subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply`-"
"dokumentationen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:86
msgid ""
"In the *Dropship Subcontractor on Order* workflow, the contracting company "
"purchases the components from a vendor, and has them delivered directly to "
"the subcontractor. This workflow is outlined in the :doc:`subcontracting/"
"subcontracting_dropship` documentation."
msgstr ""
"I *Dropship underleverandør ved ordre*-arbejdsgangen køber den kontraherende "
"virksomhed komponenterne hos en leverandør og får dem leveret direkte til "
"underleverandøren. Denne arbejdsgang er beskrevet i :doc:`subcontracting/"
"subcontracting_dropship`-dokumentationen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:90
msgid ""
"In addition to how a subcontractor obtains components, it is also necessary "
"to consider why a product is being subcontracted, as well as what happens to "
"products once they are manufactured by the subcontractor."
msgstr ""
"Ud over hvordan en underleverandør får fat i komponenter er det også "
"nødvendigt at overveje, hvorfor et produkt underleverandørarbejdes, samt "
"hvad der sker med produkter, når de er fremstillet af underleverandøren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:94
msgid ""
"In terms of why a product is being subcontracted, the two main reasons are "
"to fulfill a customer order, or to replenish the quantity of stock on-hand."
msgstr ""
"Co se týče důvodu, proč je produkt subdodavatelsky vyráběn, dva hlavní "
"důvody jsou splnění zákaznické objednávky nebo doplnění množství zásob na "
"skladě."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:97
msgid ""
"In terms of what happens to products once they are manufactured, they can "
"either be shipped to the contracting company, or dropshipped directly to an "
"end customer."
msgstr ""
"Co se týče toho, co se stane s produkty po jejich výrobě, mohou být buď "
"odeslány smluvní společnosti, nebo přímo dropshippingem koncovému "
"zákazníkovi."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:100
msgid ""
"Each of the three subcontracting workflows described above can be configured "
"to facilitate any of these possibilities, and the methods for doing so are "
"outlined in their respective documentation."
msgstr ""
"Každý ze tří výše popsaných subdodavatelských pracovních postupů může být "
"nakonfigurován tak, aby usnadnil kteroukoli z těchto možností, a metody pro "
"jejich provedení jsou popsány v příslušné dokumentaci."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:104
msgid "Subcontracted product valuation"
msgstr "Ocenění subdodavatelského produktu"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:106
msgid ""
"The valuation of a subcontracted product depends upon a few different "
"variables:"
msgstr ""
"Ocenění subdodavatelského produktu závisí na několika různých proměnných:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:108
msgid ""
"The cost of the required components, if provided by the contracting company; "
"from here on referred to as `C`."
msgstr ""
"Náklady na požadované komponenty, pokud je dodává smluvní společnost; odtud "
"dále označované jako `C`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:110
msgid ""
"The price paid to the subcontractor for the service of manufacturing the "
"subcontracted product; from here on referred to as `M`."
msgstr ""
"Cena zaplacená subdodavateli za službu výroby subdodavatelského produktu; "
"odtud dále označovaná jako `M`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:112
msgid ""
"The cost of shipping components to the subcontractor, and having them "
"shipped back to the contracting company; from here on referred to as `S`."
msgstr ""
"Náklady na přepravu komponent subdodavateli a jejich zpětné odeslání smluvní "
"společnosti; odtud dále označované jako `S`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:114
msgid ""
"The cost of dropshipping, if the components are shipped by the subcontractor "
"to the end customer; from here on referred to as `D`."
msgstr ""
"Náklady na dropshipping, pokud jsou komponenty odeslány subdodavatelem "
"koncovému zákazníkovi; odtud dále označované jako `D`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:116
msgid ""
"Any other associated costs, like import taxes, etc.; from here on referred "
"to as `x`."
msgstr ""
"Jakékoli další související náklady, jako dovozní daně atd.; odtud dále "
"označované jako `x`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:118
msgid ""
"Therefore, the total valuation of a subcontracted product (`P`) can be "
"represented by the following equation:"
msgstr ""
"Celkové ocenění subdodavatelského produktu (`P`) lze proto znázornit "
"následující rovnicí:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:121
msgid ""
"P = C + M + S + D + x\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"P = C + M + S + D + x\n"
"\n"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting.rst:124
msgid ""
"It is important to note that not every subcontracted product valuation will "
"include all of these variables. For example, if the product is not "
"dropshipped to the end customer, then there is no need to factor in the cost "
"of dropshipping."
msgstr ""
"Je důležité poznamenat, že ne každé ocenění subdodavatelského produktu bude "
"zahrnovat všechny tyto proměnné. Například pokud produkt není dropshippingem "
"doručován koncovému zákazníkovi, pak není nutné zohledňovat náklady na "
"dropshipping."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:10
msgid ""
"In basic subcontracting, a company's product is produced entirely by a "
"subcontractor. The product is first purchased from the subcontractor, who "
"acquires their own components, manufactures the final product, then delivers "
"the final product to the contracting company's warehouse."
msgstr ""
"Ved grundlæggende underleverandørarbejde produceres en virksomheds produkt "
"udelukkende af en underleverandør. Produktet købes først fra "
"underleverandøren, som anskaffer egne komponenter, fremstiller det endelige "
"produkt og derefter leverer det endelige produkt til det kontraherende "
"selskabs lager."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:14
msgid ""
"The following documentation covers how to configure a subcontracted product "
"and trigger the subcontracting process."
msgstr ""
"Følgende dokumentation dækker, hvordan man konfigurerer et "
"underleverandørprodukt og udløser underleverandørprocessen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:20
msgid ""
"To use subcontracting, contractors must first configure products with "
"a :ref:`vendor pricelist <purchase/products/pricelist>` as well as a "
"subcontracting-type |BoM|."
msgstr ""
"For at bruge underleverandørarbejde skal kontraherende parter først "
"konfigurere produkter med en :ref:`leverandørprisliste <purchase/products/"
"pricelist>` samt en underleverandørtype |BoM|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:23
msgid ""
"The pricelist allows the contracting company to purchase the product from "
"the vendor (subcontractor) through a |PO|, while the |BoM| allows the "
"product to be manufactured externally by the subcontractor."
msgstr ""
"Prislisten giver det kontraherende selskab mulighed for at købe produktet "
"fra leverandøren (underleverandøren) gennem en |PO|, mens |BoM| gør det "
"muligt at fremstille produktet eksternt af underleverandøren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:30
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:38
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:33
msgid "Configure product vendor"
msgstr "Konfigurer produktleverandør"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:32
msgid ""
"To configure a product's vendor for basic subcontracting, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> Products --> Products`. Then, select a "
"product or create a new one."
msgstr ""
"For at konfigurere en produkts leverandør til grundlæggende "
"underleverandørarbejde skal du gå til :menuselection:`Lager --> Produkter --"
"> Produkter`. Vælg derefter et produkt, eller opret et nyt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:35
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:38
msgid ""
"On the product form, click the :guilabel:`Purchase` tab and add the "
"product's subcontractor as a vendor by clicking :guilabel:`Add a line`. "
"Select the subcontractor in the :guilabel:`Vendor` drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"På produktformularen skal du klikke på fanen :guilabel:`Indkøb` og tilføje "
"produktets underleverandør som leverandør ved at klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj "
"en linje`. Vælg underleverandøren i rullemenuen :guilabel:`Leverandør`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:39
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:47
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:42
msgid "Then, enter the price of the product in the :guilabel:`Price` field."
msgstr "Indtast derefter produktets pris i feltet :guilabel:`Pris`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:41
msgid ""
"Finally, set a :doc:`lead time <../../inventory/warehouses_storage/"
"replenishment/lead_times>` for the product in the :guilabel:`Delivery Lead "
"Time` field to specify the number of days for the subcontractor to produce "
"and deliver the final product."
msgstr ""
"Angiv til sidst en :doc:`leveringstid <../../inventory/warehouses_storage/"
"replenishment/lead_times>` for produktet i feltet :guilabel:`Leveringstid` "
"for at specificere antallet af dage, det tager underleverandøren at "
"producere og levere det færdige produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:46
msgid ""
"Since contractors are only responsible for purchasing and receiving the "
"final product, they do not need to additionally configure manufacturing lead "
"times on a |BoM|. Instead, provide only a single *Delivery Lead Time* on the "
"vendor pricelist that factors in both the subcontractor's manufacturing and "
"delivery time."
msgstr ""
"Da kontraktører kun er ansvarlige for at købe og modtage det færdige "
"produkt, behøver de ikke ydderligere at konfigurere "
"produktionsleveringstider på en |BoM|. Angiv i stedet kun en enkelt "
"*Leveringstid* på leverandørprislisten, der tager højde for både "
"underleverandørens produktions- og leveringstid."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:54
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:62
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:58
msgid "Configure BoM"
msgstr "Konfigurace kusovníku"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:56
msgid ""
"After specifying the vendor, configure a subcontracting-type |BoM| for the "
"product. Click the :guilabel:`Bill of Materials` smart button on the product "
"form. Then, select the desired |BoM| or create a new one."
msgstr ""
"Når leverandøren er angivet, konfigurer en underleverance-type |BoM| for "
"produktet. Klik på smartknappen :guilabel:`Stykliste` på produktformularen. "
"Vælg derefter den ønskede |BoM| eller opret en ny."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:61
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:69
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:65
msgid ""
"Alternatively, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Products --"
"> Bills of Materials`, and select the |BoM| for the subcontracted product."
msgstr ""
"Alternativně přejděte na :menuselection:`Produktion --> Produkty --> "
"Kusovníky` a vyberte |BoM| pro subdodavatelský produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:64
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`BoM Type` field, select :guilabel:`Subcontracting`. In the "
"resulting :guilabel:`Subcontractors` field, add one or more subcontractors."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Styklistetype` vælges :guilabel:`Underleverance`. I det "
"resulterende felt :guilabel:`Underleverandører` tilføjes en eller flere "
"underleverandører."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:67
msgid ""
"Because the components and manufacturing are both handled by the "
"subcontractor, there is no need to list any components in "
"the :guilabel:`Components` tab of the |BoM|."
msgstr ""
"Da både komponenter og produktion håndteres af underleverandøren, er der "
"ingen grund til at angive nogen komponenter under "
"fanen :guilabel:`Komponenter` i |BoM|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:None
msgid "Bill of Materials configuration for subcontracting in Odoo."
msgstr "Konfiguration af stykliste til underleverance i Odoo."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:76
msgid "Basic subcontracting workflow"
msgstr "Základní subdodavatelský pracovní postup"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:None
msgid "Basic subcontracting workflow diagram in Odoo."
msgstr "Grundlæggende arbejdsgang for underleverance i Odoo."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:81
msgid ""
"The basic subcontracting workflow begins by :ref:`creating a PO "
"<subcontracting_basic/workflow/create_po>` to purchase the product from the "
"subcontractor (1)."
msgstr ""
"Den grundlæggende arbejdsgang for underleverance begynder med "
"at :ref:`oprette en IK <subcontracting_basic/workflow/create_po>` for at "
"købe produktet fra underleverandøren (1)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:84
msgid ""
"The contractor (YourCompany) then confirms the |PO|, which creates a receipt "
"to transfer the final product (2). The subcontractor manufactures the "
"product and delivers it back to the contractor when done."
msgstr ""
"Kontraktøren (DitFirma) bekræfter derefter |PO|, hvilket opretter en "
"modtagelse til overførsel af det færdige produkt (2). Underleverandøren "
"producerer produktet og leverer det tilbage til kontraktøren, når det er "
"færdigt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:87
msgid ""
"Once the product has been produced and received, the "
"contractor :ref:`validates the receipt <subcontracting_basic/workflow/"
"validate_receipt>` (5) to trigger :ref:`inventory moves "
"<subcontracting_basic/workflow/track-inventory>` from the subcontractor to "
"the company's stock (3, 4)."
msgstr ""
"Når produktet er produceret og modtaget, :ref:`validerer kontraktøren "
"modtagelsen <subcontracting_basic/workflow/validate_receipt>` (5) for at "
"udføre :ref:`lagerbevægelser <subcontracting_basic/workflow/track-"
"inventory>` fra underleverandøren til virksomhedens lager (3, 4)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:95
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:127
msgid "Create and confirm PO"
msgstr "Opret og bekræft IK"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:97
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:141
msgid ""
"To create a |PO| for the subcontracted product, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Purchase app --> Orders --> Purchase Orders`, and "
"click :guilabel:`New`."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette en |PO| for det underlevererede produkt gås "
"til :menuselection:`Indkøb-appen --> Ordrer --> Indkøbsordrer` og klik "
"på :guilabel:`Ny`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:100
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:144
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:132
msgid ""
"Begin filling out the |PO| by selecting a subcontractor from "
"the :guilabel:`Vendor` drop-down menu. In the :guilabel:`Products` tab, "
"click :guilabel:`Add a product` to create a new product line. Select the "
"subcontracted product in the :guilabel:`Product` field, and enter the "
"quantity in the :guilabel:`Quantity` field."
msgstr ""
"Begynd at udfylde |PO| ved at vælge en underleverandør fra "
"rullemenuen :guilabel:`Leverandør`. Under fanen :guilabel:`Produkter` "
"klikkes på :guilabel:`Tilføj et produkt` for at oprette en ny produktlinje. "
"Vælg det underlevererede produkt i feltet :guilabel:`Produkt` og indtast "
"mængden i feltet :guilabel:`Mængde`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:105
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:149
msgid ""
"After adding the product, the :guilabel:`Expected Arrival` field is updated "
"with the finished product's expected delivery date, as configured earlier "
"with the vendor's *Delivery Lead Time*."
msgstr ""
"Efter tilføjelse af produktet opdateres feltet :guilabel:`Forventet ankomst` "
"med det færdige produkts forventede leveringsdato, som konfigureret "
"tidligere med leverandørens *Leveringstid*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:108
msgid ""
"Finally, click :guilabel:`Confirm Order` to confirm the |PO|. A receipt is "
"automatically created, and a :guilabel:`Receipt` smart button appears at the "
"top of the form."
msgstr ""
"Klik til sidst på :guilabel:`Bekræft ordre` for at bekræfte |PO|. En "
"modtagelse oprettes automatisk, og en smartknap :guilabel:`Modtagelse` vises "
"øverst på formularen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:116
msgid ""
"After the order is confirmed, the subcontractor manufactures the product and "
"delivers the finished good back to the contracting company."
msgstr ""
"Når ordren er bekræftet, producerer underleverandøren produktet og leverer "
"den færdige vare tilbage til kontraktørvirksomheden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:119
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:164
msgid ""
"To receive the finished product from the subcontractor, click "
"the :guilabel:`Receive Products` button on the |PO|, or click "
"the :guilabel:`Receipt` smart button at the top of the page. Then, "
"click :guilabel:`Validate` to enter the incoming shipment into inventory."
msgstr ""
"For at modtage det færdige produkt fra underleverandøren klikkes på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Modtag produkter` på |PO| eller klik på "
"smartknappen :guilabel:`Modtagelse` øverst på siden. Klik derefter "
"på :guilabel:`Valider` for at registrere den indgående forsendelse på "
"lageret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:124
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:215
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:169
msgid ""
"If :doc:`multi-step inventory flows <../../inventory/shipping_receiving/"
"daily_operations>` are enabled, additional transfers must be validated to "
"enter the incoming product into stock."
msgstr ""
"Hvis :doc:`flertrinslagerstrømme <../../inventory/shipping_receiving/"
"daily_operations>` er aktiveret, skal yderligere overførsler valideres for "
"at registrere det indgående produkt på lageret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:130
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:221
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:175
msgid "Track inventory moves"
msgstr "Spor lagerbevægelser"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:132
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:223
msgid ""
"After validating a receipt, Odoo automatically generates inventory moves to "
"track the movement of subcontracted products between locations. To view "
"these inventory moves, navigate to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> "
"Reporting --> Moves History`."
msgstr ""
"Po ověření příjemky Odoo automaticky generuje skladové pohyby pro sledování "
"přesunu subdodavatelsky vyráběných produktů mezi lokacemi. Chcete-li "
"zobrazit tyto skladové pohyby, přejděte do :menuselection:`Lager --> Výkazy "
"--> Historie pohybů`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:136
msgid ""
"To track inventory movement in subcontracting, Odoo sends any product "
"components to a dedicated *Subcontracting Location*. A :ref:`virtual "
"location <inventory/warehouses_storage/location-type>` called *Production* "
"then consumes the components and produces the finished good. Once produced, "
"the good then moves back to the *Subcontracting Location* before finally "
"entering the contractor's stock when the receipt is validated."
msgstr ""
"Pro sledování skladových pohybů při subdodávkách Odoo odesílá všechny "
"komponenty produktu do vyhrazené *lokace subdodavatele*. :ref:`Virtuální "
"lokace <inventory/warehouses_storage/location-type>` nazvaná *Produktion* "
"pak spotřebovává komponenty a vyrábí hotový výrobek. Po vyrobení se výrobek "
"vrací zpět do *lokace subdodavatele*, než nakonec vstoupí do skladu "
"dodavatele, když je příjemka ověřena."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:None
msgid "Moves History page to see subcontracting moves in Odoo."
msgstr "Stránka historie pohybů pro zobrazení subdodavatelských pohybů v Odoo."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_basic.rst:146
msgid ""
"Because no components are sent in basic subcontracting, there is no movement "
"from the *Subcontracting Location* to the *Production* location."
msgstr ""
"Protože při základním subdodavatelství nejsou odesílány žádné komponenty, "
"nedochází k pohybu z *lokace subdodavatele* do lokace *Produktion*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:12
msgid ""
"In the *Dropship to Subcontractor* workflow, a company purchases the "
"components of a product from a vendor, who delivers them directly to the "
"subcontractor for manufacturing. The subcontractor then ships the finished "
"product back to the contracting company."
msgstr ""
"V pracovním postupu *Dropshipping subdodavateli* společnost nakupuje "
"komponenty produktu od dodavatele, který je doručí přímo subdodavateli k "
"výrobě. Subdodavatel poté odešle hotový výrobek zpět zadavatelské "
"společnosti."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:16
msgid ""
"The following documentation covers how to configure a subcontracted product "
"and trigger the *Dropship to Subcontractor* workflow."
msgstr ""
"Následující dokumentace popisuje, jak nakonfigurovat subdodavatelsky "
"vyráběný produkt a spustit pracovní postup *Dropshipping subdodavateli*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:24
msgid ""
"To use the *Dropship to Subcontractor* workflow, contractors must first "
"configure subcontracted products with a :ref:`vendor pricelist <purchase/"
"products/pricelist>` and a :ref:`subcontracting-type BoM <manufacturing/"
"subcontracting_dropship/config/bom-config>`. Each component must then be "
"configured with the appropriate :doc:`route <../../inventory/"
"shipping_receiving/daily_operations/use_routes>`."
msgstr ""
"Pro použití pracovního postupu *Dropshipping subdodavateli* musí zadavatelé "
"nejprve nakonfigurovat subdodavatelsky vyráběné produkty s :ref:`ceníkem "
"dodavatele <purchase/products/pricelist>` a :ref:`kusovníkem typu subdodávky "
"<manufacturing/subcontracting_dropship/config/bom-config>`. Každá komponenta "
"pak musí být nakonfigurována s příslušným :doc:`směrováním <../../inventory/"
"shipping_receiving/daily_operations/use_routes>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:30
msgid ""
"The pricelist allows the contracting company to purchase the product from "
"the vendor (subcontractor) through a |PO|, while the |BoM| allows the "
"product to be manufactured externally by the subcontractor. Routes are "
"applied to each component in order to be properly sent from the dropshipping "
"vendor to the subcontractor."
msgstr ""
"Ceník umožňuje zadavatelské společnosti nakoupit produkt od dodavatele "
"(subdodavatele) prostřednictvím |PO|, zatímco |BoM| umožňuje, aby byl "
"produkt vyráběn externě subdodavatelem. Směrování se aplikuje na každou "
"komponentu, aby byla správně odeslána od dropshippingového dodavatele "
"subdodavateli."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:40
msgid ""
"To configure a product's vendor for subcontractor dropshipping, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> Products --> Products`, and select a "
"product, or :doc:`create a new one <../../inventory/product_management/"
"configure/type>`."
msgstr ""
"Pro konfiguraci dodavatele produktu pro subdodavatelský dropshipping "
"přejděte do :menuselection:`Lager --> Produkty --> Produkty` a vyberte "
"produkt nebo :doc:`vytvořte nový <../../inventory/product_management/"
"configure/type>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:44
msgid ""
"On the product form, click the *Purchase* tab and add the product's "
"subcontractor as a vendor by clicking :guilabel:`Add a line`. Select the "
"subcontractor in the :guilabel:`Vendor` drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"Na formuláři produktu klikněte na kartu *Indk\\u00f8b* a přidejte "
"subdodavatele produktu jako dodavatele kliknutím na :guilabel:`Přidat "
"řádek`. Vyberte subdodavatele v rozevíracím menu :guilabel:`Dodavatel`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:49
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:44
msgid ""
"Finally, set a :doc:`lead time <../../inventory/warehouses_storage/"
"replenishment/lead_times>` for the product in the :guilabel:`Delivery Lead "
"Time` field to specify the number of days for the subcontractor to receive "
"components, produce the product, and deliver the finished good."
msgstr ""
"Nakonec nastavte :doc:`dodací lhůtu <../../inventory/warehouses_storage/"
"replenishment/lead_times>` pro produkt v poli :guilabel:`Dodací lhůta`, "
"abyste určili počet dnů, které subdodavatel potřebuje k přijetí komponent, "
"výrobě produktu a dodání hotového zboží."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:54
msgid ""
"Contractors do not need to configure manufacturing lead times on a |BoM|. "
"Instead, provide only a single *Delivery Lead Time* on the vendor pricelist, "
"factoring in the duration for the subcontractor to receive the components "
"from the dropship vendor, manufacture the product, and deliver the finished "
"good back to the subcontractor."
msgstr ""
"Zadavatelé nemusí konfigurovat výrobní dodací lhůty na |BoM|. Místo toho "
"uveďte pouze jednu *dodací lhůtu* v ceníku dodavatele, která zahrnuje dobu, "
"po kterou subdodavatel obdrží komponenty od dropshippingového dodavatele, "
"vyrobí produkt a dodá hotový výrobek zpět subdodavateli."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:64
msgid ""
"After specifying the vendor, configure a subcontracting-type |BoM| for the "
"product. To start, click the :icon:`fa-flask` :guilabel:`Bill of Materials` "
"smart button on the product's page. Then, select the desired |BoM| or create "
"a new one."
msgstr ""
"Po určení dodavatele nakonfigurujte |BoM| typu subdodávky pro produkt. Pro "
"začátek klikněte na inteligentní tlačítko :icon:`fa-"
"flask` :guilabel:`Kusovník` na stránce produktu. Poté vyberte požadovaný |"
"BoM| nebo vytvořte nový."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:72
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`BoM Type` field, select the :guilabel:`Subcontracting` "
"option. Then, add one or more subcontractors in "
"the :guilabel:`Subcontractors` field."
msgstr ""
"V poli :guilabel:`Typ kusovníku` vyberte možnost :guilabel:`Subdodávka`. "
"Poté přidejte jednoho nebo více subdodavatelů do "
"pole :guilabel:`Subdodavatelé`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:75
msgid ""
"Finally, make sure that all necessary components are specified on "
"the :guilabel:`Components` tab. To add a new component, click :guilabel:`Add "
"a line`, select the component in the :guilabel:`Component` drop-down menu, "
"and specify the required quantity in the :guilabel:`Quantity` field."
msgstr ""
"Nakonec se ujistěte, že jsou na záložce :guilabel:`Komponenty` uvedeny "
"všechny potřebné komponenty. Chcete-li přidat novou komponentu, klikněte "
"na :guilabel:`Přidat řádek`, vyberte komponentu v rozbalovací "
"nabídce :guilabel:`Komponenta` a zadejte požadované množství do "
"pole :guilabel:`Množství`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:None
msgid "The BoM of a product with components dropshipped to the subcontractor."
msgstr "Kusovník produktu s komponentami dropshippovanými subdodavateli."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:85
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:81
msgid "Configure components"
msgstr "Konfigurer komponenter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:87
msgid ""
"When dropshipping to subcontractors, each component of a product must have a "
"specified vendor and have the *Dropship Subcontractor on Order* route "
"enabled. This allows the components to be properly dropshipped from the "
"vendor to the subcontractor."
msgstr ""
"Při dropshippingu subdodavatelům musí mít každá komponenta produktu určeného "
"dodavatele a povolené směrování *Dropshipping subdodavateli při objednávce*. "
"To umožňuje, aby byly komponenty správně dropshippovány od dodavatele "
"subdodavateli."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:91
msgid ""
"To specify a component's vendor, select the component's name in "
"the :guilabel:`Components` tab, and click the :icon:`oi-arrow-"
"right` :guilabel:`(Internal link)` arrow."
msgstr ""
"Pro určení dodavatele komponenty vyberte název komponenty na "
"kartě :guilabel:`Komponenty` a klikněte na šipku :icon:`oi-arrow-"
"right` :guilabel:`(Interní odkaz)`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:95
msgid ""
"Alternatively, navigate to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> Products --> "
"Products` and select the component."
msgstr ""
"Případně přejděte do :menuselection:`Lager --> Produkty --> Produkty` a "
"vyberte komponentu."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:98
msgid ""
"On the component product form, click the :guilabel:`Purchase` tab. Add a "
"vendor by clicking :guilabel:`Add a line`. Then, select the vendor in "
"the :guilabel:`Vendor` field."
msgstr ""
"Na formuláři produktu komponenty klikněte na kartu :guilabel:`Indk\\u00f8b`. "
"Přidejte dodavatele kliknutím na :guilabel:`Přidat řádek`. Poté vyberte "
"dodavatele v poli :guilabel:`Dodavatel`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:101
msgid ""
"Next, to configure the route, click on the *Inventory* tab and select "
"the :guilabel:`Dropship Subcontractor on Order` route in "
"the :guilabel:`Routes` section."
msgstr ""
"Dále pro konfiguraci směrování klikněte na kartu *Lager* a vyberte "
"směrování :guilabel:`Dropshipping subdodavateli při objednávce` v "
"sekci :guilabel:`Směrování`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:104
msgid ""
"Repeat the process for every component dropshipped to the subcontractor."
msgstr ""
"Gentag processen for hver komponent, der dropshippes til underleverandøren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:None
msgid "Route for a component to be dropshipped to a subcontractor."
msgstr "Rute for en komponent, der skal dropshippes til en underleverandør."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:114
msgid ""
"The *Dropship to Subcontractor* workflow begins by :ref:`creating a PO "
"<manufacturing/subcontracting-dropship/workflow/create-po>` to purchase the "
"product from the subcontractor (1)."
msgstr ""
"*Dropship til underleverandør*-workflow begynder med at :ref:`oprette en IO "
"<manufacturing/subcontracting-dropship/workflow/create-po>` for at købe "
"produktet fra underleverandøren (1)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:118
msgid ""
"The contractor (Your Company) then confirms the *subcontractor* |PO| (2). "
"This creates an |RfQ| to purchase the components from the vendor, as well as "
"a receipt to transfer the final product."
msgstr ""
"Kontraktøren (dit firma) bekræfter derefter *underleverandørens* |PO| (2). "
"Dette opretter en |RfQ| for at købe komponenterne fra leverandøren samt en "
"kvittering for at overføre det færdige produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:121
msgid ""
"Next, the contractor :ref:`confirms the RfQ <manufacturing/subcontracting-"
"dropship/workflow/confirm-rfq>`, turning it into a *vendor* |PO| and "
"creating a dropship order to send the components from the vendor to the "
"subcontractor (3). Once the contractor :ref:`validates the dropship "
"<manufacturing/subcontracting-dropship/workflow/validate-dropship>` order, "
"the subcontractor begins to manufacture the final product with the "
"components and ships it to the contractor when done."
msgstr ""
"Herefter :ref:`bekræfter kontraktøren tilbuddet <manufacturing/"
"subcontracting-dropship/workflow/confirm-rfq>`, som derved bliver til en "
"*leverandør-* |PO| og opretter en dropship-ordre for at sende komponenterne "
"fra leverandøren til underleverandøren (3). Når kontraktøren :ref:`validerer "
"dropship- <manufacturing/subcontracting-dropship/workflow/validate-"
"dropship>`ordren, begynder underleverandøren at fremstille det færdige "
"produkt med komponenterne og sender det til kontraktøren, når det er færdigt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:128
msgid ""
"Once the product has been produced and received, the "
"contractor :ref:`validates the receipt <manufacturing/subcontracting-"
"dropship/workflow/process-receipt>` (6) to trigger :ref:`inventory moves "
"<manufacturing/subcontracting-dropship/workflow/track-inventory>` from the "
"subcontractor to the company's stock (4, 5)."
msgstr ""
"Når produktet er blevet fremstillet og modtaget, :ref:`validerer "
"kontraktøren kvitteringen <manufacturing/subcontracting-dropship/workflow/"
"process-receipt>` (6) for at udløse :ref:`lagerbevægelser <manufacturing/"
"subcontracting-dropship/workflow/track-inventory>` fra underleverandøren til "
"virksomhedens lager (4, 5)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:None
msgid "Diagram of dropship to subcontractor workflow."
msgstr "Diagram over dropship til underleverandør-workflow."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:139
msgid "Create and confirm subcontractor PO"
msgstr "Opret og bekræft underleverandør-IO"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:152
msgid ""
"Finally, click :guilabel:`Confirm Order` to confirm the |PO|. A receipt is "
"automatically created, and a :icon:`fa-truck` :guilabel:`Receipt` smart "
"button appears at the top of the form. In addition, a separate |RfQ| is "
"automatically created to purchase the components from the dropship vendor."
msgstr ""
"Klik til sidst på :guilabel:`Bekræft ordre` for at bekræfte |PO|. En "
"kvittering oprettes automatisk, og en :icon:`fa-"
"truck` :guilabel:`Kvittering`-smart-knap vises øverst i formularen. "
"Derudover oprettes automatisk en separat |RfQ| for at købe komponenterne fra "
"dropship-leverandøren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:157
msgid ""
"This |RfQ| is **not** automatically linked to the |PO|. It is accessed "
"separately on the *Requests for Quotation* page."
msgstr ""
"Denne |RfQ| er **ikke** automatisk linket til |PO|. Den tilgås separat på "
"siden *Tilbudsanmodninger*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:163
msgid "Confirm vendor RfQ"
msgstr "Potvrzení poptávky dodavatele"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:165
msgid ""
"To confirm the vendor |RfQ|, navigate to :menuselection:`Purchase app --> "
"Orders --> Requests for Quotation`. Select the newly-created |RfQ| for the "
"appropriate vendor."
msgstr ""
"For at bekræfte leverandørens |RfQ|, naviger til :menuselection:`Indkøb-app "
"--> Ordrer --> Tilbudsanmodninger`. Vælg den nyoprettede |RfQ| for den "
"relevante leverandør."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:168
msgid ""
"On the |RfQ|, the :guilabel:`Deliver To` field reads :guilabel:`Dropship "
"Subcontractor`, and the :guilabel:`Dropship Address` field shows the name of "
"the subcontractor to whom components are being dropshipped."
msgstr ""
"På |RfQ| står der :guilabel:`Lever til` i feltet :guilabel:`Dropship "
"underleverandør`, og feltet :guilabel:`Dropship-adresse` viser navnet på den "
"underleverandør, som komponenterne dropshippes til."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:172
msgid ""
"Click :guilabel:`Confirm Order` to confirm the purchase of components from "
"the vendor. Doing so turns the |RfQ| into a *vendor* |PO|. A :icon:`fa-"
"truck` :guilabel:`Dropship` smart button appears at the top of the vendor |"
"PO|."
msgstr ""
"Klik på :guilabel:`Bekræft ordre` for at bekræfte købet af komponenter fra "
"leverandøren. Dette gør |RfQ| til en *leverandør-* |PO|. En :icon:`fa-"
"truck` :guilabel:`Dropship`-smart-knap vises øverst i leverandør-|PO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:177
msgid ""
"Simultaneously, a :icon:`fa-truck` :guilabel:`Resupply` smart button appears "
"at the top of the *subcontractor* |PO| created earlier. In dropship "
"subcontracting, this smart button links to the dropship order."
msgstr ""
"Samtidig vises en :icon:`fa-truck` :guilabel:`Genforsyning`-smart-knap "
"øverst i *underleverandør-* |PO|, der blev oprettet tidligere. I dropship-"
"underleverandøraftaler linker denne smart-knap til dropship-ordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:None
msgid "Vendor RfQ for the dropshipped components of a subcontracted product."
msgstr ""
"Leverandørtilbud for de dropshippede komponenter af et "
"underleverandørprodukt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:187
msgid "Validate dropship order"
msgstr "Valider dropship-ordre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:189
msgid ""
"Once the components have been delivered to the subcontractor by the dropship "
"vendor, click the :icon:`fa-truck` :guilabel:`Dropship` smart button on the "
"vendor |PO| to open the dropship order."
msgstr ""
"Når komponenterne er blevet leveret til underleverandøren af dropship-"
"leverandøren, klik på :icon:`fa-truck` :guilabel:`Dropship`-smart-knappen på "
"leverandør-|PO| for at åbne dropship-ordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:193
msgid ""
"The dropship order can also be opened from the *subcontractor* |PO|. "
"Navigate to :menuselection:`Purchase app --> Orders --> Purchase Orders`, "
"select the |PO|, then click the :icon:`fa-truck` :guilabel:`Resupply` smart "
"button."
msgstr ""
"Dropship-ordren kan også åbnes fra *underleverandør-* |PO|. Naviger "
"til :menuselection:`Indkøb-app --> Ordrer --> Indkøbsordrer`, vælg |PO|, og "
"klik derefter på :icon:`fa-truck` :guilabel:`Genforsyning`-smart-knappen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:197
msgid ""
"Finally, click the :guilabel:`Validate` button at the top to confirm that "
"the subcontractor has received the components. The subcontractor then begins "
"manufacturing the final product."
msgstr ""
"Klik til sidst på :guilabel:`Valider`-knappen øverst for at bekræfte, at "
"underleverandøren har modtaget komponenterne. Underleverandøren begynder "
"derefter at fremstille det færdige produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:205
msgid ""
"After the subcontractor completes production, the finished product is "
"shipped to the contractor."
msgstr ""
"Efter underleverandøren har afsluttet produktionen, sendes det færdige "
"produkt til kontraktøren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:207
msgid ""
"To receive the product into stock, navigate to :menuselection:`Purchase app "
"--> Orders --> Purchase Orders`, and select the *subcontractor* |PO|."
msgstr ""
"For at modtage produktet på lager, naviger til :menuselection:`Indkøb-app --"
"> Ordrer --> Indkøbsordrer`, og vælg *underleverandør-* |PO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:210
msgid ""
"At the top of the |PO|, click the :guilabel:`Receive Products` button, or "
"click the :icon:`fa-truck` :guilabel:`Receipt` smart button. Then, "
"click :guilabel:`Validate` to enter the incoming shipment into inventory."
msgstr ""
"Øverst på |PO| klik på knappen :guilabel:`Modtag produkter`, eller klik på "
"den smarte knap :icon:`fa-truck` :guilabel:`Kvittering`. Klik derefter "
"på :guilabel:`Valider` for at indtaste den indgående forsendelse i lageret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:227
msgid ""
"In the *Dropship to Subcontractor* workflow, product components are first "
"sent from the vendors to a dedicated *Subcontracting Location*. "
"A :ref:`virtual location <inventory/warehouses_storage/location-type>` "
"called *Production* then consumes the components and produces the finished "
"good. Once produced, the good then moves back to the *Subcontracting "
"Location* before finally entering the contractor's stock when the receipt is "
"validated."
msgstr ""
"I arbejdsgangen *Dropship til underleverandør* sendes produktkomponenter "
"først fra leverandørerne til en dedikeret *underleverandørplacering*. "
"En :ref:`virtuel placering <inventory/warehouses_storage/location-type>` "
"kaldet *Produktion* forbruger derefter komponenterne og producerer det "
"færdige produkt. Når produktet er produceret, flyttes det tilbage til "
"*underleverandørplaceringen*, før det endelig kommer ind på kontrahentens "
"lager, når kvitteringen valideres."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_dropship.rst:None
msgid "Moves History for the dropship to subcontractor workflow."
msgstr "Flyttehistorik for dropship til underleverandør-arbejdsgang."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:3
msgid "Resupply subcontracting"
msgstr "Genforsyning af underleverandør"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:10
msgid ""
"In resupply subcontracting, a company supplies the components of its product "
"to a subcontractor, who manufactures the product, then delivers the finished "
"product to the contracting company's warehouse."
msgstr ""
"Ved genforsyning af underleverandør leverer en virksomhed komponenterne til "
"sit produkt til en underleverandør, som fremstiller produktet og derefter "
"leverer det færdige produkt til kontrahentvirksomhedens lager."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:13
msgid ""
"This article covers how to configure a subcontracted product and walk "
"through the resupply subcontracting process."
msgstr ""
"Denne artikel dækker, hvordan man konfigurerer et underleverandørprodukt og "
"gennemgår processen for genforsyning af underleverandør."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:21
msgid ""
"To use the resupply subcontractor workflow, contractors must first configure "
"products with a :ref:`vendor pricelist <purchase/products/pricelist>` and a "
"subcontracting-type |BoM|. Each component must then be configured with the "
"appropriate route."
msgstr ""
"For at bruge arbejdsgangen for genforsyning af underleverandør skal "
"kontrahenter først konfigurere produkter med en :ref:`leverandørprisliste "
"<purchase/products/pricelist>` og en |BoM| af typen underleverandør. Hver "
"komponent skal derefter konfigureres med den passende rute."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:25
msgid ""
"The pricelist allows the contracting company to purchase the product from "
"the vendor (subcontractor) through a |PO|, while the |BoM| allows the "
"product to be manufactured externally by the subcontractor. Routes are "
"applied to each component in order to be properly sent from the contractor "
"to the subcontractor."
msgstr ""
"Prislisten giver kontrahentvirksomheden mulighed for at købe produktet fra "
"leverandøren (underleverandøren) gennem en |PO|, mens |BoM| tillader, at "
"produktet produceres eksternt af underleverandøren. Ruter anvendes på hver "
"komponent for at blive sendt korrekt fra kontrahenten til underleverandøren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:35
msgid ""
"To configure a product's vendor for resupply subcontracting, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> Products --> Products`, and select a "
"product, or create a new one."
msgstr ""
"For at konfigurere et produkts leverandør til genforsyning af "
"underleverandør, gå til :menuselection:`Lager-app --> Produkter --> "
"Produkter`, og vælg et produkt eller opret et nyt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:49
msgid ""
"Since contractors are not responsible for manufacturing the final product, "
"there is no need to configure manufacturing lead times on a |BoM|. Instead, "
"provide only a single *Delivery Lead Time* on the vendor pricelist, "
"factoring in the duration for the subcontractor to receive the components "
"from the contractor, manufacture the product, and deliver the finished good "
"back to the contractor."
msgstr ""
"Da kontrahenter ikke er ansvarlige for at fremstille det endelige produkt, "
"er der ikke behov for at konfigurere produktionsleveringstider på en |BoM|. "
"Angiv i stedet kun en enkelt *Leveringstid* på leverandørprislisten, der "
"tager højde for varigheden for underleverandøren til at modtage "
"komponenterne fra kontrahenten, fremstille produktet og levere det færdige "
"produkt tilbage til kontrahenten."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:60
msgid ""
"After specifying the vendor, configure a subcontracting-type |BoM| for the "
"product. To start, click the :guilabel:`Bill of Materials` smart button on "
"the product's page. Then, select the desired |BoM| or create a new one."
msgstr ""
"Efter at have angivet leverandøren, konfigurer en |BoM| af typen "
"underleverandør for produktet. Klik på den smarte knap :guilabel:`Stykliste` "
"på produktets side. Vælg derefter den ønskede |BoM|, eller opret en ny."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:68
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`BoM Type` field, select the :guilabel:`Subcontracting` "
"option. Then, add one or more subcontractors in "
"the :guilabel:`Subcontractors` field below."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Styklistetype` vælg "
"indstillingen :guilabel:`Underleverandør`. Tilføj derefter en eller flere "
"underleverandører i feltet :guilabel:`Underleverandører` nedenfor."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:71
msgid ""
"Finally, add all necessary components in the :guilabel:`Components` tab. To "
"add a new component, click :guilabel:`Add a line`. Then, select the "
"component in the :guilabel:`Component` drop-down menu, and specify the "
"required quantity in the :guilabel:`Quantity` field."
msgstr ""
"Tilføj endelig alle nødvendige komponenter under "
"fanen :guilabel:`Komponenter`. For at tilføje en ny komponent klik "
"på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje`. Vælg derefter komponenten i "
"rullemenuen :guilabel:`Komponent`, og angiv den krævede mængde i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Antal`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:None
msgid "BoM for a resupply subcontracting product."
msgstr "Stykliste for et genforsyningsprodukt til underleverandør."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:83
msgid ""
"In resupply subcontracting, each component must be individually configured "
"with the *Resupply Subcontractor on Order* route. This allows the components "
"to be transferred from the contractor to the subcontractor when a |PO| is "
"made for the subcontracted product."
msgstr ""
"Ved genforsyning af underleverandør skal hver komponent individuelt "
"konfigureres med ruten *Genforsyning af underleverandør ved ordre*. Dette "
"gør det muligt at overføre komponenterne fra kontrahenten til "
"underleverandøren, når der oprettes en |PO| for det "
"underleverandørproducerede produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:87
msgid ""
"To configure a component's route, select the component's name in "
"the :guilabel:`Components` tab, and click the :icon:`oi-arrow-"
"right` :guilabel:`(Internal link)` arrow. Alternatively, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> Products --> Products`, and select the "
"component."
msgstr ""
"For at konfigurere en komponents rute, vælg komponentens navn under "
"fanen :guilabel:`Komponenter`, og klik på pilen :icon:`oi-arrow-"
"right` :guilabel:`(Internt link)`. Alternativt gå til :menuselection:`Lager-"
"app --> Produkter --> Produkter`, og vælg komponenten."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:91
msgid ""
"On the component product form, click on the :guilabel:`Inventory` tab. Then, "
"in the :guilabel:`Routes` section, select the :guilabel:`Resupply "
"Subcontractor on Order` route."
msgstr ""
"På komponentproduktformularen klik på fanen :guilabel:`Lager`. Derefter i "
"sektionen :guilabel:`Ruter` vælg ruten :guilabel:`Genforsyning af "
"underleverandør ved ordre`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:95
msgid ""
"Repeat the process for every component that must be sent to the "
"subcontractor."
msgstr ""
"Gentag processen for hver komponent, der skal sendes til underleverandøren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:None
msgid "Inventory routes for a resupply subcontracting component."
msgstr "Lagerruter for en genforsyningskomponent til underleverandør."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:None
msgid "Diagram of resupply subcontracting workflow in Odoo MRP Subcontracting."
msgstr ""
"Diagram over arbejdsgang for genforsyning af underleverandør i Odoo "
"Produktion underleverandør."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:108
msgid ""
"The resupply subcontracting workflow begins by :ref:`creating a PO "
"<manufacturing/subcontracting_resupply/workflow/create-po>` to purchase the "
"product from the subcontractor (1)."
msgstr ""
"Arbejdsgangen for genforsyning af underleverandør begynder med "
"at :ref:`oprette en indkøbsordre <manufacturing/subcontracting_resupply/"
"workflow/create-po>` for at købe produktet fra underleverandøren (1)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:112
msgid ""
"The contractor (YourCompany) then confirms the |PO|, which creates both a "
"resupply order to transfer the components and a receipt to receive the final "
"product (2) from the subcontractor."
msgstr ""
"Dodavatel (VašeFirma) poté potvrdí |PO|, což vytvoří jak objednávku doplnění "
"zásob pro převod komponent, tak příjemku pro přijetí finálního produktu (2) "
"od subdodavatele."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:115
msgid ""
"Next, the contractor :ref:`validates the transfer <manufacturing/"
"subcontracting_resupply/workflow/validate-resupply>` of components to the "
"subcontractor (3). The subcontractor begins producing the product."
msgstr ""
"Následně dodavatel :ref:`potvrdí převod <manufacturing/"
"subcontracting_resupply/workflow/validate-resupply>` komponent subdodavateli "
"(3). Subdodavatel začne vyrábět produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:119
msgid ""
"Once the product has been produced and received, the "
"contractor :ref:`validates the receipt <manufacturing/"
"subcontracting_resupply/workflow/process-receipt>` (6) to "
"trigger :ref:`inventory moves <manufacturing/subcontracting_resupply/"
"workflow/track-inventory>` from the subcontractor to the company's stock (4, "
"5)."
msgstr ""
"Jakmile je produkt vyroben a přijat, dodavatel :ref:`potvrdí příjemku "
"<manufacturing/subcontracting_resupply/workflow/process-receipt>` (6), což "
"spustí :ref:`pohyby zásob <manufacturing/subcontracting_resupply/workflow/"
"track-inventory>` od subdodavatele do skladu společnosti (4, 5)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:129
msgid ""
"To create a |PO| for the subcontracted product, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Purchase app --> Orders --> Purchase Orders` and "
"click :guilabel:`New`."
msgstr ""
"Chcete-li vytvořit |PO| pro subdodavatelsky vyrobený produkt, přejděte "
"na :menuselection:`Indkøb --> Objednávky --> Nákupní objednávky` a klikněte "
"na :guilabel:`Nový`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:137
msgid ""
"After adding the product, the :guilabel:`Expected Arrival` field is updated "
"with the finished product's expected delivery date, as configured earlier "
"with the vendor *Delivery Lead Time*."
msgstr ""
"Po přidání produktu se pole :guilabel:`Očekávaný příjezd` aktualizuje s "
"očekávaným datem dodání hotového produktu, jak bylo dříve nastaveno s "
"*dodávací lhůtou* dodavatele."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:140
msgid ""
"Finally, click :guilabel:`Confirm Order` to confirm the |PO|. A receipt and "
"a resupply order are automatically created, accessible via "
"the :guilabel:`Receipt` and :guilabel:`Resupply` smart buttons at the top of "
"the form."
msgstr ""
"Nakonec klikněte na :guilabel:`Potvrdit objednávku`, abyste potvrdili |PO|. "
"Automaticky se vytvoří příjemka a objednávka doplnění zásob, které jsou "
"přístupné přes inteligentní tlačítka :guilabel:`Příjemka` "
"a :guilabel:`Doplnění zásob` v horní části formuláře."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:147
msgid "Validate resupply order"
msgstr "Potvrdit objednávku doplnění zásob"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:149
msgid ""
"Click the :guilabel:`Resupply` smart button at the top of the |PO| to open "
"the resupply order, and click :guilabel:`Validate` to confirm that the "
"components have been sent to the subcontractor."
msgstr ""
"Klikněte na inteligentní tlačítko :guilabel:`Doplnění zásob` v horní části |"
"PO|, abyste otevřeli objednávku doplnění zásob, a klikněte "
"na :guilabel:`Potvrdit`, abyste potvrdili, že komponenty byly odeslány "
"subdodavateli."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:152
msgid ""
"Alternatively, navigate to the :menuselection:`Inventory` app, click "
"the :guilabel:`(#) To Process` button on the :guilabel:`Resupply "
"Subcontractor` card, and select the relevant resupply order. Then, "
"click :guilabel:`Validate` to confirm that the components have been sent to "
"the subcontractor."
msgstr ""
"Alternativně přejděte do aplikace :menuselection:`Lager`, klikněte na "
"tlačítko :guilabel:`(#) Ke zpracování` na kartě :guilabel:`Doplnění zásob "
"subdodavatele` a vyberte příslušnou objednávku doplnění zásob. Poté klikněte "
"na :guilabel:`Potvrdit`, abyste potvrdili, že komponenty byly odeslány "
"subdodavateli."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:161
msgid ""
"After the resupply order is confirmed, the subcontractor manufactures the "
"product and delivers the finished good back to the contracting company."
msgstr ""
"Po potvrzení objednávky doplnění zásob subdodavatel vyrobce produkt a dodá "
"hotové zboží zpět objednávající společnosti."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:177
msgid ""
"After validating the receipt, Odoo automatically generates inventory moves "
"to track the movement of subcontracted products between locations. To view "
"these inventory moves, navigate to :menuselection:`Inventory app --> "
"Reporting --> Moves History`."
msgstr ""
"Po potvrzení příjemky Odoo automaticky vygeneruje pohyby zásob pro sledování "
"přesunu subdodavatelsky vyrobených produktů mezi lokáciemi. Chcete-li "
"zobrazit tyto pohyby zásob, přejděte na :menuselection:`Lager --> Přehledy --"
"> Historie pohybů`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:181
msgid ""
"In resupply subcontracting, Odoo first transfers any product components to a "
"dedicated *Subcontracting Location*. A :ref:`virtual location <inventory/"
"warehouses_storage/location-type>` called *Production* then consumes the "
"components and produces the finished good. Once produced, the good then "
"moves back to the *Subcontracting Location* before finally entering the "
"contractor's stock when the receipt is validated."
msgstr ""
"Při doplnění zásob u subdodavatele Odoo nejprve převede všechny komponenty "
"produktu na vyhrazenou *subdodavatelskou lokáci*. :ref:`Virtuální lokáce "
"<inventory/warehouses_storage/location-type>` nazvaná *Výroba* pak "
"spotřebuje komponenty a vyrobce hotový produkt. Jakmile je produkt vyroben, "
"přesune se zpět do *subdodavatelske lokáce*, než nakonec vstoupí do skladu "
"dodavatele po potvrzení příjemky."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/subcontracting/subcontracting_resupply.rst:None
msgid "Moves History of resupply subcontracting in Odoo MRP Subcontracting."
msgstr ""
"Historie pohybů doplnění zásob u subdodavatele v Odoo MRP Subcontracting."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows.rst:5
msgid "Workflows"
msgstr "Arbejdsgang"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:3
msgid "By-Products"
msgstr "Biprodukter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:9
msgid ""
"When manufacturing certain products, it is common to be left with residual "
"materials, in addition to the finished product. These materials are known as "
"*by-products*. By specifying the by-products created during manufacturing on "
"a product's bill of materials (BoM), the quantity of by-products on-hand is "
"tracked by Odoo."
msgstr ""
"Ved fremstilling af visse produkter er det almindeligt at stå tilbage med "
"restmaterialer ud over det færdige produkt. Disse materialer er kendt som "
"*biprodukter*. Ved at angive de biprodukter, der skabes under fremstillingen "
"på et produkts stykliste (BoM), sporer Odoo mængden af biprodukter på lager."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:15
msgid ""
"Manufacturing a *rocking chair* requires ten pieces of wood. During "
"production, five pieces of *scrap wood* are created, in addition to the "
"rocking chair. By designating the scrap wood as a by-product on the rocking "
"chair's |BoM|, Odoo tracks the on-hand count of scrap wood, as well as the "
"quantity of rocking chairs produced."
msgstr ""
"Fremstilling af en *gyngestol* kræver ti stykker træ. Under produktionen "
"skabes fem stykker *affaldstræ* ud over gyngestolen. Ved at angive "
"affaldstræet som et biprodukt på gyngestolens |BoM| sporer Odoo beholdningen "
"af affaldstræ samt antallet af producerede gyngestole."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:23
msgid ""
"To specify by-products on a product's |BoM|, the *By-Products* setting "
"**must** be enabled. To do so, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app "
"--> Configuration --> Settings`, and tick the :guilabel:`By-Products` "
"checkbox, located under the :guilabel:`Operations` heading. Then, "
"click :guilabel:`Save` to apply the change."
msgstr ""
"For at angive biprodukter på et produkts |BoM| **skal** indstillingen "
"*Biprodukter* være aktiveret. Gå til :menuselection:`Produktion app --> "
"Konfiguration --> Indstillinger`, og marker "
"afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Biprodukter`, der findes under "
"overskriften :guilabel:`Operationer`. Klik derefter på :guilabel:`Gem` for "
"at anvende ændringen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:None
msgid "The By-Products setting on the Manufacturing app settings page."
msgstr "Indstillingen Biprodukter på Produktionsappens indstillingsside."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:32
msgid ""
"With the :guilabel:`By-Products` setting enabled, a :guilabel:`By-products` "
"tab appears on product |BoMs|."
msgstr ""
"Når indstillingen :guilabel:`Biprodukter` er aktiveret, vises en "
"fane :guilabel:`Biprodukter` på produkt-|BoMs|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:36
msgid "Add byproduct to BoM"
msgstr "Tilføj biprodukt til stykliste"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:38
msgid ""
"To add by-products to a |BoM|, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app "
"--> Products --> Bills of Materials`, and select a |BoM|."
msgstr ""
"For at tilføje biprodukter til en |BoM| skal du gå "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion app --> Produkter --> Styklister` og vælge en "
"|BoM|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:41
msgid ""
"On the |BoM|, select the :guilabel:`By-products` tab. Click :guilabel:`Add a "
"line`, and select the by-product in the :guilabel:`By-product` drop-down "
"field. In the :guilabel:`Quantity` field, enter the quantity of the by-"
"product produced during manufacturing."
msgstr ""
"På |BoM| skal du vælge fanen :guilabel:`Biprodukter`. Klik "
"på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje`, og vælg biproduktet i "
"rullemenuen :guilabel:`Biprodukt`. I feltet :guilabel:`Antal` skal du "
"indtaste mængden af det biprodukt, der produceres under fremstillingen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:45
msgid ""
"If the by-product is produced during a specific operation of a manufacturing "
"order (MO), select the operation in the :guilabel:`Produced in Operation` "
"field. For example, if a scrap wood by-product is produced during an "
"*Assemble* operation, select that operation in the :guilabel:`Produced in "
"Operation` field."
msgstr ""
"Hvis biproduktet produceres under en specifik operation i en "
"produktionsordre (MO), skal du vælge operationen i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Produceret i operation`. Hvis f.eks. et affaldstræs-"
"biprodukt produceres under en *Samle*-operation, skal du vælge denne "
"operation i feltet :guilabel:`Produceret i operation`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:None
msgid ""
"The By-Products tab on a BoM, configured with a \"Scrap Wood\" by-product."
msgstr ""
"Fanen Biprodukter på en stykliste, konfigureret med et \"Affaldstræ\"-"
"biprodukt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:55
msgid "Manufacture by-product"
msgstr "Fremstil biprodukt"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:57
msgid ""
"When an |MO| is completed and marked as *Done*, Odoo registers the quantity "
"of by-products created during the manufacturing process. To create a new |"
"MO|, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Operations --> "
"Manufacturing Orders`, and click :guilabel:`New`."
msgstr ""
"Når en |MO| er fuldført og markeret som *Udført*, registrerer Odoo mængden "
"af biprodukter, der er skabt under fremstillingsprocessen. For at oprette en "
"ny |MO| skal du gå til :menuselection:`Produktion app --> Operationer --> "
"Produktionsordrer` og klikke på :guilabel:`Ny`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:61
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Bill of Material` field, select a |BoM| on which by-"
"products have been specified. After doing so, the :guilabel:`Product` field "
"auto-populates with the corresponding product. Click :guilabel:`Confirm` to "
"confirm the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Stykliste` skal du vælge en |BoM|, hvor der er angivet "
"biprodukter. Derefter udfyldes feltet :guilabel:`Produkt` automatisk med det "
"tilsvarende produkt. Klik på :guilabel:`Bekræft` for at bekræfte |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:65
msgid ""
"When manufacturing is completed, click the :guilabel:`Produce All` button at "
"the top of the |MO|. After doing so, inventory counts update to reflect the "
"quantity of by-product(s) produced, as well as the quantity of the product."
msgstr ""
"Når fremstillingen er afsluttet, skal du klikke på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Producér alle` øverst på |MO|. Derefter opdateres "
"lagerbeholdningerne, så de afspejler mængden af producerede biprodukt(er) "
"samt mængden af produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:69
msgid ""
"Click the :guilabel:`Product Moves` smart button at the top of the |MO| page "
"to see the movements of components and products. Each by-product is listed "
"on the resulting :guilabel:`Inventory Moves` page, with the :guilabel:`From` "
"column displaying the virtual production location, and the :guilabel:`To` "
"column displaying the location where the by-product is stored."
msgstr ""
"Klik på smartknappen :guilabel:`Produktbevægelser` øverst på |MO|-siden for "
"at se bevægelserne af komponenter og produkter. Hvert biprodukt er angivet "
"på den resulterende side :guilabel:`Lagerbevægelser`, hvor "
"kolonnen :guilabel:`Fra` viser den virtuelle produktionsplacering, og "
"kolonnen :guilabel:`Til` viser den placering, hvor biproduktet opbevares."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/byproducts.rst:None
msgid "The Product Moves page for an MO with by-products."
msgstr "Siden Produktbevægelser for en MO med biprodukter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:3
msgid "Continuous product improvement"
msgstr "Løbende produktforbedring"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:13
msgid ""
"*Continuous improvement* is a general philosophy intended to help "
"individuals and organizations constantly improve themselves and the work "
"they produce."
msgstr ""
"*Løbende forbedring* er en generel filosofi, der har til formål at hjælpe "
"enkeltpersoner og organisationer med konstant at forbedre sig selv og det "
"arbejde, de producerer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:16
msgid ""
"There are a variety of different methodologies that fall under the umbrella "
"of continuous improvement. These include kaizen, six sigma, and lean, among "
"others. While the specific steps of each method differ, their goal remains "
"the same: implement a process by which improvement is a perpetual goal, "
"rather than a one-time accomplishment."
msgstr ""
"Der er en række forskellige metoder, der falder ind under paraplyen af "
"løbende forbedring. Disse omfatter kaizen, six sigma og lean, blandt andre. "
"Selvom de specifikke trin i hver metode er forskellige, forbliver deres mål "
"det samme: implementere en proces, hvor forbedring er et vedvarende mål "
"snarere end en engangspræstation."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:21
msgid ""
"The sections below contain details about how Odoo can be used to implement "
"four general steps common to many of the most popular continuous improvement "
"strategies, with links to documentation about configuring the necessary "
"features. The final section details how a specific company might configure "
"these Odoo implementations within their organization."
msgstr ""
"Nedenstående afsnit indeholder detaljer om, hvordan Odoo kan bruges til at "
"implementere fire generelle trin, der er fælles for mange af de mest "
"populære strategier for løbende forbedring, med links til dokumentation om "
"konfiguration af de nødvendige funktioner. Det sidste afsnit beskriver, "
"hvordan en specifik virksomhed kan konfigurere disse Odoo-implementeringer "
"inden for deres organisation."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:26
msgid ":ref:`manufacturing/workflows/ci-identify`"
msgstr ":ref:`manufacturing/workflows/ci-identify`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:27
msgid ":ref:`manufacturing/workflows/ci-suggest`"
msgstr ":ref:`manufacturing/workflows/ci-suggest`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:28
msgid ":ref:`manufacturing/workflows/ci-implement`"
msgstr ":ref:`manufacturing/workflows/ci-implement`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:29
msgid ":ref:`manufacturing/workflows/ci-review`"
msgstr ":ref:`manufacturing/workflows/ci-review`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:32
msgid ""
"Continuous improvement is not a one-size-fits-all methodology. While most "
"strategies include between four and six steps, proper implementation "
"requires developing a system tailored to the specific needs of each company."
msgstr ""
"Løbende forbedring er ikke en one-size-fits-all-metode. Selvom de fleste "
"strategier omfatter mellem fire og seks trin, kræver korrekt implementering "
"udvikling af et system, der er skræddersyet til hver virksomheds specifikke "
"behov."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:36
msgid ""
"This is not a limitation, but rather a benefit, as it makes the methodology "
"flexible enough to adapt to almost any use case. Odoo, in particular, adapts "
"well to this flexibility, as it can be configured to meet the needs of "
"almost any workflow."
msgstr ""
"Dette er ikke en begrænsning, men snarere en fordel, da det gør metoden "
"fleksibel nok til at tilpasse sig næsten enhver use case. Odoo tilpasser sig "
"især godt til denne fleksibilitet, da det kan konfigureres til at opfylde "
"behovene i næsten ethvert workflow."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:40
msgid ""
"As such, it is important to remember the content below only provides "
"*examples* of how Odoo *might* be used. They should be viewed as more of a "
"starting point, rather than a concrete outline that every organization must "
"follow."
msgstr ""
"Som sådan er det vigtigt at huske, at indholdet nedenfor kun giver "
"*eksempler* på, hvordan Odoo *kan* bruges. De bør betragtes mere som et "
"udgangspunkt end som en konkret skitse, som enhver organisation skal følge."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:47
msgid "Identify problems"
msgstr "Identificer problemer"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:49
msgid ""
"Before improvement can begin, it is necessary to determine where improvement "
"is necessary. This is where identifying problems comes into play. Two of the "
"best Odoo apps for identifying problems with products or processes are "
"*Helpdesk* and *Quality*."
msgstr ""
"Før forbedring kan begynde, er det nødvendigt at bestemme, hvor forbedring "
"er nødvendig. Det er her, identifikation af problemer kommer i spil. To af "
"de bedste Odoo-apps til at identificere problemer med produkter eller "
"processer er *Kundeservice* og *Kvalitet*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:54
msgid "Helpdesk"
msgstr "Helpdesk"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:56
msgid ""
"The *Helpdesk* app is useful for receiving feedback from outside of the "
"organization, like from clients or customers. This is accomplished by "
"implementing one (or more) of the methods for :doc:`receiving tickets "
"<../../../services/helpdesk/overview/receiving_tickets>`, including email "
"aliases, live chat conversations, and website forms."
msgstr ""
"*Kundeservice*-appen er nyttig til at modtage feedback fra uden for "
"organisationen, f.eks. fra klienter eller kunder. Dette opnås ved at "
"implementere en (eller flere) af metoderne til :doc:`modtagelse af tickets "
"<../../../services/helpdesk/overview/receiving_tickets>`, herunder e-mail-"
"aliaser, live chat-samtaler og hjemmesideformularer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:61
msgid ""
"Using these methods, customers can submit feedback about problems, which is "
"then reviewed by a member of a :doc:`helpdesk team <../../../services/"
"helpdesk>`. Depending on the outcome of the review, the team member may "
"decide to take further action to ensure the issue is addressed. This can "
"include creating a :doc:`quality alert <../../quality/quality_management/"
"quality_alerts>`."
msgstr ""
"Ved hjælp af disse metoder kan kunder indsende feedback om problemer, som "
"derefter gennemgås af et medlem af et :doc:`kundeserviceteam <../../../"
"services/helpdesk>`. Afhængigt af resultatet af gennemgangen kan "
"teammedlemmet beslutte at tage yderligere skridt for at sikre, at problemet "
"behandles. Dette kan omfatte oprettelse af en :doc:`kvalitetsalarm <../../"
"quality/quality_management/quality_alerts>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:67
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:93
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/quality.rst:7
msgid "Quality"
msgstr "Kvalitet"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:69
msgid ""
"The *Quality* app is useful for receiving feedback from *within* the "
"organization, like from employees."
msgstr ""
"*Kvalitet*-appen er nyttig til at modtage feedback fra *inden* for "
"organisationen, f.eks. fra medarbejdere."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:72
msgid ""
"One method for accomplishing this is to set up a :doc:`quality control point "
"<../../quality/quality_management/quality_control_points>` (QCP). A |QCP| is "
"used to automatically create quality checks at regular intervals, prompting "
"employees to inspect, and confirm, the quality of a product."
msgstr ""
"En metode til at opnå dette er at oprette et :doc:`kvalitetskontrolpunkt "
"<../../quality/quality_management/quality_control_points>` (QCP). Et |QCP| "
"bruges til automatisk at oprette kvalitetstjek med regelmæssige intervaller, "
"hvilket får medarbejdere til at inspicere og bekræfte kvaliteten af et "
"produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:77
msgid ""
"If an issue is found, an employee can then create a :doc:`quality alert "
"<../../quality/quality_management/quality_alerts>` to notify a quality team. "
"Quality alerts can also be created independent of a |QCP|, in the event that "
"an employee discovers an issue without being prompted to check for one. This "
"is a great way for customer support employees to notify a quality team of an "
"issue brought to their attention by a customer ticket."
msgstr ""
"Hvis et problem findes, kan en medarbejder derefter oprette "
"en :doc:`kvalitetsalarm <../../quality/quality_management/quality_alerts>` "
"for at underrette et kvalitetsteam. Kvalitetsalarmer kan også oprettes "
"uafhængigt af et |QCP|, i tilfælde af at en medarbejder opdager et problem "
"uden at blive bedt om at tjekke for et. Dette er en fantastisk måde for "
"kundesupportmedarbejdere at underrette et kvalitetsteam om et problem, der "
"er blevet bragt til deres opmærksomhed af en kundeticket."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:86
msgid "Suggest improvements"
msgstr "Foreslå forbedringer"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:88
msgid ""
"Once a problem is identified, the next step is to put forward ideas for how "
"to address the problem. As with identifying problems, the *Quality app* is "
"also useful for suggesting improvements. In addition, the *PLM* (*Product "
"Lifecycle Management*) app can be used for this purpose, as well."
msgstr ""
"Når et problem er identificeret, er næste skridt at fremsætte idéer til, "
"hvordan problemet kan løses. Som med at identificere problemer er *Kvalitet-"
"appen* også nyttig til at foreslå forbedringer. Derudover kan *PLM*-appen "
"(*Product Lifecycle Management*) også bruges til dette formål."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:95
msgid ""
"When creating a :doc:`quality alert <../../quality/quality_management/"
"quality_alerts>` to bring an issue to the attention of a quality team, "
"the :guilabel:`Corrective Actions` and :guilabel:`Preventive Actions` tabs "
"can be used to provide feedback about how the issue can be addressed."
msgstr ""
"Når der oprettes en :doc:`kvalitetsadvarsel <../../quality/"
"quality_management/quality_alerts>` for at gøre kvalitetsteamet opmærksom på "
"et problem, kan fanerne :guilabel:`Korrigerende handlinger` "
"og :guilabel:`Forebyggende handlinger` bruges til at give feedback om, "
"hvordan problemet kan håndteres."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:100
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Corrective Actions` tab is used to suggest a method for "
"fixing items affected by the issue. For example, `Screw the bolts on "
"tighter, so the seat stays in place`."
msgstr ""
"Fanen :guilabel:`Korrigerende handlinger` bruges til at foreslå en metode "
"til at rette elementer, der er påvirket af problemet. For eksempel: `Skru "
"boltene strammere, så sædet forbliver på plads`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:103
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Preventive Actions` tab is used to suggest a method for "
"preventing the issue from occurring in the future. For example, `Do not "
"tighten the screws too much, or they will be stripped`."
msgstr ""
"Fanen :guilabel:`Forebyggende handlinger` bruges til at foreslå en metode "
"til at forhindre, at problemet opstår i fremtiden. For eksempel: `Stram ikke "
"skruerne for meget, ellers bliver gevindene ødelagt`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:107
msgid ""
"The quality team that reviews the alert sees these suggested actions, and "
"can take them into account when deciding how to address the issue."
msgstr ""
"Kvalitetsteamet, der gennemgår advarslen, ser disse foreslåede handlinger og "
"kan tage dem i betragtning, når de beslutter, hvordan problemet skal "
"håndteres."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:111
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:132
msgid "PLM"
msgstr "PLM"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:113
msgid ""
"The |PLM| app is used to manage the lifecycle of a product from its "
"introduction through each successive version. As such, it is useful for "
"testing ideas for product improvements."
msgstr ""
"|PLM|-appen bruges til at håndtere et produkts livscyklus fra introduktionen "
"gennem hver successive version. Som sådan er den nyttig til at teste ideer "
"til produktforbedringer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:116
msgid ""
"Using :doc:`engineering change orders <../../plm/manage_changes/"
"engineering_change_orders>`, product management teams can create new "
"iterations of product |BoMs|, adding or removing specific components or "
"operations, as needed. The products created using these |BoMs| are put "
"through a review process to confirm the effectiveness of the changes."
msgstr ""
"Ved hjælp af :doc:`tekniske ændringsordrer <../../plm/manage_changes/"
"engineering_change_orders>` kan produktstyringsteams oprette nye iterationer "
"af produkt-|BoMs|, tilføje eller fjerne specifikke komponenter eller "
"operationer efter behov. De produkter, der oprettes ved hjælp af disse |"
"BoMs|, gennemgår en gennemgangsproces for at bekræfte effektiviteten af "
"ændringerne."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:124
msgid "Implement strategies"
msgstr "Implementer strategier"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:126
msgid ""
"Implementing strategies involves putting the proposed solutions from the "
"suggest improvements step into action. The |PLM| app continues to be useful "
"during this step, as it can be configured to make |BoM| updates. The *Field "
"Service* app can also be used by certain companies to make improvements to "
"products that have already been sold to customers."
msgstr ""
"Implementering af strategier indebærer at sætte de foreslåede løsninger fra "
"trin \"foreslå forbedringer\" i værk. |PLM|-appen er fortsat nyttig i dette "
"trin, da den kan konfigureres til at foretage |BoM|-opdateringer. *Felt "
"tjeneste*-appen kan også bruges af visse virksomheder til at foretage "
"forbedringer af produkter, der allerede er solgt til kunder."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:134
msgid ""
"Once |BoM| changes have gone through the proper review process, they can be "
"approved, and the updated |BoM| put into use. This is accomplished by "
"configuring one of the |ECO| review stages to :ref:`apply the changes <plm/"
"eco/apply-changes>` made to the |BoM|, at which point the updated |BoM| "
"becomes available for new |MOs|."
msgstr ""
"Når |BoM|-ændringer har gennemgået den rette gennemgangsproces, kan de "
"godkendes, og den opdaterede |BoM| tages i brug. Dette opnås ved at "
"konfigurere en af |ECO|-gennemgangsfaserne til at :ref:`anvende de ændringer "
"<plm/eco/apply-changes>`, der er foretaget i |BoM|, hvorefter den opdaterede "
"|BoM| bliver tilgængelig for nye |MOs|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:139
msgid ""
"Product |BoMs| can continue to be updated, as needed. The :doc:`version "
"control <../../plm/manage_changes/version_control>` features of the |PLM| "
"app allow for easy management of all versions of a given |BoM|."
msgstr ""
"Produkt-|BoMs| kan fortsat opdateres efter behov. :doc:`Versionskontrol "
"<../../plm/manage_changes/version_control>`-funktionerne i |PLM|-appen giver "
"mulighed for nem håndtering af alle versioner af en given |BoM|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:144
msgid "Field Service"
msgstr "Felt tjeneste"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:146
msgid ""
"The |PLM| app is a great way to make changes to product |BoMs|. However, "
"these changes only affect products produced using the new |BoM|. If a "
"defective product has already been sold to a customer, it may be necessary "
"to repair (or update) that product."
msgstr ""
"|PLM|-appen er en fantastisk måde at foretage ændringer på produkt-|BoMs|. "
"Disse ændringer påvirker dog kun produkter, der produceres ved hjælp af den "
"nye |BoM|. Hvis et defekt produkt allerede er solgt til en kunde, kan det "
"være nødvendigt at reparere (eller opdatere) det pågældende produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:150
msgid ""
"In such a case, the *Field Service* app can be used to schedule :doc:`onsite "
"interventions <../../../services/field_service/creating_tasks>`. These "
"interventions allow service technicians (or other employees) to be sent to a "
"customer's location to address an issue with a product."
msgstr ""
"I et sådant tilfælde kan *Felt tjeneste*-appen bruges til at "
"planlægge :doc:`interventioner på stedet <../../../services/field_service/"
"creating_tasks>`. Disse interventioner gør det muligt at sende "
"serviceteknikere (eller andre medarbejdere) til en kundes lokation for at "
"håndtere et problem med et produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:158
msgid "Review actions"
msgstr "Gennemgå handlinger"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:160
msgid ""
"Reviewing actions is where the \"continuous\" part of continuous improvement "
"comes into play, as it allows an organization to evaluate the decisions made "
"in the previous steps. As such, this step is, essentially, returning to the "
"beginning of the process, so that additional problems can be identified and "
"addressed."
msgstr ""
"Gennemgang af handlinger er, hvor den \"kontinuerlige\" del af kontinuerlig "
"forbedring kommer i spil, da det giver en organisation mulighed for at "
"evaluere de beslutninger, der er truffet i de foregående trin. Som sådan er "
"dette trin i bund og grund en tilbagevenden til begyndelsen af processen, så "
"yderligere problemer kan identificeres og håndteres."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:165
msgid ""
"This means that the *Helpdesk* and *Quality* apps should be used again to "
"receive customer and employee feedback. Another app that may be useful at "
"this stage is the *Surveys* app."
msgstr ""
"Dette betyder, at *Kundeservice*- og *Kvalitet*-apperne skal bruges igen til "
"at modtage kunde- og medarbejderfeedback. En anden app, der kan være nyttig "
"på dette trin, er *Undersøgelser*-appen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:169
msgid "Surveys"
msgstr "Undersøgelser"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:171
msgid ""
"After implementing changes to a product or process, it may be wise to "
"solicit customers for their feedback directly, rather than waiting to hear "
"from them of their own volition. This may bring to light feedback that "
"customers may have otherwise neglected to share."
msgstr ""
"Efter implementering af ændringer i et produkt eller en proces kan det være "
"klogt at bede kunder direkte om deres feedback i stedet for at vente på at "
"høre fra dem af egen drift. Dette kan bringe feedback frem, som kunderne "
"ellers kunne have undladt at dele."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:175
msgid ""
"One of the best ways to accomplish this is through the :doc:`Surveys "
"<../../../marketing/surveys>` app. Creating a survey, and sending it to "
"customers who receive an updated product, increases the likelihood of "
"receiving relevant feedback about the product."
msgstr ""
"En af de bedste måder at opnå dette på er gennem :doc:`Undersøgelser "
"<../../../marketing/surveys>`-appen. Oprettelse af en undersøgelse og "
"afsendelse af den til kunder, der modtager et opdateret produkt, øger "
"sandsynligheden for at modtage relevant feedback om produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:179
msgid "Example workflow: coat rack product improvement"
msgstr "Eksempel på workflow: forbedring af knagerækkeproduktet"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:182
msgid ""
"*Wood Hut* is a manufacturer of fine wood products. They are committed to "
"manufacturing products of the highest-possible quality, and are always "
"looking for ways to improve the products they sell, along with the processes "
"used to create them."
msgstr ""
"*Wood Hut* er en producent af fine træprodukter. De er forpligtede til at "
"fremstille produkter af højest mulig kvalitet og leder altid efter måder at "
"forbedre de produkter, de sælger, sammen med de processer, der bruges til at "
"skabe dem."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:186
msgid ""
"Wood Hut uses the Odoo platform to manage every element of their production, "
"fulfillment, and customer satisfaction processes. They have developed a "
"custom product improvement workflow that incorporates the Helpdesk, Quality, "
"PLM, and Manufacturing apps."
msgstr ""
"Wood Hut bruger Odoo-platformen til at håndtere alle elementer af deres "
"produktions-, opfyldnings- og kundetilfredshedsprocesser. De har udviklet et "
"tilpasset produktforbedringsworkflow, der inkorporerer Kundeservice-, "
"Kvalitet-, PLM- og Produktion-apperne."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:190
msgid ""
"One of Wood Hut's most popular products is their *coat rack*. It's made "
"entirely of oak, and customers describe it as \"sleek and elegant.\" "
"However, recent customer feedback about the coat rack has brought attention "
"to quality issues that necessitate revising the current manufacturing "
"process."
msgstr ""
"Et af Wood Huts mest populære produkter er deres *knagerække*. Den er lavet "
"helt af eg, og kunderne beskriver den som \"elegant og stilren.\" Men ny "
"kundefeedback om knagerækken har dog gjort opmærksom på kvalitetsproblemer, "
"der gør det nødvendigt at revidere den aktuelle produktionsproces."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:195
msgid ""
"The product revision workflow begins when the customer service team receives "
"a ticket in the Helpdesk app from a customer having problems with the coat "
"rack she purchased. The customer, Abigail Peterson, has found that her coat "
"rack falls over when more than five coats are hanging from it. This is a "
"major issue, as the coat rack has enough dowels for six coats."
msgstr ""
"Produktrevisionsarbejdsgangen begynder, når kundeserviceteamet modtager en "
"sag i Kundeservice-appen fra en kunde, der har problemer med den knagerække, "
"hun har købt. Kunden, Abigail Peterson, har opdaget, at hendes knagerække "
"vælter, når der hænger mere end fem frakker på den. Dette er et stort "
"problem, da knagerækken har nok kroge til seks frakker."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:None
msgid "A Helpdesk ticket about an issue with the coat rack product."
msgstr "En kundeservicesag om et problem med knagerækken."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:204
msgid ""
"Marc, the customer service employee assigned to the helpdesk ticket, opens "
"the Quality app, and creates a new quality alert. He tags the *Production "
"Quality Team* and assigns Julie Andreson as the quality employee responsible "
"for the alert."
msgstr ""
"Marc, kundeservicemedarbejderen tildelt sagen, åbner Kvalitet-appen og "
"opretter en ny kvalitetsadvarsel. Han markerer *produktionskvalitetsteamet* "
"og tildeler Julie Andreson som den kvalitetsansvarlige medarbejder for "
"advarslen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:208
msgid ""
"Julie reviews the alert, and consults with her team about the best course of "
"action. They decide that it is necessary to revise the product's |BoM| to "
"prevent the issue from occurring in the future, which Julie notes in "
"the :guilabel:`Corrective Actions` tab of the quality alert."
msgstr ""
"Julie gennemgår advarslen og rådslår med sit team om den bedste "
"fremgangsmåde. De beslutter, at det er nødvendigt at revidere produktets |"
"BoM| for at forhindre problemet i at opstå i fremtiden, hvilket Julie "
"noterer i fanen :guilabel:`Korrigerende handlinger` på kvalitetsadvarslen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:None
msgid "A quality alert created about the issue with the coat rack product."
msgstr "En kvalitetsadvarsel oprettet om problemet med knagerækken."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:216
msgid ""
"Then, Julie messages product engineer, Joe Kazan in the chatter of the "
"quality alert to bring it to his attention. Joe opens the |PLM| app and "
"creates a new |ECO|, noting the problem with the coat rack, and suggesting "
"that a change to the product's |BoM| may be necessary."
msgstr ""
"Derefter sender Julie en besked til produktingeniør Joe Kazan i chatten på "
"kvalitetsadvarslen for at gøre ham opmærksom på det. Joe åbner |PLM|-appen "
"og opretter en ny |ECO|, hvor han noterer problemet med knagerækken og "
"foreslår, at en ændring af produktets |BoM| kan være nødvendig."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:None
msgid "An ECO created to update the coat rack product's BoM."
msgstr "En ECO oprettet til at opdatere knagerækkens BoM."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:224
msgid ""
"Joe clicks :guilabel:`Start Revision`, and then the :guilabel:`Revision` "
"smart button to open version two of the coat rack's |BoM|. This |BoM| was "
"created alongside the |ECO|, and remains archived until it is approved."
msgstr ""
"Joe klikker på :guilabel:`Start revision` og derefter på "
"smartknappen :guilabel:`Revision` for at åbne version to af knagerækkens |"
"BoM|. Denne |BoM| blev oprettet sammen med |ECO| og forbliver arkiveret, "
"indtil den godkendes."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:228
msgid ""
"After some testing, Joe discovers that adding a metal *support rod* to the "
"coat rack strengthens it, allowing the rack to hold six or more coats "
"without falling over. He updates the |BoM| to include the support rod as one "
"of the components, and adds an extra operation to make sure it is installed "
"during the manufacturing process. Finally, he leaves a message in the "
"chatter of the |ECO|, letting his manager, Jose, know that it is ready for "
"review."
msgstr ""
"Efter nogle tests opdager Joe, at tilføjelse af en metal *støttestang* til "
"knagerækken styrker den, så rækken kan holde seks eller flere frakker uden "
"at vælte. Han opdaterer |BoM| til at inkludere støttestangen som en af "
"komponenterne og tilføjer en ekstra operation for at sikre, at den "
"installeres under produktionsprocessen. Til sidst efterlader han en besked i "
"chatten på |ECO|, hvor han fortæller sin chef Jose, at den er klar til "
"gennemgang."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:None
msgid "The coat rack BoM, updated to add an extra component and operation."
msgstr ""
"Knagerækkens BoM, opdateret til at tilføje en ekstra komponent og operation."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:238
msgid ""
"Jose reviews the changes, and confirms they are an effective method for "
"addressing the problem with the coat rack. He moves the |ECO| to the "
"*Approved* stage, which makes version two of the coat rack |BoM| the current "
"version."
msgstr ""
"Jose gennemgår ændringerne og bekræfter, at de er en effektiv metode til at "
"løse problemet med knagerækken. Han flytter |ECO| til stadiet *Godkendt*, "
"hvilket gør version to af knagerækkens |BoM| til den aktuelle version."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:242
msgid ""
"Now, each time an |MO| is created to produce a coat rack, the updated |BoM| "
"is automatically selected. Wood Hut begins producing the improved coat rack, "
"and customer feedback confirms that the new version has addressed the "
"problem with its predecessor."
msgstr ""
"Nu vælges den opdaterede |BoM| automatisk hver gang der oprettes en |MO| til "
"at producere en knagerække. Wood Hut begynder at producere den forbedrede "
"knagerække, og kundefeedback bekræfter, at den nye version har løst "
"problemet med forgængeren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/continuous_improvement.rst:246
msgid ""
"Using the Odoo platform, Wood Hut has implemented an end-to-end product "
"improvement process. Since the essential elements of this process (customer "
"feedback, quality control, etc.) are always functioning, it can be reused to "
"continuously update products and processes."
msgstr ""
"Ved at bruge Odoo-platformen har Wood Hut implementeret en ende-til-ende "
"produktforbedringsproces. Da de væsentlige elementer i denne proces "
"(kundefeedback, kvalitetskontrol osv.) altid fungerer, kan den genbruges til "
"løbende at opdatere produkter og processer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:3
msgid "Manufacture with lots and serial numbers"
msgstr "Produktion med lot- og serienumre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:8
msgid ""
"In Odoo, *lot numbers* and *serial numbers* are used to identify and track "
"products in Odoo. Serial numbers are used to assign unique numbers to "
"individual products, while lot numbers are used to assign a single number to "
"multiple units of a specific product."
msgstr ""
"I Odoo bruges *lotnumre* og *serienumre* til at identificere og spore "
"produkter i Odoo. Serienumre bruges til at tildele unikke numre til "
"individuelle produkter, mens lotnumre bruges til at tildele et enkelt nummer "
"til flere enheder af et specifikt produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:12
msgid ""
"When manufacturing products tracked using lots or serial numbers, Odoo "
"requires the lot or serial number to be assigned to each product before "
"manufacturing can be completed. This ensures that each product is properly "
"tracked from the moment it enters inventory."
msgstr ""
"Ved produktion af produkter sporet ved hjælp af lot- eller serienumre kræver "
"Odoo, at lot- eller serienummeret tildeles hvert produkt, før produktionen "
"kan afsluttes. Dette sikrer, at hvert produkt spores korrekt fra det "
"øjeblik, det kommer på lager."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:17
msgid "Configure products for tracking"
msgstr "Konfigurer produkter til sporing"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:19
msgid ""
"By default, Odoo tracks the quantity of each product on hand, but does not "
"track individual units of a product. Lot or serial number tracking must be "
"enabled for each product individually."
msgstr ""
"Som standard sporer Odoo antallet af hvert produkt på lager, men sporer ikke "
"individuelle enheder af et produkt. Sporing med lot- eller serienumre skal "
"aktiveres for hvert produkt individuelt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:22
msgid ""
"To track a product using lots or serial numbers, begin by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Inventory --> Configuration --> Settings`, then scroll "
"down to the :guilabel:`Traceability` section, and tick the :guilabel:`Lots & "
"Serial Numbers` checkbox. Finally, click :guilabel:`Save` to save the change."
msgstr ""
"For at spore et produkt ved hjælp af lot- eller serienumre skal du starte "
"med at navigere til :menuselection:`Lager --> Konfiguration --> "
"Indstillinger`, derefter rulle ned til sektionen :guilabel:`Sporbarhed` og "
"markere afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Lot- og serienumre`. Til sidst klikkes "
"på :guilabel:`Gem` for at gemme ændringen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:26
msgid ""
"Next, click on :menuselection:`Products --> Products`, and select a product "
"to track. Make sure the :guilabel:`Track Inventory` checkbox is ticked in "
"the :guilabel:`General Information` tab. Since lot and serial number "
"functionality is enabled, a drop-down menu appears next to the ticked "
"checkbox."
msgstr ""
"Klik derefter på :menuselection:`Produkter --> Produkter` og vælg et "
"produkt, der skal spores. Sørg for, at afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Spor "
"lager` er markeret under fanen :guilabel:`Generelle oplysninger`. Da "
"funktionaliteten for parti- og serienumre er aktiveret, vises en rullemenu "
"ved siden af det markerede afkrydsningsfelt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:30
msgid ""
"Click on the :guilabel:`Track Inventory` drop-down menu. By "
"default, :guilabel:`By Quantity` is selected, which only tracks the quantity "
"on hand. Select :guilabel:`By Lots` to track the product using lot numbers, "
"or :guilabel:`By Unique Serial Number` to track the product using serial "
"numbers."
msgstr ""
"Klik på rullemenuen :guilabel:`Spor lager`. Som standard er :guilabel:`Efter "
"antal` valgt, som kun sporer det tilgængelige antal. Vælg :guilabel:`Efter "
"partier` for at spore produktet ved hjælp af partinumre, "
"eller :guilabel:`Efter unikt serienummer` for at spore produktet ved hjælp "
"af serienumre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:35
msgid ""
":doc:`Lots <../../inventory/product_management/product_tracking/"
"lots>` :doc:`Serial numbers <../../inventory/product_management/"
"product_tracking/serial_numbers>`"
msgstr ""
":doc:`Partier <../../inventory/product_management/product_tracking/"
"lots>` :doc:`Serienumre <../../inventory/product_management/product_tracking/"
"serial_numbers>`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:39
msgid "Lot number manufacturing"
msgstr "Partinummerproduktion"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:41
msgid ""
"To manufacture a product tracked with lots, begin by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders`. "
"Click :guilabel:`New` to create a new manufacturing order (MO)."
msgstr ""
"For at producere et produkt sporet med partier skal du starte med at "
"navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operationer --> "
"Produktionsordrer`. Klik på :guilabel:`Ny` for at oprette en ny "
"produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:45
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Product` field, select a product tracked using lots, and "
"enter the desired :guilabel:`Quantity`. Click :guilabel:`Confirm` to confirm "
"the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Produkt` skal du vælge et produkt sporet ved hjælp af "
"partier og indtaste det ønskede :guilabel:`Antal`. Klik "
"på :guilabel:`Bekræft` for at bekræfte |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:48
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:76
msgid ""
"Once the |MO| is confirmed, a :guilabel:`Lot/Serial Number` field appears in "
"the top section of the |MO| form. By default, this field is empty."
msgstr ""
"Når |MO| er bekræftet, vises et felt :guilabel:`Parti-/serienummer` i den "
"øverste del af |MO|-formularen. Som standard er dette felt tomt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:51
msgid ""
"To populate the :guilabel:`Lot/Serial Number` field with a lot number, click "
"the :icon:`fa-plus-square-o` :guilabel:`(plus)` icon to the right of the "
"field. Doing so automatically generates a lot, using the next available "
"number, and enters it in the field."
msgstr ""
"For at udfylde feltet :guilabel:`Parti-/serienummer` med et partinummer skal "
"du klikke på :icon:`fa-plus-square-o` :guilabel:`(plus)`-ikonet til højre "
"for feltet. Dette genererer automatisk et parti ved hjælp af det næste "
"tilgængelige nummer og indtaster det i feltet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:55
msgid ""
"Alternatively, click on the :guilabel:`Lot/Serial Number` field and select "
"an existing lot number, or manually enter a new lot number and "
"click :guilabel:`Create \"#\"` in the drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"Alternativt kan du klikke på feltet :guilabel:`Parti-/serienummer` og vælge "
"et eksisterende partinummer eller manuelt indtaste et nyt partinummer og "
"klikke på :guilabel:`Opret \"#\"` i rullemenuen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:None
msgid "The \"Lot/Serial Number\" field on an MO."
msgstr "Feltet \"Parti-/serienummer\" på en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:61
msgid ""
"Either of these methods assign the product(s) in the |MO| a lot number "
"before production is finished. It is also possible to complete production "
"and close the |MO| by clicking :guilabel:`Produce All`, without assigning a "
"lot number. Doing so automatically generates and assigns a lot, using the "
"next available number."
msgstr ""
"Begge disse metoder tildeler produkt(erne) i |MO| et partinummer, før "
"produktionen er afsluttet. Det er også muligt at fuldføre produktionen og "
"lukke |MO| ved at klikke på :guilabel:`Producér alle` uden at tildele et "
"partinummer. Dette genererer og tildeler automatisk et parti ved hjælp af "
"det næste tilgængelige nummer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:67
msgid "Serial number manufacturing"
msgstr "Serienummerproduktion"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:69
msgid ""
"To manufacture a product tracked with serial numbers, begin by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders`. "
"Click :guilabel:`New` to create a new |MO|."
msgstr ""
"For at producere et produkt sporet med serienumre skal du starte med at "
"navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operationer --> "
"Produktionsordrer`. Klik på :guilabel:`Ny` for at oprette en ny |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:73
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Product` field, select a product tracked using serial "
"numbers, and enter the desired :guilabel:`Quantity`. "
"Click :guilabel:`Confirm` to confirm the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Produkt` skal du vælge et produkt sporet ved hjælp af "
"serienumre og indtaste det ønskede :guilabel:`Antal`. Klik "
"på :guilabel:`Bekræft` for at bekræfte |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:79
msgid ""
"The rest of the manufacturing process depends on how many units the |MO| "
"contains."
msgstr ""
"Resten af produktionsprocessenafhænger af, hvor mange enheder |MO| "
"indeholder."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:82
msgid "Manufacture single unit"
msgstr "Producér enkelt enhed"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:84
msgid ""
"If a single unit of the product is being manufactured, "
"clicking :guilabel:`Produce All` closes the |MO|, and automatically "
"generates and assigns the next available serial number, which appears in "
"the :guilabel:`Lot/Serial Number` field."
msgstr ""
"Hvis en enkelt enhed af produktet produceres, lukker klik "
"på :guilabel:`Producér alle` |MO| og genererer og tildeler automatisk det "
"næste tilgængelige serienummer, som vises i feltet :guilabel:`Parti-/"
"serienummer`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:88
msgid ""
"To assign a serial number without closing the |MO|, enter a number manually "
"in the :guilabel:`Lot/Serial Number` field, and click :guilabel:`Create "
"\"#\"`, or click the :icon:`fa-plus-square-o` :guilabel:`(plus)` icon to the "
"right of the field to auto-fill it with the next available number."
msgstr ""
"For at tildele et serienummer uden at lukke |MO| skal du indtaste et nummer "
"manuelt i feltet :guilabel:`Parti-/serienummer` og klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Opret \"#\"`, eller klikke på :icon:`fa-plus-square-"
"o` :guilabel:`(plus)`-ikonet til højre for feltet for automatisk at udfylde "
"det med det næste tilgængelige nummer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:97
msgid "Manufacture multiple units"
msgstr "Producér flere enheder"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:100
msgid ""
"When manufacturing a product tracked using serial numbers, an |MO| can be "
"created for multiple units. However, when serial numbers are assigned to "
"each unit, either at the end of production or before, the |MO| is split into "
"multiple |MOs|, each containing one unit of the product."
msgstr ""
"Når der produceres et produkt sporet ved hjælp af serienumre, kan en |MO| "
"oprettes for flere enheder. Når der dog tildeles serienumre til hver enhed, "
"enten ved afslutningen af produktionen eller før, opdeles |MO| i flere |"
"MOs|, der hver indeholder én enhed af produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:104
msgid ""
"Each of the split |MOs| is identified by a numerical tag added to the end of "
"the original |MO| number."
msgstr ""
"Hver af de delte |MOs| identificeres med et numerisk tag tilføjet i "
"slutningen af det originale |MO|-nummer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:108
msgid ""
"|MO| `WH/MO/00109` contains two units of a `Chair`, a product tracked using "
"serial numbers. A serial number is assigned to each unit of the chair. This "
"causes the |MO| to be split into two |MOs|, each containing one unit of the "
"chair. The |MOs| are titled `WH/MO/00109-001` and `WH/MO/00109-002`."
msgstr ""
"|MO| `WH/MO/00109` indeholder to enheder af en `Chair`, et produkt sporet "
"ved hjælp af serienumre. Et serienummer tildeles til hver enhed af stolen. "
"Dette får |MO| til at blive delt i to |MOs|, der hver indeholder én enhed af "
"stolen. |MOs| har titlerne `WH/MO/00109-001` og `WH/MO/00109-002`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:113
msgid ""
"To assign serial numbers to each unit of an |MO|, click :guilabel:`Produce "
"All` to open the :guilabel:`Batch Production` pop-up window."
msgstr ""
"For at tildele serienumre til hver enhed af en |MO|, klik "
"på :guilabel:`Producer alle` for at åbne pop op-"
"vinduet :guilabel:`Batchproduktion`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:116
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`First Lot/SN` field of the pop-up window is auto-filled with "
"the next available serial number. The :guilabel:`Number of SN` field "
"defaults to the number of units being manufactured. The values of either "
"field can be changed manually."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`Første lot/SN` i pop op-vinduet udfyldes automatisk med "
"det næste tilgængelige serienummer. Feltet :guilabel:`Antal SN` "
"standardindstilles til antallet af enheder, der produceres. Værdierne i "
"begge felter kan ændres manuelt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:120
msgid ""
"Click :guilabel:`Generate` to generate the specified number of serial "
"numbers, beginning with the number entered in the :guilabel:`First Lot/SN` "
"field. The serial numbers are displayed in the text box at the bottom of the "
"pop-up window, and can be manually changed after generation."
msgstr ""
"Klik på :guilabel:`Generer` for at generere det angivne antal serienumre, "
"startende med det nummer, der er indtastet i feltet :guilabel:`Første lot/"
"SN`. Serienumrene vises i tekstfeltet nederst i pop op-vinduet og kan ændres "
"manuelt efter generering."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:124
msgid ""
"To assign serial numbers without completing production, click "
"the :guilabel:`Prepare MO` button. Doing so splits the |MO| into individual |"
"MOs|, one for each unit in the original |MO|. Each |MO| is left open, and "
"can be closed individually."
msgstr ""
"For at tildele serienumre uden at fuldføre produktionen, klik på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Forbered MO`. Dette deler |MO| i individuelle |MOs|, én "
"for hver enhed i den originale |MO|. Hver |MO| forbliver åben og kan lukkes "
"individuelt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:128
msgid ""
"To assign serial numbers and complete production, click "
"the :guilabel:`Produce` button. Doing so splits the |MO| into individual |"
"MOs|, one for each unit in the original |MO|. All of the |MOs| are closed, "
"since production is complete."
msgstr ""
"For at tildele serienumre og fuldføre produktionen, klik på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Producer`. Dette deler |MO| i individuelle |MOs|, én for "
"hver enhed i den originale |MO|. Alle |MOs| lukkes, da produktionen er "
"fuldført."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:None
msgid ""
"The \"Batch Production\" pop-up window, from which serial numbers can be "
"assigned."
msgstr "Pop op-vinduet \"Batchproduktion\", hvorfra serienumre kan tildeles."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacture_lots_serials.rst:135
msgid ""
"After clicking :guilabel:`Prepare MO` or :guilabel:`Produce`, "
"the :menuselection:`Manufacturing` app automatically shows the first of the "
"split |MOs| (ex. `WH/MO/00109-001`). To view and access the rest the split |"
"MOs|, click the :guilabel:`Backorders` smart button at the top of the screen."
msgstr ""
"Efter at have klikket på :guilabel:`Forbered MO` eller :guilabel:`Producer`, "
"viser appen :menuselection:`Produktion` automatisk den første af de delte |"
"MOs| (f.eks. `WH/MO/00109-001`). For at se og få adgang til resten af de "
"delte |MOs|, klik på den smarte knap :guilabel:`Restordrer` øverst på "
"skærmen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:3
msgid "Manufacturing backorders"
msgstr "Produktionsrestordrer"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:7
msgid ""
"In some cases, the full quantity of a manufacturing order cannot be produced "
"immediately. When this happens, Odoo *Manufacturing* allows for the "
"manufacturing of partial quantities of the order and creates a *backorder* "
"for the remaining amount."
msgstr ""
"I nogle tilfælde kan den fulde mængde af en produktionsordre ikke produceres "
"med det samme. Når dette sker, tillader Odoo *Produktion* fremstilling af "
"delvise mængder af ordren og opretter en *restordre* for det resterende "
"antal."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:11
msgid ""
"In the *Manufacturing* app, creating a backorder splits the original "
"manufacturing order into two orders. The reference tag for each order is the "
"tag used for the original order, followed by a hyphen and then an additional "
"number to indicate that it's a backorder."
msgstr ""
"I appen *Produktion* deler oprettelsen af en restordre den originale "
"produktionsordre i to ordrer. Referencetaget for hver ordre er det tag, der "
"blev brugt til den originale ordre, efterfulgt af en bindestreg og derefter "
"et yderligere nummer for at angive, at det er en restordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:16
msgid ""
"A company creates a manufacturing order with the reference tag *WH/MO/"
"00175*, for 10 units of *Product X*. After starting work on the "
"manufacturing order, the employee working the production line realizes there "
"are only enough components in stock to produce five units of the product."
msgstr ""
"En virksomhed opretter en produktionsordre med referencetaget *WH/MO/00175* "
"for 10 enheder af *Produkt X*. Efter at have påbegyndt arbejdet med "
"produktionsordren indser medarbejderen, der arbejder på produktionslinjen, "
"at der kun er nok komponenter på lager til at producere fem enheder af "
"produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:20
msgid ""
"Instead of waiting for additional stock of the components, they manufacture "
"five units and create a backorder for the remaining five. This splits the "
"manufacturing order into two separate orders: *WH/MO/00175-001* and *WH/MO/"
"00175-002*."
msgstr ""
"I stedet for at vente på yderligere lager af komponenterne, fremstiller de "
"fem enheder og opretter en restordre for de resterende fem. Dette deler "
"produktionsordren i to separate ordrer: *WH/MO/00175-001* og *WH/MO/"
"00175-002*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:24
msgid ""
"Order *001* contains the five units that have been manufactured, and is "
"immediately marked as :guilabel:`Done`. Order *002* contains the five units "
"that still need to be manufactured and is marked as :guilabel:`In Progress`. "
"Once the remaining components are available, the employee returns to order "
"*002* and manufactures the remaining units before closing the order."
msgstr ""
"Ordre *001* indeholder de fem enheder, der er blevet fremstillet, og "
"markeres straks som :guilabel:`Udført`. Ordre *002* indeholder de fem "
"enheder, der stadig skal fremstilles, og markeres som :guilabel:`I gang`. "
"Når de resterende komponenter er tilgængelige, vender medarbejderen tilbage "
"til ordre *002* og fremstiller de resterende enheder, før ordren lukkes."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:30
msgid "Create a manufacturing backorder"
msgstr "Opret en produktionsrestordre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:32
msgid ""
"To create a backorder for part of a manufacturing order, begin by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders`. "
"Select a manufacturing order with a quantity of two or more or create one by "
"clicking :guilabel:`Create`."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette en restordre for en del af en produktionsordre, start med at "
"navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operationer --> "
"Produktionsordrer`. Vælg en produktionsordre med et antal på to eller flere, "
"eller opret en ved at klikke på :guilabel:`Opret`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:36
msgid ""
"If a new manufacturing order is created, select a product from "
"the :guilabel:`Product` drop-down menu and enter a quantity of two or more "
"in the :guilabel:`Quantity` field, then click :guilabel:`Confirm` to confirm "
"the order."
msgstr ""
"Hvis der oprettes en ny produktionsordre, vælg et produkt fra "
"rullemenuen :guilabel:`Produkt` og indtast et antal på to eller flere i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Antal`, og klik derefter på :guilabel:`Bekræft` for at "
"bekræfte ordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:40
msgid ""
"After manufacturing the quantity that is being produced immediately, enter "
"that number in the :guilabel:`Quantity` field at the top of the "
"manufacturing order."
msgstr ""
"Efter fremstilling af den mængde, der produceres med det samme, indtast "
"dette nummer i feltet :guilabel:`Antal` øverst i produktionsordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:None
msgid "The quantity field on a manufacturing order."
msgstr "Antal-feltet på en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:47
msgid ""
"Next, click :guilabel:`Validate`, and a :guilabel:`You produced less than "
"initial demand` pop-up window appears, from which a backorder can be "
"created. Click :guilabel:`Create Backorder` to split the manufacturing order "
"into two separate orders, with the reference tags *WH/MO/XXXXX-001* and *WH/"
"MO/XXXXX-002*."
msgstr ""
"Klikněte na :guilabel:`Validate` a zobrazí se vyskakovací "
"okno :guilabel:`You produced less than initial demand`, ze kterého lze "
"vytvořit nedodávku. Kliknutím na :guilabel:`Create Backorder` rozdělíte "
"výrobní zakázku na dvě samostatné zakázky s referenčními značkami *WH/MO/"
"XXXXX-001* a *WH/MO/XXXXX-002*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:None
msgid ""
"The Create Backorder button on the \"You produced less than initial demand\" "
"pop-up window."
msgstr ""
"Tlačítko Create Backorder ve vyskakovacím okně \"You produced less than "
"initial demand\"."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:56
msgid ""
"Order *001* contains the items that have been manufactured, and is closed "
"immediately. Order *002* is the backorder that contains the items that have "
"yet to be manufactured, and remains open, to be completed at a later date."
msgstr ""
"Zakázka *001* obsahuje vyrobené položky a je okamžitě uzavřena. Zakázka "
"*002* je nedodávka obsahující položky, které mají být ještě vyrobeny, a "
"zůstává otevřená k dokončení později."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:60
msgid ""
"Once the remaining units can be manufactured, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders`, "
"and then select the backorder manufacturing order. If all of the remaining "
"units are manufactured immediately, simply click :guilabel:`Validate` to "
"close the order."
msgstr ""
"Jakmile lze zbývající jednotky vyrobit, přejděte "
"do :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders` a "
"vyberte výrobní zakázku nedodávky. Pokud jsou všechny zbývající jednotky "
"vyrobeny okamžitě, jednoduše klikněte na :guilabel:`Validate` a zakázku "
"uzavřete."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:65
msgid ""
"If only some of the remaining units are manufactured immediately, create "
"another backorder for the remainder by following the steps detailed in this "
"section."
msgstr ""
"Pokud je okamžitě vyrobena pouze část zbývajících jednotek, vytvořte další "
"nedodávku pro zbytek podle kroků popsaných v této části."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:69
msgid "Create a backorder in Shop Floor"
msgstr "Vytvoření nedodávky ve værkstedu"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:71
msgid ""
"Backorders for manufacturing orders can also be created from the *Shop "
"Floor* module."
msgstr "Nedodávky pro výrobní zakázky lze také vytvářet z modulu *Værksted*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:74
msgid ""
"In order to use the *Shop Floor* module, the *Work Orders* setting must be "
"enabled. To do so, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> "
"Configuration --> Settings`, enable the :guilabel:`Work Orders` checkbox, "
"and then click :guilabel:`Save`."
msgstr ""
"Aby bylo možné používat modul *Værksted*, musí být aktivováno nastavení "
"*Work Orders*. Přejděte do :menuselection:`Produktion --> Configuration --> "
"Settings`, zaškrtněte políčko :guilabel:`Work Orders` a klikněte "
"na :guilabel:`Save`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:78
msgid ""
"To create a backorder from the *Shop Floor* module, begin by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders`. "
"Select an |MO| for multiple units of a product, for which a backorder needs "
"to be created."
msgstr ""
"Chcete-li vytvořit nedodávku z modulu *Værksted*, přejděte "
"do :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders`. "
"Vyberte |MO| pro více jednotek produktu, pro který je potřeba vytvořit "
"nedodávku."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:82
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/quality/quality_check_types/pass_fail_check.rst:121
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/quality/quality_check_types/picture_check.rst:133
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/quality/quality_management/quality_checks.rst:146
msgid ""
"On the |MO|, select the :guilabel:`Work Orders` tab, and then click "
"the :guilabel:`Open Work Order (external link icon)` button on the line of "
"the work order to be processed. On the resulting :guilabel:`Work Orders` pop-"
"up window, click the :guilabel:`Open Shop Floor` button to open the *Shop "
"Floor* module."
msgstr ""
"Na |MO| vyberte záložku :guilabel:`Work Orders` a poté klikněte na "
"tlačítko :guilabel:`Open Work Order (external link icon)` na řádku pracovní "
"zakázky, která má být zpracována. Ve vyskakovacím okně :guilabel:`Work "
"Orders` klikněte na tlačítko :guilabel:`Open Shop Floor` a otevřete modul "
"*Værksted*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:87
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/quality/quality_check_types/instructions_check.rst:80
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/quality/quality_check_types/pass_fail_check.rst:126
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/quality/quality_management/quality_checks.rst:155
msgid ""
"When accessed from a specific work order, the *Shop Floor* module opens to "
"the page for the work center where the order is configured to be processed, "
"and isolates the work order's card so that no other cards are shown."
msgstr ""
"Při přístupu z konkrétní pracovní zakázky se modul *Værksted* otevře na "
"stránce pro arbejdscenter, kde je zakázka nakonfigurována ke zpracování, a "
"izoluje kartu pracovní zakázky tak, aby nebyly zobrazeny žádné jiné karty."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:91
msgid ""
"Complete the steps on the work order's card until the :guilabel:`Register "
"Production` step is reached, and then click on it to open "
"the :guilabel:`Register Production` pop-up window."
msgstr ""
"Dokončete kroky na kartě pracovní zakázky, dokud nedosáhnete "
"kroku :guilabel:`Register Production`, a poté na něj klikněte a otevřete "
"vyskakovací okno :guilabel:`Register Production`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:95
msgid ""
"Do **not** click the :guilabel:`# Units` button on the right side of the "
"step. Doing so automatically registers the full amount of units as having "
"been produced."
msgstr ""
"**Neklikejte** na tlačítko :guilabel:`# Units` na pravé straně kroku. Tím "
"automaticky zaregistrujete celé množství jednotek jako vyrobené."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:98
msgid ""
"On the :guilabel:`Register Production` pop-up window, enter the number of "
"units produced in the :guilabel:`Quantity` field. Make sure the number "
"entered is *less* than the number of units listed to the right of the field. "
"Then, click :guilabel:`Validate`."
msgstr ""
"Ve vyskakovacím okně :guilabel:`Register Production` zadejte počet "
"vyrobených jednotek do pole :guilabel:`Quantity`. Ujistěte se, že zadané "
"číslo je *menší* než počet jednotek uvedený vpravo od pole. Poté klikněte "
"na :guilabel:`Validate`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:None
msgid "The Register Production pop-up window in the Shop Floor module."
msgstr "Vyskakovací okno Register Production v modulu Værksted."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:106
msgid ""
"The pop-up window disappears and the :guilabel:`# Units` button on the work "
"order's card updates to reflect the number of units produced, as a fraction "
"of the number of units for which the |MO| was originally created."
msgstr ""
"Vyskakovací okno zmizí a tlačítko :guilabel:`# Units` na kartě pracovní "
"zakázky se aktualizuje a zobrazí počet vyrobených jednotek jako zlomek počtu "
"jednotek, pro které byla |MO| původně vytvořena."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:110
msgid ""
"Next, click the :guilabel:`Mark as Done` button at the bottom-right of the "
"work order's card. The work order card begins to fade away. Once it "
"disappears completely, a new work order card appears, titled with the "
"original |MO|'s reference number with a `-002` tag added to the end of it."
msgstr ""
"Poté klikněte na tlačítko :guilabel:`Mark as Done` v pravém dolním rohu "
"karty pracovní zakázky. Karta pracovní zakázky začne mizet. Jakmile úplně "
"zmizí, zobrazí se nová karta pracovní zakázky s názvem odpovídajícím "
"referenčnímu číslu původní |MO| se značkou `-002` přidanou na konci."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:114
msgid ""
"This new reference number represents the backorder |MO|. The original |MO|'s "
"reference number now appears with a `-001` tag added to the end of it to "
"distinguish it from the backorder |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Toto nové referenční číslo představuje nedodávku |MO|. Referenční číslo "
"původní |MO| se nyní zobrazuje se značkou `-001` přidanou na konci, aby se "
"odlišila od nedodávky |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:117
msgid ""
"If the original |MO| has no remaining work orders, it can be closed by "
"selecting the :guilabel:`All` filter in the top navigation of the *Shop "
"Floor* module, and then clicking :guilabel:`Close Production` at the bottom "
"of the |MO|'s card."
msgstr ""
"Pokud původní |MO| nemá žádné zbývající pracovní zakázky, lze ji uzavřít "
"výběrem filtru :guilabel:`All` v horní navigaci modulu *Værksted* a "
"následným kliknutím na :guilabel:`Close Production` ve spodní části karty |"
"MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:121
msgid ""
"If the original |MO| has remaining work orders that must be completed before "
"it can be closed, cards for these work orders appear on the *Shop Floor* "
"pages for the work centers where they are configured to be carried out. They "
"can be processed as normal, and additional backorders can be created from "
"their work order cards using the instructions detailed in this section."
msgstr ""
"Pokud má původní |MO| zbývající pracovní zakázky, které musí být dokončeny "
"před uzavřením, zobrazí se karty pro tyto pracovní zakázky na stránkách "
"modulu *Værksted* pro arbejdscentre, kde mají být provedeny. Lze je "
"zpracovat běžným způsobem a z jejich karet pracovních zakázek lze vytvořit "
"další nedodávky podle pokynů uvedených v této části."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:126
msgid ""
"Once the current work order for the backorder |MO| is ready to be processed, "
"this can also be completed as normal, and an additional backorder can be "
"created from its work order card by following the instructions detailed in "
"this section."
msgstr ""
"Jakmile je aktuální pracovní příkaz pro nedodávku |MO| připraven ke "
"zpracování, lze jej také dokončit běžným způsobem a z jeho karty pracovního "
"příkazu lze vytvořit další nedodávku podle pokynů uvedených v této části."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/manufacturing_backorders.rst:130
msgid ""
"After the final work order for the backorder |MO| has been completed, the |"
"MO| can be closed by clicking the :guilabel:`Close Production` button at the "
"bottom of the work order's card."
msgstr ""
"Po dokončení posledního pracovního příkazu pro nedodávku |MO| lze |MO| "
"zavřít kliknutím na tlačítko :guilabel:`Zavřít výrobu` ve spodní části karty "
"pracovního příkazu."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:3
msgid "Scrap during manufacturing"
msgstr "Odpad během výroby"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:7
msgid ""
"During the manufacturing process, scrapping components or finished products "
"may be necessary when items are damaged, defective, or no longer usable."
msgstr ""
"Během výrobního procesu může být nutné odepsat komponenty nebo hotové "
"výrobky, když jsou položky poškozené, vadné nebo již nepoužitelné."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:10
msgid ""
"Tracking scrapped materials helps manufacturers monitor waste, identify "
"process issues, and account for production costs."
msgstr ""
"Sledování odepsaných materiálů pomáhá výrobcům monitorovat odpad, "
"identifikovat problémy v procesu a účtovat výrobní náklady."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:13
msgid ""
"In Odoo, scrapped items are removed from physical inventory and moved to a "
"virtual location called *Virtual Locations/Scrap*. This location is not a "
"physical space—it is a way to log and track losses without affecting real "
"stock levels."
msgstr ""
"V Odoo jsou odepsané položky odstraněny z fyzického skladu a přesunuty do "
"virtuálního umístění nazvaného *Virtuální umístění/Odpad*. Toto umístění "
"není fyzický prostor – je to způsob, jak zaznamenávat a sledovat ztráty, "
"aniž by to ovlivnilo skutečné skladové stavy."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:18
msgid ""
":doc:`Location types <../../inventory/warehouses_storage/"
"inventory_management>`"
msgstr ""
":doc:`Typy umístění <../../inventory/warehouses_storage/"
"inventory_management>`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:21
msgid ""
"Scrap orders can be viewed by navigating to :menuselection:`Inventory --> "
"Operations --> Scrap`. Each scrap order shows the date and time the order "
"was created, along with the product and quantity that was scrapped."
msgstr ""
"Příkazy k odpisu lze zobrazit přechodem do :menuselection:`Lager --> Operace "
"--> Odpad`. Každý příkaz k odpisu zobrazuje datum a čas vytvoření příkazu "
"spolu s produktem a množstvím, které bylo odepsáno."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:25
msgid ""
"To view the total quantity of each item scrapped, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Inventory --> Configuration --> Locations`, then remove "
"the :guilabel:`Internal` filter from the :guilabel:`Search...` bar to "
"display all virtual locations. From the list, select the :guilabel:`Virtual "
"Locations/Scrap` location."
msgstr ""
"Chcete-li zobrazit celkové množství každé odepsané položky, přejděte "
"do :menuselection:`Lager --> Konfigurace --> Umístění`, poté odeberte "
"filtr :guilabel:`Interní` z vyhledávacího pole :guilabel:`Hledat...`, abyste "
"zobrazili všechna virtuální umístění. Ze seznamu vyberte "
"umístění :guilabel:`Virtuální umístění/Odpad`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:33
msgid "Navigate to the scrap window"
msgstr "Přechod do okna odpisu"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:35
msgid ""
"Scrapping can be done in either the **Manufacturing** app or the **Shop "
"Floor** module, depending on the task."
msgstr ""
"Odpisování lze provádět buď v aplikaci **Produktion**, nebo v modulu "
"**Værksted**, v závislosti na úkolu."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:38
msgid "**Manufacturing** app allows:"
msgstr "Aplikace **Produktion** umožňuje:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:40
msgid "Scrapping finished products (only if the |MO| is in the *Done* stage)."
msgstr "Odpisování hotových výrobků (pouze pokud je |MO| ve fázi *Hotovo*)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:41
msgid ""
"Scrapping components (while the |MO| is in the *Draft* or *Confirmed* stage)."
msgstr ""
"Odpisování komponent (zatímco je |MO| ve fázi *Koncept* nebo *Potvrzeno*)."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:43
msgid "**Shop Floor** allows:"
msgstr "**Værksted** umožňuje:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:45
msgid "Scrapping only components."
msgstr "Odpisování pouze komponent."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:48
msgid "Manufacturing app"
msgstr "Aplikace Produktion"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:50
msgid ""
"To scrap a product from the **Manufacturing** app, go "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders` "
"and select the desired |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Chcete-li odepsat produkt z aplikace **Produktion**, přejděte "
"do :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operace --> Výrobní příkazy` a vyberte "
"požadovaný |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:53
msgid ""
"On the |MO|, click the :icon:`fa-cog` :guilabel:`(Actions)` icon, then "
"choose :guilabel:`Scrap` from the drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"Na |MO| klikněte na ikonu :icon:`fa-cog` :guilabel:`(Akce)`, poté z "
"rozevírací nabídky vyberte :guilabel:`Odpad`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:None
msgid "MO with the cog's drop-down menu revealed, to show the Scrap option."
msgstr ""
"Výrobní příkaz s rozevírací nabídkou ozubeného kola zobrazující možnost "
"Odpad."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:62
msgid ""
"In **Shop Floor**, only components can be scrapped. Navigate to the desired |"
"MO| card, and then tap the :icon:`fa-cog` :guilabel:`(Actions)` icon and in "
"the :guilabel:`What do you want to do?` pop-up window, "
"select :guilabel:`Scrap`."
msgstr ""
"I **Værksted** kan kun komponenter kasseres. Naviger til det ønskede |MO|-"
"kort, og tryk derefter på :icon:`fa-cog` :guilabel:`Handlinger`-ikonet, og "
"vælg :guilabel:`Kassér` i pop op-vinduet :guilabel:`Hvad vil du gøre?`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:None
msgid "Scrap pop-up window in the Shop Floor app."
msgstr "Pop op-vindue til kassering i Værksted-appen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:70
msgid "Scrap pop-up window"
msgstr "Pop op-vindue til kassering"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:72
msgid ""
"After opening the :guilabel:`Scrap Products` pop-up window using one of the "
"methods :ref:`detailed above <manufacturing/management/scrap-window>`, "
"select the component or finished product being scrapped, from "
"the :guilabel:`Product` drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"Efter åbning af pop op-vinduet :guilabel:`Kassér produkter` ved hjælp af en "
"af metoderne :ref:`beskrevet ovenfor <manufacturing/management/scrap-"
"window>`, skal du vælge den komponent eller det færdige produkt, der "
"kasseres, fra rullemenuen :guilabel:`Produkt`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:76
msgid "In the :guilabel:`Quantity` field, enter the quantity being scrapped."
msgstr "I feltet :guilabel:`Antal` skal du indtaste det antal, der kasseres."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:78
msgid ""
"By default, the :guilabel:`Source Location` field is set to the warehouse's "
"pre-production location, while the :guilabel:`Scrap Location` field is set "
"to the :guilabel:`Virtual Locations/Scrap` location. If either the source or "
"scrap location should be changed, select a different location from their "
"respective drop-down menus."
msgstr ""
"Som standard er feltet :guilabel:`Kildelokation` indstillet til lagerets "
"præproduktionslokation, mens feltet :guilabel:`Kasseringslokation` er "
"indstillet til lokationen :guilabel:`Virtuelle lokationer/Kassering`. Hvis "
"enten kilde- eller kasseringslokationen skal ændres, skal du vælge en anden "
"lokation fra de respektive rullemenuer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:83
msgid ""
"Enable the :guilabel:`Replenish Scrapped Quantities` checkbox if a picking "
"order should be created to replace the scrapped component upon confirmation "
"of the scrap order. This option should only be enabled for warehouses "
"with :doc:`two-step <../basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing>` or :doc:`three-"
"step <../basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing>` manufacturing enabled, since "
"components are not picked as part of the :doc:`one-step <../basic_setup/"
"one_step_manufacturing>` manufacturing process."
msgstr ""
"Aktivér afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Genbestil kasserede mængder`, hvis der "
"skal oprettes en plukordre for at erstatte den kasserede komponent ved "
"bekræftelse af kasseringsordren. Denne indstilling bør kun aktiveres for "
"lagre med :doc:`totrinssproduktion <../basic_setup/two_step_manufacturing>` "
"eller :doc:`tretrinssproduktion <../basic_setup/three_step_manufacturing>` "
"aktiveret, da komponenter ikke plukkes som en del "
"af :doc:`ettrinssproduktionsprocessen <../basic_setup/"
"one_step_manufacturing>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:None
msgid "The Scrap pop-up window."
msgstr "Pop op-vinduet til kassering."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/scrap_manufacturing.rst:93
msgid ""
"After filling out the :guilabel:`Scrap Products` pop-up window, click "
"the :guilabel:`Scrap Products` button. After one or more scrap orders have "
"been created, a :guilabel:`Scraps` smart button appears at the top of the "
"screen. Click it to view a list of all scrap orders for the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Efter udfyldning af pop op-vinduet :guilabel:`Kassér produkter`, skal du "
"klikke på knappen :guilabel:`Kassér produkter`. Efter at en eller flere "
"kasseringsordrer er blevet oprettet, vises en smart-"
"knap :guilabel:`Kasseringer` øverst på skærmen. Klik på den for at se en "
"liste over alle kasseringsordrer for |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:3
msgid "Split and merge manufacturing orders"
msgstr "Opdel og flet produktionsordrer"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:5
msgid ""
"In Odoo *Manufacturing*, it is possible to create manufacturing orders for a "
"single unit of an item, or multiple units of the same item. In some cases, "
"it may be necessary to split a manufacturing order that contains multiple "
"units into two or more orders, or to merge two or more orders into a single "
"order."
msgstr ""
"I Odoo *Produktion* er det muligt at oprette produktionsordrer for en enkelt "
"enhed af en vare eller flere enheder af samme vare. I nogle tilfælde kan det "
"være nødvendigt at opdele en produktionsordre, der indeholder flere enheder, "
"i to eller flere ordrer, eller at flette to eller flere ordrer til en enkelt "
"ordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:11
msgid ""
"A manufacturing order can only contain one unit of a product, or multiple "
"units of a single product that all use the same Bill of Materials (BoM). As "
"a result, it is only possible to merge manufacturing orders when every order "
"contains the same product being manufactured with the same BoM."
msgstr ""
"En produktionsordre kan kun indeholde én enhed af et produkt eller flere "
"enheder af et enkelt produkt, der alle bruger den samme stykliste (BoM). Som "
"følge heraf er det kun muligt at flette produktionsordrer, når hver ordre "
"indeholder det samme produkt, der fremstilles med den samme stykliste."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:17
msgid "Split manufacturing orders"
msgstr "Opdel produktionsordrer"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:19
msgid ""
"To split a manufacturing order into multiple orders, begin by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders`, "
"then select a manufacturing order. At the top of the page, next to "
"the :guilabel:`New` button, the manufacturing order's reference number "
"appears with a :guilabel:`⚙️ (settings)` button next to it."
msgstr ""
"For at opdele en produktionsordre i flere ordrer skal du først navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operationer --> Produktionsordrer` og "
"derefter vælge en produktionsordre. Øverst på siden ved siden af "
"knappen :guilabel:`Ny` vises produktionsordrens referencenummer med "
"en :guilabel:`⚙️ (indstillinger)`-knap ved siden af."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:24
msgid ""
"Click the :guilabel:`⚙️ (settings)` button to open the general settings for "
"the manufacturing order, then select :guilabel:`Split`."
msgstr ""
"Klik på knappen :guilabel:`⚙️ (indstillinger)` for at åbne de generelle "
"indstillinger for produktionsordren, og vælg derefter :guilabel:`Opdel`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:None
msgid "The Settings and Split buttons on a manufacturing order."
msgstr "Knapperne Indstillinger og Opdel på en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:31
msgid ""
"After selecting :guilabel:`Split`, a :guilabel:`Split production` pop-up "
"window appears. In the :guilabel:`Split #` field, enter the number of "
"manufacturing orders that the original order should be split into, then "
"click outside of the field. A table appears below, with a line for each new "
"manufacturing order that will be created by the split. In "
"the :guilabel:`Quantity To Produce` column, enter the number of units that "
"will be assigned to each new manufacturing order. Finally, "
"click :guilabel:`Split` to split the manufacturing order."
msgstr ""
"Efter valg af :guilabel:`Opdel` vises et pop op-vindue :guilabel:`Opdel "
"produktion`. I feltet :guilabel:`Opdel #` skal du indtaste antallet af "
"produktionsordrer, som den oprindelige ordre skal opdeles i, og derefter "
"klikke uden for feltet. En tabel vises nedenfor med en linje for hver ny "
"produktionsordre, der oprettes ved opdelingen. I kolonnen :guilabel:`Antal "
"at producere` skal du indtaste antallet af enheder, der tildeles hver ny "
"produktionsordre. Klik til sidst på :guilabel:`Opdel` for at opdele "
"produktionsordren."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:None
msgid "The Split production pop-up window for a manufacturing order."
msgstr "Pop op-vinduet Opdel produktion for en produktionsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:42
msgid ""
"After clicking :guilabel:`Split`, the original manufacturing order is split "
"into the number of orders that was specified in the :guilabel:`Split #` "
"field. The reference numbers for the new manufacturing orders are the "
"reference number for the original order with *-###* tags added to the end."
msgstr ""
"Efter at have klikket på :guilabel:`Opdel` opdeles den oprindelige "
"produktionsordre i det antal ordrer, der blev angivet i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Opdel #`. Referencenumrene for de nye produktionsordrer er "
"referencenummeret for den oprindelige ordre med *-###*-tags tilføjet i "
"slutningen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:48
msgid ""
"Manufacturing order *WH/MO/00012* is split into three separate orders. The "
"reference numbers for the new orders are *WH/MO/00012-001*, *WH/MO/"
"00012-002*, and *WH/MO/00012-003*."
msgstr ""
"Produktionsordre *WH/MO/00012* opdeles i tre separate ordrer. "
"Referencenumrene for de nye ordrer er *WH/MO/00012-001*, *WH/MO/00012-002* "
"og *WH/MO/00012-003*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:52
msgid "Merge manufacturing orders"
msgstr "Flet produktionsordrer"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:54
msgid ""
"To merge two or more manufacturing orders into a single order, begin by "
"navigating to :menuselection:`Manufacturing --> Operations --> Manufacturing "
"Orders`. Select the manufacturing orders that will be merged by activating "
"the checkbox to the left of the name of each order."
msgstr ""
"For at flette to eller flere produktionsordrer til en enkelt ordre skal du "
"først navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operationer --> "
"Produktionsordrer`. Vælg de produktionsordrer, der skal flettes, ved at "
"aktivere afkrydsningsfeltet til venstre for navnet på hver ordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:None
msgid ""
"Select manufacturing orders that will be merged by clicking the checkbox for "
"each."
msgstr ""
"Vælg produktionsordrer, der skal flettes, ved at klikke på "
"afkrydsningsfeltet for hver."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:62
msgid ""
"Once all manufacturing orders have been selected, click "
"the :guilabel:`Actions` button at the top of the page, then "
"select :guilabel:`Merge` from the drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"Når alle produktionsordrer er valgt, skal du klikke på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Handlinger` øverst på siden og derefter "
"vælge :guilabel:`Flet` fra rullemenuen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:None
msgid "The Actions and Merge buttons on the Manufacturing Orders page."
msgstr "Knapperne Handlinger og Flet på siden Produktionsordrer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:69
msgid ""
"The selected manufacturing orders are merged into a single order. The "
"reference number for the new manufacturing order is the next sequential "
"number that has *not* already been assigned to an order."
msgstr ""
"De valgte produktionsordrer flettes til en enkelt ordre. Referencenummeret "
"for den nye produktionsordre er det næste sekventielle nummer, der *ikke* "
"allerede er blevet tildelt en ordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:73
msgid ""
"The last reference number used for a manufacturing order was *WH/MO/00012*. "
"Two manufacturing orders, *WH/MO/00008* and *WH/MO/00009*, are merged into a "
"single order. The reference number for the manufacturing order created by "
"the merger is *WH/MO/00013*."
msgstr ""
"Det sidste referencenummer, der blev brugt til en produktionsordre, var *WH/"
"MO/00012*. To produktionsordrer, *WH/MO/00008* og *WH/MO/00009*, flettes til "
"en enkelt ordre. Referencenummeret for produktionsordren, der oprettes ved "
"fletningen, er *WH/MO/00013*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:77
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Source` field for the manufacturing order created by the "
"merger, the reference numbers of the manufacturing orders that were merged "
"are listed."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Kilde` for den produktionsordre, der oprettes ved "
"fletningen, vises referencenumrene for de produktionsordrer, der blev "
"flettet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/split_merge.rst:81
msgid ""
"Manufacturing orders *WH/MO/00009* and *WH/MO/00010* are merged to create "
"*WH/MO/00011*. The source field for *WH/MO/00011* lists both *WH/MO/00009* "
"and *WH/MO/00010*."
msgstr ""
"Produktionsordrerne *WH/MO/00009* og *WH/MO/00010* flettes for at oprette "
"*WH/MO/00011*. Kildefeltet for *WH/MO/00011* viser både *WH/MO/00009* og *WH/"
"MO/00010*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:3
msgid "Unbuild orders"
msgstr "Nedbrydningsordrer"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:7
msgid ""
"In some cases, it is necessary to dismantle manufactured products into their "
"individual components. This may be required if too many units of a product "
"were built, or if the components of one product must be reclaimed to use in "
"the manufacturing of another."
msgstr ""
"I nogle tilfælde er det nødvendigt at demontere fremstillede produkter i "
"deres individuelle komponenter. Dette kan være påkrævet, hvis der er bygget "
"for mange enheder af et produkt, eller hvis komponenterne fra et produkt "
"skal genvindes til brug i fremstillingen af et andet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:11
msgid ""
"In Odoo *Manufacturing*, products can be dismantled, and their components "
"returned to inventory, using *unbuild orders*. By using unbuild orders to "
"accomplish this task, inventory counts for the finished product and its "
"components remain accurate, based on the quantity of products dismantled, "
"and the quantity of components reclaimed."
msgstr ""
"I Odoo *Produktion* kan produkter demonteres, og deres komponenter "
"returneres til lageret ved hjælp af *nedbrydningsordrer*. Ved at bruge "
"nedbrydningsordrer til at udføre denne opgave forbliver lagerantal for det "
"færdige produkt og dets komponenter nøjagtige baseret på antallet af "
"demonterede produkter og antallet af genvundne komponenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:17
msgid "Create unbuild order"
msgstr "Opret nedbrydningsordre"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:19
msgid ""
"A new unbuild order can be created by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Operations --> Unbuild Orders`, and "
"clicking :guilabel:`New`."
msgstr ""
"En ny nedbrydningsordre kan oprettes ved at navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operationer --> Nedbrydningsordrer` og "
"klikke på :guilabel:`Ny`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:22
msgid ""
"Begin filling out the new unbuild order by selecting a :guilabel:`Product` "
"to unbuild. After doing so, the :guilabel:`Bill of Material` field auto-"
"populates with the corresponding bill of materials (BoM). If a different |"
"BoM| should be used, click on the :guilabel:`Bill of Material` field, and "
"select it from the drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"Begynd at udfylde den nye nedbrydningsordre ved at vælge "
"et :guilabel:`Produkt`, der skal nedbrydes. Derefter udfyldes "
"feltet :guilabel:`Stykliste` automatisk med den tilsvarende stykliste. Hvis "
"en anden |BoM| skal bruges, skal du klikke på feltet :guilabel:`Stykliste` "
"og vælge den fra rullemenuen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:27
msgid ""
"Alternatively, a specific |BoM| can be selected in the :guilabel:`Bill of "
"Material` field before selecting a product, which causes the corresponding "
"product to auto-populate in the :guilabel:`Product` field."
msgstr ""
"Alternativt kan en specifik |BoM| vælges i feltet :guilabel:`Stykliste`, før "
"der vælges et produkt, hvilket medfører, at det tilsvarende produkt "
"automatisk udfyldes i feltet :guilabel:`Produkt`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:31
msgid ""
"Next, specify the :guilabel:`Quantity` of the product that is being unbuilt."
msgstr "Angiv derefter :guilabel:`Antal` af det produkt, der nedbrydes."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:33
msgid ""
"If the product being unbuilt was originally manufactured in a specific "
"manufacturing order (MO), select it in the :guilabel:`Manufacturing Order` "
"field."
msgstr ""
"Hvis det produkt, der nedbrydes, oprindeligt blev fremstillet i en specifik "
"produktionsordre, skal du vælge den i feltet :guilabel:`Produktionsordre`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:36
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Source Location` field, select the location where the "
"product being unbuilt is currently stored."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Kildeplacement` skal du vælge det sted, hvor det "
"produkt, der nedbrydes, i øjeblikket opbevares."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:39
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Destination Location` field, select the location where the "
"reclaimed components are stored after the unbuild order is completed."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Destinationsplacement` skal du vælge det sted, hvor de "
"genvundne komponenter opbevares, efter at nedbrydningsordren er fuldført."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:42
msgid ""
"If the *Lots & Serial Numbers* feature is enabled in the settings of the "
"*Inventory* app, a :guilabel:`Lot/Serial Number` field appears on the "
"unbuild order, which can be used to specify the lot(s) or serial number(s) "
"of the product being unbuilt, if any are assigned."
msgstr ""
"Hvis funktionen *Partier & serienumre* er aktiveret i indstillingerne for "
"*Lager*-appen, vises et :guilabel:`Parti/serienummer`-felt på "
"nedbrydningsordren, som kan bruges til at angive parti(er) eller "
"serienummer(numre) for det produkt, der nedbrydes, hvis der er tildelt nogen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:46
msgid ""
"If the Odoo database has been configured with multiple companies, "
"a :guilabel:`Company` field appears on the unbuild order, which can be used "
"to specify the company that owns the product being unbuilt."
msgstr ""
"Hvis Odoo-databasen er konfigureret med flere virksomheder, vises "
"et :guilabel:`Virksomhed`-felt på nedbrydningsordren, som kan bruges til at "
"angive den virksomhed, der ejer det produkt, der nedbrydes."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:50
msgid ""
"Finally, once the product has been unbuilt, click the :guilabel:`Unbuild` "
"button at the top of the order to confirm that it has been completed."
msgstr ""
"Når produktet endelig er nedbrudt, klik på :guilabel:`Nedbryd`-knappen "
"øverst på ordren for at bekræfte, at den er gennemført."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:None
msgid "A filled-out unbuild order."
msgstr "En udfyldt nedbrydningsordre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:58
msgid ""
"While it is possible to create unbuild orders for products that have zero "
"(or fewer) units on-hand, this is not advised, since it can lead to "
"inventory inconsistencies."
msgstr ""
"Selvom det er muligt at oprette nedbrydningsordrer for produkter, der har "
"nul (eller færre) enheder på lager, frarådes dette, da det kan føre til "
"lageruoverensstemmelser."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:61
msgid ""
"If an unbuild order is created for a product with zero (or fewer) units on-"
"hand, a pop-up window appears, warning the user that there is an "
"insufficient quantity to unbuild."
msgstr ""
"Hvis en nedbrydningsordre oprettes for et produkt med nul (eller færre) "
"enheder på lager, vises et pop op-vindue, der advarer brugeren om, at der er "
"en utilstrækkelig mængde at nedbryde."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:64
msgid ""
"To ignore the warning, and proceed with the unbuild order, "
"click :guilabel:`Confirm` at the bottom of the pop-up window. To return to "
"the unconfirmed unbuild order, click :guilabel:`Discard`, instead."
msgstr ""
"For at ignorere advarslen og fortsætte med nedbrydningsordren skal du klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Bekræft` nederst i pop op-vinduet. For at vende tilbage til "
"den ubekræftede nedbrydningsordre skal du i stedet klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Kassér`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:0
msgid ""
"The insufficient quantity pop-up that appears after trying to confirm an "
"unbuild order\n"
"for a product with zero or fewer units on hand."
msgstr ""
"Pop op-vinduet om utilstrækkelig mængde, der vises efter forsøg på at "
"bekræfte en nedbrydningsordre\n"
"for et produkt med nul eller færre enheder på lager."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:73
msgid ""
"After completing an unbuild order, inventory counts automatically update, "
"based on the quantity of products unbuilt, and the quantity of components "
"reclaimed."
msgstr ""
"Efter gennemførelse af en nedbrydningsordre opdateres lageroptællingerne "
"automatisk baseret på mængden af nedbrydte produkter og mængden af genvundne "
"komponenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:77
msgid ""
"A `Coat Rack` product is comprised of one `Wooden Pole` component and six "
"`Wooden Dowel` components."
msgstr ""
"Et `Coat Rack`-produkt består af en `Wooden Pole`-komponent og seks `Wooden "
"Dowel`-komponenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:80
msgid ""
"An unbuild order is created for one unit of the `Coat Rack`. Once the order "
"is completed, the on-hand quantity of `Coat Racks` decreases by one, while "
"the on-hand quantities of `Wooden Poles` and `Wooden Dowels` increase by one "
"and six, respectively."
msgstr ""
"En nedbrydningsordre oprettes for en enhed af `Coat Rack`. Når ordren er "
"gennemført, falder lagerbeholdningen af `Coat Racks` med en, mens "
"lagerbeholdningerne af `Wooden Poles` og `Wooden Dowels` stiger med "
"henholdsvis en og seks."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:85
msgid "Scrap unusable components"
msgstr "Skrot ubrugelige komponenter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/unbuild_orders.rst:87
msgid ""
"In some cases, components may be unusable after the unbuilding process is "
"completed. To ensure that inventory counts accurately reflect the quantity "
"of usable components on-hand, any component that can no longer be used "
"should be removed from inventory using a :doc:`scrap order <../../inventory/"
"warehouses_storage/inventory_management/scrap_inventory>`."
msgstr ""
"I nogle tilfælde kan komponenter være ubrugelige, når nedbrydningsprocessen "
"er gennemført. For at sikre, at lageroptællingerne nøjagtigt afspejler "
"mængden af brugbare komponenter på lager, bør enhver komponent, der ikke "
"længere kan bruges, fjernes fra lageret ved hjælp af en :doc:`skrotordre "
"<../../inventory/warehouses_storage/inventory_management/scrap_inventory>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:16
msgid ""
"In Odoo's *Manufacturing* app, the *master production schedule* (MPS) is "
"used to manually plan manufacturing orders (MOs) and purchase orders (POs), "
"based on forecasted quantities of products and components."
msgstr ""
"I Odoos *Produktion*-app bruges *master production schedule* (MPS) til "
"manuelt at planlægge produktionsordrer (MOs) og indkøbsordrer (POs) baseret "
"på forventede mængder af produkter og komponenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:20
msgid ""
"By considering the impact of confirmed |MOs| and |POs|, along with manually "
"adjusted demand forecasts, the |MPS| can be used to manage long-term product "
"replenishment. This ensures the continued availability of the necessary "
"products and components."
msgstr ""
"Ved at overveje virkningen af bekræftede |MOs| og |POs| sammen med manuelt "
"justerede efterspørgselsprognoser kan |MPS| bruges til at styre langsigtet "
"produktgenopfyldning. Dette sikrer fortsat tilgængelighed af de nødvendige "
"produkter og komponenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:24
msgid ""
"Since the |MPS| allows for manual intervention, it is useful for "
"replenishing products where the demand of existing sales orders (SOs) does "
"**not** reflect probable future demand."
msgstr ""
"Da |MPS| tillader manuel indgriben, er det nyttigt til at genopfylde "
"produkter, hvor efterspørgslen fra eksisterende salgsordrer (SOs) **ikke** "
"afspejler sandsynlig fremtidig efterspørgsel."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:28
msgid ""
"A retail store sells artificial *Christmas trees* during the holiday season. "
"It is currently September, and the store has less than ten Christmas tree |"
"MOs| confirmed for the month of December."
msgstr ""
"En detailbutik sælger kunstige *juletræer* i højtidssæsonen. Det er i "
"øjeblikket september, og butikken har mindre end ti juletræs-|MOs| bekræftet "
"for december måned."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:32
msgid ""
"Despite the number of confirmed |MOs|, the procurement manager knows that "
"the demand for Christmas trees in December is going to be much higher, once "
"the holiday season starts. As a result, they manually enter a greater demand "
"in the |MPS|, so they can properly replenish the product in time for the "
"increase in customer demand."
msgstr ""
"På trods af antallet af bekræftede |MOs| ved indkøbschefen, at "
"efterspørgslen efter juletræer i december vil være meget højere, når "
"højtidssæsonen starter. Derfor indtaster de manuelt en større efterspørgsel "
"i |MPS|, så de kan genopfylde produktet i tide til stigningen i "
"kundeefterspørgslen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:38
msgid ""
"It is essential to remember that the |MPS| is a **MANUAL** tool. Adding a "
"product to the |MPS| does not cause it to be manufactured or purchased "
"automatically. The |MPS| simply suggests the amount of the product that "
"should be replenished, but requires user input to create the |MOs| or |POs| "
"that are used to replenish it."
msgstr ""
"Det er afgørende at huske, at |MPS| er et **MANUELT** værktøj. Tilføjelse af "
"et produkt til |MPS| får ikke produktet til at blive fremstillet eller "
"indkøbt automatisk. |MPS| foreslår blot den mængde af produktet, der skal "
"genopfyldes, men kræver brugerinput for at oprette de |MOs| eller |POs|, der "
"bruges til at genopfylde det."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:43
msgid ""
"For this reason, it is recommended that the |MPS| **NOT** be used alongside "
"reordering rules for the same product. Because reordering rules are an "
"automated workflow, they conflict with the manual replenishment method of |"
"MPS|. Using both, in unison, can lead to inaccurate forecasts and the "
"creation of unnecessary replenishment orders."
msgstr ""
"Af denne grund anbefales det, at |MPS| **IKKE** bruges sammen med "
"genbestillingsregler for det samme produkt. Fordi genbestillingsregler er et "
"automatiseret workflow, er de i konflikt med den manuelle "
"genopfyldningsmetode i |MPS|. Brug af begge sammen kan føre til unøjagtige "
"prognoser og oprettelse af unødvendige genopfyldningsordrer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:49
msgid "Enable and configure |MPS|"
msgstr "Aktivér og konfigurér |MPS|"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:51
msgid ""
"To use the |MPS| feature, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> "
"Configuration --> Settings`, and tick the :guilabel:`Master Production "
"Schedule` checkbox in the :guilabel:`Planning` section. Finally, "
"click :guilabel:`Save`."
msgstr ""
"For at bruge |MPS|-funktionen skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Konfiguration --> Indstillinger` og "
"markere afkrydsningsfeltet :guilabel:`Master Production Schedule` i "
"afsnittet :guilabel:`Planlægning`. Klik til sidst på :guilabel:`Gem`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:55
msgid ""
"After enabling the :guilabel:`Master Production Schedule` feature, two new "
"fields appear under it on the :guilabel:`Settings` page: :guilabel:`Time "
"Range` and :guilabel:`Number of Columns`."
msgstr ""
"Når funktionen :guilabel:`Master Production Schedule` er aktiveret, vises to "
"nye felter under den på "
"siden :guilabel:`Indstillinger`: :guilabel:`Tidsinterval` "
"og :guilabel:`Antal kolonner`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:58
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Time Range` field is used to select the period of time over "
"which planning takes place, and offers three "
"options: :guilabel:`Monthly`, :guilabel:`Weekly`, and :guilabel:`Daily`. For "
"example, if :guilabel:`Monthly` is selected, the |MPS| plans the production "
"requirements of products and components on a monthly basis."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`Tidsinterval` bruges til at vælge den tidsperiode, som "
"planlægningen foregår over, og tilbyder tre "
"muligheder: :guilabel:`Månedligt`, :guilabel:`Ugentligt` "
"og :guilabel:`Dagligt`. Hvis der f.eks. vælges :guilabel:`Månedligt`, "
"planlægger |MPS| produktionskravene for produkter og komponenter på "
"månedsbasis."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:63
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Number of Columns` field is used to specify the quantity of "
"the selected :guilabel:`Time Range` units shown on the |MPS| page. For "
"example, if the :guilabel:`Time Range` field is set to :guilabel:`Monthly`, "
"and `12` is entered in the :guilabel:`Number of Columns` field, the |MPS| "
"shows one column for the next 12 months, starting with the current month."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`Antal kolonner` bruges til at angive antallet af de "
"valgte :guilabel:`Tidsinterval`-enheder, der vises på |MPS|-siden. Hvis "
"f.eks. feltet :guilabel:`Tidsinterval` er indstillet "
"til :guilabel:`Månedligt`, og `12` indtastes i feltet :guilabel:`Antal "
"kolonner`, viser |MPS| én kolonne for de næste 12 måneder, startende med den "
"aktuelle måned."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:68
msgid ""
"If the values of the :guilabel:`Time Range` or :guilabel:`Number of Columns` "
"fields are altered, click :guilabel:`Save` again to save the changes."
msgstr ""
"Hvis værdierne i felterne :guilabel:`Tidsinterval` eller :guilabel:`Antal "
"kolonner` ændres, skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Gem` igen for at gemme "
"ændringerne."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:None
msgid "The MPS setting in the Manufacturing app's settings."
msgstr "MPS-indstillingen i Produktionsappens indstillinger."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:75
msgid "|MPS| dashboard"
msgstr "|MPS|-dashboard"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:77
msgid ""
"To open the |MPS|, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> "
"Planning --> Master Production Schedule`. The |MPS| view appears as follows:"
msgstr ""
"For at åbne |MPS| skal du navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion --> "
"Planlægning --> Master Production Schedule`. |MPS|-visningen vises som "
"følger:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:None
msgid "The Master Production Schedule in the Manufacturing app."
msgstr "Master Production Schedule i Produktionsappen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:83
msgid ""
"The grey column on the left side of the screen shows a section for every "
"product added to the |MPS|, with each product section being broken down into "
"smaller rows. The information shown in the rows depends on the filters "
"selected in the :guilabel:`Search...` bar drop-down menu at the top of the "
"page. The default categories that appear in the rows are:"
msgstr ""
"Den grå kolonne på venstre side af skærmen viser et afsnit for hvert "
"produkt, der er tilføjet til |MPS|, hvor hvert produktafsnit er opdelt i "
"mindre rækker. De oplysninger, der vises i rækkerne, afhænger af de filtre, "
"der er valgt i rullemenuen :guilabel:`Søg...` øverst på siden. "
"Standardkategorierne, der vises i rækkerne, er:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:88
msgid ""
":guilabel:`[Product] by [unit]` :icon:`fa-area-chart`: the forecasted stock "
"quantity at the beginning of each time period. :guilabel:`[Product]` "
"and :icon:`fa-area-chart` are selectable buttons which open the product's "
"page, or the forecast report for the product, respectively."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`[Produkt] efter [enhed]` :icon:`fa-area-chart`: den forventede "
"lagermængde i begyndelsen af hver tidsperiode. :guilabel:`[Produkt]` "
"og :icon:`fa-area-chart` er klikbare knapper, der åbner henholdsvis "
"produktets side eller prognserapporten for produktet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:91
msgid ""
":guilabel:`- Forecasted Demand`: the demand forecast, which is entered "
"manually. This represents an estimate of the demand for the product during "
"each time period."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`- Forventet efterspørgsel`: efterspørgselsprognosen, som "
"indtastes manuelt. Dette repræsenterer et estimat af efterspørgslen efter "
"produktet i hver tidsperiode."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:93
msgid ""
":guilabel:`- Indirect Demand Forecast`: while this is a default category, it "
"**only** appears for products that are components of other products. It "
"represents the demand for the component from existing MOs."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`- Indirekte efterspørgselsprognose`: selvom dette er en "
"standardkategori, vises den **kun** for produkter, der er komponenter i "
"andre produkter. Den repræsenterer efterspørgslen efter komponenten fra "
"eksisterende produktionsordrer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:96
msgid ""
":guilabel:`+ Suggested Replenishment`: the quantity of the product that is "
"suggested to be replenished through |MOs| or |POs|. To the right of the "
"category title is a :guilabel:`Replenish` button, which is used to manually "
"replenish the product, based on the quantity suggested to be replenished."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`+ Foreslået genopfyldning`: den mængde af produktet, der foreslås "
"genopfyldt gennem |MOs| eller |POs|. Til højre for kategorititlen er der "
"en :guilabel:`Genopfyld`-knap, som bruges til manuelt at genopfylde "
"produktet baseret på den mængde, der foreslås genopfyldt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:0
msgid "The Replenish button on the \"+ Suggested Replenishment\" row."
msgstr "Genopfyld-knappen på rækken \"+ Foreslået genopfyldning\"."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:104
msgid "The \"Replenish\" button on the \"+ Suggested Replenishment\" row."
msgstr "\"Genopfyld\"-knappen på rækken \"+ Foreslået genopfyldning\"."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:106
msgid ""
":guilabel:`= Forecasted Stock`: the quantity of the product forecasted to be "
"in stock at the end of each time period, assuming that suggested "
"replenishment numbers are fulfilled."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`= Forventet lager`: den mængde af produktet, der forventes at "
"være på lager ved slutningen af hver tidsperiode, forudsat at de foreslåede "
"genopfyldningstal opfyldes."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:109
msgid "Altogether, these default categories form an equation:"
msgstr "Tilsammen danner disse standardkategorier en ligning:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:111
msgid ""
"\\text{Forecasted Demand} + \\text{Suggested Replenishment} = "
"\\text{Forecasted Stock}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\\text{Forventet efterspørgsel} + \\text{Foreslået genopfyldning} = "
"\\text{Forventet lager}\n"
"\n"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:114
msgid ""
"In the case of components, the :guilabel:`Indirect Demand Forecast` is taken "
"into account as well."
msgstr ""
"I tilfælde af komponenter tages :guilabel:`Indirekte efterspørgselsprognose` "
"også i betragtning."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:116
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`- Forecasted Demand` and :guilabel:`+ Suggested "
"Replenishment` fields can be edited for any of the time periods to the right "
"of the product column. Doing so changes the equation, and updates the value "
"displayed in the :guilabel:`Forecasted Stock` field."
msgstr ""
"Felterne :guilabel:`- Forventet efterspørgsel` og :guilabel:`+ Foreslået "
"genopfyldning` kan redigeres for enhver af tidsperioderne til højre for "
"produktkolonnen. Dette ændrer ligningen og opdaterer værdien vist i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Forventet lager`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:120
msgid ""
"Changing the value in the :guilabel:`+ Suggested Replenishment` field also "
"makes an :icon:`fa-times` :guilabel:`(reset)` button appear to the left of "
"the field. Click the :icon:`fa-times` :guilabel:`(reset)` button next to the "
"field to reset its value back to the one calculated by the |MPS|."
msgstr ""
"Ændring af værdien i feltet :guilabel:`+ Foreslået genopfyldning` får også "
"en :icon:`fa-times` :guilabel:`(nulstil)` knap til at fremkomme til venstre "
"for feltet. Klik på :icon:`fa-times` :guilabel:`(nulstil)` knappen ved siden "
"af feltet for at nulstille værdien tilbage til den beregnet af |MPS|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:126
msgid ""
"While the |MPS| can be used with only the default categories enabled, it is "
"advisable to also enable the :guilabel:`Actual Demand` category. This is "
"done by clicking the :icon:`fa-caret-down` :guilabel:`(down arrow)` on the "
"right side of the :guilabel:`Search...` bar, and enabling "
"the :guilabel:`Actual Demand` option under the :guilabel:`Rows` header."
msgstr ""
"Selvom |MPS| kan bruges med kun de standard aktiverede kategorier, anbefales "
"det også at aktivere kategorien :guilabel:`Faktisk efterspørgsel`. Dette "
"gøres ved at klikke på :icon:`fa-caret-down` :guilabel:`(pil ned)` på højre "
"side af :guilabel:`Søg...` bjælken og aktivere "
"indstillingen :guilabel:`Faktisk efterspørgsel` under "
"overskriften :guilabel:`Rækker`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:131
msgid ""
"With the :guilabel:`Actual Demand` option enabled, the :guilabel:`- "
"Forecasted Demand` category changes to the :guilabel:`- Actual / Forecasted "
"Demand` category. In addition to the manually entered forecasted demand, "
"this category also displays the confirmed demand for the product, which is "
"based on confirmed |SOs|."
msgstr ""
"Med indstillingen :guilabel:`Faktisk efterspørgsel` aktiveret ændres "
"kategorien :guilabel:`- Forventet efterspørgsel` til kategorien :guilabel:`- "
"Faktisk / Forventet efterspørgsel`. Ud over den manuelt indtastede "
"forventede efterspørgsel viser denne kategori også den bekræftede "
"efterspørgsel for produktet, som er baseret på bekræftede |SOs|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:136
msgid ""
"Each column to the right of the products column lists one unit of the time "
"period selected in the *Time Range* field on the *Manufacturing* app "
"*Settings* page (ex. months). The number of time period columns corresponds "
"to the value entered in the *Number of Columns* field."
msgstr ""
"Hver kolonne til højre for produktkolonnen angiver en enhed af den "
"tidsperiode, der er valgt i feltet *Tidsinterval* på *Produktion* appens "
"*Indstillinger* side (f.eks. måneder). Antallet af tidsperiodekolonner "
"svarer til den værdi, der er indtastet i feltet *Antal kolonner*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:140
msgid ""
"The first time period column represents the current time period. For "
"example, if the |MPS| is configured to use months, the first column displays "
"data for the current month. On this first column, the :guilabel:`+ Suggested "
"Replenishment` field appears in one of five colors:"
msgstr ""
"Den første tidsperiodekolonne repræsenterer den aktuelle tidsperiode. Hvis |"
"MPS| f.eks. er konfigureret til at bruge måneder, viser den første kolonne "
"data for den aktuelle måned. I denne første kolonne vises "
"feltet :guilabel:`+ Foreslået genopfyldning` i en af fem farver:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:144
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Green`: a replenishment order must be generated to keep stock at "
"the :guilabel:`Safety Stock Target`, based on the configured :doc:`lead "
"times <../../inventory/warehouses_storage/replenishment/lead_times>`."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Grøn`: en genopfyldningsordre skal genereres for at holde lageret "
"på :guilabel:`Mål for sikkerhedslager`, baseret på de "
"konfigurerede :doc:`leveringstider <../../inventory/warehouses_storage/"
"replenishment/lead_times>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:147
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Gray`: a replenishment order has already been generated to keep "
"stock at the :guilabel:`Safety Stock Target`."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Grå`: en genopfyldningsordre er allerede blevet genereret for at "
"holde lageret på :guilabel:`Sikkerhedslagermål`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:149
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Orange`: a replenishment order has already been generated, but "
"the quantity it was created for is not enough to keep stock at "
"the :guilabel:`Safety Stock Target`."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Orange`: en genopfyldningsordre er allerede blevet genereret, men "
"den mængde, den blev oprettet til, er ikke nok til at holde "
"lagerbeholdningen på :guilabel:`sikkerhedslagermål`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:151
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Red`: a replenishment order has already been generated, but the "
"quantity it was created for puts the amount of stock above "
"the :guilabel:`Safety Stock Target`."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Rød`: en genopfyldningsordre er allerede blevet genereret, men "
"den mængde den blev oprettet for, sætter lagermængden "
"over :guilabel:`Sikkerhedslagermål`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:154
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`+ Suggested Replenishment` field appears white, if no "
"replenishment order has been generated, and it is not necessary to generate "
"one at the current moment."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`+ Foreslået genopfyldning` vises hvidt, hvis ingen "
"genopfyldningsordre er blevet genereret, og det ikke er nødvendigt at "
"generere en på nuværende tidspunkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:158
msgid "Add a product"
msgstr "Tilføj et produkt"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:160
msgid ""
"To use |MPS| to manage the replenishment of a product, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Planning --> Master Production "
"Schedule`. At the top of the |MPS| page, click :guilabel:`Add a Product` to "
"open the :guilabel:`Add a Product` pop-up window."
msgstr ""
"For at bruge |MPS| til at styre genopfyldningen af et produkt skal du "
"navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion app --> Planlægning --> "
"Hovedproduktionsplan`. Øverst på |MPS| siden skal du klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Tilføj et produkt` for at åbne pop-up-"
"vinduet :guilabel:`Tilføj et produkt`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:165
msgid ""
"Products **must** be properly configured to be replenished through the |MPS|."
msgstr ""
"Produkter **skal** være korrekt konfigureret for at blive genopfyldt gennem |"
"MPS|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:167
msgid ""
"In the case of manufactured products, the *Manufacture* route must be "
"selected in the *Routes* section of the *Inventory* tab, on the product's "
"form."
msgstr ""
"I tilfælde af fremstillede produkter skal *Fremstil* ruten vælges i "
"sektionen *Ruter* på fanen *Lager* på produktets formular."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:170
msgid ""
"In the case of products that are purchased, the *Buy* route must be selected "
"in the *Routes* section of the *Inventory* tab, on the product's form. "
"Additionally, a vendor and the price they sell the product for must also be "
"specified on the *Purchase* tab."
msgstr ""
"I tilfælde af produkter, der købes, skal *Køb* ruten vælges i sektionen "
"*Ruter* på fanen *Lager* på produktets formular. Derudover skal en "
"leverandør og den pris, de sælger produktet for, også specificeres på fanen "
"*Indkøb*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:174
msgid ""
"On the pop-up window, select the product to add in the :guilabel:`Product` "
"drop-down menu. If the product is replenished through manufacturing, select "
"the product's |BoM| in the :guilabel:`Bill of Materials` field."
msgstr ""
"I pop-up-vinduet skal du vælge det produkt, der skal tilføjes, i "
"rullemenuen :guilabel:`Produkt`. Hvis produktet genopfyldes gennem "
"fremstilling, skal du vælge produktets |BoM| i feltet :guilabel:`Stykliste`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:179
msgid ""
"Selecting a BoM when adding a product to the |MPS| also adds any components "
"listed on the BoM. If it is not necessary to manage the replenishment of "
"components through the |MPS|, simply leave the :guilabel:`Bill of Materials` "
"field blank."
msgstr ""
"Valg af en stykliste når du tilføjer et produkt til |MPS| tilføjer også alle "
"komponenter angivet på styklisten. Hvis det ikke er nødvendigt at styre "
"genopfyldningen af komponenter gennem |MPS|, skal du blot lade "
"feltet :guilabel:`Stykliste` stå tomt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:183
msgid ""
"If the database is configured with multiple warehouses, "
"a :guilabel:`Production Warehouse` field appears on the :guilabel:`Add a "
"Product` pop-up window. Use this field to specify which warehouse the "
"product is replenished to."
msgstr ""
"Hvis databasen er konfigureret med flere lagre, vises et "
"felt :guilabel:`Produktionslager` i pop-up-vinduet :guilabel:`Tilføj et "
"produkt`. Brug dette felt til at specificere, hvilket lager produktet "
"genopfyldes til."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:187
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Safety Stock Target` field, specify the minimum quantity "
"of the product that should be kept available for orders at all times. For "
"example, if there should always be 20 units of the product available for "
"order fulfillment, enter `20` in the :guilabel:`Safety Stock Target` field."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Sikkerhedslagermål` skal du angive den minimumskvantitet "
"af produktet, der altid skal være tilgængelig for ordrer. Hvis der f.eks. "
"altid skal være 20 enheder af produktet tilgængelige til ordrebehandling, "
"skal du indtaste `20` i feltet :guilabel:`Sikkerhedslagermål`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:192
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Minimum to Replenish` field, enter the minimum product "
"quantity for orders created to replenish the product. For example, if `5` is "
"entered in this field, replenishment orders for the product include a "
"minimum of five units."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Minimum til genopfyldning` skal du indtaste den minimale "
"produktkvantitet for ordrer oprettet til genopfyldning af produktet. Hvis "
"f.eks. `5` indtastes i dette felt, inkluderer genopfyldningsordrer for "
"produktet minimum fem enheder."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:196
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Maximum to Replenish` field, enter the maximum product "
"quantity for orders created to replenish the product. For example, if `100` "
"is entered in this field, replenishment orders for the product include a "
"maximum of 100 units."
msgstr ""
"I feltet :guilabel:`Maksimum til genopfyldning` skal du indtaste den "
"maksimale produktkvantitet for ordrer oprettet til genopfyldning af "
"produktet. Hvis f.eks. `100` indtastes i dette felt, inkluderer "
"genopfyldningsordrer for produktet maksimalt 100 enheder."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:200
msgid ""
"Finally, click :guilabel:`Save` to add the product to the |MPS|. The product "
"now appears on the |MPS| page each time it is opened. If a |BoM| was "
"selected in the :guilabel:`Bill of Materials` field of the :guilabel:`Add a "
"Product` pop-up window, any components listed on the |BoM| appear on the "
"page, as well."
msgstr ""
"Klik til sidst på :guilabel:`Gem` for at tilføje produktet til |MPS|. "
"Produktet vises nu på |MPS|-siden hver gang den åbnes. Hvis en |BoM| blev "
"valgt i feltet :guilabel:`Stykliste` i pop op-vinduet :guilabel:`Tilføj et "
"produkt`, vises alle komponenter, der er anført på |BoM|, også på siden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:None
msgid "The Add a Product pop-up window in the MPS."
msgstr "Pop op-vinduet Tilføj et produkt i MPS."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:209
msgid "Edit a product"
msgstr "Rediger et produkt"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:211
msgid ""
"After adding a product to the |MPS|, it may be necessary to change the "
"replenishment values entered on the :guilabel:`Add a Product` pop-up window. "
"To do so, click the :guilabel:`# ≤…≤ #` button to the immediate right of "
"the :guilabel:`Replenish` button, on the :guilabel:`+ Suggested "
"Replenishment` row, below the product's name."
msgstr ""
"Efter tilføjelse af et produkt til |MPS| kan det være nødvendigt at ændre de "
"genopfyldningsværdier, der blev indtastet i pop op-vinduet :guilabel:`Tilføj "
"et produkt`. Klik på knappen :guilabel:`# ≤…≤ #` umiddelbart til højre for "
"knappen :guilabel:`Genopfyld` på rækken :guilabel:`+ Foreslået "
"genopfyldning` under produktets navn."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:217
msgid ""
"The first and second number displayed on the :guilabel:`# ≤…≤ #` button "
"correspond to the values entered in the :guilabel:`Minimum to Replenish` "
"and :guilabel:`Maximum to Replenish` fields when adding the product to the |"
"MPS|."
msgstr ""
"Det første og andet tal, der vises på knappen :guilabel:`# ≤…≤ #`, svarer "
"til de værdier, der blev indtastet i felterne :guilabel:`Minimum til "
"genopfyldning` og :guilabel:`Maksimum til genopfyldning`, da produktet blev "
"tilføjet til |MPS|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:221
msgid ""
"For example, if `5` was entered in the :guilabel:`Minimum to Replenish` "
"field, and `100` was entered in the :guilabel:`Maximum to Replenish` field, "
"the button appears as :guilabel:`5 ≤…≤ 100`."
msgstr ""
"Hvis f.eks. `5` blev indtastet i feltet :guilabel:`Minimum til "
"genopfyldning`, og `100` blev indtastet i feltet :guilabel:`Maksimum til "
"genopfyldning`, vises knappen som :guilabel:`5 ≤…≤ 100`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:225
msgid ""
"Clicking the :guilabel:`# ≤…≤ #` button opens the :guilabel:`Edit Production "
"Schedule` pop-up window. This pop-up window is the same as "
"the :guilabel:`Add a Product` pop-up window, except that "
"the :guilabel:`Product` and :guilabel:`Bill of Materials` fields cannot be "
"edited."
msgstr ""
"Klik på knappen :guilabel:`# ≤…≤ #` for at åbne pop op-"
"vinduet :guilabel:`Rediger produktionsplan`. Dette pop op-vindue er det "
"samme som pop op-vinduet :guilabel:`Tilføj et produkt`, bortset fra at "
"felterne :guilabel:`Produkt` og :guilabel:`Stykliste` ikke kan redigeres."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:229
msgid ""
"On the :guilabel:`Edit Production Schedule` pop-up window, enter the desired "
"values in the :guilabel:`Safety Stock Target`, :guilabel:`Minimum to "
"Replenish`, and :guilabel:`Maximum to Replenish` fields. Then, "
"click :guilabel:`Save` to save the changes."
msgstr ""
"Indtast de ønskede værdier i "
"felterne :guilabel:`Sikkerhedslagermål`, :guilabel:`Minimum til "
"genopfyldning` og :guilabel:`Maksimum til genopfyldning` i pop op-"
"vinduet :guilabel:`Rediger produktionsplan`. Klik derefter "
"på :guilabel:`Gem` for at gemme ændringerne."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:234
msgid "Remove a product"
msgstr "Fjern et produkt"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:236
msgid ""
"To remove a product from the |MPS|, tick the checkbox to the left of its "
"name. Then, click the :icon:`fa-cog` :guilabel:`Actions` button at the top "
"of the screen, and select :guilabel:`Delete` from the resulting drop-down "
"menu. Finally, click :guilabel:`Ok` on the :guilabel:`Confirmation` pop-up "
"window."
msgstr ""
"Marker afkrydsningsfeltet til venstre for dets navn for at fjerne et produkt "
"fra |MPS|. Klik derefter på :icon:`fa-cog` :guilabel:`Handlinger`-knappen "
"øverst på skærmen, og vælg :guilabel:`Slet` fra rullemenuen. Klik til sidst "
"på :guilabel:`Ok` i pop op-vinduet :guilabel:`Bekræftelse`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:241
msgid ""
"Deleting a product from the |MPS| removes it, along with all of its data. If "
"the product is re-added, its replenishment values must be reconfigured."
msgstr ""
"Sletning af et produkt fra |MPS| fjerner det sammen med alle dets data. Hvis "
"produktet tilføjes igen, skal dets genopfyldningsværdier konfigureres igen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:245
msgid "|MPS| replenishment"
msgstr "|MPS| genopfyldning"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:247
msgid "Products in the |MPS| can be replenished in one of three ways:"
msgstr "Produkter i |MPS| kan genopfyldes på en af tre måder:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:249
msgid ""
"Click the :guilabel:`Replenish` button at the top of the screen to generate "
"replenishment orders for every product below its :guilabel:`Safety Stock "
"Target` for the current month."
msgstr ""
"Klik på knappen :guilabel:`Genopfyld` øverst på skærmen for at generere "
"genopfyldningsordrer for hvert produkt under "
"dets :guilabel:`Sikkerhedslagermål` for den aktuelle måned."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:251
msgid ""
"Click the :guilabel:`Replenish` button on the right side of the :guilabel:`+ "
"Suggested Replenishment` row of a specific product, to generate a "
"replenishment order for that specific product."
msgstr ""
"Klik på knappen :guilabel:`Genopfyld` på højre side af rækken :guilabel:`+ "
"Foreslået genopfyldning` for et bestemt produkt for at generere en "
"genopfyldningsordre for det pågældende produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:254
msgid ""
"Tick the checkbox to the left of the product name of one or more products. "
"Then, click the :icon:`fa-cog` :guilabel:`Actions` button at the top of the "
"screen, and select :guilabel:`Replenish` from the resulting drop-down menu. "
"Doing so generates a replenishment order for each selected product."
msgstr ""
"Marker afkrydsningsfeltet til venstre for produktnavnet for et eller flere "
"produkter. Klik derefter på :icon:`fa-cog` :guilabel:`Handlinger`-knappen "
"øverst på skærmen, og vælg :guilabel:`Genopfyld` fra rullemenuen. Dette "
"genererer en genopfyldningsordre for hvert valgt produkt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:259
msgid ""
"The type of replenishment order generated corresponds to the route selected "
"on the *Inventory* tab of the product's form:"
msgstr ""
"Den type genopfyldningsordre, der genereres, svarer til den rute, der er "
"valgt på fanen *Lager* i produktets formular:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:262
msgid ""
"If the *Buy* route is selected, an |RfQ| is generated to replenish the "
"product. |RfQs| can be selected by navigating to "
"the :menuselection:`Purchase` app. Any |RfQ| generated by the |MPS| "
"lists :guilabel:`MPS` in its :guilabel:`Source Document` field."
msgstr ""
"Hvis ruten *Køb* er valgt, genereres en |RfQ| for at genopfylde produktet. |"
"RfQs| kan vælges ved at navigere til appen :menuselection:`Indkøb`. Enhver |"
"RfQ|, der genereres af |MPS|, angiver :guilabel:`MPS` i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Kildedokument`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/use_mps.rst:265
msgid ""
"If the *Manufacture* route is selected, an |MO| is generated to replenish "
"the product. |MOs| can be selected by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Operations --> Manufacturing "
"Orders`. Any |MO| generated by the |MPS| lists :guilabel:`MPS` in "
"its :guilabel:`Source Document` field."
msgstr ""
"Hvis ruten *Fremstil* er valgt, genereres en |MO| for at genopfylde "
"produktet. |MOs| kan vælges ved at navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion "
"app --> Operationer --> Produktionsordrer`. Enhver |MO|, der genereres af |"
"MPS|, angiver :guilabel:`MPS` i feltet :guilabel:`Kildedokument`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:3
msgid "Work center time off"
msgstr "Arbejdscenter fri"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:7
msgid ""
"In Odoo, *work centers* are used to carry out manufacturing operations at "
"specific locations. However, if a work center cannot be used for some "
"reason, work orders begin to pile up at the work center until it is "
"operational again."
msgstr ""
"I Odoo bruges *arbejdscentre* til at udføre produktionsoperationer på "
"bestemte lokationer. Men hvis et arbejdscenter ikke kan bruges af en eller "
"anden grund, begynder arbejdsordrer at hobe sig op ved arbejdscentret, "
"indtil det er i drift igen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:11
msgid ""
"As a result, it is necessary to make the work center unavailable in Odoo so "
"new work orders are routed to alternative work centers that are operational. "
"Using Odoo's **Time Off** app, it is possible to designate a work center as "
"being unavailable for a set period of time. Doing so ensures manufacturing "
"operations can continue until the impacted work center is available again."
msgstr ""
"Som følge heraf er det nødvendigt at gøre arbejdscentret utilgængeligt i "
"Odoo, så nye arbejdsordrer dirigeres til alternative arbejdscentre, der er i "
"drift. Ved hjælp af Odoos **Fri**-app er det muligt at angive, at et "
"arbejdscenter er utilgængeligt i en bestemt periode. Dette sikrer, at "
"produktionsoperationer kan fortsætte, indtil det berørte arbejdscenter er "
"tilgængeligt igen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:19
msgid ""
"Before a work center can be designated as unavailable, the Odoo platform "
"must be properly configured. First, it is necessary to "
"enable :ref:`developer mode <developer-mode>`. This allows the *Time Off* "
"smart button to appear on each work center's *Working Hours* page."
msgstr ""
"Før et arbejdscenter kan angives som utilgængeligt, skal Odoo-platformen "
"være korrekt konfigureret. Først er det nødvendigt at "
"aktivere :ref:`udviklertilstand <developer-mode>`. Dette gør, at den smarte "
"knap *Fri* vises på hvert arbejdscenters *Arbejdstider*-side."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:23
msgid ""
"Next, install the **Time Off** app. This is the app used for managing time "
"off for all resources within Odoo, including employees and work centers."
msgstr ""
"Installér derefter **Fri**-appen. Dette er appen, der bruges til at håndtere "
"fri for alle ressourcer i Odoo, herunder medarbejdere og arbejdscentre."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:26
msgid ""
"To do so, navigate to the :menuselection:`Apps` app, then search `Time Off` "
"in the search bar. The card for the :guilabel:`Time Off` app should be the "
"only one that appears on the page. Click the :guilabel:`Install` button on "
"the card to install the app."
msgstr ""
"For at gøre dette skal du navigere til appen :menuselection:`Apps`, og "
"derefter søge efter `Time Off` i søgefeltet. Kortet for :guilabel:`Fri`-"
"appen bør være det eneste, der vises på siden. Klik på "
"knappen :guilabel:`Installér` på kortet for at installere appen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:30
msgid ""
"The last step is to properly configure work centers. For this workflow, it "
"is necessary to have at least two work centers: one that is made "
"unavailable, and a second that receives the work orders that the other "
"cannot accept. If no second work center is configured, Odoo cannot route "
"work orders away from the unavailable work center, and they pile up in its "
"queue."
msgstr ""
"Det sidste trin er at konfigurere arbejdscentre korrekt. Til denne "
"arbejdsgang er det nødvendigt at have mindst to arbejdscentre: et der gøres "
"utilgængeligt, og et andet der modtager de arbejdsordrer, som det første "
"ikke kan acceptere. Hvis der ikke er konfigureret et andet arbejdscenter, "
"kan Odoo ikke dirigere arbejdsordrer væk fra det utilgængelige "
"arbejdscenter, og de hober sig op i dets kø."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:35
msgid ""
"To create a work center, navigate to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> "
"Configuration --> Work Centers --> New`."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette et arbejdscenter skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Konfiguration --> Arbejdscentre --> Ny`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:39
msgid ""
"For a full guide to work center creation, refer to the documentation "
"on :doc:`work centers <../advanced_configuration/using_work_centers>`."
msgstr ""
"For en komplet guide til oprettelse af arbejdscentre henvises til "
"dokumentationen om :doc:`arbejdscentre <../advanced_configuration/"
"using_work_centers>`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:42
msgid ""
"Make sure both work centers have the same equipment listed under "
"the :guilabel:`Equipment` tab. This ensures operations carried out at one "
"work center can also be performed at the other."
msgstr ""
"Sørg for, at begge arbejdscentre har det samme udstyr angivet under "
"fanen :guilabel:`Udstyr`. Dette sikrer, at operationer udført på det ene "
"arbejdscenter også kan udføres på det andet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:45
msgid ""
"On the work center that is made unavailable, select the second work center "
"from the :guilabel:`Alternative Workcenters` drop-down menu. Now, Odoo knows "
"to send work orders to the second work center when the first is unavailable "
"for any reason."
msgstr ""
"På det arbejdscenter, der gøres utilgængeligt, skal du vælge det andet "
"arbejdscenter fra rullemenuen :guilabel:`Alternative arbejdscentre`. Nu ved "
"Odoo, at arbejdsordrer skal sendes til det andet arbejdscenter, når det "
"første er utilgængeligt af en eller anden grund."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:None
msgid "A work center form configured with an alternative work center."
msgstr ""
"En arbejdscenterformular konfigureret med et alternativt arbejdscenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:54
msgid "Add time off for a work center"
msgstr "Tilføj fri til et arbejdscenter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:56
msgid ""
"With configuration completed, time off can now be assigned to a work center. "
"Begin by navigating to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Configuration --"
"> Work Centers`, and selecting the affected work center. Click the :icon:`oi-"
"arrow-right` :guilabel:`(Internal link)` button on the right side of "
"the :guilabel:`Working Hours` drop-down menu, to open the working hours page "
"for the work center."
msgstr ""
"Når konfigurationen er fuldført, kan der nu tildeles fri til et "
"arbejdscenter. Begynd med at navigere til :menuselection:`Produktion --> "
"Konfiguration --> Arbejdscentre`, og vælg det berørte arbejdscenter. Klik på "
"knappen :icon:`oi-arrow-right` :guilabel:`(Internt link)` på højre side af "
"rullemenuen :guilabel:`Arbejdstider` for at åbne arbejdstidssiden for "
"arbejdscentret."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:None
msgid "The Working Hours \"External link\" button on the work center form."
msgstr "Knappen \"Eksternt link\" for arbejdstider på arbejdscenterformularen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:65
msgid ""
"The working hours page displays the standard working hours for the work "
"center. With developer mode activated, a :icon:`fa-plane` :guilabel:`Time "
"Off` smart button appears at the top of the page. Click it to open "
"the :guilabel:`Resource Time Off` page."
msgstr ""
"Arbejdstidssiden viser de normale arbejdstider for arbejdscentret. Med "
"udviklertilstand aktiveret vises en smart knap :icon:`fa-"
"plane` :guilabel:`Fri` øverst på siden. Klik på den for at åbne "
"siden :guilabel:`Ressourcefri`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:69
msgid ""
"On this page, click :guilabel:`New` to configure a new time-off entry. On "
"the time-off form, note the :guilabel:`Reason` for the work center closure "
"(e.g. broken equipment, maintenance, etc.), select the affected work center "
"as the :guilabel:`Resource`, and choose a :guilabel:`Start Date` "
"and :guilabel:`End Date` to specify the period during which the work center "
"is unavailable."
msgstr ""
"På denne side skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Ny` for at konfigurere en ny "
"fripost. På friformularen skal du angive :guilabel:`Årsag` til "
"arbejdscenterlukningen (f.eks. defekt udstyr, vedligeholdelse osv.), vælge "
"det berørte arbejdscenter som :guilabel:`Ressource` og vælge "
"en :guilabel:`Startdato` og :guilabel:`Slutdato` for at angive den periode, "
"hvor arbejdscentret er utilgængeligt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:None
msgid "The \"Resource Time Off\" form."
msgstr "Formularen \"Ressourcefri\"."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:79
msgid "Alternative work center planning"
msgstr "Planlægning af alternativt arbejdscenter"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:81
msgid ""
"Once a work center is within its specified time-off period, work orders sent "
"to it can be automatically routed to an alternative work center using the "
"*Plan* button."
msgstr ""
"Når et arbejdscenter er inden for sin angivne friperiode, kan arbejdsordrer "
"sendt til det automatisk dirigeres til et alternativt arbejdscenter ved "
"hjælp af knappen *Planlæg*."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:84
msgid ""
"Begin by creating a new manufacturing order (MO), by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Manufacturing app --> Operations --> Manufacturing Orders "
"--> New`. On the |MO| form, specify a :guilabel:`Product` that uses the "
"unavailable work center for one of its operations. Click :guilabel:`Confirm` "
"to confirm the |MO|."
msgstr ""
"Begynd med at oprette en ny produktionsordre (MO) ved at navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Operationer --> Produktionsordrer --> "
"Ny`. På |MO|formularen skal du angive et :guilabel:`Produkt`, der bruger det "
"utilgængelige arbejdscenter til en af dets operationer. Klik "
"på :guilabel:`Bekræft` for at bekræfte |MO|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:89
msgid ""
"On the confirmed |MO|, select the :guilabel:`Work Orders` tab. By default, "
"the unavailable work center is specified in the :guilabel:`Work Center` "
"column. There is also a :guilabel:`Plan` button at the top left of the page."
msgstr ""
"På den bekræftede |MO| skal du vælge fanen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer`. Som "
"standard er det utilgængelige arbejdscenter angivet i "
"kolonnen :guilabel:`Arbejdscenter`. Der er også en :guilabel:`Planlæg`-knap "
"øverst til venstre på siden."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:93
msgid ""
"Click :guilabel:`Plan`, and the work center listed in the :guilabel:`Work "
"Center` column of the :guilabel:`Work Orders` tab is automatically changed "
"to the alternative work center."
msgstr ""
"Klik på :guilabel:`Planlæg`, og arbejdscentret anført i "
"kolonnen :guilabel:`Arbejdscenter` på fanen :guilabel:`Arbejdsordrer` ændres "
"automatisk til det alternative arbejdscenter."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:100
msgid ""
"Before clicking \"Plan\", the work order is scheduled at \"Main Assembly "
"Line\"."
msgstr ""
"Før der klikkes på \"Planlæg\", er arbejdsordren planlagt ved \"Main "
"Assembly Line\"."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:100
msgid ""
"Before clicking :guilabel:`Plan`, the work order is scheduled "
"at :guilabel:`Main Assembly Line`."
msgstr ""
"Før der klikkes på :guilabel:`Planlæg`, er arbejdsordren planlagt "
"ved :guilabel:`Main Assembly Line`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:106
msgid ""
"After clicking \"Plan\", the work order is rescheduled at \"Alternative "
"Assembly Line\"."
msgstr ""
"Efter der klikkes på \"Planlæg\", bliver arbejdsordren omplanlagt ved "
"\"Alternative Assembly Line\"."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:106
msgid ""
"After clicking :guilabel:`Plan`, the work order is rescheduled "
"at :guilabel:`Alternative Assembly Line`."
msgstr ""
"Efter der klikkes på :guilabel:`Planlæg`, bliver arbejdsordren omplanlagt "
"ved :guilabel:`Alternative Assembly Line`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/manufacturing/workflows/work_center_time_off.rst:109
msgid ""
"Once the time-off period for the unavailable work center ends, Odoo "
"recognizes the work center is available again. At this point, clicking "
"the :guilabel:`Plan` button does not route work orders to an alternative "
"work center unless the first one is at capacity."
msgstr ""
"Når perioden med fravær for det utilgængelige arbejdscenter slutter, "
"genkender Odoo, at arbejdscentret igen er tilgængeligt. På dette tidspunkt "
"vil et klik på knappen :guilabel:`Planlæg` ikke dirigere arbejdsordrer til "
"et alternativt arbejdscenter, medmindre det første er ved fuld kapacitet."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm.rst:8
msgid "Product lifecycle management"
msgstr "Produktlivscyklusstyring"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm.rst:10
msgid ""
"Odoo *Product Lifecycle Management* (*PLM*) offers a systematic approach for "
"testing, collaboration, and iteration of products across concept "
"development, design, manufacturing, marketing, and post-launch support "
"stages."
msgstr ""
"Odoo *Product Lifecycle Management* (*PLM*) tilbyder en systematisk tilgang "
"til test, samarbejde og iteration af produkter på tværs af konceptudvikling, "
"design, produktion, markedsføring og support efter lanceringen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm.rst:14
msgid ""
"With approvals, key stakeholders can review changes before implementation."
msgstr ""
"Med godkendelser kan nøgleinteressenter gennemgå ændringer før "
"implementering."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes.rst:3
msgid "Change management"
msgstr "Ændringsstyring"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:10
msgid "ECO types and stages"
msgstr "ECO-typer og -stadier"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:12
msgid ""
"Engineering change orders (ECOs) are categorized by the type of change they "
"represent and their statuses are tracked via stages. Both |ECO| types and "
"stages are defined by the user and can be customized to the specific needs "
"of a business or industry."
msgstr ""
"Engineering change orders (ECO'er) kategoriseres efter den type ændring, de "
"repræsenterer, og deres status spores via stadier. Både |ECO|-typer og "
"-stadier defineres af brugeren og kan tilpasses de specifikke behov for en "
"virksomhed eller branche."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:17
msgid "ECO types"
msgstr "ECO-typer"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:19
msgid ""
"Each |ECO| type separates |ECOs| into different projects in "
"the :guilabel:`PLM Overview`, ensuring collaborators and stakeholders only "
"view and assist with relevant |BOM| improvements."
msgstr ""
"Hver |ECO|-type adskiller |ECOs| i forskellige projekter i :guilabel:`PLM-"
"oversigt`, hvilket sikrer, at samarbejdspartnere og interessenter kun ser og "
"hjælper med relevante |BOM|-forbedringer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:23
msgid ""
"An electronic chip manufacturer uses five |ECO| types: `New Product "
"Introduction`, `BOM Updates`, `Component Change`, `Product Improvement`, and "
"`Firmware Update`. In their configuration, engineers can spend time "
"exclusively on |ECOs| in the `Component Change` and `Firmware Update` types, "
"while designers see |ECOs| in the `New Product Introduction` type, allowing "
"each discipline to focus only on those changes that require their domain "
"expertise."
msgstr ""
"En producent af elektroniske chips bruger fem |ECO|-typer: `New Product "
"Introduction`, `BOM Updates`, `Component Change`, `Product Improvement` og "
"`Firmware Update`. I deres konfiguration kan ingeniører bruge tid "
"udelukkende på |ECOs| i typerne `Component Change` og `Firmware Update`, "
"mens designere ser |ECOs| i typen `New Product Introduction`, hvilket giver "
"hver disciplin mulighed for udelukkende at fokusere på de ændringer, der "
"kræver deres domæneekspertise."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:0
msgid "Example of several custom ECO types."
msgstr "Eksempel på flere brugerdefinerede ECO-typer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:33
msgid "Create an ECO type"
msgstr "Opret en ECO-type"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:35
msgid ""
"To access and manage ECO types, navigate to :menuselection:`PLM app --> "
"Configuration --> ECO Types`."
msgstr ""
"For at få adgang til og administrere ECO-typer skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`Produktion --> Konfiguration --> ECO-typer`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:38
msgid ""
"Create a new ECO type by clicking :guilabel:`New`. On the new :guilabel:`ECO "
"Types` form, fill in the following information:"
msgstr ""
"Opret en ny ECO-type ved at klikke på :guilabel:`Ny`. På den "
"nye :guilabel:`ECO-typer`-formular skal du udfylde følgende oplysninger:"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:41
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Name`: the name of the |ECO| type, which will organize all of the "
"|ECOs| of this *type* in a project."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Navn`: navnet på |ECO|-typen, som organiserer alle |ECOs| af "
"denne *type* i et projekt."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:43
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Email Alias`: if this optional field is filled, emails submitted "
"to this email address automatically generate |ECOs| in the left-most stage "
"of this |ECO| type."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`E-mail-alias`: hvis dette valgfrie felt udfyldes, genererer e-"
"mails sendt til denne e-mail-adresse automatisk |ECOs| i den venstre fase af "
"denne |ECO|-type."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:47
msgid ""
"The `Formulation change` |ECO| type is used to organize and track related |"
"ECOs| in a single project. Configuring the :guilabel:`Email Alias` field "
"generates |ECOs| in the `Formulation change` project sent to the email "
"address, `pawlish-change@pawlished-glam.odoo.com`."
msgstr ""
"|ECO|-typen `Formulation change` bruges til at organisere og spore "
"relaterede |ECOs| i et enkelt projekt. Konfiguration af feltet :guilabel:`E-"
"mail-alias` genererer |ECOs| i projektet `Formulation change` sendt til e-"
"mail-adressen `pawlish-change@pawlished-glam.odoo.com`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:0
msgid "Example of an ECO type."
msgstr "Eksempel på en ECO-type."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:55
msgid "Edit ECO types"
msgstr "Rediger ECO-typer"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:57
msgid ""
"Modify existing |ECO| type names and email aliases by navigating to "
"the :menuselection:`PLM app --> Configuration --> ECO Types` page. There, "
"click on the desired |ECO| type from the list."
msgstr ""
"Rediger eksisterende |ECO|-typenavne og e-mail-aliaser ved at navigere til "
"siden :menuselection:`PLM-app --> Konfiguration --> ECO-typer`. Klik der på "
"den ønskede |ECO|-type fra listen."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:60
msgid ""
"On the form for each |ECO| type, edit the :guilabel:`Name` "
"or :guilabel:`Email Alias` fields."
msgstr ""
"På formularen for hver |ECO|-type skal du redigere felterne :guilabel:`Navn` "
"eller :guilabel:`E-mail-alias`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:65
msgid "Stages"
msgstr "Faser"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:67
msgid ""
"Within the :guilabel:`Engineering Change Orders` Kanban view for a specific |"
"ECO| type, *stages* are milestones used to identify the progress of the |"
"ECO| before the changes are ready to be applied. By default, Odoo uses "
"`New`, `In Progress`, `Validated`, and `Effective`, but these are fully "
"customizable to the specific life cycle of an |ECO| type."
msgstr ""
"I Kanban-visningen :guilabel:`Engineering Change Orders` for en specifik |"
"ECO|-type er *faser* milepæle, der bruges til at identificere fremskridt for "
"|ECO|, inden ændringerne er klar til at blive anvendt. Som standard bruger "
"Odoo `New`, `In Progress`, `Validated` og `Effective`, men disse kan fuldt "
"ud tilpasses til den specifikke livscyklus for en |ECO|-type."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:None
msgid "Default stages for an ECO type."
msgstr "Standardfaser for en ECO-type."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:76
msgid ""
"The `Effective` stage is folded by default to avoid listing every single |"
"ECO| that has gone into effect. See :ref:`Closing stage <plm/eco/closing-"
"stage>` for more on this configuration."
msgstr ""
"Fasen `Effective` er som standard foldet sammen for at undgå at liste hver "
"eneste |ECO|, der er trådt i kraft. Se :ref:`Afsluttende fase <plm/eco/"
"closing-stage>` for mere om denne konfiguration."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:79
msgid ""
":ref:`Verification stages <plm/eco/verification-stage>` require a designated "
"user to approve, ensuring that changes do not proceed until the |ECO| "
"changes have been reviewed by the appropriate stake holders. :ref:`Closing "
"stages<plm/eco/closing-stage>` that can apply changes put |BOM| and "
"operations changes into immediate effect, changing all pending and "
"future :abbr:`MO (Manufacturing orders)` to the latest |BOM| version."
msgstr ""
":ref:`Verificeringsfaser <plm/eco/verification-stage>` kræver en udpeget "
"bruger til at godkende, hvilket sikrer, at ændringer ikke fortsætter, før |"
"ECO|-ændringerne er blevet gennemgået af de relevante "
"interessenter. :ref:`Afsluttende faser<plm/eco/closing-stage>`, der kan "
"anvende ændringer, sætter |BOM|- og operationsændringer i øjeblikkelig "
"effekt og ændrer alle afventende og fremtidige :abbr:`produktionsordrer` til "
"den seneste |BOM|-version."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:86
msgid ""
"The most common practice is to have at least one *verification* stage, which "
"is a stage with a required approver, and one *closing* stage, which stores |"
"ECOs| that have been either cancelled or approved for use as the next "
"production |BOM|."
msgstr ""
"Den mest almindelige praksis er at have mindst én *verificeringsfase*, som "
"er en fase med en påkrævet godkender, og én *afsluttende fase*, som gemmer |"
"ECOs|, der enten er blevet annulleret eller godkendt til brug som den næste "
"produktions-|BOM|."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:91
msgid ":doc:`Approvals<../management/approvals>`"
msgstr ":doc:`Godkendelser<../management/approvals>`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:96
msgid "Verification stages"
msgstr "Verificeringsfaser"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:98
msgid ""
"To configure a verification stage, hover over the intended stage, and select "
"the :icon:`fa-gear` :guilabel:`(Actions)`. Then, click :guilabel:`Edit` to "
"open a pop-up window and check the box for :guilabel:`Allow to apply "
"changes`."
msgstr ""
"For at konfigurere en verificeringsfase skal du holde markøren over den "
"ønskede fase og vælge :icon:`fa-gear` :guilabel:`Handlinger`. Klik derefter "
"på :guilabel:`Rediger` for at åbne et pop-up-vindue og markér "
"afkrydsningsfeltet for :guilabel:`Tillad at anvende ændringer`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:102
msgid ""
"Next, add an approver in the :guilabel:`Approvers` section, by "
"clicking :guilabel:`Add a line`, and specifying the :guilabel:`Role` of the "
"reviewer, the :guilabel:`User`, and an :guilabel:`Approval Type` "
"of :guilabel:`Is required to approve`. See :ref:`more about approval types. "
"<plm/approvals/approval-type>`"
msgstr ""
"Tilføj derefter en godkender i sektionen :guilabel:`Godkendere` ved at "
"klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje` og angive :guilabel:`Rolle` for "
"revieweren, :guilabel:`Bruger`, og en :guilabel:`Godkendelsestype` "
"på :guilabel:`Er påkrævet for at godkende`. Se :ref:`mere om "
"godkendelsestyper. <plm/approvals/approval-type>`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:107
msgid ""
"The approver listed is automatically notified when |ECOs| are dropped in the "
"stage specified in the pop-up window. Once finished, click :guilabel:`Save & "
"Close`."
msgstr ""
"Den anførte godkender underrettes automatisk, når |ECOs| placeres i den "
"fase, der er angivet i pop-up-vinduet. Når du er færdig, skal du klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Gem og luk`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:111
msgid ":doc:`../management/approvals`"
msgstr ":doc:`../management/approvals`"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:116
msgid "Closing stages"
msgstr "Afsluttende faser"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:118
msgid ""
"Click an |ECO| type from :menuselection:`PLM app --> Overview` to open the "
"Kanban view of |ECOs| of this type."
msgstr ""
"Klik på en |ECO|-type fra :menuselection:`PLM-app --> Oversigt` for at åbne "
"Kanban-visningen af |ECOs| af denne type."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:121
msgid ""
"To configure a closing stage that applies |BOM|, edit the stage and tick the "
"boxes for :guilabel:`Folded in kanban view`, :guilabel:`Allow to apply "
"changes`, and :guilabel:`Final Stage`. When ECO cards are placed in a stage "
"that will *Allow to apply changes*, then any |BOM| and operations changes "
"validated in the |ECOs| will immediately be put into effect. To create a "
"cancelled stage, create or edit a stage and tick the boxes "
"for :guilabel:`Folded in kanban view` and :guilabel:`Final Stage`. |ECOs| in "
"this stage are removed from the pipeline, but will not make changes."
msgstr ""
"Hvis du vil konfigurere en afsluttende fase, der anvender |BOM|, skal du "
"redigere fasen og markere boksene for :guilabel:`Folded in kanban "
"view`, :guilabel:`Allow to apply changes` og :guilabel:`Final Stage`. Når "
"ECO-kort placeres i en fase, der vil *Allow to apply changes*, vil "
"eventuelle |BOM| og operationsændringer, der er valideret i |ECOs|, straks "
"træde i kraft. Hvis du vil oprette en annulleret fase, skal du oprette eller "
"redigere en fase og markere boksene for :guilabel:`Folded in kanban view` "
"og :guilabel:`Final Stage`. |ECOs| i denne fase fjernes fra pipelinen, men "
"vil ikke foretage ændringer."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/plm/manage_changes/eco_type.rst:130
msgid ""
"The closing stage, `Effective` is configured by checking "
"the :guilabel:`Folded in kanban view`, :guilabel:`Allow to apply changes`, "
"and :guilabel:`Final Stage` options"
msgstr ""
"Den afsluttende fase, `Effective`, konfigureres ved at markere "
"indstillingerne :guilabel:`Folded in kanban view`, :guilabel:`Allow to apply "
